2439 void TTrain::PickUpBackgroundBitmap(int Caller, int HOffset, int VOffset, int Element, int EntryPos, Graphics::TBitmap *GraphicPtr) const
2440 {
2441  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",PickUpBackgroundBitmap," + AnsiString(HOffset) + "," +
2442  AnsiString(VOffset) + "," + AnsiString(Element) + "," + AnsiString(EntryPos) + "," + HeadCode);
2443  Graphics::TBitmap *EXGraphicPtr = RailGraphics->bmTransparentBgnd;
2444  // default values
2445  Graphics::TBitmap *EntryDirectionGraphicPtr = RailGraphics->bmTransparentBgnd;
2446 
2447  TAllRoutes::TRouteType RouteType;
2448 
2449  RouteType = AllRoutes->GetRouteTypeAndGraphics(11, Element, EntryPos, EXGraphicPtr, EntryDirectionGraphicPtr);
2450 
2451  TRect SourceRect, DestRect;
2452 
2453  DestRect.init(0, 0, 8, 8); // initialise left, top, right, bottom
2454  // note right and bottom rect co-ordinates are 1 greater than the pixel area
2455  SourceRect.init(HOffset, VOffset, HOffset + 8, VOffset + 8);
2456  Graphics::TBitmap *TempGraphic = new Graphics::TBitmap;
2457 
2458  TempGraphic->PixelFormat = pf8bit;
2459  TempGraphic->Width = 16;
2460  TempGraphic->Height = 16;
2461  TTrackElement TempElement = Track->TrackElementAt(286, Element);
2462 
2463  if(TempElement.TrackType == Points)
2464  {
2465  TempGraphic->Assign(TempElement.GraphicPtr);
2466  TempGraphic->Transparent = true;
2467  TempGraphic->TransparentColor = Utilities->clTransparent;
2468  if(RouteType == TAllRoutes::AutoSigsRoute)
2469  {
2470  TempGraphic->Canvas->Draw(0, 0, EXGraphicPtr);
2471  TempGraphic->Canvas->Draw(0, 0, EntryDirectionGraphicPtr);
2472  }
2473  else
2474  TempGraphic->Canvas->Draw(0, 0, Track->GetFilletGraphic(1, TempElement)); // add fillet
2475  GraphicPtr->Canvas->CopyRect(DestRect, TempGraphic->Canvas, SourceRect);
2476  }
2477  else if(TempElement.TrackType == GapJump) // plot set gap
2478  {
2479  if(TempElement.SpeedTag == 88)
2480  TempGraphic->Assign(RailGraphics->gl88set);
2481  else if(TempElement.SpeedTag == 89)
2482  TempGraphic->Assign(RailGraphics->gl89set);
2483  else if(TempElement.SpeedTag == 90)
2484  TempGraphic->Assign(RailGraphics->gl90set);
2485  else if(TempElement.SpeedTag == 91)
2486  TempGraphic->Assign(RailGraphics->gl91set);
2487  else if(TempElement.SpeedTag == 92)
2488  TempGraphic->Assign(RailGraphics->gl92set);
2489  else if(TempElement.SpeedTag == 93)
2490  TempGraphic->Assign(RailGraphics->bm93set);
2491  else if(TempElement.SpeedTag == 94)
2492  TempGraphic->Assign(RailGraphics->bm94set);
2493  else if(TempElement.SpeedTag == 95)
2494  TempGraphic->Assign(RailGraphics->gl95set);
2495  TempGraphic->Transparent = true;
2496  TempGraphic->TransparentColor = Utilities->clTransparent;
2497  if(RouteType == TAllRoutes::AutoSigsRoute)
2498  {
2499  TempGraphic->Canvas->Draw(0, 0, EXGraphicPtr);
2500  TempGraphic->Canvas->Draw(0, 0, EntryDirectionGraphicPtr);
2501  }
2502  GraphicPtr->Canvas->CopyRect(DestRect, TempGraphic->Canvas, SourceRect);
2503  }
2504  // new for version 0.6
2505  else if(TempElement.TrackType == SignalPost)
2506  {
2507  if(TempElement.SigAspect == TTrackElement::GroundSignal)
2508  {
2509  for(int x = 0; x < 40; x++)
2510  {
2511  if((Track->SigTableGroundSignal[x].SpeedTag == TempElement.SpeedTag) && (Track->SigTableGroundSignal[x].Attribute == 0))
2512  // need to stop aspect
2513  {
2514  TempGraphic->Assign(Track->SigTableGroundSignal[x].SigPtr);
2515  break;
2516  }
2517  }
2518  }
2519  else // normal signal
2520  {
2521  TempGraphic->Assign(TempElement.GraphicPtr);
2522  // GraphicPtr set to normal signal in a signal track element
2523  }
2524  TempGraphic->Transparent = true;
2525  TempGraphic->TransparentColor = Utilities->clTransparent;
2526  if(RouteType == TAllRoutes::AutoSigsRoute)
2527  {
2528  TempGraphic->Canvas->Draw(0, 0, EXGraphicPtr);
2529  TempGraphic->Canvas->Draw(0, 0, EntryDirectionGraphicPtr);
2530  }
2531  GraphicPtr->Canvas->CopyRect(DestRect, TempGraphic->Canvas, SourceRect);
2532  }
2533  else
2534  {
2535  // first check if there's a NamedNonStationLocation element at that position & if so pick up that as the background
2536  // can't name points gaps or signals so 'else' OK
2537  bool FoundFlag;
2538  TTrack::TIMPair IMPair = Track->GetVectorPositionsFromInactiveTrackMap(4, TempElement.HLoc, TempElement.VLoc, FoundFlag);
2539  if(FoundFlag)
2540  {
2541  if(Track->InactiveTrackElementAt(25, IMPair.first).TrackType == NamedNonStationLocation)
2542  {
2543  GraphicPtr->Canvas->CopyRect(DestRect, Track->InactiveTrackElementAt(26, IMPair.first).GraphicPtr->Canvas, SourceRect);
2544  TempGraphic->Assign(RailGraphics->bmName);
2545  TempGraphic->Transparent = true;
2546  TempGraphic->TransparentColor = Utilities->clTransparent;
2547  if(RouteType == TAllRoutes::AutoSigsRoute)
2548  {
2549  TempGraphic->Canvas->Draw(0, 0, EXGraphicPtr);
2550  TempGraphic->Canvas->Draw(0, 0, EntryDirectionGraphicPtr);
2551  }
2552  else
2553  TempGraphic->Canvas->Draw(0, 0, TempElement.GraphicPtr);
2554  // draw track on top
2555  GraphicPtr->Canvas->CopyRect(DestRect, TempGraphic->Canvas, SourceRect);
2556  }
2557  else if(Track->InactiveTrackElementAt(116, IMPair.first).TrackType == LevelCrossing)
2558  {
2559  TempGraphic->Assign(TempElement.GraphicPtr);
2560  TempGraphic->Transparent = true;
2561  TempGraphic->TransparentColor = Utilities->clTransparent;
2562  // note that can't be an AutoSigsRoute
2563  // now overlay the LC central portion
2564  TempGraphic->Canvas->Draw(0, 0, RailGraphics->LCPlain);
2565  GraphicPtr->Canvas->CopyRect(DestRect, TempGraphic->Canvas, SourceRect);
2566  }
2567  else
2568  {
2569  TempGraphic->Assign(TempElement.GraphicPtr);
2570  TempGraphic->Transparent = true;
2571  TempGraphic->TransparentColor = Utilities->clTransparent;
2572  if(RouteType == TAllRoutes::AutoSigsRoute)
2573  {
2574  TempGraphic->Canvas->Draw(0, 0, EXGraphicPtr);
2575  TempGraphic->Canvas->Draw(0, 0, EntryDirectionGraphicPtr);
2576  }
2577  GraphicPtr->Canvas->CopyRect(DestRect, TempGraphic->Canvas, SourceRect);
2578  }
2579  }
2580  else
2581  {
2582  TempGraphic->Assign(TempElement.GraphicPtr);
2583  TempGraphic->Transparent = true;
2584  TempGraphic->TransparentColor = Utilities->clTransparent;
2585  if(RouteType == TAllRoutes::AutoSigsRoute)
2586  {
2587  TempGraphic->Canvas->Draw(0, 0, EXGraphicPtr);
2588  TempGraphic->Canvas->Draw(0, 0, EntryDirectionGraphicPtr);
2589  }
2590  GraphicPtr->Canvas->CopyRect(DestRect, TempGraphic->Canvas, SourceRect);
2591  }
2592  }
2593  delete TempGraphic;
2594  Utilities->CallLogPop(675);
2595 }

2738  TempGraphic->Assign(TempElement.GraphicPtr);
2739  TempGraphic->Transparent = true;
2740  TempGraphic->TransparentColor = Utilities->clTransparent;
2741  // note that can't be an AutoSigsRoute
2742  // now overlay the LC central portion
2743  TempGraphic->Canvas->Draw(0, 0, RailGraphics->LCPlain);
2744  GraphicPtr->Canvas->CopyRect(DestRect, TempGraphic->Canvas,
2745  SourceRect);
2746  }
2747  else {
2748  TempGraphic->Assign(TempElement.GraphicPtr);
2749  TempGraphic->Transparent = true;
2750  TempGraphic->TransparentColor = Utilities->clTransparent;
2751  if (RouteType == TAllRoutes::AutoSigsRoute) {
2752  TempGraphic->Canvas->Draw(0, 0, EXGraphicPtr);
2753  TempGraphic->Canvas->Draw(0, 0, EntryDirectionGraphicPtr);
2754  }
2755  GraphicPtr->Canvas->CopyRect(DestRect, TempGraphic->Canvas,
2756  SourceRect);
2757  }
2758  }
2759  else {
2760  TempGraphic->Assign(TempElement.GraphicPtr);
2761  TempGraphic->Transparent = true;
2762  TempGraphic->TransparentColor = Utilities->clTransparent;
2763  if (RouteType == TAllRoutes::AutoSigsRoute) {
2764  TempGraphic->Canvas->Draw(0, 0, EXGraphicPtr);
2765  TempGraphic->Canvas->Draw(0, 0, EntryDirectionGraphicPtr);
2766  }
2767  SourceGraphic->Canvas->CopyRect(DestRect, TempGraphic->Canvas, SourceRect);
2768  GraphicPtr->Canvas->Draw(0, 0, SourceGraphic);
2769  }
2770  }
2771  delete TempGraphic;
2772  delete SourceGraphic;
2773  Utilities->CallLogPop();
2774  }
2775 */

2778 void TTrain::PlotTrainGraphic(int Caller, int ArrayNumber, TDisplay *Disp)

2785  }

2789  ((Track->TrackElementAt(296, PlotElement[ArrayNumber]).VLoc * 16) + VOffset[ArrayNumber]), HeadCodePosition[ArrayNumber]);

2791  Plotted = true;
2792  Utilities->CallLogPop(677);

2932 void TTrain::ResetTrainElementID(int Caller, unsigned int TrackVectorPosition, int EntryPos)
2933 {
2934  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",ResetTrainElementID," + AnsiString(TrackVectorPosition) + "," +
2935  AnsiString(EntryPos) + "," + HeadCode);

2939  }
2940  else
2941  {
2942  if(EntryPos == -1)

2948  else
2949  Track->TrackElementAt(317, TrackVectorPosition).TrainIDOnBridgeTrackPos23 = -1;

2951  // i.e. other train on track 2&3
2952  {
2953  Track->TrackElementAt(319, TrackVectorPosition).TrainIDOnElement = Track->TrackElementAt(320, TrackVectorPosition).TrainIDOnBridgeTrackPos23;
2954  }
2955  else if((EntryPos > 1) && (Track->TrackElementAt(321, TrackVectorPosition).TrainIDOnBridgeTrackPos01 > -1))
2956  // i.e. other train on track 1&2
2957  {
2958  Track->TrackElementAt(322, TrackVectorPosition).TrainIDOnElement = Track->TrackElementAt(323, TrackVectorPosition).TrainIDOnBridgeTrackPos01;
2959  }
2960  else
2961  Track->TrackElementAt(324, TrackVectorPosition).TrainIDOnElement = -1;
2962  }
2963  Utilities->CallLogPop(691);
2964 }

3069 void TTrain::CheckAndCancelRouteForWrongEndEntry(int Caller, int Element, int EntryPos)
3070 {
3071  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",CheckAndCancelRouteForWrongEndEntry," + AnsiString(Element) + "," +
3072  AnsiString(EntryPos) + "," + HeadCode);
3073  int RouteNumber;
3074  bool WrongRoute = false;
3075  TPrefDirElement RouteElement;
3076  TAllRoutes::TRouteElementPair RoutePair;
3077  TAllRoutes::TRoute2MultiMapIterator Route2MultiMapIterator;
3078 
3079  if(AllRoutes->GetRouteTypeAndNumber(11, Element, EntryPos, RouteNumber) == TAllRoutes::NoRoute)
3080  // here if single track element & no route, or double track element with no route at EntryPos but still need to check if on points or a crossover on non-route track,
3081  // and force-erase route if so (bridge OK of course) note that GetRouteTypeAndNumber allows for points having an EntryPos of 0 or 2 & still returns correct values
3082  {
3083  if((Track->TrackElementAt(340, Element).TrackType == Crossover) || (Track->TrackElementAt(341, Element).TrackType == Points))
3084  {
3085  if(AllRoutes->GetRouteTypeAndNumber(12, Element, (3 - EntryPos), RouteNumber) != TAllRoutes::NoRoute)
3086  // (3-EntryPos) guarantees other route (0->3; 1->2; 2->1; 3->0)
3087  {
3088  if(AllRoutes->GetFixedRouteAt(179, RouteNumber).PrefDirSize() > 2)
3089  { // don't call for stub end routes
3090  TrainController->LogActionError(49, HeadCode, "", RouteForceCancelled, Track->TrackElementAt(799, Element).ElementID);
3091  }
3092  AllRoutes->GetModifiableRouteAt(13, RouteNumber).ForceCancelRoute(1);
3093  Utilities->CallLogPop(697);
3094  return;
3095  }
3096  }
3097  // also need to check for a route on a crossing diagonal
3098  TTrackElement TrackElement = Track->TrackElementAt(892, Element);
3099  int LinkNumber = TrackElement.Link[EntryPos];
3100  if((LinkNumber == 1) || (LinkNumber == 3) || (LinkNumber == 7) || (LinkNumber == 9))
3101  {
3102  if(AllRoutes->DiagonalFouledByRoute(0, TrackElement.HLoc, TrackElement.VLoc, LinkNumber))
3103  {
3104  // for LinkNumber = 1, potentially fouled diagonals are at H-1, V, Lk 3 & H, V-1, Lk 7
3105  bool LogActionErrorCalled = false;
3106  // to ensure only called once if have 2 routes on the 2 crossed diagonals
3107  if(LinkNumber == 1)
3108  {
3109  if(AllRoutes->FindRouteNumberFromRoute2MultiMapNoErrors(0, TrackElement.HLoc - 1, TrackElement.VLoc, 3, RouteNumber))
3110  {
3111  if(AllRoutes->GetFixedRouteAt(207, RouteNumber).PrefDirSize() > 2)
3112  { // don't call for stub end routes
3113  TrainController->LogActionError(55, HeadCode, "", RouteForceCancelled, TrackElement.ElementID);
3114  LogActionErrorCalled = true;
3115  }
3116  AllRoutes->GetModifiableRouteAt(20, RouteNumber).ForceCancelRoute(3);
3117  }
3118  if(AllRoutes->FindRouteNumberFromRoute2MultiMapNoErrors(1, TrackElement.HLoc, TrackElement.VLoc - 1, 7, RouteNumber))
3119  // not else in case have different routes on each diagonal, though shouldn't be possible
3120  {
3121  if(!LogActionErrorCalled && AllRoutes->GetFixedRouteAt(208, RouteNumber).PrefDirSize() > 2)
3122  { // don't call for stub end routes
3123  TrainController->LogActionError(56, HeadCode, "", RouteForceCancelled, TrackElement.ElementID);
3124  }
3125  AllRoutes->GetModifiableRouteAt(21, RouteNumber).ForceCancelRoute(4);
3126  }
3127  }
3128 
3129  // for LinkNumber = 3, potentially fouled diagonals are at H+1, V, Lk 1 & H, V-1 Lk 9
3130  else if(LinkNumber == 3)
3131  {
3132  if(AllRoutes->FindRouteNumberFromRoute2MultiMapNoErrors(2, TrackElement.HLoc + 1, TrackElement.VLoc, 1, RouteNumber))
3133  {
3134  if(AllRoutes->GetFixedRouteAt(209, RouteNumber).PrefDirSize() > 2)
3135  { // don't call for stub end routes
3136  TrainController->LogActionError(57, HeadCode, "", RouteForceCancelled, TrackElement.ElementID);
3137  LogActionErrorCalled = true;
3138  }
3139  AllRoutes->GetModifiableRouteAt(22, RouteNumber).ForceCancelRoute(5);
3140  }
3141  if(AllRoutes->FindRouteNumberFromRoute2MultiMapNoErrors(3, TrackElement.HLoc, TrackElement.VLoc - 1, 9, RouteNumber))
3142  // not else in case have different routes on each diagonal, though shouldn't be possible
3143  {
3144  if(!LogActionErrorCalled && AllRoutes->GetFixedRouteAt(210, RouteNumber).PrefDirSize() > 2)
3145  { // don't call for stub end routes
3146  TrainController->LogActionError(58, HeadCode, "", RouteForceCancelled, TrackElement.ElementID);
3147  }
3148  AllRoutes->GetModifiableRouteAt(23, RouteNumber).ForceCancelRoute(6);
3149  }
3150  }
3151 
3152  // for LinkNumber = 7, potentially fouled diagonals are at H-1, V, Lk 9 & H, V+1 Lk 1
3153  else if(LinkNumber == 7)
3154  {
3155  if(AllRoutes->FindRouteNumberFromRoute2MultiMapNoErrors(4, TrackElement.HLoc - 1, TrackElement.VLoc, 9, RouteNumber))
3156  {
3157  if(AllRoutes->GetFixedRouteAt(211, RouteNumber).PrefDirSize() > 2)
3158  { // don't call for stub end routes
3159  TrainController->LogActionError(59, HeadCode, "", RouteForceCancelled, TrackElement.ElementID);
3160  LogActionErrorCalled = true;
3161  }
3162  AllRoutes->GetModifiableRouteAt(24, RouteNumber).ForceCancelRoute(7);
3163  }
3164  if(AllRoutes->FindRouteNumberFromRoute2MultiMapNoErrors(5, TrackElement.HLoc, TrackElement.VLoc + 1, 1, RouteNumber))
3165  // not else in case have different routes on each diagonal, though shouldn't be possible
3166  {
3167  if(!LogActionErrorCalled && AllRoutes->GetFixedRouteAt(212, RouteNumber).PrefDirSize() > 2)
3168  { // don't call for stub end routes
3169  TrainController->LogActionError(60, HeadCode, "", RouteForceCancelled, TrackElement.ElementID);
3170  }
3171  AllRoutes->GetModifiableRouteAt(25, RouteNumber).ForceCancelRoute(8);
3172  }
3173  }
3174 
3175  // for LinkNumber = 9, potentially fouled diagonals are at H+1, V, Lk 7 & H, V+1 Lk 3
3176  else if(LinkNumber == 9)
3177  {
3178  if(AllRoutes->FindRouteNumberFromRoute2MultiMapNoErrors(6, TrackElement.HLoc + 1, TrackElement.VLoc, 7, RouteNumber))
3179  {
3180  if(AllRoutes->GetFixedRouteAt(213, RouteNumber).PrefDirSize() > 2)
3181  { // don't call for stub end routes
3182  TrainController->LogActionError(61, HeadCode, "", RouteForceCancelled, TrackElement.ElementID);
3183  LogActionErrorCalled = true;
3184  }
3185  AllRoutes->GetModifiableRouteAt(26, RouteNumber).ForceCancelRoute(9);
3186  }
3187  if(AllRoutes->FindRouteNumberFromRoute2MultiMapNoErrors(7, TrackElement.HLoc, TrackElement.VLoc + 1, 3, RouteNumber))
3188  // not else in case have different routes on each diagonal, though shouldn't be possible
3189  {
3190  if(!LogActionErrorCalled && AllRoutes->GetFixedRouteAt(214, RouteNumber).PrefDirSize() > 2)
3191  { // don't call for stub end routes
3192  TrainController->LogActionError(62, HeadCode, "", RouteForceCancelled, TrackElement.ElementID);
3193  }
3194  AllRoutes->GetModifiableRouteAt(27, RouteNumber).ForceCancelRoute(10);
3195  }
3196  }
3197  }
3198  }
3199  Utilities->CallLogPop(698);
3200  return; // no route on other track or no other track
3201  }
3202  // here if there is a route at Element & EntryPos - so there can't be a route on the other track if a 4 track element, unless it's a bridge & that's ok
3203  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < AllRoutes->GetFixedRouteAt(155, RouteNumber).PrefDirSize(); x++)
3204  {
3205  RouteElement = AllRoutes->GetFixedRouteAt(156, RouteNumber).GetFixedPrefDirElementAt(165, x);
3206  bool PointsAtElement = (Track->TrackElementAt(987, Element).TrackType == Points); // new after v2.4.1 for points check - Xeon repoted it 30/05/20. He found that for routes that
3207  if(RouteElement.GetTrackVectorPosition() == (unsigned int)Element) // cross bridges at both levels can have entrypos 0 & other exitpos 2 so if don't have this check can cancel a route wrongly
3208  {
3209  if(RouteElement.GetELinkPos() == EntryPos)
3210  {
3211  Utilities->CallLogPop(699);
3212  return; // right direction
3213  }
3214  else if((RouteElement.GetELinkPos() == 2) && (EntryPos == 0) && PointsAtElement)
3215  {
3216  Utilities->CallLogPop(700);
3217  return; // right direction (points)
3218  }
3219  else if((RouteElement.GetELinkPos() == 0) && (EntryPos == 2) && PointsAtElement)
3220  {
3221  Utilities->CallLogPop(701);
3222  return; // right direction (points)
3223  }
3224  else if(RouteElement.GetXLinkPos() == EntryPos)
3225  {
3226  WrongRoute = true;
3227  break; // wrong direction
3228  }
3229  else if((RouteElement.GetXLinkPos() == 2) && (EntryPos == 0) && PointsAtElement) // ok for bridges
3230  {
3231  WrongRoute = true;
3232  break; // wrong direction
3233  }
3234  else if((RouteElement.GetXLinkPos() == 0) && (EntryPos == 2) && PointsAtElement) // ok for bridges
3235  {
3236  WrongRoute = true;
3237  break; // wrong direction
3238  }
3239  }
3240  }
3241  if(!WrongRoute)
3242  {
3243  throw Exception("Error, Element in route but no route found in CheckAndCancelRouteForWrongEndEntry");
3244  }
3245  if(AllRoutes->GetFixedRouteAt(180, RouteNumber).PrefDirSize() > 2)
3246  { // don't call for stub end routes
3247  TrainController->LogActionError(50, HeadCode, "", RouteForceCancelled, Track->TrackElementAt(800, Element).ElementID);
3248  }
3249  AllRoutes->GetModifiableRouteAt(14, RouteNumber).ForceCancelRoute(2);
3250  Utilities->CallLogPop(703);
3251 }

3289 
3290 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
3291 
3292 void TTrain::SetTrainMovementValues(int Caller, int TrackVectorPosition, int EntryPos)
3293 /*
3294 Note: Within the loop BrakeRate can only increase and MaxExitSpeed can only reduce
3295 
3296 Summary: Called during PlotStartPosition to set initial values, when stopped and need to restart, and during UpdateTrain when Straddle is LeadMidLag,
3297 i.e. just as the front of a train is about to move fully onto an element, where TrackVectorPosition is the element immediately in front
3298 of the element the front of the train is moving fully on to. The function calculates the times and speeds at the next half-element and
3299 full-element moves.
3300 
3301 Detail: TrackVectorPosition & EntryPos correspond to the TrackVector element immediately in front of where the train is at
3302 the end of the current Update(). EntrySpeed is needed but this is a class data member so isn't passed in. Set the
3303 train BrakeRate to zero (for now, likely to be altered later), & check if zero entry speed with another train directly in front & if so
3304 remain stopped. Pick up the half length value and speed limit for the EntryPos track, and set FrontElementLength to the length of the
3305 EntryPos track, then set LimitingSpeed to the minimum of the element speed limit or the train's maximum speed. Check if running past a
3306 red signal and set SPADFlag if so (use 1 for EntrySpeed rather than 0 as this value is a double so could be slightly in excess of 0).
3307 In this case set the brake rate to maximum to stop as soon as possible.
3308 
3309 For no SPAD calculate the distance that will be travelled at the maximum speed at which the train can exit the next element at half
3310 MaxBrakeRate, this is DistanceAtHalfBraking (also calculate DistanceAtThreeQuarterBraking - used for stopping under signaller control).
3311 DistanceAtHalfBraking is used as the limiting forward look from the next element (i.e. following EntryPos)
3312 for computing the actual braking rate. If no more restrictive speed limits or reasons to stop are found within the forward look then the
3313 train can accelerate or stay at its (local) maximum speed for the next element. The maximum speed on exit from the next element is used
3314 for calculating the forward look because it represents the worst case - i.e. assumes that the train accelerates for the next element.
3315 
3316 A loop is now entered where the CumulativeLength is updated and each successive element (if there are any - current element checked
3317 first to see whether buffers or continuation) in turn is examined: first the length of the
3318 current element is added to the cumulative length; then the half length and speedlimit are set for the next element - points are
3319 followed according to their current setting (Attribute), but derailments are ignored as these are dealt with outside this function; checks
3320 are then made to see whether the next element is a red signal (train should stop before it); next element is a buffer (train should stop
3321 at the end of it so the cumulative length has the next element length added); current element is a buffer (train should stop
3322 at the end of the current element so no need to alter the cumulative length); or have reached a named location stop position. For any of
3323 these reasons, or if stopping under signaller control, there is no more looping, instead the braking rate is calculated to bring the train
3324 to a stop over CumulativeLength. For all normal purposes the braking rate will be less than half (light braking), or less than three
3325 quarters if stopping under signaller control (heavy braking). However if signals are reset in front of a train then the train may need
3326 emergency braking (> 90% max brake rate) and a SPAD may result. Similarly if points are chaged in front of a train that divert it into a
3327 siding then again emeregency braking may be necessary and a crash may result.
3328 
3329 If the train is due to stop then the function calculates the half and full times and speeds and returns. However the calculation depends
3330 on the conditions at entry. If the EntrySpeed is lower than MaxHalfSpeed and the EntryPos element is the one
3331 that the train has to stop at the end of, as it might be for example if train had been stopped at a signal and the next element is a
3332 buffer, then the train accelerates for half the element and brakes for the other half.
3333 Now the BrakeRate is calculated (limited to the MaxBrakeRate), but if it is less than a value calculated at an earlier pass round
3334 the loop then it retains its earlier value (may be due to a close speed restriction that requires more braking than a more distant stop
3335 requirement). The MaxExitSpeedAtHalfBraking (maximum speed at which the train can leave the current element and still stop when required
3336 at half the max braking rate) value is also calculated using EntrySpeed and CumulativeLength, but limiting it to the line speed limit or
3337 train MaxRunningSpeed whichever is the lower. If EntrySpeed > MaxExitSpeedAtHalfBraking then braking is required, so the half and full
3338 speed and time values for the current element are calculated using BrakeRate, EntrySpeed and CurrentElementHalfLength. If need to stop
3339 at the end of the current elemecumulativent for other than a red signal (SPADs can occur) then ExitSpeedFull is set to 0. It should be calculated
3340 as 0 anyway for other than a red signal but this makes sure. If EntrySpeed <= MaxExitSpeedAtHalfBraking then can calculate the half and
3341 full speed and time values for acceleration over the current element, but limit ExitSpeedHalf & Full to MaxExitSpeedAtHalfBraking or to
3342 the current element speed limit if necessary. Check whether ExitSpeedHalf <= EntrySpeed (+0.01 since it's a double) and use constant speed
3343 time values for Half & Full if so, but prior to this increase EntrySpeed if necessary to avoid a divide by zero error.
3344 
3345 If the train is not due to stop within the DistanceAtHalfBraking from the next element following EntryPos then the next element (if there
3346 is one) is checked to see if its speed limit is less than the current value of LimitingSpeed (which is the minimum of any earlier element's
3347 speed limit that has been examined within the loop and the train's MaxRunning speed), and if so LimitingSpeed is set down to it. Now
3348 the MaxExitSpeedAtHalfBraking is calculated, limiting it to LimitingSpeed if less, in case need to accelerate in the current element, in
3349 which case the exit speeds need to be limited to MaxExitSpeedAtHalfBraking. If EntrySpeed > LimitingSpeed then calculate the braking rate
3350 to bring the speed down to LimitingSpeed in CumulativeLength, keeping the existing BrakeRate value if lower and keeping it within
3351 MaxBrakeRate.
3352 
3353 Then, providing the current element isn't a buffer or continuation, the 'Current' values are updated from the 'Next' values ready for
3354 the next loop iteration. The loop is broken out of if the current element is a buffer or continuation, the next element is a
3355 continuation, or (CumulativeLength - FrontElementLength) >= DistanceAtHalfBraking.
3356 
3357 Now the final Half and Full values can be set for braking (if BrakeRate > 0.01), or accelerating - limiting the half and full exit speed
3358 values to MaxExitSpeedAtHalfBraking if necessary, and using constant speed time values if the exit speeds aren't much different to
3359 EntrySpeed and EntrySpeed > 0.01 (to avoid a divide by zero error).
3360 
3361 Note that in no circumstances will a train stop when straddling 3 elements, it will always be fully on two elements. This is ensured
3362 by UpdateTrain() which never sets any stop conditions unless the train is fully on 2 elements when that function returns, i.e. entered
3363 when Straddle == LeadMidLag
3364 */
3365 {
3366  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",SetTrainMovementValues," + AnsiString(TrackVectorPosition) + "," +
3367  AnsiString(EntryPos) + "," + HeadCode);
3368  int EntryHalfLength, CurrentElementHalfLength, NextElementHalfLength, CumulativeLength = 0, CurrentTrackVectorPosition = TrackVectorPosition;
3369  int DistanceAtHalfBraking, DistanceAtThreeQuarterBraking, ExitPos, NextTrackVectorPosition, NextEntryPos;
3370  bool RedSignalFlag = false, BuffersFlag = false, StationFlag = false, BuffersOrContinuationNowFlag = false, ContinuationNextFlag = false,
3371  TrainInFrontInSignallerModeFlag = false;
3372  double LimitingSpeed, FrontElementMaxSpeed, MaxExitSpeedAtHalfBrakingSquared, MaxExitSpeedAtHalfBraking, NextSpeedLimit, TempBrakeRate;
3373  double ExitSpeedHalfSquared, ExitSpeedFullSquared;
3374  bool SignallerStopRequired = false;
3375 
3376  MaxExitSpeed = MaxRunningSpeed;
3377  // set high to begin with to avoid divide by zero errors on restart after stops, will be set lower later
3378 
3379  // Member variables: EntrySpeed, ExitSpeedHalf, ExitSpeedFull, MaxExitSpeed, BrakeRate, EntryTime, ExitTimeHalf, ExitTimeFull, FrontElementSpeedLimit, FrontElementLength;
3380 
3381  OneLengthAccelDecel = false;
3382  BrakeRate = 0;
3383 
3384 //find FrontElementLength & FrontElementSpeedLimit (these correspond to TrackVectorPosition input value);
3385  if(CurrentTrackVectorPosition > -1)
3386  {
3387  if(Track->TrackElementAt(855, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).TrackType == Points) // this test & section added at v0.6
3388  {
3389  if((EntryPos == 0) || (EntryPos == 2))
3390  {
3391  if(Track->TrackElementAt(856, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).Attribute == 0)
3392  {
3393  CurrentElementHalfLength = (Track->TrackElementAt(857, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).Length01) / 2;
3394  FrontElementSpeedLimit = Track->TrackElementAt(858, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).SpeedLimit01;
3395  }
3396  else
3397  {
3398  CurrentElementHalfLength = (Track->TrackElementAt(859, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).Length23) / 2;
3399  FrontElementSpeedLimit = Track->TrackElementAt(860, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).SpeedLimit23;
3400  }
3401  }
3402  else if(EntryPos == 1)
3403  {
3404  CurrentElementHalfLength = (Track->TrackElementAt(861, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).Length01) / 2;
3405  FrontElementSpeedLimit = Track->TrackElementAt(862, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).SpeedLimit01;
3406  }
3407  else // == 3
3408  {
3409  CurrentElementHalfLength = (Track->TrackElementAt(863, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).Length23) / 2;
3410  FrontElementSpeedLimit = Track->TrackElementAt(864, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).SpeedLimit23;
3411  }
3412  }
3413  else
3414  {
3415  if(EntryPos > 1)
3416  {
3417  CurrentElementHalfLength = (Track->TrackElementAt(348, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).Length23) / 2;
3418  FrontElementSpeedLimit = Track->TrackElementAt(349, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).SpeedLimit23;
3419  }
3420  else
3421  {
3422  CurrentElementHalfLength = (Track->TrackElementAt(350, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).Length01) / 2;
3423  FrontElementSpeedLimit = Track->TrackElementAt(351, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).SpeedLimit01;
3424  }
3425  }
3426  EntryHalfLength = CurrentElementHalfLength;
3427  FrontElementLength = 2 * CurrentElementHalfLength;
3428  }
3429  else
3430  {
3431  throw Exception("Error - CurrentTrackVectorPosition < 0 in SetTrainMovementValues");
3432  }
3433  if((CurrentElementHalfLength < 0) || (FrontElementSpeedLimit < 0))
3434  {
3435  throw Exception("Error - HalfLength or SpeedLimit < 0 in SetTrainMovementValues");
3436  }
3437 
3438  // check if zero entry speed with another train directly in front & if so remain stopped
3439  if(Track->OtherTrainOnTrack(2, CurrentTrackVectorPosition, EntryPos, TrainID) && (EntrySpeed < 1))
3440  {
3441  EntrySpeed = 0;
3442  ExitSpeedHalf = 0;
3443  ExitSpeedFull = 0;
3444  MaxExitSpeed = 0;
3445  BrakeRate = 0;
3446  ExitTimeHalf = EntryTime + TDateTime(1/24); //set this high in case used later though unlikely
3447  ExitTimeFull = EntryTime + TDateTime(1/23); //set about 2.5 mins later than half time
3448  StoppedForTrainInFront = true;
3449  Utilities->CallLogPop(705);
3450  return;
3451  }
3452 
3453  // new at v2.4.0 - check for stopped and zero power
3454  if((EntrySpeed < 1) && PowerAtRail < 1)
3455  {
3456  EntrySpeed = 0;
3457  ExitSpeedHalf = 0;
3458  ExitSpeedFull = 0;
3459  MaxExitSpeed = 0;
3460  BrakeRate = 0;
3461  ExitTimeHalf = EntryTime + TDateTime(1/24); //set this high in case used later though unlikely
3462  ExitTimeFull = EntryTime + TDateTime(1/23); //set about 2.5 mins later than half time
3463  StoppedWithoutPower = true;
3464  Utilities->CallLogPop(2125);
3465  return;
3466  }
3467 
3468 //set LimitingSpeed & FrontElementMaxSpeed (internal values)
3469  if(BeingCalledOn)
3470  {
3471  LimitingSpeed = CallOnMaxSpeed;
3472  }
3473  else
3474  {
3475  LimitingSpeed = MaximumSpeedLimit;
3476  }
3477  if(LimitingSpeed > FrontElementSpeedLimit)
3478  LimitingSpeed = FrontElementSpeedLimit;
3479  if(LimitingSpeed > MaxRunningSpeed) //MaxRunningSpeed is set in AddTrain depending on timetable or signaller control mode
3480  LimitingSpeed = MaxRunningSpeed;
3481  FrontElementMaxSpeed = LimitingSpeed;
3482 
3483 /*
3484  for braking the deceleration rate is constant so the following formuli (Newton's Laws) are used:-
3485  (1) V^2/(3.6^2) = U^2/(3.6^2) - 2FS;
3486  (2) V/3.6 = U/3.6 - FT;
3487  (3) S = UT/3.6 - 0.5FT^2
3488  where(V = final speed in kph [km/h/3.6 = m/s], U = initial speed in km/h, F = deceleration rate in m/s/s, S = distance in m & T = time in secs)
3489 
3490  for accelerating the energy input rate (PowerAtRail) is constant so the following formuli are used:-
3491  (4) V^2/(3.6^2) - U^2/(3.6^2) = A^2T;
3492  (5) V = 3.6 * ((1.5*S*A^2) + U^3/ (3.6)^3)^0.333334;
3493  where A is a constant (2*PowerAtRail/Mass)^0.5; V = final speed in kph, U = initial speed in kph , S = distance in m & T = time in secs
3494  It's a bit unrealistic during the early acceleration phase as it will be too rapid, but shouldn't affect the running unduly
3495 
3496  calc max speed that can attain on exit from next element (as could accelerate over next element) and use that speed to calc
3497  DistanceAtHalfBraking, if use actual speed may miss a stop requirement just outside look-ahead & accelerate, and at next calc
3498  be unable to stop or have hard acceleration followed immediately by hard braking, this speed makes for smoother operation
3499 */
3500 
3501 // check if running past a red signal without permission
3502  if((Track->TrackElementAt(352, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).Config[Track->GetNonPointsOppositeLinkPos(EntryPos)] == Signal) && (Track->TrackElementAt(353,
3503  CurrentTrackVectorPosition).Attribute == 0) && (EntrySpeed > 1) && !AllowedToPassRedSignal)
3504  {
3505  SPADFlag = true; // user has to intervene to reset & restart after spad
3506  }
3507 
3508  if(!SPADFlag)
3509  {
3510  ExitSpeedFull = 3.6 * Power(((3 * EntryHalfLength * AValue * AValue) + (EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed / 3.6 / 3.6 / 3.6)), 0.333334);
3511 
3512  double ExitSpeedAtMaxBraking;
3513  // below introduced at v2.4.0, was ExitSpeedFull = LimitingSpeed; but that allowed very high brake rates when
3514  // took signaller control of a fast failed train with signaller limiting speed 30km/h
3515  if((EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed) <= (2 * MaxBrakeRate * FrontElementLength))
3516  {
3517  ExitSpeedAtMaxBraking = 0;
3518  }
3519  else
3520  {
3521  ExitSpeedAtMaxBraking = sqrt((EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed) - 2 * MaxBrakeRate * FrontElementLength);
3522  }
3523  double SpeedToUse;
3524  // use the highest of LimitingSpeed or ExitSpeedAtMaxBraking - added after v2.4.1 because trains entering at a continuation with zero (or very low) speed
3525  // & 2 elements before signal caused ExitSpeedAtMaxBraking & hence DistanceAtHalfBraking and DistanceAtThreeQuarterBraking to be zero, so no restriction was recognised
3526  // for first element & train accelerated at maximum rate, then at 2nd element train couldn't brake in time and overran the signal - notified by Micke via Discord on 02/06/20
3527  if(ExitSpeedAtMaxBraking > LimitingSpeed)
3528  {
3529  SpeedToUse = ExitSpeedAtMaxBraking;
3530  }
3531  else
3532  {
3533  SpeedToUse = LimitingSpeed;
3534  }
3535  if(ExitSpeedFull > SpeedToUse)
3536  {
3537  ExitSpeedFull = SpeedToUse;
3538  }
3539  DistanceAtHalfBraking = ExitSpeedFull * ExitSpeedFull / 3.6 / 3.6 / MaxBrakeRate;
3540  DistanceAtThreeQuarterBraking = ExitSpeedFull * ExitSpeedFull / 3.6 / 3.6 / 1.5 / MaxBrakeRate; // used for signaller stops
3541 
3542  //now enter a do loop to examine each element in turn from the front of the train to calc the cumulative length and to see if a stop is required (flag set if so -
3543  //RedSignalFlag, BuffersFlag, StationFlag, TrainInFrontInSignallerModeFlag, SignallerStopRequired, StepForwardFlag) in which case there are no more loops
3544  // break out of the loop when ((CumulativeLength - FrontElementLength) < DistanceAtHalfBraking ) && ((!BuffersOrContinuationNowFlag && !ContinuationNextFlag) || SignallerStoppingFlag);
3545 
3546  do
3547  {
3548  RedSignalFlag = false;
3549  BuffersFlag = false;
3550  StationFlag = false;
3551  BuffersOrContinuationNowFlag = false;
3552  ContinuationNextFlag = false;
3553  // have to reset this after the above test
3554  // add current element length to CumulativeLength
3555  CumulativeLength += (2 * CurrentElementHalfLength);
3556  if((CumulativeLength >= DistanceAtThreeQuarterBraking) && (TrainMode == Signaller) && SignallerStoppingFlag)
3557  {
3558  SignallerStopRequired = true;
3559  // once set stays set until SignallerStoppingFlag reset, providing !BuffersOrContinuationNowFlag,
3560  // set SignallerStopBrakeRate to stop in CumulativeLength unless already higher (i.e. can only increase)
3561  double TempBR = EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed / 2 / 3.6 / 3.6 / CumulativeLength;
3562  if(SignallerStopBrakeRate < TempBR)
3563  {
3564  SignallerStopBrakeRate = TempBR;
3565  }
3566  }
3567  // first check for stops within the length of the current element, where don't want any more checks & don't want
3568  // to add in any extra to the CumulativeLength. Only applies for buffers & station stops as signals should have been caught
3569  // during the last loop when the NextTrackVectorPosition was the signal.
3570 
3571  // check if current element is a buffer
3572  if(Track->TrackElementAt(374, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).TrackType == Buffers)
3573  {
3574  // no need to add in the length of this element to CumulativeLength as already included
3575  BuffersFlag = true;
3576  }
3577  // check if current element is a station stop
3578  if(TrainMode == Timetable)
3579  {
3580  bool StopRequired = false;
3581  if(!TimetableFinished && (NameInTimetableBeforeCDT(12, Track->TrackElementAt(375, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).ActiveTrackElementName,
3582  StopRequired) > -1) && ((Track->TrackElementAt(376, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).StationEntryStopLinkPos1 == EntryPos) ||
3583  (Track->TrackElementAt(377, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).StationEntryStopLinkPos2 == EntryPos)))
3584  {
3585  // no need to add in the length of element to CumulativeLength
3586  if(StopRequired)
3587  StationFlag = true;
3588  }
3589  }
3590  else
3591  {
3592  StationFlag = false;
3593  }
3594 
3595  // set NextHalfLength & NextSpeedLimit, but only if current element not buffers or exit continuation - no next element for them
3596  if(((Track->TrackElementAt(354, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).TrackType == Buffers) || (Track->TrackElementAt(355,
3597  CurrentTrackVectorPosition).TrackType == Continuation)) && (EntryPos == 1))
3598  {
3599  BuffersOrContinuationNowFlag = true;
3600  }
3601  if(!BuffersOrContinuationNowFlag && !BuffersFlag && !StationFlag) // skip if buffers or station flags already set
3602  {
3603  if(Track->TrackElementAt(356, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).TrackType == Points)
3604  {
3605  if((EntryPos == 0) || (EntryPos == 2))
3606  {
3607  if(Track->TrackElementAt(357, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).Attribute == 0)
3608  ExitPos = 1;
3609  else
3610  ExitPos = 3;
3611  }
3612  else
3613  ExitPos = 0;
3614  }
3615  else
3616  ExitPos = Track->GetNonPointsOppositeLinkPos(EntryPos);
3617  NextTrackVectorPosition = Track->TrackElementAt(358, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).Conn[ExitPos];
3618  NextEntryPos = Track->TrackElementAt(359, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).ConnLinkPos[ExitPos];
3619  if(NextTrackVectorPosition > -1)
3620  {
3621  if(Track->TrackElementAt(845, NextTrackVectorPosition).TrackType == Points)
3622  // this test & section added at v0.6
3623  {
3624  if((NextEntryPos == 0) || (NextEntryPos == 2))
3625  {
3626  if(Track->TrackElementAt(846, NextTrackVectorPosition).Attribute == 0)
3627  {
3628  NextElementHalfLength = (Track->TrackElementAt(847, NextTrackVectorPosition).Length01) / 2;
3629  NextSpeedLimit = Track->TrackElementAt(848, NextTrackVectorPosition).SpeedLimit01;
3630  }
3631  else
3632  {
3633  NextElementHalfLength = (Track->TrackElementAt(849, NextTrackVectorPosition).Length23) / 2;
3634  NextSpeedLimit = Track->TrackElementAt(850, NextTrackVectorPosition).SpeedLimit23;
3635  }
3636  }
3637  else if(NextEntryPos == 1)
3638  {
3639  NextElementHalfLength = (Track->TrackElementAt(851, NextTrackVectorPosition).Length01) / 2;
3640  NextSpeedLimit = Track->TrackElementAt(852, NextTrackVectorPosition).SpeedLimit01;
3641  }
3642  else // == 3
3643  {
3644  NextElementHalfLength = (Track->TrackElementAt(853, NextTrackVectorPosition).Length23) / 2;
3645  NextSpeedLimit = Track->TrackElementAt(854, NextTrackVectorPosition).SpeedLimit23;
3646  }
3647  }
3648  else
3649  {
3650  if(NextEntryPos > 1)
3651  {
3652  NextElementHalfLength = (Track->TrackElementAt(360, NextTrackVectorPosition).Length23) / 2;
3653  NextSpeedLimit = Track->TrackElementAt(361, NextTrackVectorPosition).SpeedLimit23;
3654  }
3655  else
3656  {
3657  NextElementHalfLength = (Track->TrackElementAt(362, NextTrackVectorPosition).Length01) / 2;
3658  NextSpeedLimit = Track->TrackElementAt(363, NextTrackVectorPosition).SpeedLimit01;
3659  }
3660  }
3661  }
3662  else
3663  {
3664  throw Exception("Error - Trying to access NextTrackVectorPosition when none present in SetTrainMovementValues");
3665  }
3666  // now check for stops, first cover those where don't want to add in length of next element
3667  // check if next element is a red signal - Attr 0,
3668  // note that this doesn't apply to trains stopped at a red signal since the signal position is
3669  // CurrentTrackVectorPosition not NextTrackVectorPosition
3670  bool StopRequired;
3671  if(Track->TrackElementAt(364, NextTrackVectorPosition).Config[Track->GetNonPointsOppositeLinkPos(NextEntryPos)] == Signal)
3672  {
3673  if(Track->TrackElementAt(365, NextTrackVectorPosition).Attribute == 0)
3674  // no need to add in the length of element to CumulativeLength
3675  RedSignalFlag = true;
3676  // next element is a red signal
3677  }
3678  // check if current element is a station & next element contains a train - trains will always stop without crashing at a
3679  // station they are due to stop at even if there is a train in front blocking the normal stop position - providing there is
3680  // at least one platform element free
3681  else if((TrainMode == Timetable) && !TimetableFinished && (NameInTimetableBeforeCDT(10, Track->TrackElementAt(368,
3682  CurrentTrackVectorPosition).ActiveTrackElementName, StopRequired) > -1) && Track->OtherTrainOnTrack(3, NextTrackVectorPosition,
3683  NextEntryPos, TrainID))
3684  {
3685  // no need to add in the length of element to CumulativeLength
3686  if(StopRequired)
3687  StationFlag = true;
3688  }
3689  // check if next element contains a train & in Signaller mode (always stops for train in front if in signaller mode)
3690  else if((TrainMode == Signaller) && Track->OtherTrainOnTrack(4, NextTrackVectorPosition, NextEntryPos, TrainID))
3691  // (Track->TrackElementAt(651, NextTrackVectorPosition).TrainIDOnElement > -1))
3692  {
3693  // no need to add in the length of element to CumulativeLength
3694  TrainInFrontInSignallerModeFlag = true;
3695  }
3696  // check if next element is a buffer
3697  else if(Track->TrackElementAt(366, NextTrackVectorPosition).TrackType == Buffers)
3698  {
3699  // need to add in the length of that element to CumulativeLength
3700  CumulativeLength += Track->TrackElementAt(367, NextTrackVectorPosition).Length01;
3701  BuffersFlag = true;
3702  }
3703  // check if next element is a station stop
3704  else if((TrainMode == Timetable) && !TimetableFinished && (NameInTimetableBeforeCDT(11, Track->TrackElementAt(370,
3705  NextTrackVectorPosition).ActiveTrackElementName, StopRequired) > -1) && ((Track->TrackElementAt(371,
3706  NextTrackVectorPosition).StationEntryStopLinkPos1 == EntryPos) || (Track->TrackElementAt(372,
3707  NextTrackVectorPosition).StationEntryStopLinkPos2 == EntryPos)))
3708  {
3709  // need to add in the length of that element to CumulativeLength if a stop required
3710  if(StopRequired)
3711  {
3712  StationFlag = true;
3713  CumulativeLength += Track->TrackElementAt(373, NextTrackVectorPosition).Length01;
3714  }
3715  }
3716  }
3717  //now can decide whether need to stop over CumulativeLength
3718  if(RedSignalFlag || BuffersFlag || StationFlag || TrainInFrontInSignallerModeFlag || SignallerStopRequired || StepForwardFlag) // no more loops
3719  {
3720  // have to come to a stop over CumulativeLength
3721  if(CumulativeLength == FrontElementLength)
3722  // will be if StepForwardFlag (if stopped to begin with on zero power then earlier check will intercept it and it won't reach here
3723  // only one length to go before stop so check whether need to accelerate for half length then brake for latter
3724  // half; calc speed at halfway point that corresponds to half braking rate for latter half of track element,
3725  // and if less than EntrySpeed then skip this section (don't need any acceleration)
3726  // if not calc speed at halfway point & if less than above set half speed to this value;
3727  // use constant acceleration in calculating half time point
3728  {
3729  MaxExitSpeed = 0;
3730  double MaxHalfSpeed;
3731  double MaxHalfSpeedAtHalfBraking = 3.6 * sqrt(MaxBrakeRate * FrontElementLength / 2);
3732  // have to halve the element length, & can't be zero or negative so no need to test
3733  // if(MaxHalfSpeedAtHalfBraking > LimitingSpeed) MaxHalfSpeed = LimitingSpeed; else MaxHalfSpeed = MaxHalfSpeedAtHalfBraking;
3734  if(MaxHalfSpeedAtHalfBraking > FrontElementMaxSpeed)
3735  MaxHalfSpeed = FrontElementMaxSpeed;
3736  else
3737  MaxHalfSpeed = MaxHalfSpeedAtHalfBraking;
3738  if(MaxHalfSpeed > (2 * EntrySpeed))
3739  // use 2x to prevent kangarooing at last element when had
3740  // been braking smoothly at less that 50% braking rate, 2x should prevent all but extreme cases
3741  {
3742  ExitSpeedHalf = 3.6 * Power(((1.5 * EntryHalfLength * AValue * AValue) + (EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed / 3.6 / 3.6 / 3.6)),
3743  0.333334);
3744  bool HalfSpeedLimited = false;
3745  if(MaxHalfSpeed < ExitSpeedHalf)
3746  {
3747  ExitSpeedHalf = MaxHalfSpeed;
3748  HalfSpeedLimited = true;
3749  }
3750  if(PowerAtRail > 1)
3751  // added at v2.4.0 in case reach here with failed train, when can't use AValue in denominator as close zero
3752  { // [km/h/3.6 = m/s]
3753  ExitTimeHalf =
3754  EntryTime + TDateTime(((ExitSpeedHalf * ExitSpeedHalf) - (EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed)) / 3.6 / 3.6 / (AValue * AValue) / 86400.0);
3755  }
3756  else
3757  {
3758  ExitTimeHalf = EntryTime + TDateTime(EntryHalfLength * 3.6 / EntrySpeed / 86400.0);
3759  }
3760  // the above is the time taken to accelerate to ExitSpeedHalf, so if this is reached before the half
3761  // way point (i.e. HalfSpeedLimited is set) then the time will be too short; change later to equal the
3762  // braking time; not fully accurate but better to be equal than have a short acceleration period followed
3763  // by a long braking period
3764  ExitSpeedFull = 0;
3765  TempBrakeRate = ExitSpeedHalf * ExitSpeedHalf / 2 / 3.6 / 3.6 / EntryHalfLength;
3766  if(TempBrakeRate > MaxBrakeRate)
3767  TempBrakeRate = MaxBrakeRate;
3768  // shouldn't be but leave in anyway
3769  if(TempBrakeRate > BrakeRate)
3770  BrakeRate = TempBrakeRate;
3771  // BrakeRate may already have been set in an earlier loop so don't want to reduce it
3772  ExitTimeFull = ExitTimeHalf + TDateTime(ExitSpeedHalf / 3.6 / BrakeRate / 86400.0);
3773  if(HalfSpeedLimited)
3774  // this is the change referred to above
3775  {
3776  TDateTime BrakingTime = ExitTimeFull - ExitTimeHalf;
3777  ExitTimeHalf = EntryTime + BrakingTime;
3778  ExitTimeFull = ExitTimeHalf + BrakingTime;
3779  }
3780  OneLengthAccelDecel = true; //used in TrackTrainFloat in InterfaceUnit.cpp to show accelerating for first half move then decelerating
3781  Utilities->CallLogPop(1095);
3782  return;
3783  }
3784  }
3785  // set braking to achieve speed = 0 @ CumulativeLength up to MaxBrakeRate
3786  // calc MaxExitSpeed for element at EntryPosition & set to this or existing val if lower,
3787  // calc th, tf, sh, & sf
3788  TempBrakeRate = EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed / 2 / 3.6 / 3.6 / CumulativeLength;
3789  if(TempBrakeRate > MaxBrakeRate)
3790  TempBrakeRate = MaxBrakeRate;
3791  if(TempBrakeRate > BrakeRate)
3792  BrakeRate = TempBrakeRate;
3793  // BrakeRate may already have been set in an earlier loop so don't want to reduce it
3794  if(SignallerStopRequired)
3795  // set BrakeRate to max of its calculated value or SignallerStopBrakeRate
3796  {
3797  if(SignallerStopBrakeRate < BrakeRate)
3798  {
3799  SignallerStopBrakeRate = BrakeRate;
3800  // this prevents the brakerate from reducing for a signaller stop
3801  // regardless of other conditions that may change as progress round the loop
3802  }
3803  }
3804  if(SignallerStopBrakeRate > BrakeRate)
3805  // prevents BrakeRate dropping below SignallerStopBrakeRate once it's been set whether or not SignallerStopRequired set
3806  // SignallerStopRequired may not be set if a red signal found in a later calc, & brakerate may then drop
3807  {
3808  BrakeRate = SignallerStopBrakeRate;
3809  }
3810  int TempMaxExitSpeed;
3811  // calc current value & if less than MaxExitSpeed set that to this
3812  MaxExitSpeedAtHalfBrakingSquared = 3.6 * 3.6 * MaxBrakeRate * (CumulativeLength - FrontElementLength);
3813  if(MaxExitSpeedAtHalfBrakingSquared < 10)
3814  MaxExitSpeedAtHalfBraking = 0;
3815  else
3816  MaxExitSpeedAtHalfBraking = sqrt(MaxExitSpeedAtHalfBrakingSquared);
3817  // if(MaxExitSpeedAtHalfBraking > LimitingSpeed) MaxExitSpeed = LimitingSpeed; else MaxExitSpeed = MaxExitSpeedAtHalfBraking;
3818  // I think the above was dropped because it could cause MaxExitSpeed to increase (MaxExitSpeed is an external variable retained between loops)
3819  if(MaxExitSpeedAtHalfBraking > FrontElementMaxSpeed)
3820  TempMaxExitSpeed = FrontElementMaxSpeed;
3821  else
3822  TempMaxExitSpeed = MaxExitSpeedAtHalfBraking;
3823  if(TempMaxExitSpeed < MaxExitSpeed)
3824  MaxExitSpeed = TempMaxExitSpeed;
3825 
3826  // here have EntrySpeed & MaxExitSpeed (for the next element), BrakeRate (to bring speed to zero over
3827  // Cumulativelength, and Cumulativelength
3828 
3829  if((EntrySpeed > MaxExitSpeed) || SignallerStopRequired || (SignallerStopBrakeRate > 0.01)) // need to brake
3830  {
3831  ExitSpeedHalfSquared = (EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed) - (3.6 * 3.6 * 2 * BrakeRate * EntryHalfLength);
3832  if(ExitSpeedHalfSquared < 10)
3833  ExitSpeedHalf = 0;
3834  else
3835  ExitSpeedHalf = sqrt(ExitSpeedHalfSquared);
3836  ExitTimeHalf = EntryTime + TDateTime((EntrySpeed - ExitSpeedHalf) / 3.6 / BrakeRate / 86400.0);
3837  ExitSpeedFullSquared = (EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed) - (3.6 * 3.6 * 4 * BrakeRate * EntryHalfLength);
3838  if(ExitSpeedFullSquared < 10)
3839  ExitSpeedFull = 0;
3840  else
3841  ExitSpeedFull = sqrt(ExitSpeedFullSquared);
3842  if((StationFlag) && (CumulativeLength == FrontElementLength))
3843  {
3844  ExitSpeedFull = 0;
3845  // force a stop for station (not for buffers or red signal)
3846  }
3847  ExitTimeFull = EntryTime + TDateTime((EntrySpeed - ExitSpeedFull) / 3.6 / BrakeRate / 86400.0);
3848  }
3849  // new condition at v2.4.0
3850  else if(PowerAtRail <= 1)
3851  // use EntrySpeed, CumulativeLength & BrakeRate to calculate the half and full exit times and speeds for next element
3852  // avoid using AValue in denominator or have excessively long times
3853  {
3854  ExitSpeedHalfSquared = (EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed) - (3.6 * 3.6 * BrakeRate * FrontElementLength);
3855  ExitSpeedHalf = sqrt(ExitSpeedHalfSquared);
3856  ExitTimeHalf = EntryTime + TDateTime((EntrySpeed - ExitSpeedHalf) / (3.6 * BrakeRate * 86400.0));
3857 
3858  ExitSpeedFullSquared = (EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed) - (3.6 * 3.6 * 2 * BrakeRate * FrontElementLength);
3859  ExitSpeedFull = sqrt(ExitSpeedFullSquared);
3860  ExitTimeFull = EntryTime + TDateTime((EntrySpeed - ExitSpeedFull) / (3.6 * BrakeRate * 86400.0));
3861  }
3862  else // e.g. moving towards a signal or station after a speed limit, so can accelerate unless no power
3863  // without the power need above condition or have hours of delay times, above added at v2.4.0
3864  {
3865  // for accelerating the energy input rate (PowerAtRail) is constant so the following formuli are used:-
3866  // (1) V^2/(3.6^2) - U^2/(3.6^2) = A^2T; (2) V = 3.6 * ((1.5*S*A^2) + U^3/(3.6^3))^0.333334;
3867  // where A is a constant (2*PowerAtRail/Mass)^0.5; V = final speed in kph, U = initial speed in kph, S = distance & T = time, note that km/h/3.6 = m/s
3868  // This is a bit unrealistic during the early acceleration phase as it will be too rapid, but shouldn't affect the running unduly
3869  BrakeRate = 0;
3870  ExitSpeedHalf = 3.6 * Power(((1.5 * EntryHalfLength * AValue * AValue) + (EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed / 3.6 / 3.6 / 3.6)),
3871  0.333334);
3872  ExitSpeedFull = 3.6 * Power(((3 * EntryHalfLength * AValue * AValue) + (EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed / 3.6 / 3.6 / 3.6)), 0.333334);
3873  // above valid for ExitSpeedHalf & Full <= MaxExitSpeed
3874  if(ExitSpeedHalf <= MaxExitSpeed)
3875  // can accelerate continually over the half length
3876  {
3877  ExitTimeHalf = EntryTime + TDateTime(((ExitSpeedHalf * ExitSpeedHalf) - (EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed)) / 3.6 / 3.6 / (AValue * AValue)
3878  / 86400.0);
3879  if(ExitSpeedFull <= MaxExitSpeed)
3880  // can accelerate continually over the full length
3881  // i.e both (ExitSpeedHalf <= MaxExitSpeed) & (ExitSpeedFull <= MaxExitSpeed)
3882  {
3883  ExitTimeFull =
3884  EntryTime + TDateTime(((ExitSpeedFull * ExitSpeedFull) - (EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed)) / 3.6 / 3.6 / (AValue * AValue) / 86400.0);
3885  }
3886  else // (ExitSpeedHalf <= MaxExitSpeed) but (ExitSpeedFull > MaxExitSpeed)
3887  // accelerate to MaxExitSpeed then reamin at this speed for rest of element
3888  {
3889  // added at v0.6 as a safeguard
3890  if(MaxExitSpeed < EntrySpeed)
3891  MaxExitSpeed = EntrySpeed;
3892  // to prevent DeltaExitTimeToMaxInSecs being negative
3893  if(MaxExitSpeed < 1)
3894  MaxExitSpeed = 1;
3895  // to prevent divide by zero error
3896  // below as was
3897  ExitSpeedFull = MaxExitSpeed;
3898  double DeltaExitTimeToMaxInSecs = ((MaxExitSpeed * MaxExitSpeed) - (EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed)) / 3.6 / 3.6 / (AValue * AValue);
3899  double DistanceToMax = ((MaxExitSpeed * MaxExitSpeed * MaxExitSpeed) - (EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed)) / 3.6 / 3.6 / 3.6 /
3900  (1.5 * AValue * AValue);
3901  double RemainingDistance = double(FrontElementLength) - DistanceToMax;
3902  double DeltaRemainingTimeInSecs = 3.6 * RemainingDistance / MaxExitSpeed;
3903  ExitTimeFull = EntryTime + TDateTime((DeltaExitTimeToMaxInSecs + DeltaRemainingTimeInSecs) / 86400.0);
3904  }
3905  }
3906  else // ExitSpeedHalf > MaxExitSpeed, so ExitSpeedFull must also be > MaxExitSpeed
3907  // accelerate over first half to MaxExitSpeed then remain at this speed for rest of the first and
3908  // second halves of the element
3909  {
3910  // added at v0.6 as a safeguard
3911  if(MaxExitSpeed < EntrySpeed)
3912  MaxExitSpeed = EntrySpeed;
3913  // to prevent DeltaExitTimeToMaxInSecs being negative
3914  if(MaxExitSpeed < 1)
3915  MaxExitSpeed = 1; // to prevent divide by zero error
3916  // below as was
3917  ExitSpeedHalf = MaxExitSpeed;
3918  double DeltaExitTimeToMaxInSecs = ((MaxExitSpeed * MaxExitSpeed) - (EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed)) / 3.6 / 3.6 / (AValue * AValue);
3919  double DistanceToMax = ((MaxExitSpeed * MaxExitSpeed * MaxExitSpeed) - (EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed)) / 3.6 / 3.6 / 3.6 /
3920  (1.5 * AValue * AValue);
3921  double RemainingDistance = double(FrontElementLength / 2) - DistanceToMax;
3922  // remaining distance to half length
3923  double DeltaRemainingTimeInSecs = 3.6 * RemainingDistance / MaxExitSpeed;
3924  ExitTimeHalf = EntryTime + TDateTime((DeltaExitTimeToMaxInSecs + DeltaRemainingTimeInSecs) / 86400.0);
3925  ExitSpeedFull = MaxExitSpeed;
3926  ExitTimeFull = ExitTimeHalf + TDateTime(3.6 * EntryHalfLength / MaxExitSpeed / 86400.0);
3927  }
3928  }
3929  Utilities->CallLogPop(706);
3930  return;
3931  }
3932  else
3933  {
3934  if(!BuffersOrContinuationNowFlag)
3935  {
3936  if(NextSpeedLimit < LimitingSpeed)
3937  LimitingSpeed = NextSpeedLimit;
3938  }
3939  // calc max exit speed at half braking to ensure don't accelerate past it (if acceleration is required)
3940  int TempMaxExitSpeed;
3941  // calc current value & if less than MaxExitSpeed set that to this
3942  // Note that LimitingSpeed is the max value at the end of CumulativeLength, so MaxExitSpeedAtHalfBrakingSquared will be larger
3943  MaxExitSpeedAtHalfBrakingSquared = (LimitingSpeed * LimitingSpeed) + (3.6 * 3.6 * MaxBrakeRate * (CumulativeLength - FrontElementLength));
3944  if(MaxExitSpeedAtHalfBrakingSquared < 10)
3945  MaxExitSpeedAtHalfBraking = 0;
3946  else
3947  MaxExitSpeedAtHalfBraking = sqrt(MaxExitSpeedAtHalfBrakingSquared);
3948  if(MaxExitSpeedAtHalfBraking > FrontElementMaxSpeed)
3949  TempMaxExitSpeed = FrontElementMaxSpeed;
3950  else
3951  TempMaxExitSpeed = MaxExitSpeedAtHalfBraking;
3952  if(TempMaxExitSpeed < MaxExitSpeed)
3953  MaxExitSpeed = TempMaxExitSpeed;
3954  // MaxExitSpeed is an external variable & this can reduce its value
3955  if(EntrySpeed > LimitingSpeed)
3956  // note that LimitingSpeed is more restrictive than MaxExitSpeed
3957  // calc TempBrakeRate & set BrakeRate to this or keep existing val if higher
3958  {
3959  TempBrakeRate = ((EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed) - (LimitingSpeed * LimitingSpeed)) / 3.6 / 3.6 / 2 / CumulativeLength;
3960  if(TempBrakeRate > MaxBrakeRate)
3961  TempBrakeRate = MaxBrakeRate;
3962  // shouldn't be for speedlimits since all known in advance, but include anyway
3963  if(TempBrakeRate > BrakeRate)
3964  BrakeRate = TempBrakeRate;
3965  // BrakeRate may already have been set in an earlier loop so don't want to reduce it
3966  }
3967  }
3968  if(!BuffersOrContinuationNowFlag)
3969  {
3970  CurrentTrackVectorPosition = NextTrackVectorPosition;
3971  EntryPos = NextEntryPos;
3972  CurrentElementHalfLength = NextElementHalfLength;
3973  if(Track->TrackElementAt(378, NextTrackVectorPosition).TrackType == Continuation)
3974  {
3975  ContinuationNextFlag = true;
3976  }
3977  }
3978  }
3979  while(((CumulativeLength - FrontElementLength) < DistanceAtHalfBraking) && ((!BuffersOrContinuationNowFlag && !ContinuationNextFlag) ||
3980  SignallerStoppingFlag));
3981  // check from the end of the front element, if include the front element and could brake during it, then will skip further loops
3982  // & miss a stop requirement just beyond the front element. happened in Richard Standing's railway where a new service introduced
3983  // on a 100m length, with 20m length after & then a red signal - train accelerated over the 100m then caused a SPAD as too short a
3984  // stopping distance after it.
3985 
3986  //(!BuffersOrContinuationNowFlag && !ContinuationNextFlag) true when no continuation on either the next element and next but one element.
3987  //There won't be a buffer on the next element or would have caught earlier, just using this flag for convenience.
3988 
3989  // If SignallerStoppingFlag then don't exit loop because of an imminent continuation, because continuation
3990  // not immediately in front (if it is then LeadElement will be the continuation & SignallerStoppingFlag will be reset in UpdateTrain()),
3991  // need to at least give a chance to stop on signaller command, if keep moving until continuation is immediately in front then will
3992  // exit loop & that is OK as don't want to stop so close to a continuation, if that happens it means that the command to stop was given
3993  // too late
3994 
3995  // set final braking or acc'n speed & time values
3996  if(BrakeRate > 0.01)
3997  {
3998  ExitSpeedHalfSquared = (EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed) - (3.6 * 3.6 * 2 * BrakeRate * EntryHalfLength);
3999  if(ExitSpeedHalfSquared < 10)
4000  ExitSpeedHalf = 0;
4001  else
4002  ExitSpeedHalf = sqrt(ExitSpeedHalfSquared);
4003  ExitTimeHalf = EntryTime + TDateTime((EntrySpeed - ExitSpeedHalf) / 3.6 / BrakeRate / 86400.0);
4004  ExitSpeedFullSquared = (EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed) - (3.6 * 3.6 * 4 * BrakeRate * EntryHalfLength);
4005  if(ExitSpeedFullSquared < 10)
4006  ExitSpeedFull = 0;
4007  else
4008  ExitSpeedFull = sqrt(ExitSpeedFullSquared);
4009  ExitTimeFull = EntryTime + TDateTime((EntrySpeed - ExitSpeedFull) / 3.6 / BrakeRate / 86400.0);
4010  }
4011  else
4012  {
4013  // for accelerating the energy input rate (PowerAtRail) is constant so the following formuli are used:-
4014  // (1) V^2/(3.6^2) - U^2/(3.6^2) = A^2T; (2) V = 3.6 * ((1.5*S*A^2) + U^3/ (3.6)^3)^0.333334;
4015  // where A is a constant (2*PowerAtRail/Mass)^0.5; V = final speed in kph, U = initial speed in kph , S = distance in m & T = time
4016  // This is a bit unrealistic during the early acceleration phase as it will be too rapid, but shouldn't affect the running unduly
4017 
4018  BrakeRate = 0;
4019  ExitSpeedHalf = 3.6 * Power(((1.5 * EntryHalfLength * AValue * AValue) + (EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed / 3.6 / 3.6 / 3.6)), 0.333334);
4020  ExitSpeedFull = 3.6 * Power(((3 * EntryHalfLength * AValue * AValue) + (EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed / 3.6 / 3.6 / 3.6)), 0.333334);
4021  // above valid for ExitSpeedHalf & Full <= MaxExitSpeed
4022  if(ExitSpeedHalf <= MaxExitSpeed)
4023  {
4024  if(PowerAtRail > 1)
4025  // added at v2.4.0 in case reach here with failed train, when can't use AValue in denominator as close zero

4027  ExitTimeHalf = EntryTime + TDateTime(((ExitSpeedHalf * ExitSpeedHalf) - (EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed)) / 3.6 / 3.6 / (AValue * AValue)

4033  }
4034 
4035  if(ExitSpeedFull <= MaxExitSpeed)
4036  // (ExitSpeedHalf <= MaxExitSpeed) & (ExitSpeedFull <= MaxExitSpeed)
4037  {
4038  if(PowerAtRail > 1)
4039  // added at v2.4.0 in case reach here with failed train, when can't use AValue in denominator as close zero
4040  { // [km/h/3.6 = m/s]
4041  ExitTimeFull = EntryTime + TDateTime(((ExitSpeedFull * ExitSpeedFull) - (EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed)) / 3.6 / 3.6 / (AValue * AValue)
4042  / 86400.0);
4043  }
4044  else
4045  {
4046  ExitTimeFull = EntryTime + TDateTime(2 * EntryHalfLength * 3.6 / EntrySpeed / 86400.0);
4047  }
4048  }
4049  else // (ExitSpeedHalf <= MaxExitSpeed) & (ExitSpeedFull > MaxExitSpeed)
4050  {
4051  // added at v0.6 as a safeguard
4052  if(MaxExitSpeed < EntrySpeed)
4053  MaxExitSpeed = EntrySpeed;
4054  // to prevent DeltaExitTimeToMaxInSecs being negative
4055  if(MaxExitSpeed < 1)

4059  double DeltaExitTimeToMaxInSecs;
4060  double DistanceToMax;
4061  if(PowerAtRail > 1) // added at v2.4.0

4064  DistanceToMax = ((MaxExitSpeed * MaxExitSpeed * MaxExitSpeed) - (EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed)) / 3.6 / 3.6 / 3.6 /

4067  else // shouldn't ever get here given that ExitSpeedFull > ExitSpeedHalf

4075  ExitTimeFull = EntryTime + TDateTime((DeltaExitTimeToMaxInSecs + DeltaRemainingTimeInSecs) / 86400.0);
4076  }

4078  else // ExitSpeedHalf > MaxExitSpeed, ExitSpeedFull must be > MaxExitSpeed
4079  {

4081  if(MaxExitSpeed < EntrySpeed)

4083  // to prevent DeltaExitTimeToMaxInSecs being negative
4084  if(MaxExitSpeed < 1)

4093  DistanceToMax = ((MaxExitSpeed * MaxExitSpeed * MaxExitSpeed) - (EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed)) / 3.6 / 3.6 / 3.6 /

4099  // these not really accurate but will be good enough
4100  DistanceToMax = EntryHalfLength / 2;

4103  double DeltaRemainingTimeInSecs = 3.6 * RemainingDistance / MaxExitSpeed;
4104  ExitTimeHalf = EntryTime + TDateTime((DeltaExitTimeToMaxInSecs + DeltaRemainingTimeInSecs) / 86400.0);
4105  ExitSpeedFull = MaxExitSpeed;
4106  ExitTimeFull = ExitTimeHalf + TDateTime(3.6 * EntryHalfLength / MaxExitSpeed / 86400.0);
4107  }
4108  }
4109  }
4110 
4111  else // SPADFlag set
4112  {
4113  BrakeRate = MaxBrakeRate;
4114  ExitSpeedHalfSquared = (EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed) - (3.6 * 3.6 * 2 * BrakeRate * EntryHalfLength);
4115  if(ExitSpeedHalfSquared < 10)
4116  ExitSpeedHalf = 0;
4117  else
4118  ExitSpeedHalf = sqrt(ExitSpeedHalfSquared);
4119  ExitTimeHalf = EntryTime + TDateTime((EntrySpeed - ExitSpeedHalf) / 3.6 / BrakeRate / 86400.0);
4120  ExitSpeedFullSquared = (EntrySpeed * EntrySpeed) - (3.6 * 3.6 * 4 * BrakeRate * EntryHalfLength);
4121  if(ExitSpeedFullSquared < 10)
4122  ExitSpeedFull = 0;
4123  else
4124  ExitSpeedFull = sqrt(ExitSpeedFullSquared);
4125  ExitTimeFull = EntryTime + TDateTime((EntrySpeed - ExitSpeedFull) / 3.6 / BrakeRate / 86400.0);
4126 
4127  // check if the exit speed is < 80% of the stopping speed for the next element, and if so stop at end of this element
4128  // this is because would stop short of end of next element (in reality the time to reach the end of the next element
4129  // would be too short (could be so short as to make the train jump) as time is calculated purely on speed & brake rate);
4130  // 80% is used as the brake rate might be set to come to a halt at the end of the next element in which case the speed
4131  // will be the stopping speed.
4132  if(ExitSpeedFull > 0)
4133  {
4134  if(Track->TrackElementAt(746, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).TrackType == Points)
4135  {
4136  if((EntryPos == 0) || (EntryPos == 2))
4137  {
4138  if(Track->TrackElementAt(747, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).Attribute == 0)
4139  ExitPos = 1;
4140  else
4141  ExitPos = 3;
4142  }
4143  else
4144  ExitPos = 0;
4145  }
4146  else
4147  ExitPos = Track->GetNonPointsOppositeLinkPos(EntryPos);
4148  NextTrackVectorPosition = Track->TrackElementAt(748, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).Conn[ExitPos];
4149  NextEntryPos = Track->TrackElementAt(749, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).ConnLinkPos[ExitPos];
4150  if(NextTrackVectorPosition > -1) // not a continuation or buffer
4151  {
4152  int NextElementLength;
4153  if(NextEntryPos > 1)
4154  {
4155  NextElementLength = (Track->TrackElementAt(750, NextTrackVectorPosition).Length23);
4156  }
4157  else
4158  {
4159  NextElementLength = (Track->TrackElementAt(751, NextTrackVectorPosition).Length01);
4160  }
4161  double NextStoppingSpeed = sqrt(3.6 * 3.6 * 2 * BrakeRate * NextElementLength);
4162  if(ExitSpeedFull < (0.8 * NextStoppingSpeed))
4163  {
4164  ExitSpeedFull = 0;
4165  }
4166  }
4167  }
4168  }
4169  // allow all values to be set normally in case need to brake, then test for zero power & need to coast
4170  if(PowerAtRail < 1) // new at v2.4.0 note that km/h/3.6 = m/s
4171  { // bring to a stop in 20 elements at 100km/h & assume each 100m long for calculating exit times but if on a continuation maintain speed
4172  if(LeadElement > -1)
4173  {
4174  if(Track->TrackElementAt(961, LeadElement).TrackType == Continuation)
4175  // don't stop on a continuation either entering or leaving
4176  {
4177  ExitSpeedHalf = EntrySpeed;
4178  ExitSpeedFull = EntrySpeed;
4179  MaxExitSpeed = LimitingSpeed;
4180  BrakeRate = 0;
4181  ExitTimeHalf = EntryTime + TDateTime((50 * 3.6 / (EntrySpeed) / 86400.0));
4182  // assume length is 50m for ease of calc
4183  ExitTimeFull = ExitTimeHalf + TDateTime((50 * 3.6 / (ExitSpeedHalf) / 86400.0));
4184  Utilities->CallLogPop(2126);
4185  return;
4186  }
4187  }
4188  else if(MidElement > -1)
4189  {
4190  if(Track->TrackElementAt(962, MidElement).TrackType == Continuation)
4191  {
4192  ExitSpeedHalf = EntrySpeed;
4193  ExitSpeedFull = EntrySpeed;
4194  MaxExitSpeed = LimitingSpeed;
4195  BrakeRate = 0;
4196  ExitTimeHalf = EntryTime + TDateTime((50 * 3.6 / (EntrySpeed) / 86400.0));
4197  // assume length is 50m for ease of calc
4198  ExitTimeFull = ExitTimeHalf + TDateTime((50 * 3.6 / (ExitSpeedHalf) / 86400.0));
4199  Utilities->CallLogPop(2127);
4200  return;
4201  }
4202  }
4203  else if(LagElement > -1)
4204  {
4205  if(Track->TrackElementAt(963, LagElement).TrackType == Continuation)
4206  {
4207  ExitSpeedHalf = EntrySpeed;
4208  ExitSpeedFull = EntrySpeed;
4209  MaxExitSpeed = LimitingSpeed;
4210  BrakeRate = 0;
4211  ExitTimeHalf = EntryTime + TDateTime((50 * 3.6 / (EntrySpeed) / 86400.0));
4212  // assume length is 50m for ease of calc
4213  ExitTimeFull = ExitTimeHalf + TDateTime((50 * 3.6 / (ExitSpeedHalf) / 86400.0));
4214  Utilities->CallLogPop(2128);
4215  return;
4216  }
4217  }
4218 
4219  if(EntrySpeed > 7.5) // keep going for at least another element
4220  {
4221  ExitSpeedHalf = EntrySpeed - 2.5;
4222  ExitSpeedFull = EntrySpeed - 5;
4223  MaxExitSpeed = LimitingSpeed;
4224  BrakeRate = 0;
4225  ExitTimeHalf = EntryTime + TDateTime((50 * 3.6 / (EntrySpeed - 1.25) / 86400.0));
4226  // assume length is 50m for ease of calc
4227  ExitTimeFull = ExitTimeHalf + TDateTime((50 * 3.6 / (ExitSpeedHalf - 1.25) / 86400.0));
4228  Utilities->CallLogPop(2129);
4229  return;
4230  }
4231  else // stop immediately, don't enter next element, floating label had displayed last exit speed full on 2nd half move so with zero when fully on element
4232  { // will appear to have slowed at steady rate
4233  ExitSpeedHalf = 0;
4234  ExitSpeedFull = 0;
4235  MaxExitSpeed = LimitingSpeed;
4236  BrakeRate = 0;
4237  ExitTimeHalf = EntryTime + TDateTime(1/24); //set this high in case used later though unlikely
4238  ExitTimeFull = EntryTime + TDateTime(1/23); //set about 2.5 mins later than half time
4239  StoppedWithoutPower = true;
4240  Utilities->CallLogPop(2130);
4241  return;
4242  }
4243  }
4244 
4245  // TempBrakeRate=MinSingle; TempBrakeRate=MaxSingle; TempBrakeRate=MinDouble; TempBrakeRate=MaxDouble;//included to stop warnings from unused declarations in math.hpp
4246  // TempBrakeRate=MinExtended; TempBrakeRate=MaxExtended; TempBrakeRate=MinComp; TempBrakeRate=MaxComp;//included to stop warnings from unused declarations in math.hpp
4247  Utilities->CallLogPop(707);
4248 }

4250 /*
4251  bool TTrain::IsTerminalStation(int TrackVectorPosition, int EntryPos)
4252  {
4253  int NextExitPos;
4254  TTrackElement NextElement = Track->TrackElementAt(379, TrackVectorPosition), TempElement;
4255  if(TimetableVector.empty()) return false;
4256  if(NextElement.ActiveTrackElementName != TimetableVector.begin()->LocationName) return false;
4257  while((NextElement.ActiveTrackElementName == TimetableVector.begin()->LocationName) && (NextElement.TrackType != Buffers))
4258  {
4259  //check for points & follow attribute, but don't worry about a derail as that dealt with elsewhere
4260  if((NextElement.TrackType != Points) || ((EntryPos != 0) && (EntryPos != 2)))
4261  {
4262  NextExitPos = Track->GetNonPointsOppositeLinkPos(EntryPos);
4263  }
4264  else if((NextElement.TrackType == Points) && ((EntryPos == 0) || (EntryPos == 2)))
4265  {
4266  if(NextElement.Attribute == 0) NextExitPos = 1; else NextExitPos = 3;
4267  }

4278 int TTrain::NameInTimetableBeforeCDT(int Caller, AnsiString Name, bool &Stop)
4279 /*
4280  returns the number by which the train ActionVectorEntryPtr needs
4281  to be incremented to point to the location arrival entry or passtime entry before a change of direction. Used to display missed
4282  actions when a stop or pass location has been reached before other timetabled actions have been carried out. If can't find it, or Name
4283  is "", -1 is returned. A change of direction is the limit of the search because a train may not stop at a location on the way out
4284  but stop on way back, and in these circumstances no actions have been missed. Stop indicates whether the train will stop at (true)
4285  or pass (false) the location.
4286 */ {
4287  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",NameInTimetableBeforeCDT," + Name + "," + HeadCode);
4288  Stop = false;
4289  if(TimetableFinished || (Name == ""))
4290  {
4291  Utilities->CallLogPop(957);
4292  return -1;
4293  }
4294  // start looking from current pointer position
4295  for(TActionVectorEntry * Ptr = ActionVectorEntryPtr; Ptr < &TrainDataEntryPtr->ActionVector.back(); Ptr++)
4296  {
4297  if((Ptr->Command == "cdt") || (Ptr->FormatType == Repeat))
4298  {
4299  break;
4300  }
4301  if((Ptr->ArrivalTime > TDateTime(-1)) && (Ptr->LocationName == Name))
4302  {
4303  if((Ptr->FormatType == TimeLoc) || (Ptr->FormatType == TimeTimeLoc))
4304  {
4305  Stop = true;
4306  Utilities->CallLogPop(960);
4307  return (Ptr - ActionVectorEntryPtr);
4308  }
4309  }
4310  if((Ptr->EventTime > TDateTime(-1)) && (Ptr->LocationName == Name) && (Ptr->Command == "pas"))
4311  {
4312  Utilities->CallLogPop(1517);
4313  return (Ptr - ActionVectorEntryPtr);
4314  }
4315  }
4316  Utilities->CallLogPop(959);
4317  return -1; // not found a valid entry
4318 }

4322 bool TTrain::ClearToNextSignal(int Caller)
4323 /* Checks forward from train LeadElement, following leading point attributes but ignoring trailing point attributes,
4324  until finds either a train or a signal/buffers/continuation/loop. If finds a train returns false, else returns true.
4325  Ignores the call-on signal.
4326 */ {
4327  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",ClearToNextSignal" + "," + HeadCode);
4328  int ReturnVal = 0;
4329 
4330  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < Track->TrackVector.size(); x++)
4331  {
4332  Track->TrackVector.at(x).TempTrackMarker01 = false;
4333  Track->TrackVector.at(x).TempTrackMarker23 = false;
4334  }
4335  int CurrentTrackVectorPosition = LeadElement, NextTrackVectorPosition;
4336  int EntryPos = LeadEntryPos, ExitPos, NextEntryPos;
4337 
4338  while(true)
4339  {
4340  if((Track->TrackElementAt(382, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).TrainIDOnElement > -1) && (Track->TrackElementAt(383,
4341  CurrentTrackVectorPosition).TrainIDOnElement != TrainID))
4342  {
4343  ReturnVal = 1;
4344  break;
4345  }
4346  if(((Track->TrackElementAt(384, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).TrackType == Buffers) || (Track->TrackElementAt(385,
4347  CurrentTrackVectorPosition).TrackType == Continuation)) && (EntryPos == 1))
4348  {
4349  ReturnVal = 2;
4350  break;
4351  }
4352  if((EntryPos < 2) && (Track->TrackElementAt(386, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).Config[1 - EntryPos] == Signal) && (Track->TrackElementAt(529,
4353  CurrentTrackVectorPosition).Attribute != 4)) // Attr 4 == call-on signal
4354  {
4355  ReturnVal = 3;
4356  break;
4357  }
4358  if((Track->TrackElementAt(387, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).TrackType == Bridge) || (Track->TrackElementAt(388,
4359  CurrentTrackVectorPosition).TrackType == Crossover))
4360  {
4361  if((EntryPos < 2) && (Track->TrackElementAt(523, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).TempTrackMarker01))
4362  // must be a loop - reached same point as examined earlier
4363  {
4364  ReturnVal = 4;
4365  break;
4366  }
4367  else if((EntryPos > 1) && (Track->TrackElementAt(524, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).TempTrackMarker23))
4368  {
4369  ReturnVal = 4;
4370  break;
4371  }
4372  }
4373  else
4374  {
4375  if((Track->TrackElementAt(525, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).TempTrackMarker01) || (Track->TrackElementAt(526,
4376  CurrentTrackVectorPosition).TempTrackMarker23))
4377  {
4378  ReturnVal = 4;
4379  break;
4380  }
4381  }
4382  if(EntryPos < 2)
4383  Track->TrackElementAt(389, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).TempTrackMarker01 = true;
4384  else
4385  Track->TrackElementAt(527, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).TempTrackMarker23 = true;
4386 
4387  if(Track->TrackElementAt(390, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).TrackType == Points)
4388  {
4389  if((EntryPos == 0) || (EntryPos == 2))
4390  {
4391  if(Track->TrackElementAt(391, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).Attribute == 0)
4392  ExitPos = 1;
4393  else
4394  ExitPos = 3;
4395  }
4396  else
4397  ExitPos = 0;
4398  }
4399  else
4400  ExitPos = Track->GetNonPointsOppositeLinkPos(EntryPos);
4401  NextTrackVectorPosition = Track->TrackElementAt(392, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).Conn[ExitPos];
4402  NextEntryPos = Track->TrackElementAt(393, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).ConnLinkPos[ExitPos];
4403  CurrentTrackVectorPosition = NextTrackVectorPosition;
4404  EntryPos = NextEntryPos;
4405  }
4406  if(ReturnVal == 1)
4407  {
4408  Utilities->CallLogPop(708);
4409  return false;
4410  }
4411  if(ReturnVal == 2)
4412  {
4413  Utilities->CallLogPop(709);
4414  return true;
4415  }
4416  if(ReturnVal == 3)
4417  {
4418  Utilities->CallLogPop(946);
4419  return true;
4420  }
4421  if(ReturnVal == 4)
4422  {
4423  Utilities->CallLogPop(947);
4424  return true;
4425  }
4426  else
4427  {
4428  throw Exception("Error - failed to set ReturnVal in ClearToNextSignal()");
4429  }
4430 }
