4433 
4434 bool TTrain::CallingOnAllowed(int Caller)
4435 /*
4436  Check whether calling-on conditions met - a) approaching train has stopped at a signal but not at a location;
4437  b) if there is a facing train at the station, it is being held appropriately (must be awaiting a join (Fjo or jbo) or a
4438  change of direction (cdt), remaining here (Frh), or under signaller control);
4439  c) at least 1 platform available for the approaching train; d) points (if any) set for direct route into platform;
4440  e) approaching train is to stop at station; f) no more facing signals between train and platform; g) [dropped g]
4441  h) train in front preventing route being set far enough to release stop signal; i) train in front not exiting at continuation; j) signal must be within 4km of
4442  the stop platform; k) [dropped (k), now can set a reoute or part route into platform so can set points more easily.] and l) no existing route conflicts with the route into the platform
4443  If all OK & route or part route not already set then set an unrestricted route into the station (just to the first platform), to prevent point changing or other route conflicts - if a partial route set than can still
4444  change points outside the route or have a route conflict if another route is set.
4445 */ {
4446  if(Track->RouteFlashFlag)
4447  return false;
4448 
4449  // don't want to create a new route from the stop signal if one is already in construction as
4450  // some of the callingon route elements may be involved
4451  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",CallingOnAllowed" + "," + HeadCode);
4452  bool PlatformFoundFlag = false, StopRequired = false, SkipRouteCheck = false, RouteOrPartRouteSet = false; // last added at v1.2.0
4453  int CurrentTrackVectorPosition = LeadElement, NextTrackVectorPosition, ElementNumber = 0, Distance = 0;
4454  int RouteStartPosition;
4455  // this is the track vector position of the start element for the new unrestricted route - one past the stop signal
4456  int PlatformPosition;
4457  // the track vector position of the first stop platfrom
4458  int EntryPos = LeadEntryPos, ExitPos, NextEntryPos, RouteID;
4459  // not used here
4460  AnsiString LeadStationName = Track->TrackElementAt(395, LeadElement).ActiveTrackElementName; // still OK even if ""
4461 
4462  // must be stopped at a signal but not at a location & still in timetable (a)
4463 
4464  if(StoppedAtLocation || !StoppedAtSignal || TimetableFinished || Crashed || Derailed || DerailPending || StoppedAfterSPAD || StoppedForTrainInFront)
4465  // no need to check for SignallerStopped as this function only called in Timetable mode
4466  {
4467  Utilities->CallLogPop(711);
4468  return false;
4469  }
4470  while(true)
4471  {
4472  TTrackElement &CurrentTrackElement = Track->TrackElementAt(396, CurrentTrackVectorPosition);
4473  // don't look further than 4km ahead (j)
4474  if(Distance > 4000)
4475  {
4476  Utilities->CallLogPop(967);
4477  return false;
4478  }
4479  // if find another train on an element in front, before find a valid platform, return false (c)
4480  if((CurrentTrackElement.TrainIDOnElement > -1) && (CurrentTrackElement.TrainIDOnElement != TrainID) && !PlatformFoundFlag)
4481  {
4482  Utilities->CallLogPop(713);
4483  return false;
4484  }
4485  // if find another train in front when there is a valid platform (keep searching after find a platform as train may still
4486  // be facing later on)
4487  if((CurrentTrackElement.TrainIDOnElement > -1) && (CurrentTrackElement.TrainIDOnElement != TrainID) && PlatformFoundFlag)
4488  {
4489  // get LeadElement, if -1 return (could be exiting at continuation) (i)
4490  TTrain OtherTrain = TrainController->TrainVectorAtIdent(12, CurrentTrackElement.TrainIDOnElement);
4491  if(OtherTrain.LeadElement == -1)
4492  {
4493  Utilities->CallLogPop(714);
4494  return false;
4495  }
4496  // if a facing train then make sure it is awaiting a join (Fjo or jbo) or a change of direction (cdt), or remaining here (Frh) (b)
4497  if(OtherTrain.LeadElement == CurrentTrackVectorPosition)
4498  {
4499  AnsiString OtherCommand = OtherTrain.ActionVectorEntryPtr->Command;
4500  if((OtherCommand == "Fjo") || (OtherCommand == "jbo") || (OtherCommand == "cdt") || (OtherCommand == "Frh") ||
4501  (OtherTrain.TrainMode == Signaller))
4502  {
4503  break;
4504  }
4505  else
4506  {
4507  Utilities->CallLogPop(955);
4508  return false;
4509  }
4510  }
4511  else // (h)
4512  {
4513  break;
4514  }
4515  }
4516  // if reach buffers or exit continuation return false (can set route)
4517  if(((CurrentTrackElement.TrackType == Buffers) || (CurrentTrackElement.TrackType == Continuation)) && (EntryPos == 1))
4518  {
4519  Utilities->CallLogPop(716);
4520  return false;
4521  }
4522  // if reach forward signal (other than the one the train is waiting at) return false (can set route) (f)
4523  if((EntryPos < 2) && (CurrentTrackElement.Config[1 - EntryPos] == Signal) && (CurrentTrackVectorPosition != Track->TrackElementAt(404,
4524  LeadElement).Conn[LeadExitPos]))
4525  {
4526  Utilities->CallLogPop(717);
4527  return false;
4528  }
4529  // if reach a location that isn't in timetable return false - drop this as still can't set a route
4530 /*
4531  if((Track->TrackElementAt(405, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).ActiveTrackElementName != "") && (Track->TrackElementAt(406, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).ActiveTrackElementName != LeadStationName) &&
4532  (NameInTimetableBeforeCDT(14, Track->TrackElementAt(407, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).ActiveTrackElementName) == -1))
4533  {
4534  Utilities->CallLogPop(718);
4535  return false;
4536  }
4537 */
4538  // if reach a location that is in timetable set PlatformFoundFlag (but not if position is points set to diverge) (e)
4539  if((CurrentTrackElement.ActiveTrackElementName != "") && (CurrentTrackElement.ActiveTrackElementName != LeadStationName) &&
4540  (NameInTimetableBeforeCDT(15, CurrentTrackElement.ActiveTrackElementName, StopRequired) > -1))
4541  {
4542  if(StopRequired)
4543  {
4544  if((CurrentTrackElement.TrackType != Points) || ((CurrentTrackElement.TrackType == Points) && (CurrentTrackElement.Attribute == 0)))
4545  {
4546  if(!PlatformFoundFlag)
4547  PlatformPosition = CurrentTrackVectorPosition;
4548  // ensure this only set once at first valid platform position - the unrestricted route will end here
4549  PlatformFoundFlag = true;
4550  }
4551  }
4552  }
4553  // Drop this below - was to prevent call-on if front train had left the station. Criterion now is not that front
4554  // train has to be at station but that has to be before the next forward signal
4555 /*
4556  if((Track->TrackElementAt(411, CurrentTrackVectorPosition).ActiveTrackElementName == "") && (PlatformFoundFlag))
4557  {
4558  Utilities->CallLogPop(719);
4559  return false;
4560  }
4561 */
4562  // make sure points are followed correctly (d) & set ExitPos
4563  if(CurrentTrackElement.TrackType == Points)
4564  {
4565  if((EntryPos == 0) || (EntryPos == 2))
4566  {
4567  if(CurrentTrackElement.Attribute == 0)
4568  ExitPos = 1;
4569  else
4570  ExitPos = 3;
4571  }
4572  if(EntryPos == 1)
4573  {
4574  if(CurrentTrackElement.Attribute == 0)
4575  ExitPos = 0;
4576  else
4577  {
4578  Utilities->CallLogPop(720);
4579  return false;
4580  }
4581  }
4582  if(EntryPos == 3)
4583  {
4584  if(CurrentTrackElement.Attribute == 1)
4585  ExitPos = 0;
4586  else
4587  {
4588  Utilities->CallLogPop(721);
4589  return false;
4590  }
4591  }
4592  }
4593  else
4594  ExitPos = Track->GetNonPointsOppositeLinkPos(EntryPos);
4595 
4596  // check existing routes - if element forward of the signal (ElementNumber == 2) is AutoSignals then OK without further checks as this route must extend to
4597  // the next signal so must at least reach the station, also if have another route set (must be unrestricted) from either the stop signal or the element after it
4598  // to or towards the platform (& all points set correctly) then OK, otherwise reject if (1) there are any route elements already set from element
4599  // forward of element after the signal to & including the first platform element (covers crossover with other route set) or (2) a fouled diagonal (k)
4600  if(ElementNumber < 2)
4601  SkipRouteCheck = true;
4602  else
4603  SkipRouteCheck = false;
4604  if(ElementNumber == 1) // the stop signal
4605  {
4606  RouteStartPosition = CurrentTrackVectorPosition;
4607  }
4608 /*
4609  if(ElementNumber == 2)
4610  {
4611  if(AllRoutes->GetRouteTypeAndNumber(18, CurrentTrackVectorPosition, EntryPos, RouteID) == AllRoutes->AutoSigsRoute) AutoSigs = true;
4612  else AutoSigs = false;
4613  if(AllRoutes->GetRouteTypeAndNumber(25, CurrentTrackVectorPosition, EntryPos, RouteID) == AllRoutes->NotAutoSigsRoute) OtherFullRouteSet = true;
4614  }
4615 */
4616  if(ElementNumber > 1)
4617  {
4618  if(AllRoutes->GetRouteTypeAndNumber(26, CurrentTrackVectorPosition, EntryPos, RouteID) != AllRoutes->NoRoute)
4619  RouteOrPartRouteSet = true;
4620  else
4621  RouteOrPartRouteSet = false;
4622  }
4623  if(!SkipRouteCheck && !RouteOrPartRouteSet)
4624  {
4625  if(AllRoutes->TrackIsInARoute(16, CurrentTrackVectorPosition, EntryPos)) // must be a conflicting route
4626  {
4627  Utilities->CallLogPop(1859);
4628  return false;
4629  }
4630  int ExitLink = CurrentTrackElement.Link[ExitPos];
4631  if((ExitLink == 1) || (ExitLink == 3) || (ExitLink == 7) || (ExitLink == 9))
4632  {
4633  if(AllRoutes->DiagonalFouledByRouteOrTrain(6, CurrentTrackElement.HLoc, CurrentTrackElement.VLoc, ExitLink))
4634  {
4635  Utilities->CallLogPop(1850);
4636  return false;
4637  }
4638  }
4639  }
4640 
4641  // finished all checks, now update CurrentTrackVectorPosition & EntryPos for the next iteration
4642  if(EntryPos < 2)
4643  Distance += CurrentTrackElement.Length01;
4644  else
4645  Distance += CurrentTrackElement.Length23;
4646  NextTrackVectorPosition = CurrentTrackElement.Conn[ExitPos];
4647  NextEntryPos = CurrentTrackElement.ConnLinkPos[ExitPos];
4648  CurrentTrackVectorPosition = NextTrackVectorPosition;
4649  EntryPos = NextEntryPos;
4650  ElementNumber++;
4651  } // while(true)
4652 
4653  // if all OK & autosigs route not already set then set an unrestricted route into the station (just to the first platform)
4654  // from the stop signal (note that it may be last in an autosigs route)
4655  // a single element route at the stop signal should have been removed prior to this function being called (that called before
4656  // this in ClockTimer2)
4657 
4658  // now add elements to the CallonVector
4659  TAllRoutes::TCallonEntry CallonEntry(RouteOrPartRouteSet, RouteStartPosition, PlatformPosition);
4660 
4661  AllRoutes->CallonVector.push_back(CallonEntry);
4662  Utilities->CallLogPop(1860);
4663  return true; // return false if fail to set route for any reason

4700 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
4701 
4702 bool TTrain::IsThereAnAdjacentTrain(int Caller, TTrain *&TrainToBeJoinedBy)
4703 { // Used to check for a stopped adjacent train for use in PopUp menu //new at v2.4.0
4704  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",IsThereAnAdjacentTrain" + "," + HeadCode);
4705  // check if there's a stopped adjacent train, if there is but not under sig control give a message in calling function
4706  // first check that train is fully on the railway
4707  bool FrontValid = false, RearValid = false;
4708  TTrackElement FrontAdjacentTrackElement, RearAdjacentTrackElement;
4709 
4710  if((LeadElement == -1) || (MidElement == -1))
4711  {
4712  TrainToBeJoinedBy = NULL;
4713  Utilities->CallLogPop(2131);
4714  return false;
4715  }
4716  if(Track->TrackElementAt(964, LeadElement).Conn[LeadExitPos] > -1)
4717  {
4718  FrontAdjacentTrackElement = Track->TrackElementAt(965, (Track->TrackElementAt(966, LeadElement).Conn[LeadExitPos]));
4719  FrontValid = true;
4720  }
4721  if(Track->TrackElementAt(967, MidElement).Conn[MidEntryPos] > -1)
4722  {
4723  RearAdjacentTrackElement = Track->TrackElementAt(968, (Track->TrackElementAt(969, MidElement).Conn[MidEntryPos]));
4724  RearValid = true;
4725  }
4726  int TrainToBeJoinedByID = -1;
4727 
4728  // first check if on a 2-track element & select correct ID number if so
4729  if(FrontValid)
4730  {
4731  if(FrontAdjacentTrackElement.TrackType == Bridge)
4732  {
4733  if(Track->TrackElementAt(970, LeadElement).ConnLinkPos[LeadExitPos] > 1)
4734  {
4735  TrainToBeJoinedByID = FrontAdjacentTrackElement.TrainIDOnBridgeTrackPos23;
4736  }
4737  else
4738  {
4739  TrainToBeJoinedByID = FrontAdjacentTrackElement.TrainIDOnBridgeTrackPos01;
4740  }
4741  }
4742  else
4743  {
4744  TrainToBeJoinedByID = FrontAdjacentTrackElement.TrainIDOnElement;
4745  }
4746  }
4747  if((TrainToBeJoinedByID < 0) && RearValid)
4748  {
4749  // first check if on a 2-track element & select correct ID number if so
4750  if(RearAdjacentTrackElement.TrackType == Bridge)
4751  {
4752  if(Track->TrackElementAt(971, MidElement).ConnLinkPos[MidEntryPos] > 1)
4753  {
4754  TrainToBeJoinedByID = RearAdjacentTrackElement.TrainIDOnBridgeTrackPos23;
4755  }
4756  else
4757  {
4758  TrainToBeJoinedByID = RearAdjacentTrackElement.TrainIDOnBridgeTrackPos01;
4759  }
4760  }
4761  else
4762  {
4763  TrainToBeJoinedByID = RearAdjacentTrackElement.TrainIDOnElement;
4764  }
4765  }
4766  if(TrainToBeJoinedByID < 0) // no adjacent train
4767  {
4768  TrainToBeJoinedBy = NULL;
4769  Utilities->CallLogPop(2132);
4770  return false;
4771  }
4772  TrainToBeJoinedBy = &(TrainController->TrainVectorAtIdent(44, TrainToBeJoinedByID));
4773  if(!TrainToBeJoinedBy->Stopped())
4774  {
4775  TrainToBeJoinedBy = NULL;
4776  Utilities->CallLogPop(2133);
4777  return false;
4778  }
4779  Utilities->CallLogPop(2134);
4780  return true;
4781 }

4785 void TTrain::LogAction(int Caller, AnsiString OwnHeadCode, AnsiString OtherHeadCode, TActionType ActionType, AnsiString LocationName,
4786  TDateTime TimetableNonRepeatTime, bool Warning)
4787 /*
4788  Time = timetable time, the time adjustments for repeat trains is carried out internally
4789  Not all messages need this, if not needed a dummy value is required but not used
4790 
4791  Arrive: 06:05:40: 2F46 arrived at Old Street 1 minute late
4792  Pass: 06:05:40: 2F46 passed Old Street 1 minute late
4793  Terminate: 06:05:40: 2F46 terminated at Old Street 1 minute late
4794  //NB for Frh just give terminated message but without event time - don't use this function
4795  Depart: 06:05:15: 3F43 departed from Essex Road 2 minutes late
4796  Create: 06:05:40: 2F46 created at Old Street 1 minute late
4797  Enter: 06:05:40: 2F46 entered railway at Old Street 1 minute late
4798  Leave: 06:05:40: 2F46 left railway at 57-N4 1 minute late
4799  FrontSplit: 06:05:40: 2F46 split from front to 3D54 at Old Street 1 minute late
4800  RearSplit: 06:05:40: 2F46 split from rear to 3D54 at Old Street 1 minute late
4801  JoinedByOther: 06:05:40: 2F46 joined by 3D54 at Old Street 1 minute late
4802  ChangeDirection: 06:05:40: 2F46 changed direction at Old Street 1 minute late
4803  NewService: 06:05:40: 2F46 became new service 3D54 at Old Street 1 minute late
4804  TakeManualControl: 06:05:40: 2F46 taken under signaller control at Old Street
4805  RestoreTimetableControl: 06:05:40: 2F46 restored to timetable control at Old Street
4806  RemoveTrain: 06:05:40: 2F46 REMOVED FROM RAILWAY DUE TO CRASH at Old Street
4807  RemoveTrain: 06:05:40: 2F46 REMOVED FROM RAILWAY DUE TO DERAILMENT at Old Street
4808  RemoveTrain: 06:05:40: 2F46 REMOVED FROM RAILWAY at Old Street
4809  SignallerMoveForwards 06:05:40: 2F46 received signaller authority to proceed
4810  SignallerChangeDirection 06:05:40: 2F46 changed direction under signaller control at Old Street
4811  SignallerPassRedSignal 06:05:40: 2F46 received signaller authority to pass red signal
4812  SignallerJoin 06:05:40: 2F46 joined under signaller control by 3D54 at Old Street //new at v2.4.0
4813  TrainFailure 06:05:40: 2F46 suffered an onboard power failure at Old Street //new at v2.4.0
4814  RepairFailedTrain 06:05:40: 2F46 failure repaired at Old Street //new at v2.4.0
4815  SignallerControlStop 06:05:40: 2F46 received signaller instruction to stop
4816  SignallerStop 06:05:40: 2F46 stopped on signaller command
4817  SignallerLeave: 06:05:40: 2F46 left railway under signaller control at 57-N4
4818  SignallerStepForward: 06:05:40: 2F46 received signaller authority to step forward
4819 */ {
4820  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",LogAction," + OwnHeadCode + "," + OtherHeadCode + "," +
4821  AnsiString(ActionType) + "," + LocationName + "," + HeadCode);
4822  AnsiString BaseLog = "", WarningBaseLog = "", PerfLog = "", ActionLog = "";
4823  int IntMinsLate = 0;
4824 
4825  // need to set it in case MinsLate == 0, since it isn't tested for that
4826  if(ActionType == Arrive)
4827  ActionLog = " arrived at ";
4828  if(ActionType == Terminate)
4829  {
4830  if(TerminatedMessageSent) // to avoid it being sent twice
4831  {
4832  Utilities->CallLogPop(1104);
4833  return;
4834  }
4835  ActionLog = " terminated at ";
4836  TerminatedMessageSent = true;
4837  }
4838  if(ActionType == Depart)
4839  ActionLog = " departed from ";
4840  if(ActionType == Pass)
4841  ActionLog = " passed ";
4842  if(ActionType == Create)
4843  ActionLog = " created at ";
4844  if(ActionType == Enter)
4845  ActionLog = " entered railway at ";
4846  if(ActionType == Leave)
4847  ActionLog = " left railway at ";
4848  if(ActionType == FrontSplit)
4849  ActionLog = " split from front to ";
4850  if(ActionType == RearSplit)
4851  ActionLog = " split from rear to ";
4852  if(ActionType == JoinedByOther)
4853  ActionLog = " joined by ";
4854  if(ActionType == ChangeDirection)
4855  ActionLog = " changed direction at ";
4856  if(ActionType == NewService)
4857  ActionLog = " became new service ";
4858  if(ActionType == TakeSignallerControl)
4859  ActionLog = " taken under signaller control at ";
4860  if(ActionType == RestoreTimetableControl)
4861  ActionLog = " restored to timetable control at ";
4862  if(ActionType == RemoveTrain)
4863  {
4864  if(Crashed)
4865  ActionLog = " REMOVED FROM RAILWAY DUE TO CRASH at ";
4866  else if(Derailed)
4867  ActionLog = " REMOVED FROM RAILWAY DUE TO DERAILMENT at ";
4868  else
4869  ActionLog = " REMOVED FROM RAILWAY at ";
4870  }
4871  if(ActionType == SignallerMoveForwards)
4872  ActionLog = " received signaller authority to proceed";
4873  if(ActionType == SignallerStepForward)
4874  ActionLog = " received signaller authority to step forward";
4875  if(ActionType == SignallerChangeDirection)
4876  ActionLog = " changed direction under signaller control at ";
4877  if(ActionType == SignallerPassRedSignal)
4878  ActionLog = " received signaller authority to pass red signal";
4879  if(ActionType == SignallerControlStop)
4880  ActionLog = " received signaller instruction to stop";
4881  if(ActionType == SignallerStop)
4882  ActionLog = " stopped on signaller instruction ";
4883  if(ActionType == SignallerJoin)
4884  ActionLog = " joined under signaller control by ";
4885  if(ActionType == TrainFailure)
4886  ActionLog = " suffered an onboard power failure at ";
4887  if(ActionType == RepairFailedTrain)
4888  ActionLog = " failure repaired at ";
4889  if(ActionType == SignallerLeave)
4890  ActionLog = " left railway under signaller control at ";
4891  if(OtherHeadCode != "")
4892  OtherHeadCode += " at ";
4893  TDateTime ActualTime = TrainController->TTClockTime;
4894 
4895  if(Warning)
4896  {
4897  BaseLog = Utilities->Format96HHMMSS(ActualTime) + " WARNING: " + HeadCode + ActionLog + OtherHeadCode + LocationName;
4898  WarningBaseLog = HeadCode + ActionLog + OtherHeadCode + LocationName;
4899  }
4900  else
4901  {
4902  BaseLog = Utilities->Format96HHMMSS(ActualTime) + ": " + HeadCode + ActionLog + OtherHeadCode + LocationName;
4903  }
4904  bool TimePerformance = true;
4905 
4906  if((ActionType == TakeSignallerControl) || (ActionType == RestoreTimetableControl) || (ActionType == RemoveTrain) || (ActionType == SignallerMoveForwards)
4907  || (ActionType == SignallerChangeDirection) || (ActionType == SignallerPassRedSignal) || (ActionType == SignallerControlStop) ||
4908  (ActionType == SignallerStop) || (ActionType == SignallerLeave) || (ActionType == SignallerStepForward) || (ActionType == SignallerJoin) ||
4909  (ActionType == TrainFailure) || (ActionType == RepairFailedTrain))
4910  // SignallerJoin & RepairFailedTrain new at v2.4.0
4911  {
4912  TimePerformance = false;
4913  }
4914  if(TimePerformance)
4915  {
4916  double MinsLate = ((double)(ActualTime - GetTrainTime(1, TimetableNonRepeatTime))) * 1440;
4917  MinsDelayed = float(MinsLate);
4918  // new v2.2.0 for OpActionPanel, can be positive or negative
4919  if(ActionType == Arrive)
4920  MinsDelayed -= FirstLaterStopRecoverableTime;
4921  // since train has just arrived this value is the
4922  // recoverable time available at this stop, so reduce MinsDelayed by this amount to prevent it being
4923  // subtracted from later stop recoverable times.
4924  if(MinsLate < 0)
4925  {
4926  IntMinsLate = int(ceil(MinsLate));
4927  }
4928  if(MinsLate > 0)
4929  {
4930  IntMinsLate = int(floor(MinsLate));
4931  }
4932  if(IntMinsLate == 0)
4933  {
4934  PerfLog = " on time";
4935  }
4936  else if(IntMinsLate == 1)
4937  PerfLog = " 1 minute late";
4938  else if(IntMinsLate == -1)
4939  PerfLog = " 1 minute early";
4940  else if(IntMinsLate > 1)
4941  PerfLog = " " + AnsiString(IntMinsLate) + " minutes late";
4942  else if(IntMinsLate < -1)
4943  {
4944  int PosIntMinsLate = -IntMinsLate;
4945  PerfLog = " " + AnsiString(PosIntMinsLate) + " minutes early";
4946  }
4947  if(LocationName.Pos('-') > 0)
4948  {
4949  PerfLog = "," + PerfLog;
4950  // if a position add a comma to separate vertical position number from number of minutes (better appearance)
4951  }
4952  Display->PerformanceLog(0, BaseLog + PerfLog);
4953  }
4954  else
4955  Display->PerformanceLog(1, BaseLog);
4956  if(Warning)
4957  {
4958  Display->WarningLog(0, WarningBaseLog);
4959  }
4960 
4961  // update statistics
4962  if((ActionType == Arrive) && (IntMinsLate == 0))
4963  {
4964  TrainController->OnTimeArrivals++;
4965  }
4966  else if((ActionType == Arrive) && (IntMinsLate > 0))
4967  {
4968  TrainController->LateArrivals++;
4969  TrainController->TotLateArrMins += IntMinsLate;
4970  }
4971  else if((ActionType == Arrive) && (IntMinsLate < 0))
4972  {
4973  TrainController->EarlyArrivals++;
4974  TrainController->TotEarlyArrMins += abs(IntMinsLate);
4975  }
4976  else if((ActionType == Pass) && (IntMinsLate == 0))
4977  {
4978  TrainController->OnTimePasses++;
4979  }
4980  else if((ActionType == Pass) && (IntMinsLate > 0))
4981  {
4982  TrainController->LatePasses++;
4983  TrainController->TotLatePassMins += IntMinsLate;
4984  }
4985  else if((ActionType == Pass) && (IntMinsLate < 0))
4986  {
4987  TrainController->EarlyPasses++;
4988  TrainController->TotEarlyPassMins += abs(IntMinsLate);
4989  }
4990  else if((ActionType == Depart) && (IntMinsLate == 0))
4991  {
4992  TrainController->OnTimeDeps++;
4993  }
4994  else if((ActionType == Depart) && (IntMinsLate > 0))
4995  {
4996  TrainController->LateDeps++;
4997  TrainController->TotLateDepMins += IntMinsLate;
4998  }
4999  Utilities->CallLogPop(968);
5000 }

5004 void TTrain::TrainHasFailed(int Caller)
5005 {
5006  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",TrainHasFailed," + HeadCode);
5007  if(Crashed || Derailed || DerailPending)
5008  {
5009  TrainFailurePending = false;
5010  Utilities->CallLogPop(2135);
5011  return;
5012  }
5013  AnsiString LocName = "";
5014 
5015  if(LeadElement > -1)
5016  {
5017  LocName = Track->TrackElementAt(972, LeadElement).ActiveTrackElementName;
5018  }
5019  if((LocName == "") && (MidElement > -1))
5020  {
5021  LocName = Track->TrackElementAt(973, MidElement).ActiveTrackElementName;
5022  }
5023  if((LocName == "") && LeadElement > -1)
5024  {
5025  LocName = Track->TrackElementAt(974, LeadElement).ElementID;
5026  }
5027  if((LocName == "") && (MidElement > -1))
5028  {
5029  LocName = Track->TrackElementAt(975, MidElement).ElementID;
5030  }
5031  TrainController->StopTTClockMessage(81, HeadCode + " has suffered an onboard power failure at " + LocName);
5032  TrainFailed = true;
5033  TrainFailurePending = false;
5034  OriginalPowerAtRail = PowerAtRail;
5035  PowerAtRail = 0.08;
5036  AValue = sqrt(2 * PowerAtRail / Mass);
5037  PlotTrainWithNewBackgroundColour(48, clTrainFailedBackground, Display);
5038  // TrainFailed only called when PlotElements properly set to lead, Mid & Lag elements
5039  if(Stopped())
5040  {
5041  EntrySpeed = 0;
5042  ExitSpeedHalf = 0;
5043  ExitSpeedFull = 0;
5044  MaxExitSpeed = 0;
5045  BrakeRate = 0;
5046  StoppedWithoutPower = true;
5047  }
5048  TrainController->NumFailures++;
5049  LogAction(33, HeadCode, "", TrainFailure, LocName, TDateTime(0), true);
5050  // true for warning, TDateTime not used
5051  Utilities->CallLogPop(2136);
5052 }

5054 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
5055 
5056 void TTrain::FrontTrainSplit(int Caller)
5057 {
5058 /*
5059  Split logic is:- at least one of 4 final train positions must overlap with one of original train positions, & final 4 positions
5060  will maximise the number at the location. Note that this function isn't sophisticated enough to account for trains already at the
5061  location in determining the 4 positions, and will give a failure message if a train obstructs any of the 4 positions. In these
5062  circumstances the other train will need to be moved sufficiently away to release all 4 positions, then the train will split.
5063 */
5064  TrainController->LogEvent("" + AnsiString(Caller) + ",FrontTrainSplit" + "," + HeadCode);
5065  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",FrontTrainSplit" + "," + HeadCode);
5066  if(PowerAtRail < 1)
5067  // new at v2.4.0 (ActionVectorEntryPtr not incremented so can split when power restored
5068  {
5069  if(!ZeroPowerNoFrontSplitMessage)
5070  TrainController->StopTTClockMessage(82, HeadCode + ": A train without power can't split");
5071  ZeroPowerNoFrontSplitMessage = true;
5072  Utilities->CallLogPop(2137);
5073  return;
5074  }
5075  AnsiString LocationName = Track->TrackElementAt(555, LeadElement).ActiveTrackElementName;
5076 
5077  if(LocationName == "")
5078  LocationName = Track->TrackElementAt(837, MidElement).ActiveTrackElementName;
5079  int FirstNamedElementPos, SecondNamedElementPos, FirstNamedLinkedElementPos, SecondNamedLinkedElementPos;
5080  int RearTrainRearPosition, RearTrainFrontPosition, RearTrainExitPos;
5081  int FrontTrainRearPosition, FrontTrainFrontPosition, FrontTrainExitPos;
5082  AnsiString OtherHeadCode = TrainController->GetRepeatHeadCode(1, ActionVectorEntryPtr->OtherHeadCode, RepeatNumber, IncrementalDigits);
5083 
5084  // determine all positions & exits
5085  if(LocationName != "")
5086  {
5087  // if message given only call at ~5 sec intervals
5088  if(!(TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).EventReported == FailLocTooShort) || (UpdateCounter == 0))
5089  {
5090  FirstNamedElementPos = LeadElement;
5091  if(!Track->ThisNamedLocationLongEnoughForSplit(0, LocationName, FirstNamedElementPos,
5092  // check if possible with LeadElement as First
5093  SecondNamedElementPos, FirstNamedLinkedElementPos, SecondNamedLinkedElementPos))
5094  {
5095  FirstNamedElementPos = MidElement;
5096  if(!Track->ThisNamedLocationLongEnoughForSplit(1, LocationName, FirstNamedElementPos,
5097  // if not then accept second if possible (though if Lead no good hard to see how Mid could work, but leave in)
5098  SecondNamedElementPos, FirstNamedLinkedElementPos, SecondNamedLinkedElementPos))
5099  {
5100  if(TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).EventReported != FailLocTooShort)
5101  {
5102  TrainController->LogActionError(6, HeadCode, "", FailLocTooShort, LocationName);
5103  TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).EventReported = FailLocTooShort;
5104  }
5105  Utilities->CallLogPop(1009);
5106  return;
5107  }
5108  }
5109  else
5110  {
5111  // if first is possible then check if all 4 positions at location, and if not try the second
5112  int LeadPosA = FirstNamedElementPos;
5113  int LeadPosB = FirstNamedLinkedElementPos;
5114  int LeadPosC = SecondNamedElementPos;
5115  int LeadPosD = SecondNamedLinkedElementPos;
5116  // count number of positions that are at the location
5117  int LeadNumAtLoc = 0;
5118  if(Track->TrackElementAt(758, LeadPosA).ActiveTrackElementName == LocationName)
5119  LeadNumAtLoc++;
5120  if(Track->TrackElementAt(759, LeadPosB).ActiveTrackElementName == LocationName)
5121  LeadNumAtLoc++;
5122  if(Track->TrackElementAt(760, LeadPosC).ActiveTrackElementName == LocationName)
5123  LeadNumAtLoc++;
5124  if(Track->TrackElementAt(761, LeadPosD).ActiveTrackElementName == LocationName)
5125  LeadNumAtLoc++;
5126  if(LeadNumAtLoc < 4)
5127  {
5128  FirstNamedElementPos = MidElement;
5129  if(!Track->ThisNamedLocationLongEnoughForSplit(4, LocationName, FirstNamedElementPos, SecondNamedElementPos, FirstNamedLinkedElementPos,
5130  SecondNamedLinkedElementPos)) // restore originals
5131  {
5132  FirstNamedElementPos = LeadPosA;
5133  FirstNamedLinkedElementPos = LeadPosB;
5134  SecondNamedElementPos = LeadPosC;
5135  SecondNamedLinkedElementPos = LeadPosD;
5136  }
5137  else // count number at location
5138  {
5139  int MidNumAtLoc = 0;
5140  if(Track->TrackElementAt(762, FirstNamedElementPos).ActiveTrackElementName == LocationName)
5141  MidNumAtLoc++;
5142  if(Track->TrackElementAt(763, FirstNamedLinkedElementPos).ActiveTrackElementName == LocationName)
5143  MidNumAtLoc++;
5144  if(Track->TrackElementAt(764, FirstNamedLinkedElementPos).ActiveTrackElementName == LocationName)
5145  MidNumAtLoc++;
5146  if(Track->TrackElementAt(765, SecondNamedLinkedElementPos).ActiveTrackElementName == LocationName)
5147  MidNumAtLoc++;
5148  if(LeadNumAtLoc > MidNumAtLoc)
5149  // change back, else keep new values
5150  {
5151  FirstNamedElementPos = LeadPosA;
5152  FirstNamedLinkedElementPos = LeadPosB;
5153  SecondNamedElementPos = LeadPosC;
5154  SecondNamedLinkedElementPos = LeadPosD;
5155  }
5156  }
5157  }
5158  }
5159  }
5160  else
5161  {
5162  Utilities->CallLogPop(1791);
5163  return;
5164  }
5165  }
5166  else
5167  throw Exception("Error - LocationName not set in FrontTrainSplit");
5168  // set front & rear train parameters
5169  // need RearTrainRearPosition, RearTrainFrontPosition, RearTrainExitPos, FrontTrainRearPosition, FrontTrainFrontPosition & FrontTrainExitPos;
5170  // have LeadElement & MidElement of train defining its direction, & one or other on FirstNamedElementPos
5171  // have FirstNamedElementPos, SecondNamedElementPos, FirstNamedLinkedElementPos & SecondNamedLinkedElementPos from ThisNamedLocationLongEnoughForSplit.
5172  if(LeadElement == FirstNamedElementPos)
5173  {
5174  if(MidElement == SecondNamedElementPos)
5175  {
5176  FrontTrainFrontPosition = FirstNamedLinkedElementPos;
5177  FrontTrainRearPosition = FirstNamedElementPos;
5178  RearTrainFrontPosition = SecondNamedElementPos;
5179  RearTrainRearPosition = SecondNamedLinkedElementPos;
5180  }
5181  else // MidElement must == FirstNamedLinkedElementPos
5182  {
5183  FrontTrainFrontPosition = SecondNamedLinkedElementPos;
5184  FrontTrainRearPosition = SecondNamedElementPos;
5185  RearTrainFrontPosition = FirstNamedElementPos;
5186  RearTrainRearPosition = FirstNamedLinkedElementPos;
5187  }
5188  }
5189  else // MidElement == FirstNamedElementPos
5190  {
5191  if(LeadElement == SecondNamedElementPos)
5192  {
5193  FrontTrainFrontPosition = SecondNamedLinkedElementPos;
5194  FrontTrainRearPosition = SecondNamedElementPos;
5195  RearTrainFrontPosition = FirstNamedElementPos;
5196  RearTrainRearPosition = FirstNamedLinkedElementPos;
5197  }
5198  else // LeadElement must == FirstNamedLinkedElementPos
5199  {
5200  FrontTrainFrontPosition = FirstNamedLinkedElementPos;
5201  FrontTrainRearPosition = FirstNamedElementPos;
5202  RearTrainFrontPosition = SecondNamedElementPos;
5203  RearTrainRearPosition = SecondNamedLinkedElementPos;
5204  }
5205  }
5206  RearTrainExitPos = -1;
5207  for(int x = 0; x < 4; x++)
5208  {
5209  if(Track->TrackElementAt(584, RearTrainRearPosition).Conn[x] == RearTrainFrontPosition)
5210  {
5211  RearTrainExitPos = x;
5212  break;
5213  }
5214  }
5215  if(RearTrainExitPos == -1)
5216  throw Exception("Error - RearTrainRearPosition not linked to RearTrainFrontPosition in FrontTrainSplit");
5217 
5218  FrontTrainExitPos = -1;
5219  for(int x = 0; x < 4; x++)
5220  {
5221  if(Track->TrackElementAt(585, FrontTrainRearPosition).Conn[x] == FrontTrainFrontPosition)
5222  {
5223  FrontTrainExitPos = x;
5224  break;
5225  }
5226  }
5227  if(FrontTrainExitPos == -1)
5228  throw Exception("Error - FrontTrainRearPosition not linked to FrontTrainFrontPosition in FrontTrainSplit");
5229 
5230  // check no train (apart from self) on any of the 4 elements & fail if so
5231  int TrainIDOnRearOfRearTrain, TrainIDOnFrontOfRearTrain, TrainIDOnRearOfFrontTrain, TrainIDOnFrontOfFrontTrain;
5232  TTrackElement RearMostElement = Track->TrackElementAt(574, RearTrainRearPosition);
5233 
5234  if((RearMostElement.TrackType == Bridge) && (RearTrainExitPos > 1))
5235  TrainIDOnRearOfRearTrain = RearMostElement.TrainIDOnBridgeTrackPos23;
5236  else if((RearMostElement.TrackType == Bridge) && (RearTrainExitPos < 2))
5237  TrainIDOnRearOfRearTrain = RearMostElement.TrainIDOnBridgeTrackPos01;
5238  else
5239  TrainIDOnRearOfRearTrain = RearMostElement.TrainIDOnElement;
5240  // RearTrainFrontPosition = RearMostElement.Conn[RearTrainExitPos];
5241  TrainIDOnFrontOfRearTrain = Track->TrackElementAt(575, RearTrainFrontPosition).TrainIDOnElement;
5242  // can't be a bridge
5243  TrainIDOnRearOfFrontTrain = Track->TrackElementAt(576, FrontTrainRearPosition).TrainIDOnElement;
5244  // can't be a bridge
5245  // FrontTrainFrontPosition = Track->TrackElementAt(578,FrontTrainRearPosition).Conn[FrontTrainExitPos];
5246  TTrackElement FrontMostElement = Track->TrackElementAt(577, FrontTrainFrontPosition);
5247 
5248  if((FrontMostElement.TrackType == Bridge) && (FrontTrainExitPos > 1))
5249  TrainIDOnFrontOfFrontTrain = FrontMostElement.TrainIDOnBridgeTrackPos23;
5250  else if((FrontMostElement.TrackType == Bridge) && (FrontTrainExitPos < 2))
5251  TrainIDOnFrontOfFrontTrain = FrontMostElement.TrainIDOnBridgeTrackPos01;
5252  else
5253  TrainIDOnFrontOfFrontTrain = FrontMostElement.TrainIDOnElement;
5254 
5255  if(((TrainIDOnRearOfRearTrain > -1) && (TrainIDOnRearOfRearTrain != TrainID)) || ((TrainIDOnFrontOfRearTrain > -1) && (TrainIDOnFrontOfRearTrain != TrainID)
5256  ) || ((TrainIDOnRearOfFrontTrain > -1) && (TrainIDOnRearOfFrontTrain != TrainID)) ||
5257  ((TrainIDOnFrontOfFrontTrain > -1) && (TrainIDOnFrontOfFrontTrain != TrainID)))
5258  {
5259  if(TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).EventReported != FailSplitDueToOtherTrain)
5260  {
5261  TrainController->LogActionError(8, HeadCode, "", FailSplitDueToOtherTrain, LocationName);
5262  TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).EventReported = FailSplitDueToOtherTrain;
5263  }
5264  // don't advance ActionVectorEntryPtr as need to keep trying, other train may move off eventually
5265  Utilities->CallLogPop(1010);
5266  return;
5267  }
5268 
5269  if(TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).EventReported == FailSplitDueToOtherTrain)
5270  {
5271  TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).EventReported = NoEvent;
5272  }
5273  // reposition existing rear train, need to do this first for 2 reasons - 1) will likely be in the way of the new front train, and 2)
5274  // the new train will likely cause a reallocation of the TrainVector, and if so the reference to the existing train will be invalidated.
5275  // Hence deal with existing train while it references a valid entry in the vector, but retain the Old ActionVectorEntryPtr in a separate
5276  // variable as it is needed for setting up the new train
5277  TActionVectorEntry *OldActionVectorEntryPtr = ActionVectorEntryPtr;
5278 
5279  UnplotTrain(0);
5280  StartSpeed = 0;
5281  RearStartElement = RearTrainRearPosition;
5282  RearStartExitPos = RearTrainExitPos;
5283  StoppedAtLocation = true;
5284  if((PowerAtRail < 1) && EntrySpeed < 1) // added at v2.4.0
5285  {
5286  StoppedWithoutPower = true;
5287  }
5288  PlotStartPosition(3);
5289  PlotTrainWithNewBackgroundColour(14, clStationStopBackground, Display);
5290  LogAction(9, HeadCode, OtherHeadCode, FrontSplit, ActionVectorEntryPtr->LocationName, ActionVectorEntryPtr->EventTime, ActionVectorEntryPtr->Warning);
5291  ActionVectorEntryPtr++;
5292  LastActionTime = TrainController->TTClockTime;
5293 
5294  Mass = Mass / 2;
5295  MaxBrakeRate = MaxBrakeRate / 2;
5296  PowerAtRail = PowerAtRail / 2;
5297  AValue = sqrt(2 * PowerAtRail / Mass);
5298  // shouldn't change but include in case not set earlier
5299 
5300  // create new front train
5301 /*
5302  TrainController::AddTrain(int RearPosition, int FrontPosition, AnsiString HeadCode, int StartSpeed, int Mass,
5303  double MaxRunningSpeed, double MaxBrakeRate, double PowerAtRail, AnsiString ModeStr, TTrainDataEntry *TrainDataEntryPtr,
5304  int RepeatNumber, int IncrementalMinutes, int SignallerSpeed)
5305 */
5306  // same Mass, MaxBrakeRate & PowerAtRail as this train's halved values, and same MaxRunningSpeed as this train
5307  TActionEventType EventType = NoEvent;
5308 
5309  if(!TrainController->AddTrain(0, FrontTrainRearPosition, FrontTrainFrontPosition, OtherHeadCode, 0, Mass, MaxRunningSpeed, MaxBrakeRate, PowerAtRail,
5310  "Timetable", OldActionVectorEntryPtr->LinkedTrainEntryPtr, RepeatNumber, IncrementalMinutes, IncrementalDigits, SignallerMaxSpeed, false, EventType))
5311  // false for SignallerControl
5312  {
5313  Utilities->CallLogPop(1721); // EventType not used here
5314  // if fails either a throw will have been sent in AddTrain or start position failed prob because of
5315  // another train, in which case a message will have been sent to the perf log, also might well clear later
5316  // when other train moves away
5317  return;
5318  }
5319  // Note data in 'this' now probably invalid as there has been a new addition to the TrainVector, so the train is likely to have a new address, hence make no more changes for the current train
5320  // see mods in UpdateTrain for v1.3.2
5321  TrainController->TrainAdded = true;
5322 
5323  TTrainOperatingData &TTOD = OldActionVectorEntryPtr->LinkedTrainEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber); // this is for the newly created train
5324 
5325  TTOD.TrainID = TrainController->TrainVector.back().TrainID;
5326  TTOD.RunningEntry = Running;
5327  Utilities->CallLogPop(998);
5328 }

5330 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
5331 
5332 void TTrain::RearTrainSplit(int Caller)
5333 {
5334 /*
5335  Split logic is:- at least one of 4 final train positions must overlap with one of original train positions, & final 4 positions
5336  will maximise the number at the location. Note that this function isn't sophisticated enough to account for trains already at the
5337  location in determining the 4 positions, and will give a failure message if a train obstructs any of the 4 positions. In these
5338  circumstances the other train will need to be moved sufficiently away to release all 4 positions, then the train will split.
5339 */
5340  TrainController->LogEvent("" + AnsiString(Caller) + ",RearTrainSplit" + "," + HeadCode);
5341  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",RearTrainSplit" + "," + HeadCode);
5342  if(PowerAtRail < 1)
5343  // new at v2.4.0 (ActionVectorEntryPtr not incremented so can split when power restored
5344  {
5345  if(!ZeroPowerNoRearSplitMessage)
5346  TrainController->StopTTClockMessage(83, HeadCode + ": A train without power can't split");
5347  ZeroPowerNoRearSplitMessage = true;
5348  Utilities->CallLogPop(2138);
5349  return;
5350  }
5351  AnsiString LocationName = Track->TrackElementAt(587, LeadElement).ActiveTrackElementName;
5352 
5353  if(LocationName == "")
5354  LocationName = Track->TrackElementAt(838, MidElement).ActiveTrackElementName;
5355  int FirstNamedElementPos, SecondNamedElementPos, FirstNamedLinkedElementPos, SecondNamedLinkedElementPos;
5356  int RearTrainRearPosition, RearTrainFrontPosition, RearTrainExitPos;
5357  int FrontTrainRearPosition, FrontTrainFrontPosition, FrontTrainExitPos;
5358  AnsiString OtherHeadCode = TrainController->GetRepeatHeadCode(2, ActionVectorEntryPtr->OtherHeadCode, RepeatNumber, IncrementalDigits);
5359 
5360  // determine all positions & exits
5361  if(LocationName != "")
5362  {
5363  // if message given only call at ~5 sec intervals
5364  if(!(TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).EventReported == FailLocTooShort) || (UpdateCounter == 0))
5365  {
5366  FirstNamedElementPos = LeadElement;
5367  if(!Track->ThisNamedLocationLongEnoughForSplit(2, LocationName, FirstNamedElementPos, SecondNamedElementPos, FirstNamedLinkedElementPos,
5368  SecondNamedLinkedElementPos))
5369  {
5370  FirstNamedElementPos = MidElement;
5371  if(!Track->ThisNamedLocationLongEnoughForSplit(3, LocationName, FirstNamedElementPos, SecondNamedElementPos, FirstNamedLinkedElementPos,
5372  SecondNamedLinkedElementPos))
5373  {
5374  if(TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).EventReported != FailLocTooShort)
5375  {
5376  TrainController->LogActionError(9, HeadCode, "", FailLocTooShort, LocationName);
5377  TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).EventReported = FailLocTooShort;
5378  }
5379  Utilities->CallLogPop(1013);
5380  return;
5381  }
5382  }
5383  else
5384  {
5385  // if first is possible then check if all 4 positions at location, and if not try the second
5386  int LeadPosA = FirstNamedElementPos;
5387  int LeadPosB = FirstNamedLinkedElementPos;
5388  int LeadPosC = SecondNamedElementPos;
5389  int LeadPosD = SecondNamedLinkedElementPos;
5390  // count number of positions that are at the location
5391  int LeadNumAtLoc = 0;
5392  if(Track->TrackElementAt(767, LeadPosA).ActiveTrackElementName == LocationName)
5393  LeadNumAtLoc++;
5394  if(Track->TrackElementAt(768, LeadPosB).ActiveTrackElementName == LocationName)
5395  LeadNumAtLoc++;
5396  if(Track->TrackElementAt(769, LeadPosC).ActiveTrackElementName == LocationName)
5397  LeadNumAtLoc++;
5398  if(Track->TrackElementAt(770, LeadPosD).ActiveTrackElementName == LocationName)
5399  LeadNumAtLoc++;
5400  if(LeadNumAtLoc < 4)
5401  {
5402  FirstNamedElementPos = MidElement;
5403  if(!Track->ThisNamedLocationLongEnoughForSplit(5, LocationName, FirstNamedElementPos, SecondNamedElementPos, FirstNamedLinkedElementPos,
5404  SecondNamedLinkedElementPos)) // restore originals
5405  {
5406  FirstNamedElementPos = LeadPosA;
5407  FirstNamedLinkedElementPos = LeadPosB;
5408  SecondNamedElementPos = LeadPosC;
5409  SecondNamedLinkedElementPos = LeadPosD;
5410  }
5411  else // count number at location
5412  {
5413  int MidNumAtLoc = 0;
5414  if(Track->TrackElementAt(771, FirstNamedElementPos).ActiveTrackElementName == LocationName)
5415  MidNumAtLoc++;
5416  if(Track->TrackElementAt(772, FirstNamedLinkedElementPos).ActiveTrackElementName == LocationName)
5417  MidNumAtLoc++;
5418  if(Track->TrackElementAt(773, FirstNamedLinkedElementPos).ActiveTrackElementName == LocationName)
5419  MidNumAtLoc++;
5420  if(Track->TrackElementAt(774, SecondNamedLinkedElementPos).ActiveTrackElementName == LocationName)
5421  MidNumAtLoc++;
5422  if(LeadNumAtLoc > MidNumAtLoc)
5423  // change back, else keep new values
5424  {
5425  FirstNamedElementPos = LeadPosA;
5426  FirstNamedLinkedElementPos = LeadPosB;
5427  SecondNamedElementPos = LeadPosC;
5428  SecondNamedLinkedElementPos = LeadPosD;
5429  }
5430  }
5431  }
5432  }
5433  }
5434  else
5435  {
5436  Utilities->CallLogPop(1792);
5437  return;
5438  }
5439  }
5440  else
5441  throw Exception("Error - LocationName not set in RearTrainSplit");
5442  // set front & rear train parameters
5443  // need RearTrainRearPosition, RearTrainFrontPosition, RearTrainExitPos, FrontTrainRearPosition, FrontTrainFrontPosition & FrontTrainExitPos;
5444  // have LeadElement & MidElement of train defining its direction, & one or other on FirstNamedElementPos
5445  // have FirstNamedElementPos, SecondNamedElementPos, FirstNamedLinkedElementPos & SecondNamedLinkedElementPos from ThisNamedLocationLongEnoughForSplit.
5446  if(LeadElement == FirstNamedElementPos)
5447  {
5448  if(MidElement == SecondNamedElementPos)
5449  {
5450  FrontTrainFrontPosition = FirstNamedLinkedElementPos;
5451  FrontTrainRearPosition = FirstNamedElementPos;
5452  RearTrainFrontPosition = SecondNamedElementPos;
5453  RearTrainRearPosition = SecondNamedLinkedElementPos;
5454  }
5455  else // MidElement must == FirstNamedLinkedElementPos
5456  {
5457  FrontTrainFrontPosition = SecondNamedLinkedElementPos;
5458  FrontTrainRearPosition = SecondNamedElementPos;
5459  RearTrainFrontPosition = FirstNamedElementPos;
5460  RearTrainRearPosition = FirstNamedLinkedElementPos;
5461  }
5462  }
5463  else // MidElement == FirstNamedElementPos
5464  {
5465  if(LeadElement == SecondNamedElementPos)
5466  {
5467  FrontTrainFrontPosition = SecondNamedLinkedElementPos;
5468  FrontTrainRearPosition = SecondNamedElementPos;
5469  RearTrainFrontPosition = FirstNamedElementPos;
5470  RearTrainRearPosition = FirstNamedLinkedElementPos;
5471  }
5472  else // LeadElement must == FirstNamedLinkedElementPos
5473  {
5474  FrontTrainFrontPosition = FirstNamedLinkedElementPos;
5475  FrontTrainRearPosition = FirstNamedElementPos;
5476  RearTrainFrontPosition = SecondNamedElementPos;
5477  RearTrainRearPosition = SecondNamedLinkedElementPos;
5478  }
5479  }
5480  RearTrainExitPos = -1;
5481  for(int x = 0; x < 4; x++)
5482  {
5483  if(Track->TrackElementAt(588, RearTrainRearPosition).Conn[x] == RearTrainFrontPosition)
5484  {
5485  RearTrainExitPos = x;
5486  break;
5487  }
5488  }
5489  if(RearTrainExitPos == -1)
5490  throw Exception("Error - RearTrainRearPosition not linked to RearTrainFrontPosition in RearTrainSplit");
5491  FrontTrainExitPos = -1;
5492  for(int x = 0; x < 4; x++)
5493  {
5494  if(Track->TrackElementAt(589, FrontTrainRearPosition).Conn[x] == FrontTrainFrontPosition)
5495  {
5496  FrontTrainExitPos = x;
5497  break;
5498  }
5499  }
5500  if(FrontTrainExitPos == -1)
5501  throw Exception("Error - FrontTrainRearPosition not linked to FrontTrainFrontPosition in RearTrainSplit");
5502 
5503  // check no train (apart from self) on any of the 4 elements & fail if so
5504  int TrainIDOnRearOfRearTrain, TrainIDOnFrontOfRearTrain, TrainIDOnRearOfFrontTrain, TrainIDOnFrontOfFrontTrain;
5505  TTrackElement RearMostElement = Track->TrackElementAt(590, RearTrainRearPosition);
5506 
5507  if((RearMostElement.TrackType == Bridge) && (RearTrainExitPos > 1))
5508  TrainIDOnRearOfRearTrain = RearMostElement.TrainIDOnBridgeTrackPos23;
5509  else if((RearMostElement.TrackType == Bridge) && (RearTrainExitPos < 2))
5510  TrainIDOnRearOfRearTrain = RearMostElement.TrainIDOnBridgeTrackPos01;
5511  else
5512  TrainIDOnRearOfRearTrain = RearMostElement.TrainIDOnElement;
5513  // RearTrainFrontPosition = RearMostElement.Conn[RearTrainExitPos];
5514  TrainIDOnFrontOfRearTrain = Track->TrackElementAt(591, RearTrainFrontPosition).TrainIDOnElement;
5515  // can't be a bridge
5516  TrainIDOnRearOfFrontTrain = Track->TrackElementAt(592, FrontTrainRearPosition).TrainIDOnElement;
5517  // can't be a bridge
5518  // FrontTrainFrontPosition = Track->TrackElementAt(593,FrontTrainRearPosition).Conn[FrontTrainExitPos];
5519  TTrackElement FrontMostElement = Track->TrackElementAt(594, FrontTrainFrontPosition);
5520 
5521  if((FrontMostElement.TrackType == Bridge) && (FrontTrainExitPos > 1))
5522  TrainIDOnFrontOfFrontTrain = FrontMostElement.TrainIDOnBridgeTrackPos23;
5523  else if((FrontMostElement.TrackType == Bridge) && (FrontTrainExitPos < 2))
5524  TrainIDOnFrontOfFrontTrain = FrontMostElement.TrainIDOnBridgeTrackPos01;
5525  else
5526  TrainIDOnFrontOfFrontTrain = FrontMostElement.TrainIDOnElement;
5527 
5528  if(((TrainIDOnRearOfRearTrain > -1) && (TrainIDOnRearOfRearTrain != TrainID)) || ((TrainIDOnFrontOfRearTrain > -1) && (TrainIDOnFrontOfRearTrain != TrainID)
5529  ) || ((TrainIDOnRearOfFrontTrain > -1) && (TrainIDOnRearOfFrontTrain != TrainID)) ||
5530  ((TrainIDOnFrontOfFrontTrain > -1) && (TrainIDOnFrontOfFrontTrain != TrainID)))
5531  {
5532  if(TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).EventReported != FailSplitDueToOtherTrain)
5533  {
5534  TrainController->LogActionError(11, HeadCode, "", FailSplitDueToOtherTrain, LocationName);
5535  TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).EventReported = FailSplitDueToOtherTrain;
5536  }
5537  // don't advance ActionVectorEntryPtr as need to keep trying, other train may move off eventually
5538  Utilities->CallLogPop(1014);
5539  return;
5540  }
5541 
5542  if(TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).EventReported == FailSplitDueToOtherTrain)
5543  {
5544  TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).EventReported = NoEvent;
5545  }
5546 
5547  // reposition existing front train, need to do this first for 2 reasons - 1) will likely be in the way of the new rear train, and 2)
5548  // the new train will likely cause a reallocation of the TrainVector, and if so the reference to the existing train will be invalidated.
5549  // Hence deal with existing train while it references a valid entry in the vector, but retain the Old ActionVectorEntryPtr in a separate
5550  // variable as it is needed for setting up the new train
5551  TActionVectorEntry *OldActionVectorEntryPtr = ActionVectorEntryPtr;
5552 
5553  UnplotTrain(1);
5554  StartSpeed = 0;
5555  RearStartElement = FrontTrainRearPosition;
5556  RearStartExitPos = FrontTrainExitPos;
5557  StoppedAtLocation = true;
5558  if((PowerAtRail < 1) && EntrySpeed < 1) // added at v2.4.0
5559  {
5560  StoppedWithoutPower = true;
5561  }
5562  PlotStartPosition(4);
5563  PlotTrainWithNewBackgroundColour(15, clStationStopBackground, Display);
5564  LogAction(10, HeadCode, OtherHeadCode, RearSplit, ActionVectorEntryPtr->LocationName, ActionVectorEntryPtr->EventTime, ActionVectorEntryPtr->Warning);
5565  ActionVectorEntryPtr++;
5566  LastActionTime = TrainController->TTClockTime;
5567  Mass = Mass / 2;
5568  // TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).Mass = Mass;
5569  MaxBrakeRate = MaxBrakeRate / 2;
5570  // TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).MaxBrakeRate = MaxBrakeRate;
5571  PowerAtRail = PowerAtRail / 2;
5572  // TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).PowerAtRail = PowerAtRail;
5573  AValue = sqrt(2 * PowerAtRail / Mass);
5574  // shouldn't change but include in case not set earlier
5575 
5576  // create new rear train
5577 /*
5578  TrainController::AddTrain(int RearPosition, int FrontPosition, AnsiString HeadCode, int StartSpeed, int Mass,
5579  double MaxRunningSpeed, double MaxBrakeRate, double PowerAtRail, AnsiString ModeStr, TTrainDataEntry *TrainDataEntryPtr,
5580  int RepeatNumber, int IncrementalMinutes)
5581 */
5582  // same Mass, MaxBrakeRate & PowerAtRail as this train's halved values, and same MaxRunningSpeed as this train
5583  TActionEventType EventType = NoEvent;
5584 
5585  if(!TrainController->AddTrain(1, RearTrainRearPosition, RearTrainFrontPosition, OtherHeadCode, 0, Mass, MaxRunningSpeed, MaxBrakeRate, PowerAtRail,
5586  "Timetable", OldActionVectorEntryPtr->LinkedTrainEntryPtr, RepeatNumber, IncrementalMinutes, IncrementalDigits, SignallerMaxSpeed, false, EventType))
5587  // false for SignallerControl
5588  {
5589  Utilities->CallLogPop(1722); // EventType not used here
5590  // if fails either a throw will have been sent in AddTrain or start position failed prob because of
5591  // another train, in which case a message will have been sent to the perf log, also might well clear later
5592  // when other train moves away
5593  return;
5594  }
5595  // Note data in 'this' now probably invalid as there has been a new addition to the TrainVector, so the train is likely to have a new address, hence make no more changes for the current train
5596  // see mods in UpdateTrain for v1.3.2
5597  TrainController->TrainAdded = true;
5598  TTrainOperatingData &TTOD = OldActionVectorEntryPtr->LinkedTrainEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber); // this is for the newly created train
5599 
5600  TTOD.TrainID = TrainController->TrainVector.back().TrainID;
5601  TTOD.RunningEntry = Running;
5602  Utilities->CallLogPop(1015);
5603 }

5607 void TTrain::FinishJoin(int Caller)
5608 {
5609  if(FinishJoinLogSent == false)
5610  {
5611  TrainController->LogEvent("" + AnsiString(Caller) + ",FinishJoin" + "," + HeadCode);
5612  FinishJoinLogSent = true; // so don't keep logging this event
5613  // don't need to reset it to false after the event as the train is deleted
5614  }
5615  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",FinishJoin" + "," + HeadCode);
5616  if(TrainFailed)
5617  // new at v2.4.0 (ActionVectorEntryPtr not incremented so can join when repaired) Can FinishJoin if zero power & not failed, as for empty stock
5618  {
5619  if(!FailedTrainNoFinishJoinMessage)
5620  TrainController->StopTTClockMessage(84, HeadCode + ": A failed train can't join another under timetable control");
5621  FailedTrainNoFinishJoinMessage = true;
5622  Utilities->CallLogPop(2139);
5623  return;
5624  }
5625  if(TrainGone)
5626  // this means that the train has already joined the other & is awaiting deletion by TrainController
5627  // without this the 'waiting' message can be given since the other train's ActionVectorEntryPtr has moved
5628  // on from jbo & TrainToJoinIsAdjacent returns false
5629  {
5630  Utilities->CallLogPop(1035);
5631  return;
5632  }
5633  TTrain *TrainToJoin;
5634  AnsiString JBOHeadCode = TrainController->GetRepeatHeadCode(3, ActionVectorEntryPtr->OtherHeadCode, RepeatNumber, IncrementalDigits);
5635 
5636  if(!TrainToJoinIsAdjacent(0, TrainToJoin))
5637  {
5638  if(TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).EventReported != WaitingForJBO)
5639  {
5640  // Display->PerformanceLog(2, TrainController->TTClockTime.FormatString("hh:nn:ss") + ": " + HeadCode + " waiting to join " + JBOHeadCode + " at " + ActionVectorEntryPtr->LocationName);
5641  TrainController->LogActionError(51, HeadCode, JBOHeadCode, WaitingForJBO, ActionVectorEntryPtr->LocationName);
5642  TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).EventReported = WaitingForJBO;
5643  }
5644  Utilities->CallLogPop(1030);
5645  return; // keep this here in case need to add code before final return
5646  }
5647  // no need to clear error report flag here, cleared in jbo function
5648  // No need to set TimetableFinished, done in jbo function
5649  Utilities->CallLogPop(1031);
5650 }

5654 void TTrain::JoinedBy(int Caller)
5655 {
5656  TrainController->LogEvent("" + AnsiString(Caller) + ",JoinedBy" + "," + HeadCode);
5657  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",JoinedBy" + "," + HeadCode);
5658  if(PowerAtRail < 1)
5659  // new at v2.4.0 (ActionVectorEntryPtr not incremented so can join when power restored)
5660  {
5661  if(!ZeroPowerNoJoinedByMessage)
5662  TrainController->StopTTClockMessage(85, HeadCode + ": A train without power can't be joined by another under timetable control");
5663  ZeroPowerNoJoinedByMessage = true;
5664  Utilities->CallLogPop(2140);
5665  return;
5666  }
5667  TTrain *TrainToBeJoinedBy;
5668  AnsiString FJOHeadCode = TrainController->GetRepeatHeadCode(4, ActionVectorEntryPtr->OtherHeadCode, RepeatNumber, IncrementalDigits);
5669 
5670  if(!TrainToBeJoinedByIsAdjacent(0, TrainToBeJoinedBy))
5671  {
5672  if(TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).EventReported != WaitingForFJO)
5673  {
5674  // Display->PerformanceLog(3, TrainController->TTClockTime.FormatString("hh:nn:ss") + ": " + HeadCode + " waiting to be joined by " + FJOHeadCode + " at " + ActionVectorEntryPtr->LocationName);
5675  TrainController->LogActionError(52, HeadCode, FJOHeadCode, WaitingForFJO, ActionVectorEntryPtr->LocationName);
5676  TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).EventReported = WaitingForFJO;
5677  }
5678  LastActionDelayFlag = true;
5679  // need to update LastActionTime if this train first to arrive as need 30s after
5680  // both adjacent before the join
5681  Utilities->CallLogPop(1032);
5682  return;
5683  }
5684  // here when other train is adjacent
5685  if(LastActionDelayFlag)
5686  {
5687  LastActionTime = TrainController->TTClockTime;
5688  // need to update this as need 30s after both adjacent before the join
5689  LastActionDelayFlag = false;
5690  Utilities->CallLogPop(1033);
5691  return;
5692  }
5693  // here when other train is adjacent & 30 secs elapsed since both adjacent
5694 
5695  // set new values for mass etc
5696  if(MaxRunningSpeed > TrainToBeJoinedBy->MaxRunningSpeed)
5697  MaxRunningSpeed = TrainToBeJoinedBy->MaxRunningSpeed;
5698  double OtherBrakeForce = TrainToBeJoinedBy->MaxBrakeRate * TrainToBeJoinedBy->Mass;
5699  double OwnBrakeForce = MaxBrakeRate * Mass;
5700  double CombinedBrakeRate = (OtherBrakeForce + OwnBrakeForce) / (TrainToBeJoinedBy->Mass + Mass);
5701 
5702  Mass += TrainToBeJoinedBy->Mass;
5703  MaxBrakeRate = CombinedBrakeRate;
5704  PowerAtRail += TrainToBeJoinedBy->PowerAtRail;
5705  AValue = sqrt(2 * PowerAtRail / Mass);
5706 
5707  TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).EventReported = NoEvent;
5708  TrainToBeJoinedBy->TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).EventReported = NoEvent;
5709  TrainToBeJoinedBy->TimetableFinished = true;
5710  TrainToBeJoinedBy->TrainGone = true;
5711  // this will cause other train to be deleted
5712  TrainToBeJoinedBy->JoinedOtherTrainFlag = true;
5713  LogAction(11, HeadCode, FJOHeadCode, JoinedByOther, ActionVectorEntryPtr->LocationName, ActionVectorEntryPtr->EventTime, ActionVectorEntryPtr->Warning);
5714  ActionVectorEntryPtr++;
5715  LastActionTime = TrainController->TTClockTime;
5716  Utilities->CallLogPop(1034);
5717 }
5718

5720 
5721 void TTrain::ChangeTrainDirection(int Caller)
5722 {
5723  TrainController->LogEvent("" + AnsiString(Caller) + ",ChangeTrainDirection" + "," + HeadCode);
5724  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",ChangeTrainDirection" + "," + HeadCode);
5725  if(PowerAtRail < 1)
5726  // new at v2.4.0 (ActionVectorEntryPtr not incremented so can change direction when power restored)
5727  {
5728  if(!ZeroPowerNoCDTMessage)
5729  TrainController->StopTTClockMessage(86, HeadCode + ": A train without power can't change direction under timetable control");
5730  ZeroPowerNoCDTMessage = true;
5731  Utilities->CallLogPop(2141);
5732  return;
5733  }
5734  TColor TempColour = BackgroundColour;
5735 
5736  UnplotTrain(2);
5737  RearStartElement = LeadElement;
5738  RearStartExitPos = LeadEntryPos;
5739  StartSpeed = 0;
5740  StoppedAtLocation = true;
5741  PlotStartPosition(1);
5742  PlotTrainWithNewBackgroundColour(27, TempColour, Display);
5743  // plot same as was - should always be pale green
5744  LogAction(12, HeadCode, "", ChangeDirection, ActionVectorEntryPtr->LocationName, ActionVectorEntryPtr->EventTime, ActionVectorEntryPtr->Warning);
5745  ActionVectorEntryPtr++;
5746  LastActionTime = TrainController->TTClockTime;
5747 
5748  //now erase a stub route if there is one, added at v2.5.1
5749  //first element of route is now immediately behind the train (i.e. next to MidElement)
5750  if(MidEntryPos >= 0)
5751  {
5752  TTrackElement MidTrackElement = Track->TrackElementAt(996, MidElement);
5753  int FirstRouteElementVecPos = MidTrackElement.Conn[MidEntryPos];
5754  int FirstRouteLinkPos = MidTrackElement.ConnLinkPos[MidEntryPos];
5755  int RouteNumber = -1;
5756  TAllRoutes::TRouteType RouteType = AllRoutes->GetRouteTypeAndNumber(34, FirstRouteElementVecPos, FirstRouteLinkPos, RouteNumber);
5757  if(RouteType == TAllRoutes::NotAutoSigsRoute)
5758  {
5759  TOneRoute &OR = AllRoutes->GetModifiableRouteAt(28, RouteNumber);
5760  TTrackElement TE = Track->TrackElementAt(997, FirstRouteElementVecPos);
5761  if((TE.TrackType != SignalPost) && (TE.TrackType != Continuation))//all autosigs routes have signalpost or continuation at 0 so they are automatically excluded
5762  {
5763  while(OR.PrefDirSize() > 0) //remove the route up to but not including the next facing signal, in case a pref dir route extends to another signal
5764  {
5765  TPrefDirElement PDE = OR.GetFixedPrefDirElementAt(247, 0); //these will change at each element removal because OR is a reference to the real route
5766  int TVPos2 = PDE.GetTrackVectorPosition();
5767  TTrackElement TE2 = Track->TrackElementAt(998, TVPos2);
5768  if(Track->TrackElementAt(999, PDE.GetTrackVectorPosition()).Config[PDE.GetXLinkPos()] != Signal)
5769  {
5770  AllRoutes->RemoveRouteElement(22, TE2.HLoc, TE2.VLoc, PDE.GetELink());
5771  }
5772  else
5773  {
5774  break;
5775  }
5776  }
5777  AllRoutes->RebuildRailwayFlag = true;
5778  // to force ClearandRebuildRailway at next clock tick if not in zoom-out mode, to replot without stub route
5779  }
5780  }
5781  }
5782  Utilities->CallLogPop(1012);
5783 }

5787 void TTrain::NewTrainService(int Caller)

5844 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
5845 
5846 void TTrain::SendMissedActionLogs(int Caller, int IncNum, TActionVectorEntry *Ptr)
5847 /*
5848  Enter with pointer at next expected action, and IncNum the number by which have to increase the pointer
5849  to reach the action that is valid for the train's current position. i.e. IncNum error messages to be sent
5850  except where an action is a departure, starting at the current value for the pointer
5851  If IncNum is -1, then send messages for all remaining actions, including Fer if present
5852  If IncNum is -2, then send messages for all remaining actions, except Fer if present
5853 */ {
5854  if((Ptr->Command == "Snt") && Ptr->SignallerControl)
5855  return; // if remove train that starts under signaller control no messages needed
5856 
5857  TrainController->LogEvent("" + AnsiString(Caller) + ",SendMissedActionLogs," + AnsiString(IncNum) + "," + HeadCode);
5858  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",SendMissedActionLogs," + AnsiString(IncNum) + "," + HeadCode);
5859  if(IncNum > 0)
5860  {
5861  for(int x = 0; x < IncNum; x++)
5862  {
5863  if(x > 0)
5864  Ptr++;
5865  // arrival - no need to test for termination as this section only covers missed actions up to the
5866  // arrival point - may terminate later but that not missed
5867  if((Ptr->FormatType == TimeLoc) && (Ptr->ArrivalTime > TDateTime(-1)))
5868  {
5869  TrainController->LogActionError(12, HeadCode, "", FailMissedArrival, Ptr->LocationName);
5870  }
5871  // arrival & departure
5872  if(Ptr->FormatType == TimeTimeLoc)
5873  {
5874  TrainController->LogActionError(13, HeadCode, "", FailMissedArrival, Ptr->LocationName);
5875  }
5876  // departure
5877  else if((Ptr->FormatType == TimeLoc) && (Ptr->ArrivalTime == TDateTime(-1)))
5878  {
5879  continue; // skip TimeLoc departures, message given for arrivals
5880  }
5881  // pass
5882  else if(Ptr->FormatType == PassTime)
5883  {
5884  TrainController->LogActionError(36, HeadCode, "", FailMissedPass, Ptr->LocationName);
5885  }
5886  // split
5887  else if((Ptr->Command == "fsp") || (Ptr->Command == "rsp"))
5888  {
5889  TrainController->LogActionError(14, HeadCode, "", FailMissedSplit, Ptr->LocationName);
5890  }
5891  // jbo
5892  else if(Ptr->Command == "jbo")
5893  {
5894  TrainController->LogActionError(15, HeadCode, "", FailMissedJBO, Ptr->LocationName);
5895  }
5896  // Errors - have reached a station stop point (before a cdt) during Train->Update() so intervening actions can't
5897  // be starts, finishes or cdt
5898  else if((Ptr->Command == "Fns") || (Ptr->Command == "Frh") || (Ptr->Command == "Fer") || (Ptr->Command == "Fjo") || (Ptr->Command == "Snt") ||
5899  (Ptr->Command == "Sfs") || (Ptr->Command == "Snt-sh") || (Ptr->Command == "Sns") || (Ptr->Command == "Sns-sh") || (Ptr->Command == "Sns-fsh") ||
5900  (Ptr->Command == "cdt") || (Ptr->Command == "Frh-sh") || (Ptr->Command == "Fns-sh") || (Ptr->Command == "F-nshs") ||
5901  (Ptr->FormatType == Repeat))
5902  {
5903  throw Exception("Error - illegal command in SendMissedActionLogs for IncNum = " + AnsiString(IncNum) + ", and command = " + Ptr->Command);
5904  }
5905  }
5906  }
5907  else
5908  {
5909  bool IncludeFER = false;
5910  if(IncNum == -1)
5911  IncludeFER = true;
5912  while(true) // finish commands & repeats break out of loop
5913  {
5914  // Fer & excluded - send normal exit log to give minutes late or early - no, have already sent an unexpected exit message
5915  if(!IncludeFER && (Ptr->Command == "Fer"))
5916  {
5917  break;
5918  }
5919  // Fer & included
5920  else if(IncludeFER && (Ptr->Command == "Fer"))
5921  {
5922  TrainController->LogActionError(19, HeadCode, "", FailMissedExitRailway, "");
5923  break;
5924  }
5925  // Repeat
5926  else if(Ptr->FormatType == Repeat)
5927  {
5928  break;
5929  }
5930  // Fjo
5931  else if(Ptr->Command == "Fjo")
5932  {
5933  TrainController->LogActionError(16, HeadCode, "", FailMissedJoinOther, Ptr->LocationName);
5934  break;
5935  }
5936  // Frh
5937  else if(Ptr->Command == "Frh")
5938  {
5939  if(!TerminatedMessageSent)
5940  {
5941  TrainController->LogActionError(17, HeadCode, "", FailMissedTerminate, Ptr->LocationName);
5942  TerminatedMessageSent = true;
5943  }
5944  break;
5945  }
5946  // Frh-sh
5947  else if(Ptr->Command == "Frh-sh")
5948  {
5949  if(!TerminatedMessageSent)
5950  {
5951  TrainController->LogActionError(53, HeadCode, "", FailMissedNewService, Ptr->LocationName);
5952  TerminatedMessageSent = true;
5953  }
5954  break;
5955  }
5956  // Fns, F-nshs, Fns-sh
5957  else if((Ptr->Command == "Fns") || (Ptr->Command == "F-nshs") || (Ptr->Command == "Fns-sh"))
5958  {
5959  TrainController->LogActionError(18, HeadCode, "", FailMissedNewService, Ptr->LocationName);
5960  break;
5961  }
5962  // end of breakout actions
5963  // arrival
5964  if((Ptr->FormatType == TimeLoc) && (Ptr->ArrivalTime > TDateTime(-1)))
5965  {
5966  if(IsTrainTerminating(1))
5967  {
5968  TrainController->LogActionError(20, HeadCode, "", FailMissedTerminate, Ptr->LocationName);
5969  TerminatedMessageSent = true;
5970  }
5971  else
5972  {
5973  TrainController->LogActionError(21, HeadCode, "", FailMissedArrival, Ptr->LocationName);
5974  }
5975  }
5976  // arrival & departure
5977  else if(Ptr->FormatType == TimeTimeLoc)
5978  {
5979  TrainController->LogActionError(22, HeadCode, "", FailMissedArrival, Ptr->LocationName);
5980  }
5981  // departure
5982  else if((Ptr->FormatType == TimeLoc) && (Ptr->ArrivalTime == TDateTime(-1)))
5983  {
5984  Ptr++;
5985  continue; // skip TimeLoc departures, message given for arrivals
5986  }
5987  // pass
5988  else if(Ptr->FormatType == PassTime)
5989  {
5990  TrainController->LogActionError(37, HeadCode, "", FailMissedPass, Ptr->LocationName);
5991  }
5992  // split
5993  else if((Ptr->Command == "fsp") || (Ptr->Command == "rsp"))
5994  {
5995  TrainController->LogActionError(23, HeadCode, "", FailMissedSplit, Ptr->LocationName);
5996  }
5997  // jbo
5998  else if(Ptr->Command == "jbo")
5999  {
6000  TrainController->LogActionError(24, HeadCode, "", FailMissedJBO, Ptr->LocationName);
6001  }
6002  // cdt
6003  else if(Ptr->Command == "cdt")
6004  {
6005  TrainController->LogActionError(25, HeadCode, "", FailMissedChangeDirection, Ptr->LocationName);
6006  }
6007  // Errors
6008  else if((Ptr->Command == "Snt-sh") || (Ptr->Command == "Sfs") || (Ptr->Command == "Sns") || (Ptr->Command == "Sns-sh") ||
6009  (Ptr->Command == "Sns-fsh") || ((Ptr->Command == "Snt") && !Ptr->SignallerControl))
6010  {
6011  throw Exception("Error - illegal command in SendMissedActionLogs for IncNum = " + AnsiString(IncNum) + ", and command = " + Ptr->Command);
6012  }
6013  Ptr++;
6014  }
6015  TimetableFinished = true;
6016  }
6017  Utilities->CallLogPop(1021);
6018 }

6022 bool TTrain::TrainToJoinIsAdjacent(int Caller, TTrain* &TrainToJoin)
6023  // ensure same repeatnumber
6024 {
6025  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",TrainToJoinIsAdjacent" + "," + HeadCode);
6026  TTrainDataEntry *TrainToJoinTDEntry = ActionVectorEntryPtr->LinkedTrainEntryPtr;
6027 
6028  if(TrainToJoinTDEntry->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).RunningEntry != Running)
6029  {
6030  Utilities->CallLogPop(1024);
6031  return false;
6032  }
6033  TrainToJoin = &(TrainController->TrainVectorAtIdent(33, TrainToJoinTDEntry->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).TrainID));
6034  if(TrainToJoin->StoppedAtLocation && (TrainToJoin->TrainMode == Timetable) && (TrainToJoin->ActionVectorEntryPtr->Command == "jbo"))
6035  {
6036  if((Track->TrackElementAt(610, LeadElement).Conn[LeadExitPos] == TrainToJoin->LeadElement) || (Track->TrackElementAt(611,
6037  LeadElement).Conn[LeadExitPos] == TrainToJoin->MidElement) || (Track->TrackElementAt(612, MidElement).Conn[MidEntryPos] == TrainToJoin->LeadElement)
6038  || (Track->TrackElementAt(613, MidElement).Conn[MidEntryPos] == TrainToJoin->MidElement))
6039  {
6040  Utilities->CallLogPop(1025);
6041  return true;
6042  }
6043  }
6044  Utilities->CallLogPop(1026);
6045  return false;
6046 }

6050 bool TTrain::TrainToBeJoinedByIsAdjacent(int Caller, TTrain* &TrainToBeJoinedBy)
6051  // ensure same repeatnumber
6052 {
6053  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",TrainToBeJoinedByIsAdjacent" + "," + HeadCode);
6054  TTrainDataEntry *TrainToBeJoinedByTDEntry = ActionVectorEntryPtr->LinkedTrainEntryPtr;
6055 
6056  if(TrainToBeJoinedByTDEntry->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).RunningEntry != Running)
6057  {
6058  Utilities->CallLogPop(1027);
6059  return false;
6060  }
6061  TrainToBeJoinedBy = &(TrainController->TrainVectorAtIdent(15, TrainToBeJoinedByTDEntry->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).TrainID));
6062  if(TrainToBeJoinedBy->StoppedAtLocation && (TrainToBeJoinedBy->TrainMode == Timetable) && (TrainToBeJoinedBy->ActionVectorEntryPtr->Command == "Fjo"))
6063  {
6064  if((Track->TrackElementAt(614, LeadElement).Conn[LeadExitPos] == TrainToBeJoinedBy->LeadElement) || (Track->TrackElementAt(615,
6065  LeadElement).Conn[LeadExitPos] == TrainToBeJoinedBy->MidElement) || (Track->TrackElementAt(616,
6066  MidElement).Conn[MidEntryPos] == TrainToBeJoinedBy->LeadElement) || (Track->TrackElementAt(617,
6067  MidElement).Conn[MidEntryPos] == TrainToBeJoinedBy->MidElement))
6068  {
6069  Utilities->CallLogPop(1028);
6070  return true;
6071  }
6072  }
6073  Utilities->CallLogPop(1029);
6074  return false;
6075 }

6117 
6118 void TTrain::RepeatShuttleOrRemainHere(int Caller)
6119  // need to check whether all repeats finished or not
6120 {
6121  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",RepeatShuttleOrRemainHere" + "," + HeadCode);
6122  if(RemainHereLogNotSent) // to prevent repeated logs
6123  {
6124  TrainController->LogEvent("" + AnsiString(Caller) + ",RepeatShuttleOrRemainHere" + "," + HeadCode);
6125  RemainHereLogNotSent = false;
6126  }
6127  if(RepeatNumber >= (TrainDataEntryPtr->NumberOfTrains - 1))
6128  // finished all repeats
6129  {
6130  if(TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).EventReported != ShuttleFinishedRemainingHere)
6131  {
6132  LogAction(26, HeadCode, "", Terminate, ActionVectorEntryPtr->LocationName, ActionVectorEntryPtr->EventTime, ActionVectorEntryPtr->Warning);
6133  TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).EventReported = ShuttleFinishedRemainingHere;
6134  TerminatedMessageSent = true;
6135  // no need to clear message as no more actions
6136  }
6137  TimetableFinished = true;
6138  Utilities->CallLogPop(1080);
6139  return;
6140  }
6141  if(PowerAtRail < 1)
6142  // new at v2.4.0 (ActionVectorEntryPtr not incremented so can for new service when power restored)
6143  {
6144  if(!ZeroPowerNoRepeatShuttleMessage)
6145  TrainController->StopTTClockMessage(89, HeadCode + ": A train without power can't form a new service");
6146  ZeroPowerNoRepeatShuttleMessage = true;
6147  Utilities->CallLogPop(2144);
6148  return;
6149  }
6150  int TempRepeatNumber = RepeatNumber + 1;
6151  // need the next repeat value in order to obtain a correct NewHeadCode, but don't increase it
6152  // until after LogAction or the wrong time will be used
6153  AnsiString NewHeadCode = TrainController->GetRepeatHeadCode(6, ActionVectorEntryPtr->OtherHeadCode, TempRepeatNumber, IncrementalDigits);
6154 
6155  LogAction(16, HeadCode, NewHeadCode, NewService, ActionVectorEntryPtr->LocationName, ActionVectorEntryPtr->EventTime, ActionVectorEntryPtr->Warning);
6156  RepeatNumber++;
6157  UnplotTrain(5);
6158  RearStartElement = MidElement;
6159  RearStartExitPos = MidExitPos;
6160  StartSpeed = 0;
6161  TrainDataEntryPtr = ActionVectorEntryPtr->LinkedTrainEntryPtr;
6162  TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).TrainID = TrainID;
6163  TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).RunningEntry = Running;
6164  ActionVectorEntryPtr = &(TrainDataEntryPtr->ActionVector.at(0));
6165  HeadCode = NewHeadCode;
6166  StoppedAtLocation = true;
6167  PlotStartPosition(7);
6168  PlotTrainWithNewBackgroundColour(23, clStationStopBackground, Display);
6169  // pale green
6170  ActionVectorEntryPtr++;
6171  LastActionTime = TrainController->TTClockTime;
6172  TerminatedMessageSent = false;
6173  Utilities->CallLogPop(1079);
6174 }

6189  return;
6190  }
6191  if(RepeatNumber >= (TrainDataEntryPtr->NumberOfTrains - 1))
6192  // finished all repeats
6193  {
6194  AnsiString NewHeadCode = ActionVectorEntryPtr->NonRepeatingShuttleLinkHeadCode;
6195  LogAction(17, HeadCode, NewHeadCode, NewService, ActionVectorEntryPtr->LocationName, ActionVectorEntryPtr->EventTime, ActionVectorEntryPtr->Warning);
6196  RepeatNumber = 0;
6197  UnplotTrain(6);
6198  RearStartElement = MidElement;
6199  RearStartExitPos = MidExitPos;
6200  StartSpeed = 0;
6201  TrainDataEntryPtr = ActionVectorEntryPtr->NonRepeatingShuttleLinkEntryPtr;
6202  TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).TrainID = TrainID; // but note that RepeatNumber = 0
6203  TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).RunningEntry = Running; // but note that RepeatNumber = 0
6204  ActionVectorEntryPtr = &(TrainDataEntryPtr->ActionVector.at(0));
6205  HeadCode = NewHeadCode;
6206  StoppedAtLocation = true;
6207  PlotStartPosition(9);
6208  PlotTrainWithNewBackgroundColour(24, clStationStopBackground, Display); // pale green
6209  ActionVectorEntryPtr++;
6210  LastActionTime = TrainController->TTClockTime;
6211  TerminatedMessageSent = false;
6212  Utilities->CallLogPop(1081);
6213  return;
6214  }
6215  int TempRepeatNumber = RepeatNumber + 1;
6216  // need the next repeat value in order to obtain a correct NewHeadCode, but don't increase it
6217  // until after LogAction or the wrong time will be used
6218  AnsiString NewHeadCode = TrainController->GetRepeatHeadCode(7, ActionVectorEntryPtr->OtherHeadCode, TempRepeatNumber, IncrementalDigits);
6219 
6220  LogAction(18, HeadCode, NewHeadCode, NewService, ActionVectorEntryPtr->LocationName, ActionVectorEntryPtr->EventTime, ActionVectorEntryPtr->Warning);
6221  RepeatNumber++;
6222  UnplotTrain(7);
6223  RearStartElement = MidElement;
6224  RearStartExitPos = MidExitPos;
6225  StartSpeed = 0;
6226  TrainDataEntryPtr = ActionVectorEntryPtr->LinkedTrainEntryPtr;
6227  TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).TrainID = TrainID;
6228  TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).RunningEntry = Running;
6229  ActionVectorEntryPtr = &(TrainDataEntryPtr->ActionVector.at(0));
6230  HeadCode = NewHeadCode;
6231  StoppedAtLocation = true;
6232  PlotStartPosition(8);
6233  PlotTrainWithNewBackgroundColour(25, clStationStopBackground, Display);
6234  // pale green
6235  ActionVectorEntryPtr++;
6236  LastActionTime = TrainController->TTClockTime;
6237  TerminatedMessageSent = false;
6238  Utilities->CallLogPop(1082);
6239 }
6240 
6241 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
6242 
6243 bool TTrain::IsTrainTerminating(int Caller)
6244 {
6245  // Search ActionVector from the position after the entry value for Ptr to the end, and return true if find a Finish
6246  // entry before Fer or TimeLoc. No point checking for TimeTimeLoc since at a stop location now so a later TimeTimeLoc
6247  // must be preceded by a TimeLoc departure
6248  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",IsTrainTerminating" + "," + HeadCode);
6249  for(unsigned int x = 1; x < TrainDataEntryPtr->ActionVector.size(); x++)
6250  {
6251  if((ActionVectorEntryPtr + x) < &TrainDataEntryPtr->ActionVector.back())
6252  {
6253  if(((ActionVectorEntryPtr + x)->Command == "Fer") || ((ActionVectorEntryPtr + x)->FormatType == TimeLoc))
6254  {
6255  Utilities->CallLogPop(1083);
6256  return false;
6257  }
6258  else if((ActionVectorEntryPtr + x)->SequenceType == Finish)
6259  {
6260  Utilities->CallLogPop(1084);
6261  return true;
6262  }
6263  }
6264  }
6265  Utilities->CallLogPop(1085);
6266  return false;
6267 }
