6269 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
6270 
6271 bool TTrain::AbleToMove(int Caller)
6272 {
6273  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",AbleToMove" + "," + HeadCode);
6274  bool Able = true;
6275 
6276  if(Crashed || Derailed || StoppedAtBuffers || StoppedAtSignal || StoppedWithoutPower) // StoppedWithoutPower added at v2.4.0 &
6277  { // StoppedForTrainInFront removed as tested below
6278  Able = false;
6279  Utilities->CallLogPop(2146); // added v2.4.0
6280  return Able; // added v2.4.0
6281  }
6282  if(LeadElement > -1)
6283  {
6284  int FrontPos = Track->TrackElementAt(678, LeadElement).Conn[LeadExitPos];
6285  int FrontEntryPos = Track->TrackElementAt(679, LeadElement).ConnLinkPos[LeadExitPos];
6286  if((FrontPos > -1) && (TrainMode == Signaller) && StoppedForTrainInFront)
6287  {
6288  TTrackElement TrackElement = Track->TrackElementAt(680, FrontPos);
6289  if((TrackElement.TrackType != Bridge) && (TrackElement.TrainIDOnElement == -1))
6290  {
6291  Able = true;
6292  StoppedForTrainInFront = false;
6293  }
6294  else if((TrackElement.TrackType == Bridge) && (FrontEntryPos < 2) && (TrackElement.TrainIDOnBridgeTrackPos01 == -1))
6295  {
6296  Able = true;
6297  StoppedForTrainInFront = false;
6298  }
6299  else if((TrackElement.TrackType == Bridge) && (FrontEntryPos > 1) && (TrackElement.TrainIDOnBridgeTrackPos23 == -1))
6300  {
6301  Able = true;
6302  StoppedForTrainInFront = false;
6303  }
6304  }
6305  else
6306  {
6307  if(Track->TrackElementAt(801, LeadElement).TrackType == Buffers)
6308  Able = false;
6309  // don't set StoppedAtBuffers as (presumably) StoppedAtLocation & leave it at that
6310  }
6311  }
6312  else // leaving at a continuation so keep going
6313  {
6314  Able = true;
6315  StoppedForTrainInFront = false;
6316  }
6317  Utilities->CallLogPop(1454);
6318  return Able;
6319 }
6320 
6321 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
6322 
6323 bool TTrain::AbleToMoveButForSignal(int Caller)
6324 {
6325  // first check if a train immediately in front (may have moved there since this train stopped so StoppedForTrainInFront
6326  // won't be set; if there is a train then set StoppedForTrainInFront
6327  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",AbleToMoveButForSignal" + "," + HeadCode);
6328  // addition below for v1.3.2 after Carwyn Thomas fault reported 24/05/15 - need to check if exiting at continuation (LeadElement == -1) as if so fails at VecPos = .....
6329  if(LeadElement == -1) // exiting at continuation
6330  {
6331  Utilities->CallLogPop(2045);
6332  return false;
6333  }
6334  // end of addition
6335  int VecPos = Track->TrackElementAt(654, LeadElement).Conn[LeadExitPos];
6336  int NextEntryPos = Track->TrackElementAt(655, LeadElement).ConnLinkPos[LeadExitPos];
6337 
6338  if(Track->OtherTrainOnTrack(5, VecPos, NextEntryPos, TrainID))
6339  {
6340  StoppedForTrainInFront = true;
6341  Utilities->CallLogPop(1455);
6342  return false;
6343  }
6344  else
6345  {
6346  Utilities->CallLogPop(1456);
6347  return StoppedAtSignal && !(Crashed || Derailed || StoppedAtBuffers || StoppedForTrainInFront || StoppedWithoutPower);
6348  // StoppedWithoutPower added v2.4.0
6349  }
6350 }

6360  UnplotTrain(8);

6362  RearStartExitPos = LeadEntryPos;
6363  StartSpeed = 0;

6366  Utilities->CallLogPop(1102);
6367 }

6369 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
6370 
6371 AnsiString TTrain::FloatingLabelNextString(int Caller, TActionVectorEntry *Ptr)
6372 {
6373  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + "," + AnsiString(Ptr - &TrainDataEntryPtr->ActionVector.front()) +
6374  ",FloatingLabelNextString" + "," + HeadCode);
6375  AnsiString RetStr = "", LocationName = "";
6376 
6377  if((Ptr->Command != "") && (Ptr->Command[1] == 'S'))
6378  {
6379  throw Exception("Error - start entry in FloatingLabelNextString");
6380  }
6381  if(Ptr->FormatType == TimeTimeLoc)
6382  {
6383  if(TrainMode == Timetable)
6384  {
6385  if(!TrainAtLocation(0, LocationName) || (LocationName != Ptr->LocationName))
6386  // not arrived yet in tt mode
6387  {
6388  RetStr = "Arrive " + Ptr->LocationName + " at " + Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(2, Ptr->ArrivalTime));
6389  }
6390  else
6391  {
6392  RetStr = "Depart " + Ptr->LocationName + " at " + Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(3, Ptr->DepartureTime));
6393  }
6394  }
6395  else // TrainMode == Signaller
6396  {
6397  if(!DepartureTimeSet) // not arrived yet
6398  {
6399  RetStr = "Arrive " + Ptr->LocationName + " at " + Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(45, Ptr->ArrivalTime));
6400  }
6401  else
6402  {
6403  RetStr = "Depart " + Ptr->LocationName + " at " + Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(36, Ptr->DepartureTime));
6404  }
6405  }
6406  }
6407  else if((Ptr->FormatType == TimeLoc) && (Ptr->ArrivalTime != TDateTime(-1)))
6408  {
6409  RetStr = "Arrive " + Ptr->LocationName + " at " + Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(4, Ptr->ArrivalTime));
6410  }
6411  else if((Ptr->FormatType == TimeLoc) && (Ptr->ArrivalTime == TDateTime(-1)))
6412  {
6413  RetStr = "Depart " + Ptr->LocationName + " at " + Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(5, Ptr->DepartureTime));
6414  }
6415  else if(Ptr->FormatType == PassTime) // new
6416  {
6417  RetStr = "Pass " + Ptr->LocationName + " at " + Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(31, Ptr->EventTime));
6418  }
6419  else if(Ptr->Command == "Fns")
6420  {
6421  RetStr = "Forms new service " + TrainController->GetRepeatHeadCode(8, Ptr->OtherHeadCode, RepeatNumber, IncrementalDigits) + " at " +
6422  Ptr->LocationName + " at " + Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(6, Ptr->EventTime));
6423  RetStr = CheckNewServiceDepartureTime(0, Ptr, RepeatNumber, Ptr->LinkedTrainEntryPtr, RetStr); //if there is a next service this adds the new service departure time to RetStr
6424  }
6425  else if(Ptr->Command == "F-nshs")
6426  {
6427  RetStr = "Forms new service " + Ptr->NonRepeatingShuttleLinkHeadCode + " at " + Ptr->LocationName + " at " +
6428  Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(32, Ptr->EventTime));
6429  RetStr = CheckNewServiceDepartureTime(1, Ptr, 0, Ptr->LinkedTrainEntryPtr, RetStr); //if there is a next service this adds the new service departure time to RetStr
6430  //note that use LinkedTrainEntryPtr and not NonRepeatingShuttleLinkEntryPtr because the forward link from the feeder is LinkedTrainEntryPtr.
6431  //NonRepeatingShuttleLinkEntryPtr is in the shuttle's ActionVector to point back to the feeder.
6432  //NonRepeatingShuttleLinkEntryPtr is used below from the last shuttle as the forward link to the finishing service
6433  }
6434  else if((Ptr->Command == "Fns-sh") && (RepeatNumber < (TrainDataEntryPtr->NumberOfTrains - 1))) // not last repeat number
6435  {
6436  RetStr = "Forms new service " + TrainController->GetRepeatHeadCode(9, Ptr->OtherHeadCode, RepeatNumber + 1, IncrementalDigits) + " at " +
6437  Ptr->LocationName + " at " + Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(7, Ptr->EventTime));
6438  // use RepeatNumber+1 as it's the repeat number of the NEXT shuttle service that is relevant
6439  RetStr = CheckNewServiceDepartureTime(2, Ptr, RepeatNumber + 1, Ptr->LinkedTrainEntryPtr, RetStr); //if there is a next service this adds the new service departure time to RetStr
6440  }
6441  else if((Ptr->Command == "Fns-sh") && (RepeatNumber >= (TrainDataEntryPtr->NumberOfTrains - 1))) // last repeat number
6442  {
6443  RetStr = "Forms new service " + Ptr->NonRepeatingShuttleLinkHeadCode,
6444  + " at " + Ptr->LocationName + " at " + Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(8, Ptr->EventTime));
6445  RetStr = CheckNewServiceDepartureTime(3, Ptr, 0, Ptr->NonRepeatingShuttleLinkEntryPtr, RetStr); //if there is a next service this adds the new service departure time to RetStr
6446  }
6447  else if((Ptr->Command == "Frh-sh") && (RepeatNumber < (TrainDataEntryPtr->NumberOfTrains - 1))) // not last repeat number
6448  {
6449  RetStr = "Forms new service " + TrainController->GetRepeatHeadCode(10, Ptr->OtherHeadCode, RepeatNumber + 1, IncrementalDigits) + " at " +
6450  Ptr->LocationName + " at " + Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(9, Ptr->EventTime));
6451  // use RepeatNumber+1 as it's the repeat number of the NEXT shuttle service that is relevant
6452  RetStr = CheckNewServiceDepartureTime(4, Ptr, RepeatNumber + 1, Ptr->LinkedTrainEntryPtr, RetStr); //if there is a next service this adds the new service departure time to RetStr
6453  }
6454  else if((Ptr->Command == "Frh-sh") && (RepeatNumber >= (TrainDataEntryPtr->NumberOfTrains - 1))) // last repeat number
6455  {
6456  RetStr ="None, train terminated at " + Ptr->LocationName;
6457  }
6458  else if(Ptr->Command == "Frh")
6459  {
6460  RetStr = "None, train terminated at " + Ptr->LocationName;
6461  }
6462  else if(Ptr->Command == "Fer")
6463  {
6464  RetStr = "Exit railway" + TrainController->GetExitLocationAndAt(1, Ptr->ExitList) + " at " + Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(10, Ptr->EventTime));
6465  }
6466  else if(Ptr->Command == "Fjo")
6467  {
6468  RetStr = "Join " + TrainController->GetRepeatHeadCode(11, Ptr->OtherHeadCode, RepeatNumber, IncrementalDigits) + " at " + Ptr->LocationName + " at " +
6469  Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(11, Ptr->EventTime));
6470  }
6471  else if(Ptr->Command == "jbo")
6472  {
6473  RetStr = "Joined by " + TrainController->GetRepeatHeadCode(12, Ptr->OtherHeadCode, RepeatNumber, IncrementalDigits) + " at " + Ptr->LocationName +
6474  " at " + Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(12, Ptr->EventTime));
6475  }
6476  else if(Ptr->Command == "fsp")
6477  {
6478  RetStr = "Front split to " + TrainController->GetRepeatHeadCode(13, Ptr->OtherHeadCode, RepeatNumber, IncrementalDigits) + " at " + Ptr->LocationName +
6479  " at " + Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(13, Ptr->EventTime));
6480  }
6481  else if(Ptr->Command == "rsp")
6482  {
6483  RetStr = "Rear split to " + TrainController->GetRepeatHeadCode(14, Ptr->OtherHeadCode, RepeatNumber, IncrementalDigits) + " at " + Ptr->LocationName +
6484  " at " + Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(14, Ptr->EventTime));
6485  }
6486  else if(Ptr->Command == "cdt")
6487  {
6488  RetStr = "Change direction at " + Ptr->LocationName + " at " + Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(15, Ptr->EventTime));
6489  }
6490  Utilities->CallLogPop(1124);
6491  return RetStr;
6492 }

6494 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
6495 
6496 AnsiString TTrain::CheckNewServiceDepartureTime(int Caller, TActionVectorEntry *Ptr, int RptNum, TTrainDataEntry *LinkedTrainDataPtr, AnsiString RetStr)
6497 {
6498  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + "," + AnsiString(Ptr - &TrainDataEntryPtr->ActionVector.front()) + ","
6499  + AnsiString(RptNum) + ",CheckNewServiceDepartureTime," + HeadCode);
6500  AnsiString DepTime = "", EventTime = "";
6501  bool CDTFlag = false; //reports if train changes direction before departs
6502  TActionVector NewServiceAV = LinkedTrainDataPtr->ActionVector;
6503  for(TActionVectorIterator AVI = NewServiceAV.begin(); AVI < NewServiceAV.end(); AVI++)
6504  {
6505  if(AVI->Command == "cdt")
6506  {
6507  CDTFlag = !CDTFlag; //toggles flag - allows for there being more than one cdt before departure
6508  continue;
6509  }
6510  if((AVI->Command == "fsp") || (AVI->Command == "rsp"))
6511  {
6512  EventTime = Utilities->Format96HHMM(TrainController->GetControllerTrainTime(19, AVI->EventTime, RptNum, IncrementalMinutes));
6513  RetStr += "\nNew service splits at " + EventTime;
6514  Utilities->CallLogPop(2234);
6515  return RetStr;
6516  }
6517  if(AVI->Command == "jbo")
6518  {
6519  EventTime = Utilities->Format96HHMM(TrainController->GetControllerTrainTime(20, AVI->EventTime, RptNum, IncrementalMinutes));
6520  RetStr += "\nNew service joined by " + AVI->OtherHeadCode + " at " + EventTime;
6521  Utilities->CallLogPop(2235);
6522  return RetStr;
6523  }
6524  if((AVI->FormatType == TimeLoc) && (AVI->DepartureTime > TDateTime(-1))) //departure time set
6525  {
6526  DepTime = Utilities->Format96HHMM(TrainController->GetControllerTrainTime(17, AVI->DepartureTime, RptNum, IncrementalMinutes));
6527  if(CDTFlag)
6528  {
6529  RetStr += "\nNew service changes direction then departs at " + DepTime;
6530  }
6531  else
6532  {
6533  RetStr += "\nNew service departs at " + DepTime;
6534  }
6535  Utilities->CallLogPop(2236);
6536  return RetStr;
6537  }
6538  }
6539  Utilities->CallLogPop(2208);
6540  return RetStr; //if reach here then RetStr doesn't change
6541 }

6543 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
6544 
6545 AnsiString TTrain::FloatingTimetableString(int Caller, TActionVectorEntry *Ptr)
6546  // Enter with Ptr pointing to first action to be listed (i.e. next action)
6547 {
6548  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + "," + AnsiString(Ptr - &TrainDataEntryPtr->ActionVector.front()) +
6549  ",FloatingTimetableString" + "," + HeadCode);
6550  AnsiString RetStr = "", PartStr = "";
6551  int Count = 0;
6552 
6553  if((Ptr->Command != "") && (Ptr->Command[1] == 'S') && (TrainMode == Timetable))
6554  // can start in signaller control so exclude this
6555  {
6556  throw Exception("Error - start entry in FloatingTimetableString");
6557  }
6558  Ptr--; // because incremented at start of loop
6559  bool FirstPass = true;
6560 
6561  // different first TimeTimeLoc display if in signaller control
6562  do
6563  {
6564  Ptr++;
6565  if((Ptr->FormatType == Repeat) || TimetableFinished)
6566  break;
6567  if((Ptr->FormatType == TimeTimeLoc) && FirstPass)
6568  {
6569  AnsiString TrainLoc = "";
6570  if(TrainMode == Timetable)
6571  {
6572  if(TrainAtLocation(1, TrainLoc) && (TrainLoc == Ptr->LocationName))
6573  {
6574  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(33, Ptr->DepartureTime)) + ": Depart from " + Ptr->LocationName;
6575  }
6576  else if(Ptr->ArrivalTime == Ptr->DepartureTime)
6577  {
6578  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(34, Ptr->ArrivalTime)) + ": Arrive & depart from " + Ptr->LocationName;
6579  }
6580  else
6581  {
6582  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(16, Ptr->ArrivalTime)) + ": Arrive at " + Ptr->LocationName + '\n' +
6583  Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(17, Ptr->DepartureTime)) + ": Depart from " + Ptr->LocationName;
6584  Count++; // because there are 2 entries
6585  }
6586  }
6587  else // TrainMode == Signaller
6588  {
6589  if(DepartureTimeSet)
6590  {
6591  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(37, Ptr->DepartureTime)) + ": Depart from " + Ptr->LocationName;
6592  }
6593  else if(Ptr->ArrivalTime == Ptr->DepartureTime)
6594  {
6595  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(38, Ptr->ArrivalTime)) + ": Arrive & depart from " + Ptr->LocationName;
6596  }
6597  else
6598  {
6599  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(39, Ptr->ArrivalTime)) + ": Arrive at " + Ptr->LocationName + '\n' +
6600  Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(40, Ptr->DepartureTime)) + ": Depart from " + Ptr->LocationName;
6601  Count++; // because there are 2 entries
6602  }
6603  }
6604  }
6605  else if((Ptr->FormatType == TimeTimeLoc) && !FirstPass)
6606  {
6607  AnsiString TrainLoc = "";
6608  if((TrainAtLocation(2, TrainLoc)) && (TrainLoc == Ptr->LocationName))
6609  {
6610  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(41, Ptr->DepartureTime)) + ": Depart from " + Ptr->LocationName;
6611  }
6612  else if(Ptr->ArrivalTime == Ptr->DepartureTime)
6613  {
6614  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(42, Ptr->ArrivalTime)) + ": Arrive & depart from " + Ptr->LocationName;
6615  }
6616  else
6617  {
6618  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(43, Ptr->ArrivalTime)) + ": Arrive at " + Ptr->LocationName + '\n' +
6619  Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(44, Ptr->DepartureTime)) + ": Depart from " + Ptr->LocationName;
6620  Count++; // because there are 2 entries
6621  }
6622  }
6623  else if((Ptr->FormatType == TimeLoc) && (Ptr->ArrivalTime != TDateTime(-1)))
6624  {
6625  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(18, Ptr->ArrivalTime)) + ": Arrive at " + Ptr->LocationName;
6626  }
6627  else if((Ptr->FormatType == TimeLoc) && (Ptr->ArrivalTime == TDateTime(-1)))
6628  {
6629  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(19, Ptr->DepartureTime)) + ": Depart from " + Ptr->LocationName;
6630  }
6631  else if(Ptr->FormatType == PassTime) // new
6632  {
6633  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(30, Ptr->EventTime)) + ": Pass " + Ptr->LocationName;
6634  }
6635  else if(Ptr->Command == "Fns")
6636  {
6637  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(20, Ptr->EventTime)) + ": Form new service " + TrainController->GetRepeatHeadCode(15,
6638  Ptr->OtherHeadCode, RepeatNumber, IncrementalDigits) + " at " + Ptr->LocationName;
6639  PartStr = CheckNewServiceDepartureTime(5, Ptr, RepeatNumber, Ptr->LinkedTrainEntryPtr, PartStr); //if there is a next service this adds the new service departure time to PartStr
6640  }
6641  else if(Ptr->Command == "F-nshs")
6642  {
6643  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(35, Ptr->EventTime)) + ": Form new service " + Ptr->NonRepeatingShuttleLinkHeadCode + " at " +
6644  Ptr->LocationName;
6645  PartStr = CheckNewServiceDepartureTime(6, Ptr, 0, Ptr->LinkedTrainEntryPtr, PartStr); //if there is a next service this adds the new service departure time to RetStr
6646  //note that use LinkedTrainEntryPtr and not NonRepeatingShuttleLinkEntryPtr because the forward link from the feeder is LinkedTrainEntryPtr.
6647  //NonRepeatingShuttleLinkEntryPtr is in the shuttle's ActionVector to point back to the feeder.
6648  //NonRepeatingShuttleLinkEntryPtr is used below from the last shuttle as the forward link to the finishing service
6649  }
6650  else if((Ptr->Command == "Fns-sh") && (RepeatNumber < (TrainDataEntryPtr->NumberOfTrains - 1))) // not the last repeat number
6651  {
6652  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(21, Ptr->EventTime)) + ": Form new service " + TrainController->GetRepeatHeadCode(16,
6653  Ptr->OtherHeadCode, RepeatNumber + 1, IncrementalDigits) + " at " + Ptr->LocationName;
6654  // use RepeatNumber+1 because it's the repeat number of the NEXT shuttle service that is relevant
6655  PartStr = CheckNewServiceDepartureTime(7, Ptr, RepeatNumber + 1, Ptr->LinkedTrainEntryPtr, PartStr); //if there is a next service this adds the new service departure time to RetStr
6656  }
6657  else if((Ptr->Command == "Fns-sh") && (RepeatNumber >= (TrainDataEntryPtr->NumberOfTrains - 1))) // last repeat number
6658  {
6659  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(22, Ptr->EventTime)) + ": Form new service " + Ptr->NonRepeatingShuttleLinkHeadCode,
6660  + " at " + Ptr->LocationName;
6661  PartStr = CheckNewServiceDepartureTime(8, Ptr, 0, Ptr->NonRepeatingShuttleLinkEntryPtr, PartStr); //if there is a next service this adds the new service departure time to RetStr
6662  }
6663  else if((Ptr->Command == "Frh-sh") && (RepeatNumber < (TrainDataEntryPtr->NumberOfTrains - 1))) // not the last repeat number
6664  {
6665  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(23, Ptr->EventTime)) + ": Form new service " + TrainController->GetRepeatHeadCode(17,
6666  Ptr->OtherHeadCode, RepeatNumber + 1, IncrementalDigits) + " at " + Ptr->LocationName;
6667  // use RepeatNumber+1 because it's the repeat number of the NEXT shuttle service that is relevant
6668  PartStr = CheckNewServiceDepartureTime(9, Ptr, RepeatNumber + 1, Ptr->LinkedTrainEntryPtr, PartStr); //if there is a next service this adds the new service departure time to RetStr
6669  }
6670  else if((Ptr->Command == "Frh-sh") && (RepeatNumber >= (TrainDataEntryPtr->NumberOfTrains - 1))) // last repeat number
6671  {
6672  PartStr = "Terminate at " + Ptr->LocationName;
6673  }
6674  else if(Ptr->Command == "Frh")
6675  {
6676  PartStr = "Terminate at " + Ptr->LocationName;
6677  }
6678  else if(Ptr->Command == "Fer")
6679  {
6680  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(24, Ptr->EventTime)) + ": Exit railway" + TrainController->GetExitLocationAndAt(2, Ptr->ExitList);
6681  }
6682  else if(Ptr->Command == "Fjo")
6683  {
6684  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(25, Ptr->EventTime)) + ": Join " + TrainController->GetRepeatHeadCode(18, Ptr->OtherHeadCode,
6685  RepeatNumber, IncrementalDigits) + " at " + Ptr->LocationName;
6686  }
6687  else if(Ptr->Command == "jbo")
6688  {
6689  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(26, Ptr->EventTime)) + ": Joined by " + TrainController->GetRepeatHeadCode(19, Ptr->OtherHeadCode,
6690  RepeatNumber, IncrementalDigits) + " at " + Ptr->LocationName;
6691  }
6692  else if(Ptr->Command == "fsp")
6693  {
6694  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(27, Ptr->EventTime)) + ": Front split to " + TrainController->GetRepeatHeadCode(20,
6695  Ptr->OtherHeadCode, RepeatNumber, IncrementalDigits) + " at " + Ptr->LocationName;
6696  }
6697  else if(Ptr->Command == "rsp")
6698  {
6699  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(28, Ptr->EventTime)) + ": Rear split to " + TrainController->GetRepeatHeadCode(21,
6700  Ptr->OtherHeadCode, RepeatNumber, IncrementalDigits) + " at " + Ptr->LocationName;
6701  }
6702  else if(Ptr->Command == "cdt")
6703  {
6704  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetTrainTime(29, Ptr->EventTime)) + ": Change direction at " + Ptr->LocationName;
6705  }
6706  if(RetStr != "")
6707  RetStr = RetStr + '\n' + PartStr;
6708  else
6709  RetStr = PartStr;
6710  FirstPass = false;
6711  Count++;
6712  }
6713  while(!TimetableFinished && (Count < 32) && ((Ptr->Command == "") || ((Ptr->Command != "") && (Ptr->Command[1] != 'F'))));
6714  // limit of 32 allows a max of 34 entries (33 + 1 for the new service departure time) (may have gone from 32 to 34 because of a TimeTimeLoc), which with track and
6715  // train status gives a max of 48 lines, at 13 pixels each, = 624 pixels & screen height has 641 so will fit comfortably. Also 34 timetable entries is as far
6716  // forward as anyone should wish to see without looking at the full timetable
6717  if(TimetableFinished)
6718  {
6719  if(TrainMode == Timetable)
6720  RetStr = "Timetable finished";
6721  else
6722  RetStr = "No timetable";
6723  }
6724  Utilities->CallLogPop(1125);
6725  return RetStr;
6726 }

6883  // RestoreTimetableLocation + marker
6884  }
6885  // Note: including RestoreTimetableLocation with the marker is to correct an oversight - it should have been saved earlier
6886  Utilities->CallLogPop(1457);
6887 }

6891 void TTrain::LoadOneSessionTrain(int Caller, std::ifstream &InFile)
6892 {
6893  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",LoadOneSessionTrain"); // don't have headcode yet
6894  HeadCode = Utilities->LoadFileString(InFile);
6895  RearStartElement = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6896  RearStartExitPos = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6897  StartSpeed = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6898  SignallerMaxSpeed = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6899  if(SignallerMaxSpeed < 10)
6900  SignallerMaxSpeed = 10; // added at v0.6 to avoid low max speeds
6901  HoldAtLocationInTTMode = Utilities->LoadFileBool(InFile);
6902  RepeatNumber = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6903  IncrementalMinutes = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6904  IncrementalDigits = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6905  Mass = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6906  FrontElementSpeedLimit = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6907  if(FrontElementSpeedLimit > TTrain::MaximumSpeedLimit)
6908  FrontElementSpeedLimit = TTrain::MaximumSpeedLimit;
6909  // above added at v2.1.0 for legacy session files where value may not have been limited
6910  FrontElementLength = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6911  EntrySpeed = Utilities->LoadFileDouble(InFile);
6912  ExitSpeedHalf = Utilities->LoadFileDouble(InFile);
6913  ExitSpeedFull = Utilities->LoadFileDouble(InFile);
6914  TimetableMaxRunningSpeed = Utilities->LoadFileDouble(InFile);
6915  if(TimetableMaxRunningSpeed < 10)
6916  {
6917  TimetableMaxRunningSpeed = 10; // added at v0.6 to avoid low max speeds
6918  }
6919  MaxRunningSpeed = Utilities->LoadFileDouble(InFile);
6920  if(MaxRunningSpeed < 10)
6921  {
6922  MaxRunningSpeed = 10; // added at v0.6 to avoid low max speeds
6923  }
6924  MaxExitSpeed = Utilities->LoadFileDouble(InFile);
6925  MaxBrakeRate = Utilities->LoadFileDouble(InFile);
6926  BrakeRate = Utilities->LoadFileDouble(InFile);
6927  PowerAtRail = Utilities->LoadFileDouble(InFile);
6928  FirstHalfMove = Utilities->LoadFileBool(InFile);
6929  OneLengthAccelDecel = Utilities->LoadFileBool(InFile);
6930  EntryTime = TDateTime(Utilities->LoadFileDouble(InFile));
6931  ExitTimeHalf = TDateTime(Utilities->LoadFileDouble(InFile));
6932  ExitTimeFull = TDateTime(Utilities->LoadFileDouble(InFile));
6933  ReleaseTime = TDateTime(Utilities->LoadFileDouble(InFile));
6934  TRSTime = TDateTime(Utilities->LoadFileDouble(InFile));
6935  LastActionTime = TDateTime(Utilities->LoadFileDouble(InFile));
6936  CallingOnFlag = Utilities->LoadFileBool(InFile);
6937  BeingCalledOn = Utilities->LoadFileBool(InFile);
6938  DepartureTimeSet = Utilities->LoadFileBool(InFile);
6939  TrainMode = TTrainMode(Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile));
6940  TimetableFinished = Utilities->LoadFileBool(InFile);
6941  LastActionDelayFlag = Utilities->LoadFileBool(InFile);
6942  SignallerRemoved = Utilities->LoadFileBool(InFile);
6943  TerminatedMessageSent = Utilities->LoadFileBool(InFile);
6944  Derailed = Utilities->LoadFileBool(InFile);
6945  DerailPending = Utilities->LoadFileBool(InFile);
6946  Crashed = Utilities->LoadFileBool(InFile);
6947  StoppedAtBuffers = Utilities->LoadFileBool(InFile);
6948  StoppedAtSignal = Utilities->LoadFileBool(InFile);
6949  StoppedAtLocation = Utilities->LoadFileBool(InFile);
6950  SignallerStopped = Utilities->LoadFileBool(InFile);
6951  StoppedAfterSPAD = Utilities->LoadFileBool(InFile);
6952  StoppedForTrainInFront = Utilities->LoadFileBool(InFile);
6953  NotInService = Utilities->LoadFileBool(InFile);
6954  Plotted = Utilities->LoadFileBool(InFile);
6955  TrainGone = Utilities->LoadFileBool(InFile);
6956  SPADFlag = Utilities->LoadFileBool(InFile);
6957  TimeTimeLocArrived = Utilities->LoadFileBool(InFile);
6958  HOffset[0] = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6959  HOffset[1] = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6960  HOffset[2] = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6961  HOffset[3] = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6962  VOffset[0] = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6963  VOffset[1] = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6964  VOffset[2] = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6965  VOffset[3] = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6966  PlotElement[0] = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6967  PlotElement[1] = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6968  PlotElement[2] = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6969  PlotElement[3] = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6970  PlotEntryPos[0] = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6971  PlotEntryPos[1] = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6972  PlotEntryPos[2] = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6973  PlotEntryPos[3] = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6974  TrainCrashedInto = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6975  Straddle = (TStraddle)(Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile));
6976  NextTrainID = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6977  // will be same for all but best to save all anyway
6978  TrainID = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6979  LeadElement = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6980  LeadEntryPos = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6981  LeadExitPos = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6982  MidElement = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6983  MidEntryPos = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6984  MidExitPos = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6985  LagElement = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6986  LagEntryPos = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6987  LagExitPos = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
6988  int ColourNumber = TColor(Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile));
6989 
6990  if(ColourNumber == 0)
6991  BackgroundColour = clBufferAttentionNeeded;
6992  else if(ColourNumber == 1)
6993  BackgroundColour = clBufferStopBackground;
6994  else if(ColourNumber == 2)
6995  BackgroundColour = clCallOnBackground;
6996  else if(ColourNumber == 3)
6997  BackgroundColour = clCrashedBackground;
6998  else if(ColourNumber == 4)
6999  BackgroundColour = clDerailedBackground;
7000  else if(ColourNumber == 5)
7001  BackgroundColour = clFrontCodeSignaller;
7002  else if(ColourNumber == 6)
7003  BackgroundColour = clFrontCodeTimetable;
7004  else if(ColourNumber == 7)
7005  BackgroundColour = clNormalBackground;
7006  else if(ColourNumber == 8)
7007  BackgroundColour = clSignallerStopped;
7008  else if(ColourNumber == 9)
7009  BackgroundColour = clSignalStopBackground;
7010  else if(ColourNumber == 10)
7011  BackgroundColour = clSPADBackground;
7012  else if(ColourNumber == 11)
7013  BackgroundColour = clStationStopBackground;
7014  else if(ColourNumber == 12)
7015  BackgroundColour = clStoppedTrainInFront;
7016  else if(ColourNumber == 13)
7017  BackgroundColour = clTRSBackground;
7018  else if(ColourNumber == 14)
7019  BackgroundColour = clTrainFailedBackground; // added at v2.4.0
7020 
7021  // additional data
7022  SetHeadCodeGraphics(1, HeadCode);
7023  // sets the BackgroundColour to the loaded value
7024  bool ForwardHeadCode = Utilities->LoadFileBool(InFile);
7025 
7026  if(ForwardHeadCode)
7027  {
7028  for(int x = 0; x < 4; x++)
7029  {
7030  HeadCodePosition[x] = HeadCodeGrPtr[x];
7031  }
7032  }
7033  else
7034  {
7035  for(int x = 0; x < 4; x++)
7036  {
7037  HeadCodePosition[x] = HeadCodeGrPtr[3 - x];
7038  }
7039  }
7040 
7041  // if crashed & in timetable mode then change FrontCodePtr to black, if in signaller mode then change to blue whether crashed or not
7042  if(TrainMode == Timetable)
7043  {
7044  if(Crashed)
7045  RailGraphics->ChangeForegroundColour2(0, HeadCodePosition[0], FrontCodePtr, clB0G0R0, BackgroundColour);
7046  else
7047  RailGraphics->ChangeForegroundColour2(1, HeadCodePosition[0], FrontCodePtr, clFrontCodeTimetable, BackgroundColour);
7048  }
7049  else
7050  RailGraphics->ChangeForegroundColour2(2, HeadCodePosition[0], FrontCodePtr, clFrontCodeSignaller, BackgroundColour);
7051  HeadCodePosition[0] = FrontCodePtr;
7052  // pick up background bitmaps, none if MidLag as no train plotted - entering at continuation
7053  if(Straddle == LeadMid)
7054  {
7055  if(LeadElement > -1)
7056  PickUpBackgroundBitmap(6, HOffset[0], VOffset[0], LeadElement, LeadEntryPos, BackgroundPtr[0]);
7057  if(LeadElement > -1)
7058  PickUpBackgroundBitmap(7, HOffset[1], VOffset[1], LeadElement, LeadEntryPos, BackgroundPtr[1]);
7059  if(MidElement > -1)
7060  PickUpBackgroundBitmap(8, HOffset[2], VOffset[2], MidElement, MidEntryPos, BackgroundPtr[2]);
7061  if(MidElement > -1)
7062  PickUpBackgroundBitmap(9, HOffset[3], VOffset[3], MidElement, MidEntryPos, BackgroundPtr[3]);
7063  }
7064  else if(Straddle == LeadMidLag)
7065  {
7066  if(LeadElement > -1)
7067  PickUpBackgroundBitmap(10, HOffset[0], VOffset[0], LeadElement, LeadEntryPos, BackgroundPtr[0]);
7068  if(MidElement > -1)
7069  PickUpBackgroundBitmap(11, HOffset[1], VOffset[1], MidElement, MidEntryPos, BackgroundPtr[1]);
7070  if(MidElement > -1)
7071  PickUpBackgroundBitmap(12, HOffset[2], VOffset[2], MidElement, MidEntryPos, BackgroundPtr[2]);
7072  if(LagElement > -1)
7073  PickUpBackgroundBitmap(13, HOffset[3], VOffset[3], LagElement, LagEntryPos, BackgroundPtr[3]);
7074  }
7075 
7076  int TrainDataEntryValue = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
7077 
7078  TrainDataEntryPtr = &(TrainController->TrainDataVector.at(0)) + TrainDataEntryValue;
7079  int ActionVectorEntryValue = Utilities->LoadFileInt(InFile);
7080 
7081  ActionVectorEntryPtr = &(TrainDataEntryPtr->ActionVector.at(0)) + ActionVectorEntryValue;
7082 
7083  // need to set the TrainID if arriving at a continuation but hasn't been plotted yet
7084  if(LeadElement > -1)
7085  // need to include this in case train exiting & no lead element
7086  {
7087  if(Track->TrackElementAt(667, LeadElement).TrackType == Continuation)
7088  {
7089  Track->TrackElementAt(668, LeadElement).TrainIDOnElement = TrainID; // no need to stop gap flashing if a continuation
7090  }
7091  }
7092  AValue = sqrt(2 * PowerAtRail / Mass);
7093 
7094  AnsiString LocationAndMarker = Utilities->LoadFileString(InFile);
7095 
7096  // possible RestoreTimetableLocation + Marker, where Marker is
7097  // "*****0" for !StoppedWithoutPower and "*****1" otherwise (from v2.4.0)
7098  // Note: including RestoreTimetableLocation with the marker is to correct an oversight - RestoreTimetableLocation should have been saved earlier
7099  // added at beta v0.2e
7100  if((LocationAndMarker[1] != '*') && (LocationAndMarker.Length() > 6))
7101  // name not allowed to include the '*' character
7102  {
7103  AnsiString Location = LocationAndMarker.SubString(1, LocationAndMarker.Length() - 6);
7104  bool GiveMessagesFalse = false;
7105  bool CheckLocationsExistInRailwayTrue = true;
7106  if(TrainController->CheckLocationValidity(3, Location, GiveMessagesFalse, CheckLocationsExistInRailwayTrue))
7107  { // otherwise take no action
7108  RestoreTimetableLocation = Location;
7109  }
7110  }
7111  AnsiString Marker = LocationAndMarker.SubString(LocationAndMarker.Length() - 5, 6);
7112 
7113  StoppedWithoutPower = false;
7114  if(Marker[6] == '1')
7115  {
7116  StoppedWithoutPower = true;
7117  }
7118  Utilities->CallLogPop(1458);
7119 }

7388 
7389 void TTrain::PlotTrainInZoomOutMode(int Caller, bool Flash)
7390 {
7391  // order below reflects significance so earlier shows first, as may have more than one flag set
7392  // only plot flashing trains when Flash is true
7393 
7394 /*
7395  clCrashedBackground (TColor)0x0000FF red
7396  clDerailedBackground (TColor)0x0000FF red
7397  clSPADBackground (TColor)0x00FFFF yellow
7398  clTrainFailedBackground (TColor)0x0066FF orange new at v2.4.0
7399  clCallOnBackground (TColor)0xFF33FF light magenta
7400  clSignalStopBackground (TColor)0x00FF66 green
7401  clBufferAttentionNeeded (TColor)0xFFFF00 cyan
7402  clStationStopBackground (TColor)0xCCFFCC pale green
7403  clTRSBackground (TColor)0xFFCCFF light pink
7404  clBufferStopBackground (TColor)0xFFFFCC pale cyan
7405  clStoppedTrainInFront (TColor)0xFF9999 lavender blue
7406  clSignallerStopped (TColor)0x99CCFF caramel
7407  clNormalBackground (TColor)0xCCCCCC grey
7408 */
7409 
7410  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",PlotTrainInZoomOutMode" + "," + HeadCode);
7411  bool HideFlashingTrain = true;
7412  // hide it when Flash false so it blinks on and off
7413  // if don't hide it it stays displayed all the time
7414  Graphics::TBitmap *SmallTrainBitmap;
7415 
7416  // NB ensure retain same order as zoomed in order so colours correspond
7417  if(BackgroundColour == clCrashedBackground)
7418  {
7419  TrainController->CrashWarning = true;
7420  SmallTrainBitmap = RailGraphics->smRed;
7421  }
7422  else if(BackgroundColour == clDerailedBackground)
7423  {
7424  TrainController->DerailWarning = true;
7425  SmallTrainBitmap = RailGraphics->smRed;
7426  }
7427  else if(BackgroundColour == clSPADBackground)
7428  {
7429  TrainController->SPADWarning = true;
7430  SmallTrainBitmap = RailGraphics->smYellow;
7431  }
7432  else if(BackgroundColour == clTrainFailedBackground)
7433  {
7434  TrainController->TrainFailedWarning = true;
7435  SmallTrainBitmap = RailGraphics->smOrange;
7436  }
7437  else if(BackgroundColour == clCallOnBackground)
7438  {
7439  TrainController->CallOnWarning = true;
7440  SmallTrainBitmap = RailGraphics->smMagenta;
7441  }
7442  else if(BackgroundColour == clSignalStopBackground)
7443  {
7444  TrainController->SignalStopWarning = true;
7445  SmallTrainBitmap = RailGraphics->smBrightGreen;
7446  }
7447  else if(BackgroundColour == clBufferAttentionNeeded)
7448  {
7449  TrainController->BufferAttentionWarning = true;
7450  SmallTrainBitmap = RailGraphics->smCyan;
7451  }
7452  else if((BackgroundColour == clStationStopBackground) || (BackgroundColour == clTRSBackground))
7453  {
7454  SmallTrainBitmap = RailGraphics->smPaleGreen;
7455  HideFlashingTrain = false;
7456  }
7457  else if(BackgroundColour == clBufferStopBackground)
7458  {
7459  SmallTrainBitmap = RailGraphics->smCyan;
7460  HideFlashingTrain = false;
7461  }
7462  else if(BackgroundColour == clStoppedTrainInFront)
7463  {
7464  SmallTrainBitmap = RailGraphics->smLightBlue;
7465  HideFlashingTrain = false;
7466  }
7467  else if(BackgroundColour == clSignallerStopped)
7468  {
7469  SmallTrainBitmap = RailGraphics->smCaramel;
7470  HideFlashingTrain = false;
7471  }
7472  else
7473  {
7474  SmallTrainBitmap = RailGraphics->smBlack; // moving
7475  HideFlashingTrain = false;
7476  }
7477 
7478  // now plot the new train
7479  // just plot lead & mid, unless lead == -1 in which case plot mid & lag
7480  if((LeadElement > -1) && (!HideFlashingTrain || Flash))
7481  {
7482  Display->PlotSmallOutput(4, Track->TrackElementAt(441, LeadElement).HLoc * 4, Track->TrackElementAt(442, LeadElement).VLoc * 4, SmallTrainBitmap);
7483  }
7484  if((MidElement > -1) && (!HideFlashingTrain || Flash))
7485  {
7486  Display->PlotSmallOutput(5, Track->TrackElementAt(443, MidElement).HLoc * 4, Track->TrackElementAt(444, MidElement).VLoc * 4, SmallTrainBitmap);
7487  }
7488  if((LeadElement == -1) && (LagElement > -1) && (!HideFlashingTrain || Flash))
7489  {
7490  Display->PlotSmallOutput(6, Track->TrackElementAt(445, LagElement).HLoc * 4, Track->TrackElementAt(446, LagElement).VLoc * 4, SmallTrainBitmap);
7491  }
7492  OldZoomOutElement[0] = LeadElement;
7493  OldZoomOutElement[1] = MidElement;
7494  OldZoomOutElement[2] = LagElement;
7495  Utilities->CallLogPop(1459);
7496 }

7500 void TTrain::UnplotTrainInZoomOutMode(int Caller)
7501 {
7502  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",UnplotTrainInZoomOutMode," + AnsiString(TrainID) + "," + HeadCode);
7503  if(!Display->ZoomOutFlag)
7504  {
7505  Utilities->CallLogPop(1304);
7506  return;
7507  }
7508  for(int y = 0; y < 3; y++)
7509  {
7510  if(OldZoomOutElement[y] > -1)
7511  {
7512  bool FoundFlag = false;
7513  TTrackElement ATElement = Track->TrackElementAt(717, OldZoomOutElement[y]);
7514  TTrackElement IATElement1, IATElement2;
7515  // default elements to begin with
7516  Display->PlotSmallOutput(7, ATElement.HLoc * 4, ATElement.VLoc * 4, RailGraphics->smSolidBgnd); // plot the blank
7517  TTrack::TIMPair IMPair = Track->GetVectorPositionsFromInactiveTrackMap(14, ATElement.HLoc, ATElement.VLoc, FoundFlag);
7518  // Note, have to plot inactives before track because track has to overwrite NamedLocationElements
7519  if(FoundFlag)
7520  {
7521  IATElement1 = Track->InactiveTrackElementAt(87, IMPair.first);
7522  Display->PlotSmallOutput(8, IATElement1.HLoc * 4, IATElement1.VLoc * 4, IATElement1.SmallGraphicPtr);
7523  if(IMPair.first != IMPair.second)
7524  {
7525  IATElement2 = Track->InactiveTrackElementAt(88, IMPair.second);
7526  Display->PlotSmallOutput(9, IATElement2.HLoc * 4, IATElement2.VLoc * 4, IATElement2.SmallGraphicPtr);
7527  }
7528  }
7529  Display->PlotSmallOutput(10, ATElement.HLoc * 4, ATElement.VLoc * 4, ATElement.SmallGraphicPtr);
7530  }
7531  }
7532  Utilities->CallLogPop(1305);
7533 }

7537 bool TTrain::TrainAtLocation(int Caller, AnsiString &LocationName)
7538 {
7539  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",TrainAtLocation" + "," + HeadCode);
7540  LocationName = "";
7541  if(!StoppedAtLocation)
7542  {
7543  Utilities->CallLogPop(1398);
7544  return false;
7545  }
7546  if(LeadElement > -1)
7547  {
7548  LocationName = Track->TrackElementAt(681, LeadElement).ActiveTrackElementName;
7549  }
7550  if((LocationName == "") && (MidElement > -1))
7551  {
7552  LocationName = Track->TrackElementAt(682, MidElement).ActiveTrackElementName;
7553  }
7554  if((LocationName == "") && (LagElement > -1))
7555  {
7556  LocationName = Track->TrackElementAt(683, LagElement).ActiveTrackElementName;
7557  }
7558  if(LocationName == "")
7559  {
7560  throw Exception("Error - Location name not set in TrainAtLocation");
7561  }
7562  Utilities->CallLogPop(1399);
7563  return true;
7564 }

7594 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
7595 
7596 bool TTrain::LinkOccupied(int Caller, int TrackVectorPosition, int LinkNumber) // added at v1.2.0
7597 {
7598  // return true for any part of train occupying LinkNumber at TrackVectorPosition, false for anything else, including no LinkNumber & no TrackVectorPosition
7599  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",LinkOccupied," + AnsiString(TrackVectorPosition) + "," +
7600  AnsiString(LinkNumber) + "," + HeadCode);
7601 
7602 /* Note on Straddle: Straddle defines the actual train position wrt Lag, Mid & Lead elements at all times other than within UpdateTrain. Is only MidLag outside UpdateTrain
7603  on first entry at a continuation (with no train plotted), and that has no relevance here. In all other cases it is either LeadMid (when train fully
7604  on Lead & Mid elements) or LeadMidLag (when train straddling 3 elements).
7605 */
7606 
7607  // note that MidElement always fully occupied
7608  if((MidElement == TrackVectorPosition) && ((Track->TrackElementAt(883, TrackVectorPosition).Link[MidEntryPos] == LinkNumber) || (Track->TrackElementAt(884,
7609  TrackVectorPosition).Link[MidExitPos] == LinkNumber)))
7610  {
7611  Utilities->CallLogPop(2005);
7612  return true;
7613  }
7614  if(Straddle == LeadMid)
7615  {
7616  if((LeadElement == TrackVectorPosition) && ((Track->TrackElementAt(885, TrackVectorPosition).Link[LeadEntryPos] == LinkNumber) ||
7617  (Track->TrackElementAt(886, TrackVectorPosition).Link[LeadExitPos] == LinkNumber)))
7618  {
7619  Utilities->CallLogPop(2006);
7620  return true;
7621  }
7622  }
7623  else if(Straddle == LeadMidLag)
7624  {
7625  if((LeadElement == TrackVectorPosition) && (Track->TrackElementAt(887, TrackVectorPosition).Link[LeadEntryPos] == LinkNumber))
7626  // only interested in LeadEntryPos as train not occupying ExitPos yet
7627  {
7628  Utilities->CallLogPop(2007);
7629  return true;
7630  }
7631  else if((LagElement == TrackVectorPosition) && (Track->TrackElementAt(888, TrackVectorPosition).Link[LagExitPos] == LinkNumber))
7632  // only interested in LagExitPos as train has left EntryPos
7633  {
7634  Utilities->CallLogPop(2008);
7635  return true;
7636  }
7637  }
7638  Utilities->CallLogPop(2009);
7639  return false;
7640 }
7641 
7642 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
7643 
7644 float TTrain::CalcTimeToAct(int Caller) // only called for running trains
7649 {
7650  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",CalcTimeToAct, " + HeadCode);
7651  int DistanceToRedSignal = 0;
7652  float TimeToAct = 0;
7653 
7654  if(TrainFailed)
7655  {
7656  Utilities->CallLogPop(2147);
7657  return 0; // time to act now
7658  }
7659 
7660  if(SignallerStopped)
7661  {
7662  Utilities->CallLogPop(2080);
7663  return -1;
7664  }
7665 
7666  if(!Stopped() || StoppedAtLocation)
7667  {
7668  // calc distance to next red signal but check for continuation exit
7669  if(LeadElement == -1)
7670  // if -1 it's on an end element so no action needed
7671  {
7672  Utilities->CallLogPop(2075);
7673  return -1;
7674  }
7675  else
7676  {
7677  int FirstPosToBeMeasured = Track->TrackElementAt(953, LeadElement).Conn[LeadExitPos];
7678  int FirstEntryPos = Track->TrackElementAt(954, LeadElement).ConnLinkPos[LeadExitPos];
7679  if((Straddle == LeadMidLag) && (TrainMode == Timetable))
7680 /* In TTMode it's important to set the first element to be measured ahead of the lead element only when the train fully on
7681  2 elements. Otherwise, if the train is only half on the lead element and approaching a station stop where the platform doesn't
7682  extend beyond the lead element stop point, the element ahead of the lead element is not a location whereas the ActionVector
7683  still points to the station stop location. In these circumstances the train hasn't yet stopped, so the dwell time at the
7684  stop isn't calculated, and the station to be stopped at isn't found as a future stop and nor are any other future stops
7685  because the ActionVector name never matches a future station. Hence all dwell times are omitted until the train lands fully
7686  on two elements. To avoid this when Straddle is LeadMidLag the first element to be measured is set to the lead element, so
7687  before the train has stopped the current station is still recognised as a future stop.
7688  In signaller mode stops don't count, and if pass red signal command is given then when have LeadMidLag the current element
7689  becomes the signal, and the time to act indication becomes 'NOW'.
7690 */ {
7691  FirstPosToBeMeasured = LeadElement;
7692  FirstEntryPos = LeadEntryPos;
7693  }
7694  float CurrentStopTime; // set to 0 at start of function
7695  float LaterStopTime; // set to 0 at start of function
7696  float RecoverableTime; // set to 0 at start of function
7697  int AvTrackSpeed; // set to zero at start of function
7698  bool SigControlAndCanPassRedSignal = ((TrainMode == Signaller) && AllowedToPassRedSignal);
7699  DistanceToRedSignal = TrainController->CalcDistanceToRedSignalandStopTime(0, FirstPosToBeMeasured, FirstEntryPos, SigControlAndCanPassRedSignal,
7700  ActionVectorEntryPtr, HeadCode, TrainID, CurrentStopTime, LaterStopTime, RecoverableTime, AvTrackSpeed);
7701  if(DistanceToRedSignal == -1) // -1 for no action needed
7702  {
7703  Utilities->CallLogPop(2076);
7704  return -1;
7705  }
7706 /* Have MinsDelayed; pos or neg,
7707  CurrentStopTime; pos or zero
7708  LaterStopTime; pos or zero
7709  RecoverableTime; pos or zero
7710 
7711  & from these calculate TotalStopTime. noting that:
7712  If stopped CurrentStopTime automatically adjusts for all early running and for as much late running as possible
7713  RecoverableTime always < LaterStopTime or both zero
7714  can't subtract more than RecoverableTime (MinsDelayed > 0)
7715  only subtract from LaterStopTime, not CurrentTime (MinsDelayed > 0)
7716  only subtract from LaterStopTime if LaterStopTime > 0 (MinsDelayed > 0)
7717  only add to LaterStopTime if LaterStopTime > 0 (MinsDelayed < 0)
7718  if running early & stopped at location CurrentStopTime will automatically include the excess
7719 */
7720  float TimeToSubtract, TotalStopTime;
7721  if(MinsDelayed > RecoverableTime)
7722  TimeToSubtract = RecoverableTime;
7723  else
7724  TimeToSubtract = MinsDelayed; // may be negative;
7725 
7726  if(MinsDelayed < 0) // running early
7727  {
7728  if(CurrentStopTime > 0)
7729  TotalStopTime = CurrentStopTime + LaterStopTime;
7730  // stopped at loc, will depart on time
7731  else
7732  TotalStopTime = LaterStopTime - MinsDelayed;
7733  // not stopped, will depart on time at first later stop so add the delay
7734  }
7735  else // on time or running late
7736  {
7737  if(LaterStopTime == 0)
7738  TotalStopTime = CurrentStopTime;
7739  // no later stops, if stopped now will depart as soon as possible,
7740  // if not stopped no stop times to add
7741  else
7742  TotalStopTime = CurrentStopTime + LaterStopTime - TimeToSubtract; // later stops so deduct as much as can
7743  }
7744 
7745  if(AvTrackSpeed < 30)
7746  AvTrackSpeed = 30;
7747  int Speed = AvTrackSpeed;
7748  if(AvTrackSpeed > int(MaxRunningSpeed))
7749  Speed = int(MaxRunningSpeed);
7750  if(TrainMode == Signaller)
7751  {
7752  Speed = SignallerMaxSpeed;
7753  TotalStopTime = 0;
7754  }
7755  TimeToAct = TotalStopTime + DistanceToRedSignal * 3.6 / 60 / Speed;
7756  // accel & decel taken into account in
7757  // CalcDistanceToRedSignalandStopTime
7758  // 3.6 convertsKm/h to m/s & 60 converts seconds to minutes
7759  Utilities->CallLogPop(2079);
7760  return TimeToAct;
7761  }
7762  }
7763  else // stopped not at location
7764  {
7765  if(Crashed || Derailed || StoppedAtBuffers || StoppedAtSignal || StoppedAfterSPAD)
7766  TimeToAct = 0.0;
7767  // but if stopped at a signal & autosigs route after it then ok
7768  if(StoppedAtSignal)
7769  {
7770  int NextElement = Track->TrackElementAt(928, LeadElement).Conn[LeadExitPos];
7771  int NextEntryPos = Track->TrackElementAt(929, LeadElement).ConnLinkPos[LeadExitPos];
7772  int NextExitPos;
7773  if(Track->TrackElementAt(930, NextElement).TrackType == Points)
7774  {
7775  if((NextEntryPos == 0) || (NextEntryPos == 2))
7776  // leading entry point
7777  {
7778  if(Track->TrackElementAt(931, NextElement).Attribute == 0)
7779  NextExitPos = 1;
7780  else
7781  NextExitPos = 3;
7782  }
7783  else
7784  NextExitPos = 0; // trailing entry point
7785  }
7786  else
7787  NextExitPos = Track->GetNonPointsOppositeLinkPos(NextEntryPos);
7788  int NextButOneElement = Track->TrackElementAt(932, NextElement).Conn[NextExitPos];
7789  int NextButOneEntryPos = Track->TrackElementAt(933, NextElement).ConnLinkPos[NextExitPos];
7790  int RouteNumber; // holder for referenced value, not used
7791  if(AllRoutes->GetRouteTypeAndNumber(32, NextButOneElement, NextButOneEntryPos, RouteNumber) == TAllRoutes::AutoSigsRoute)
7792  {
7793  TimeToAct = -1;
7794  }
7795  }
7796  Utilities->CallLogPop(2074);
7797  return TimeToAct;
7798  }
7799 }

7803 bool TTrain::TrainOnContinuation(int Caller)
7804 {
7805  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",TrainOnContinuation, " + HeadCode);
7806  if(LeadElement > -1)
7807  {
7808  if(Track->TrackElementAt(976, LeadElement).TrackType == Continuation)
7809  {
7810  Utilities->CallLogPop(2148);
7811  return true;
7812  }
7813  }
7814  if(MidElement > -1)
7815  {
7816  if(Track->TrackElementAt(977, MidElement).TrackType == Continuation)
7817  {
7818  Utilities->CallLogPop(2149);
7819  return true;
7820  }
7821  }
7822  if(LagElement > -1)
7823  {
7824  if(Track->TrackElementAt(978, LagElement).TrackType == Continuation)
7825  {
7826  Utilities->CallLogPop(2150);
7827  return true;
7828  }
7829  }
7830  Utilities->CallLogPop(2151);
7831  return false;
7832 }

7896 void TTrainController::LogEvent(AnsiString Str)

7899

7906 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
7907 
7908 void TTrainController::Operate(int Caller)
7909 {
7910  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",Operate");
7911  bool ClockState = Utilities->Clock2Stopped;
7912 
7913  Utilities->Clock2Stopped = true;
7914  // new section dealing with Snt & Snt-sh additions
7915  // BUT don't add trains if points or route flashing [conditions added for Version 0.6 as a result of Najamuddin's error - 15/01/11] - wait until next
7916  // clock tick after stops flashing
7917  if(!Track->RouteFlashFlag && !Track->PointFlashFlag)
7918  {
7919  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++)
7920  {
7921  TTrainDataEntry & TDEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x);
7922  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry0 = TDEntry.ActionVector.at(0);
7923  TActionEventType EventType = NoEvent;
7924  if(AVEntry0.Command == "Snt")
7925  {
7926  // calc below only for Snt & Snt-sh entries rather than all entries to save time
7927  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntryLast = TDEntry.ActionVector.at(TDEntry.ActionVector.size() - 1);
7928  int IncrementalMinutes = 0;
7929  int IncrementalDigits = 0;
7930  if(AVEntryLast.FormatType == Repeat)
7931  {
7932  IncrementalMinutes = AVEntryLast.RearStartOrRepeatMins;
7933  IncrementalDigits = AVEntryLast.FrontStartOrRepeatDigits;
7934  }
7935  if((AVEntryLast.FormatType == Repeat) && (TDEntry.NumberOfTrains < 2))
7936  {
7937  throw Exception("Error - Repeat entry && less than two trains for Snt entry: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
7938  }
7939  // see above note
7940 
7941  for(int y = 0; y < TDEntry.NumberOfTrains; y++)
7942  {
7943  TTrainOperatingData &TTOD = TDEntry.TrainOperatingDataVector.at(y);
7944  if(TTOD.RunningEntry != NotStarted)
7945  continue;
7946  if(GetRepeatTime(2, AVEntry0.EventTime, y, IncrementalMinutes) > TTClockTime)
7947  break; // all the rest will also be greater
7948  AnsiString TrainHeadCode = GetRepeatHeadCode(22, TDEntry.HeadCode, y, IncrementalDigits);
7949  if(AddTrain(2, AVEntry0.RearStartOrRepeatMins, AVEntry0.FrontStartOrRepeatDigits, TrainHeadCode, TDEntry.StartSpeed, TDEntry.Mass,
7950  TDEntry.MaxRunningSpeed, TDEntry.MaxBrakeRate, TDEntry.PowerAtRail, "Timetable", &TDEntry, y, IncrementalMinutes, IncrementalDigits,
7951  TDEntry.SignallerSpeed, AVEntry0.SignallerControl, EventType))
7952  {
7953  TTOD.TrainID = TrainVector.back().TrainID;
7954  TTOD.RunningEntry = Running;
7955  }
7956  else if(EventType == FailTrainEntry)
7957  {
7958  break; // if a train can't enter no point checking any more repeats as they won't be able to enter either
7959  }
7960  }
7961  }
7962 
7963  if(AVEntry0.Command == "Snt-sh")
7964  // just start this once, shuttle repeats take care of restarts
7965  {
7966  // calc below only for Snt & Snt-sh entries rather than all entries to save time
7967  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntryLast = TDEntry.ActionVector.at(TDEntry.ActionVector.size() - 1);
7968  int IncrementalMinutes = 0;
7969  int IncrementalDigits = 0;
7970  if(AVEntryLast.FormatType == Repeat)
7971  {
7972  IncrementalMinutes = AVEntryLast.RearStartOrRepeatMins;
7973  IncrementalDigits = AVEntryLast.FrontStartOrRepeatDigits;
7974  }
7975  if((AVEntryLast.FormatType == Repeat) && (TDEntry.NumberOfTrains < 2))
7976  {
7977  throw Exception("Error - Repeat entry && less than two trains for Snt-sh entry: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
7978  }
7979  // see above note
7980  TTrainOperatingData &TTOD = TDEntry.TrainOperatingDataVector.at(0);
7981  if(TTOD.RunningEntry == NotStarted)
7982  {
7983  if(AVEntry0.EventTime <= TTClockTime)
7984  {
7985  if(AddTrain(3, AVEntry0.RearStartOrRepeatMins, AVEntry0.FrontStartOrRepeatDigits, TDEntry.HeadCode, TDEntry.StartSpeed, TDEntry.Mass,
7986  TDEntry.MaxRunningSpeed, TDEntry.MaxBrakeRate, TDEntry.PowerAtRail, "Timetable", &TDEntry, 0, IncrementalMinutes, IncrementalDigits,
7987  TDEntry.SignallerSpeed, false, EventType))
7988  // false for SignallerControl
7989  {
7990  TTOD.TrainID = TrainVector.back().TrainID;
7991  TTOD.RunningEntry = Running;
7992  }
7993  else if(EventType == FailTrainEntry)
7994  {
7995  break; // if a train can't enter no point checking any more repeats as they won't be able to enter either
7996  }
7997  }
7998  }
7999  }
8000  }
8001  }
8002 
8003  // deal with running trains but abort if any vectors added, would probably be OK but don't risk a vector reallocation disrupting the
8004  // iteration, next cycle will catch up with any other pending updates
8005  if(!TrainVector.empty())
8006  {
8007  TrainAdded = false;
8008  AllRoutes->CallonVector.clear();
8009  // this will be rebuilt during the calls to UpdateTrain
8010  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainVector.size(); x++)
8011  {
8012  TrainVectorAt(33, x).UpdateTrain(0);
8013  if(TrainAdded || TrainVectorAt(35, x).HasTrainGone())
8014  // added HasTrainGone() condition in v0.4c to prevent 2 trains both having TrainGone set
8015  // at the same time. That caused the error Craig Weekes reported in November 2010 where 2 trains exited at the same time, and later the TrainVector
8016  // iterates in reverse to erase the second train to have gone, but afterwards ReplotTrains iterates forwards and therefore replots the first train to
8017  // have gone and therefore sets the TrainIDOnElement value to the exited train, with nothing to reset it. Hovering the mouse over that element with
8018  // train information enabled causes an error because the track element thinks the train is still there, whereas it is missing from the TrainVector.
8019  {
8020  break;
8021  }
8022  }
8023  // set warning flags
8024  CrashWarning = false;
8025  DerailWarning = false;
8026  SPADWarning = false;
8027  CallOnWarning = false;
8028  SignalStopWarning = false;
8029  BufferAttentionWarning = false;
8030  TrainFailedWarning = false;
8031  for(int x = TrainVector.size() - 1; x >= 0; x--) // reverse because of erase
8032  {
8033  TTrain &Train = TrainVectorAt(34, x);
8034  if(Train.Crashed)
8035  // can't use background colours for crashed & derailed because same colour
8036  {
8037  CrashWarning = true;
8038  }
8039  else if(Train.Derailed)
8040  // can't use background colours for crashed & derailed because same colour
8041  {
8042  DerailWarning = true;
8043  }
8044  else if(Train.BackgroundColour == clSPADBackground)
8045  // use colour as that changes as soon as passes signal
8046  {
8047  SPADWarning = true;
8048  }
8049  else if(Train.BackgroundColour == clTrainFailedBackground)
8050  {
8051  TrainFailedWarning = true;
8052  }
8053  else if(Train.BackgroundColour == clCallOnBackground)
8054  // use colour as also stopped at signal
8055  {
8056  CallOnWarning = true;
8057  }
8058  else if(Train.BackgroundColour == clSignalStopBackground)
8059  // use colour to distinguish from call-on
8060  {
8061  SignalStopWarning = true;
8062  }
8063  else if(Train.BackgroundColour == clBufferAttentionNeeded)
8064  // use colour to distinguish from ordinary buffer stop
8065  {
8066  BufferAttentionWarning = true;
8067  }
8068  if(Train.HasTrainGone())
8069  {
8070  AnsiString Loc = "";
8071  bool ElementFound = false;
8072  TTrackElement TE;
8073  if(Train.LagElement > -1)
8074  {
8075  TE = Track->TrackElementAt(531, Train.LagElement);
8076  ElementFound = true;
8077  }
8078  else if(Train.MidElement > -1)
8079  {
8080  TE = Track->TrackElementAt(779, Train.MidElement);
8081  ElementFound = true;
8082  }
8083  else if(Train.LeadElement > -1)
8084  {
8085  TE = Track->TrackElementAt(780, Train.LeadElement);
8086  ElementFound = true;
8087  }
8088  if(ElementFound)
8089  {
8090  if(TE.ActiveTrackElementName != "")
8091  {
8092  Loc = TE.ActiveTrackElementName + ", track element " + TE.ElementID;
8093  }
8094  else
8095  {
8096  Loc = "track element " + TE.ElementID;
8097  }
8098  }
8099 
8100  TActionVectorEntry *AVEntryPtr = Train.ActionVectorEntryPtr;
8101  if((Train.SignallerRemoved) || (Train.JoinedOtherTrainFlag))
8102  // need above first because may also have ActionVectorEntryPtr == "Fer"
8103  {
8104  Train.UnplotTrain(9);
8105  // added at v1.3.0 to reset signals after train removed from an autosigsroute
8106  if(SignallerTrainRemovedOnAutoSigsRoute)
8107  {
8108  AllRoutes->SignallerRemovedTrainAutoRoute.SetRouteSignals(9);
8109  SignallerTrainRemovedOnAutoSigsRoute = false;
8110  }
8111  // end of addition
8112  AllRoutes->RebuildRailwayFlag = true;
8113  // to force ClearandRebuildRailway at next clock tick if not in zoom-out mode, to replot LCs
8114  // correctly after a crash
8115  }
8116  else if(AVEntryPtr->Command == "Fer")
8117  {
8118  bool CorrectExit = false;
8119  if(!AVEntryPtr->ExitList.empty())
8120  {
8121  for(TExitListIterator ELIT = AVEntryPtr->ExitList.begin(); ELIT != AVEntryPtr->ExitList.end(); ELIT++)
8122  {
8123  if(*ELIT == Train.LagElement)
8124  CorrectExit = true;
8125  }
8126  }
8127  if(CorrectExit)
8128  {
8129  Train.LogAction(19, Train.HeadCode, "", Leave, Loc, AVEntryPtr->EventTime, AVEntryPtr->Warning);
8130  }
8131  else
8132  {
8133  LogActionError(38, Train.HeadCode, "", FailIncorrectExit, Loc);
8134  }
8135  }
8136  else
8137  {
8138  if(!AVEntryPtr->SignallerControl)
8139  {
8140  LogActionError(26, Train.HeadCode, "", FailUnexpectedExitRailway, Loc);
8141  Train.SendMissedActionLogs(2, -2, AVEntryPtr);
8142  // -2 is marker for send messages for all remaining actions except Fer if present
8143  }
8144  else
8145  {
8146  Train.LogAction(31, Train.HeadCode, "", SignallerLeave, Loc, TDateTime(0), false); // false for Warning
8147  }
8148  }
8149  Train.TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(Train.RepeatNumber).RunningEntry = Exited;
8150  Train.DeleteTrain(1);
8151  TrainVector.erase(TrainVector.begin() + x);
8152  ReplotTrains(1, Display);
8153  // to reset ElementIDs for remaining trains when have removed a train
8154  }
8155  }
8156  }
8157  else
8158  {
8159  // reset all flags in case last train removed with flag set
8160  CrashWarning = false;
8161  DerailWarning = false;
8162  SPADWarning = false;
8163  CallOnWarning = false;
8164  SignalStopWarning = false;
8165  BufferAttentionWarning = false;
8166  TrainFailedWarning = false;
8167  }
8168 
8169  // update OpTimeToActMultimap
8170  if((OpTimeToActUpdateCounter == 0) && TrainController->OpActionPanelVisible) // new v2.2.0
8171  {
8172  RebuildOpTimeToActMultimap(0);
8173  // clears entries then adds values for running trains then for continuation entries
8174  }
8175 
8176  Utilities->Clock2Stopped = ClockState;
8177  Utilities->CallLogPop(723);
8178 }

8207  Display->GetOutputLog2()->Caption = "";
8208  Display->GetOutputLog3()->Caption = "";
8209  Display->GetOutputLog4()->Caption = "";
8210  Display->GetOutputLog5()->Caption = "";
8211  Display->GetOutputLog6()->Caption = "";
8212  Display->GetOutputLog7()->Caption = "";
8213  Display->GetOutputLog8()->Caption = "";
8214  Display->GetOutputLog9()->Caption = "";
8215  Display->GetOutputLog10()->Caption = "";
8216  Utilities->CallLogPop(1352);
8217 }

8265 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
8266 
8267 bool TTrainController::AddTrain(int Caller, int RearPosition, int FrontPosition, AnsiString HeadCode, int StartSpeed, int Mass, double MaxRunningSpeed,
8268  double MaxBrakeRate, double PowerAtRail, AnsiString ModeStr, TTrainDataEntry *TrainDataEntryPtr, int RepeatNumber, int IncrementalMinutes,
8269  int IncrementalDigits, int SignallerSpeed, bool SignallerControl, TActionEventType &EventType)
8270 {
8271  LogEvent(AnsiString(Caller) + ",AddTrain," + AnsiString(RearPosition) + "," + AnsiString(FrontPosition) + "," + HeadCode + "," + AnsiString(StartSpeed) +
8272  "," + AnsiString(Mass) + "," + ModeStr);
8273  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",AddTrain," + AnsiString(RearPosition) + "," + AnsiString(FrontPosition) +
8274  "," + HeadCode + "," + AnsiString(StartSpeed) + "," + AnsiString(Mass) + "," + ModeStr + "," + HeadCode);
8275 
8276  int RearExitPos = -1;
8277 
8278  for(int x = 0; x < 4; x++)
8279  {
8280  if(Track->TrackElementAt(519, RearPosition).Conn[x] == FrontPosition)
8281  {
8282  RearExitPos = x;
8283  }
8284  }
8285  if(RearExitPos == -1)
8286  {
8287  throw Exception("Error, RearExit == -1 in AddTrain");
8288  }
8289 
8290  bool ReportFlag = true;
8291 
8292  // used to stop repeated messages from CheckStartAllowable when split failed
8293  if(TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).EventReported != NoEvent)
8294  ReportFlag = false;
8295 
8296  if(!CheckStartAllowable(0, RearPosition, RearExitPos, HeadCode, ReportFlag, EventType))
8297  { // messages sent to performance log in CheckStartAllowable if ReportFlag true
8298  TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).EventReported = EventType;
8299  Utilities->CallLogPop(938);
8300  return false;
8301  }
8302 
8303  TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(RepeatNumber).EventReported = NoEvent;
8304  TTrainMode TrainMode = NoMode;
8305 
8306  if(ModeStr == "Timetable")
8307  TrainMode = Timetable;
8308  // all else gives 'None', 'Signaller' set within program
8309 
8310  if(MaxRunningSpeed < 10)
8311  {
8312  MaxRunningSpeed = 10; // added at v0.6 to avoid low max speeds
8313  }
8314  if(SignallerSpeed < 10)
8315  SignallerSpeed = 10; // added at v0.6 to avoid low max speeds
8316  TTrain *NewTrain = new TTrain(0, RearPosition, RearExitPos, HeadCode, StartSpeed, Mass, MaxRunningSpeed, MaxBrakeRate, PowerAtRail, TrainMode,
8317  TrainDataEntryPtr, RepeatNumber, IncrementalMinutes, IncrementalDigits, SignallerSpeed);
8318 
8319  NewTrain->ActionVectorEntryPtr = &(TrainDataEntryPtr->ActionVector.at(0));
8320  // initialise here rather than in TTrain constructor as create trains
8321  // with Null TrainDataEntryPtr when loading session trains
8322  if(SignallerControl)
8323  {
8324  NewTrain->TimetableFinished = true;
8325  NewTrain->SignallerStoppingFlag = false;
8326  NewTrain->TrainMode = Signaller;
8327  if(NewTrain->MaxRunningSpeed > NewTrain->SignallerMaxSpeed)
8328  {
8329  NewTrain->MaxRunningSpeed = NewTrain->SignallerMaxSpeed;
8330  }
8331  RailGraphics->ChangeForegroundColour(17, NewTrain->HeadCodePosition[0], NewTrain->FrontCodePtr, clFrontCodeSignaller, NewTrain->BackgroundColour);
8332  }
8333 
8334  // deal with starting conditions:-
8335  // unlocated Snt: just report entry & advance pointer
8336  // located Snt or Sfs: set station conditions as would if had reached stop point in Update(), & advance the ActionVectorEntryPtr
8337  // Sns doesn't need a new train
8338  if(NewTrain->ActionVectorEntryPtr->LocationName != "")
8339  // covers all above located starts
8340  // if location of Snt was a station (that is set as LocationName, i.e. not just any station) that isn't next departure station then
8341  // wouldn't have accepted the timetable
8342  {
8343  // first check if LeadElement (can't access LeadElement directly yet as not set, use FrontPosition instead) is buffers, note that
8344  // StoppedAtBuffers is set in UpdateTrain()
8345  if(Track->TrackElementAt(520, FrontPosition).TrackType == Buffers)
8346  // buffer end must be ahead of train or would have failed start position check
8347  {
8348  NewTrain->StoppedAtLocation = true;
8349  NewTrain->PlotStartPosition(0);
8350  NewTrain->PlotTrainWithNewBackgroundColour(13, clStationStopBackground, Display); // pale green
8351  NewTrain->LogAction(20, NewTrain->HeadCode, "", Create, NewTrain->ActionVectorEntryPtr->LocationName, NewTrain->ActionVectorEntryPtr->EventTime,
8352  NewTrain->ActionVectorEntryPtr->Warning);
8353  if(!SignallerControl) // don't advance if SignalControlEntry
8354  {
8355  NewTrain->ActionVectorEntryPtr++;
8356  // should be a command, could be a location departure but if so can't depart so set 'Hold' anyway
8357  }
8358  NewTrain->LastActionTime = TTClockTime;
8359  }
8360  // else a through station stop
8361  else
8362  {
8363  NewTrain->StoppedAtLocation = true;
8364  NewTrain->PlotStartPosition(10);
8365  NewTrain->PlotTrainWithNewBackgroundColour(18, clStationStopBackground, Display); // pale green
8366  NewTrain->LogAction(21, NewTrain->HeadCode, "", Create, NewTrain->ActionVectorEntryPtr->LocationName, NewTrain->ActionVectorEntryPtr->EventTime,
8367  NewTrain->ActionVectorEntryPtr->Warning);
8368  if(!SignallerControl) // don't advance if SignalControlEntry
8369  {
8370  NewTrain->ActionVectorEntryPtr++;
8371  }
8372  NewTrain->LastActionTime = TTClockTime;
8373  }
8374  }
8375  else // unlocated entry (i.e. not a stop entry, but could still be at a named location)
8376  {
8377  NewTrain->PlotStartPosition(11);
8378  TTrackElement TE = Track->TrackElementAt(530, NewTrain->RearStartElement);
8379  AnsiString Loc = "";
8380  if(TE.ActiveTrackElementName != "")
8381  {
8382  Loc = TE.ActiveTrackElementName + ", track element " + TE.ElementID;
8383  }
8384  else
8385  {
8386  Loc = "track element " + TE.ElementID;
8387  }
8388  if(TE.TrackType == Continuation)
8389  {
8390  NewTrain->LogAction(22, NewTrain->HeadCode, "", Enter, Loc, NewTrain->ActionVectorEntryPtr->EventTime, NewTrain->ActionVectorEntryPtr->Warning);
8391  }
8392  else
8393  {
8394  NewTrain->LogAction(23, NewTrain->HeadCode, "", Create, Loc, NewTrain->ActionVectorEntryPtr->EventTime, NewTrain->ActionVectorEntryPtr->Warning);
8395  }
8396  if(!SignallerControl) // don't advance if SignalControlEntry
8397  {
8398  NewTrain->ActionVectorEntryPtr++;
8399  }
8400  NewTrain->LastActionTime = TTClockTime;
8401  // no need to set LastActionTime for an unlocated entry
8402  }
8403 
8404  // cancel a wrong-direction route if either element of train starts on one
8405  if(NewTrain->LeadElement > -1)
8406  {
8407  NewTrain->CheckAndCancelRouteForWrongEndEntry(3, NewTrain->LeadElement, NewTrain->LeadEntryPos);
8408  }
8409  if(NewTrain->MidElement > -1)
8410  {
8411  NewTrain->CheckAndCancelRouteForWrongEndEntry(4, NewTrain->MidElement, NewTrain->MidEntryPos);
8412  }
8413 
8414  // set signals for a right-direction autosigs route for either element of train on one
8415  // erase elements back to start for a non-autosigs route & check if an autosigs route immediately behind it, and if so set its signals
8416  // note that all but autosigs routes become part of a single route, so there can only be an autosigs route behind the non-autosigs route
8417  int RouteNumber = -1;
8418  bool SignalsSet = false;
8419 
8420  if(NewTrain->LeadElement > -1)
8421  {
8422  if(AllRoutes->GetRouteTypeAndNumber(13, NewTrain->LeadElement, NewTrain->LeadEntryPos, RouteNumber) == TAllRoutes::AutoSigsRoute)
8423  { // below added in place of SetRouteSignals in v2.4.0 as don't want to set signals from start of route for a new train addition
8424  int RouteStartPosition;
8425  TAllRoutes::TRouteElementPair FirstPair, SecondPair;
8426  FirstPair = AllRoutes->GetRouteElementDataFromRoute2MultiMap(21, Track->TrackElementAt(955, FrontPosition).HLoc,
8427  Track->TrackElementAt(956, FrontPosition).VLoc, SecondPair);
8428  if(FirstPair.first == RouteNumber)
8429  {
8430  RouteStartPosition = FirstPair.second;
8431  }
8432  else if(SecondPair.first == RouteNumber)
8433  {
8434  RouteStartPosition = SecondPair.second;
8435  }
8436  else
8437  {
8438  throw Exception("Error, RouteNumber not found in Route2MultiMap in 1st of 2 calls to SetAllRearwardsSignals in AddTrain");
8439  }
8440  AllRoutes->SetAllRearwardsSignals(10, 0, RouteNumber, RouteStartPosition);
8441  SignalsSet = true;
8442  // AllRoutes->GetFixedRouteAt(, RouteNumber).SetRouteSignals(); above substituted in v2.4.0
8443  }
8444  else if(RouteNumber > -1) // non-autosigsroute
8445  {
8446  TPrefDirElement TempPDE = AllRoutes->GetFixedRouteAt(181, RouteNumber).GetFixedPrefDirElementAt(194, 0);
8447  int FirstTVPos = TempPDE.GetTrackVectorPosition();
8448  int FirstELinkPos = TempPDE.GetELinkPos();
8449  while(TempPDE.GetTrackVectorPosition() != (unsigned int)(NewTrain->LeadElement))
8450  {
8451  AllRoutes->RemoveRouteElement(16, TempPDE.HLoc, TempPDE.VLoc, TempPDE.GetELink());
8452  TempPDE = AllRoutes->GetFixedRouteAt(182, RouteNumber).GetFixedPrefDirElementAt(195, 0);
8453  }
8454  if(TempPDE.GetTrackVectorPosition() == (unsigned int)(NewTrain->LeadElement))
8455  {
8456  AllRoutes->RemoveRouteElement(17, TempPDE.HLoc, TempPDE.VLoc, TempPDE.GetELink());
8457  // remove the last element under LeadElement
8458  }
8459  AllRoutes->RebuildRailwayFlag = true;
8460  // to force ClearandRebuildRailway at next clock tick if not in zoom-out mode
8461  // now deal with a rear linked autosigs route
8462  if(Track->TrackElementAt(820, FirstTVPos).Conn[FirstELinkPos] > -1)
8463  {
8464  int LinkedRouteNumber = -1;
8465  if(AllRoutes->GetRouteTypeAndNumber(17, Track->TrackElementAt(821, FirstTVPos).Conn[FirstELinkPos],
8466  Track->TrackElementAt(822, FirstTVPos).ConnLinkPos[FirstELinkPos], LinkedRouteNumber) == TAllRoutes::AutoSigsRoute)
8467  {
8468  AllRoutes->GetFixedRouteAt(169, LinkedRouteNumber).SetRouteSignals(0);
8469  // this is ok as here we are setting signals from the start of the route
8470  }
8471  }
8472  SignalsSet = true;
8473  }
8474  }
8475  if(NewTrain->MidElement > -1)
8476  // if entering at a continuation MidElement == -1
8477  { // this is included in case a train starts with LeadElement on no route and MidElement on a route
8478  if(!SignalsSet)
8479  {
8480  RouteNumber = -1;
8481  if(AllRoutes->GetRouteTypeAndNumber(14, NewTrain->MidElement, NewTrain->MidEntryPos, RouteNumber) == TAllRoutes::AutoSigsRoute)
8482  { // below added in place of SetRouteSignals in v2.4.0 as don't want to set signals from start of route for a new train addition
8483  int RouteStartPosition;
8484  TAllRoutes::TRouteElementPair FirstPair, SecondPair;
8485  FirstPair = AllRoutes->GetRouteElementDataFromRoute2MultiMap(22, Track->TrackElementAt(957, RearPosition).HLoc,
8486  Track->TrackElementAt(958, RearPosition).VLoc, SecondPair);
8487  if(FirstPair.first == RouteNumber)
8488  {
8489  RouteStartPosition = FirstPair.second;
8490  }
8491  else if(SecondPair.first == RouteNumber)
8492  {
8493  RouteStartPosition = SecondPair.second;
8494  }
8495  else
8496  {
8497  throw Exception("Error, RouteNumber not found in Route2MultiMap in 2nd of 2 calls to SetAllRearwardsSignals in AddTrain");
8498  }
8499  AllRoutes->SetAllRearwardsSignals(11, 0, RouteNumber, RouteStartPosition);
8500  SignalsSet = true;
8501  // AllRoutes->GetFixedRouteAt(, RouteNumber).SetRouteSignals(); above substituted in v2.4.0
8502  }
8503  else if(RouteNumber > -1) // non-autosigsroute
8504  {
8505  TPrefDirElement TempPDE = AllRoutes->GetFixedRouteAt(184, RouteNumber).GetFixedPrefDirElementAt(196, 0);
8506  int FirstTVPos = TempPDE.GetTrackVectorPosition();
8507  int FirstELinkPos = TempPDE.GetELinkPos();
8508  while(TempPDE.GetTrackVectorPosition() != (unsigned int)(NewTrain->MidElement))
8509  {
8510  AllRoutes->RemoveRouteElement(18, TempPDE.HLoc, TempPDE.VLoc, TempPDE.GetELink());
8511  TempPDE = AllRoutes->GetFixedRouteAt(185, RouteNumber).GetFixedPrefDirElementAt(197, 0);
8512  }
8513  if(TempPDE.GetTrackVectorPosition() == (unsigned int)(NewTrain->MidElement))
8514  {
8515  AllRoutes->RemoveRouteElement(19, TempPDE.HLoc, TempPDE.VLoc, TempPDE.GetELink());
8516  // remove the last element under LeadElement
8517  }
8518  AllRoutes->RebuildRailwayFlag = true;
8519  // to force ClearandRebuildRailway at next clock tick if not in zoom-out mode
8520  // now deal with a rear linked autosigs route
8521  if(Track->TrackElementAt(823, FirstTVPos).Conn[FirstELinkPos] > -1)
8522  {
8523  int LinkedRouteNumber = -1;
8524  if(AllRoutes->GetRouteTypeAndNumber(19, Track->TrackElementAt(824, FirstTVPos).Conn[FirstELinkPos],
8525  Track->TrackElementAt(825, FirstTVPos).ConnLinkPos[FirstELinkPos], LinkedRouteNumber) == TAllRoutes::AutoSigsRoute)
8526  {
8527  AllRoutes->GetFixedRouteAt(170, LinkedRouteNumber).SetRouteSignals(1);
8528  // this is ok as now we are setting signals from the start of the route
8529  }
8530  }
8531  }
8532  }
8533  }
8534 
8535  TrainVector.push_back(*NewTrain);
8536  Utilities->CallLogPop(731);
8537  return true;
8538 }

8542 int TTrainController::EntryPos(int Caller, int TrainIDIn, int TrackVectorNumber)
8543 {
8544  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",EntryPos," + AnsiString(TrainIDIn) + "," +
8545  AnsiString(TrackVectorNumber));
8546  int VecPos = -1;
8547 
8548  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainVector.size(); x++)
8549  {
8550  if(TrainVectorAt(1, x).TrainID == TrainIDIn)
8551  {
8552  VecPos = x;
8553  }
8554  }
8555  if(VecPos == -1)
8556  {
8557  throw Exception("Error, VecPos not set in EntryPos");
8558  }
8559  if(TrainVectorAt(2, VecPos).LeadElement == TrackVectorNumber)
8560  {
8561  Utilities->CallLogPop(734);
8562  return TrainVectorAt(3, VecPos).LeadEntryPos;
8563  }
8564  else if(TrainVectorAt(4, VecPos).MidElement == TrackVectorNumber)
8565  {
8566  Utilities->CallLogPop(735);
8567  return TrainVectorAt(5, VecPos).MidEntryPos;
8568  }
8569  else if(TrainVectorAt(6, VecPos).LagElement == TrackVectorNumber)
8570  {
8571  Utilities->CallLogPop(736);
8572  return TrainVectorAt(7, VecPos).LagEntryPos;
8573  }
8574  Utilities->CallLogPop(737);
8575  return -1;
8576 }

8589  }
8590  }
8591  throw Exception("Error - No Train identified in TrainVectorAtIdent with ID = " + AnsiString(TrainID));
8592 }
