8625 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
8626 
8627 AnsiString TTrainController::ContinuationEntryFloatingTTString(int Caller, TTrainDataEntry *TTDEPtr, int RepNum, int IncMins, int IncDig)
8628  // Enter with Ptr pointing to first action to be listed (i.e. next action)
8629 {
8630  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",ContinuationEntryFloatingTTString" + "," + TTDEPtr->HeadCode);
8631  AnsiString RetStr = "", PartStr = "";
8632  int Count = 0;
8633  TActionVectorIterator Ptr = TTDEPtr->ActionVector.begin();
8634 
8635  Ptr--; // because incremented at start of loop
8636  do
8637  {
8638  Ptr++;
8639  if((Ptr->Command != "") && (Ptr->Command[1] == 'S'))
8640  {
8641  continue; // move past the starting entry
8642  }
8643  if((Ptr->FormatType == Repeat) || Ptr >= TTDEPtr->ActionVector.end())
8644  break;
8645  if(Ptr->SignallerControl)
8646  {
8647  RetStr = "Train under signaller control";
8648  break;
8649  }
8650  if(Ptr->FormatType == TimeTimeLoc)
8651  {
8652  if(Ptr->ArrivalTime == Ptr->DepartureTime)
8653  {
8654  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetControllerTrainTime(0, Ptr->ArrivalTime, RepNum, IncMins)) + ": Arrive & depart from " + Ptr->LocationName;
8655  }
8656  else
8657  {
8658  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetControllerTrainTime(1, Ptr->ArrivalTime, RepNum, IncMins)) + ": Arrive at " + Ptr->LocationName + '\n' +
8659  Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetControllerTrainTime(2, Ptr->DepartureTime, RepNum, IncMins)) + ": Depart from " + Ptr->LocationName;
8660  Count++; // because there are 2 entries
8661  }
8662  }
8663  else if((Ptr->FormatType == TimeLoc) && (Ptr->ArrivalTime != TDateTime(-1)))
8664  {
8665  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetControllerTrainTime(3, Ptr->ArrivalTime, RepNum, IncMins)) + ": Arrive at " + Ptr->LocationName;
8666  }
8667  else if((Ptr->FormatType == TimeLoc) && (Ptr->ArrivalTime == TDateTime(-1)))
8668  {
8669  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetControllerTrainTime(4, Ptr->DepartureTime, RepNum, IncMins)) + ": Depart from " + Ptr->LocationName;
8670  }
8671  else if(Ptr->FormatType == PassTime) // new
8672  {
8673  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetControllerTrainTime(5, Ptr->EventTime, RepNum, IncMins)) + ": Pass " + Ptr->LocationName;
8674  }
8675  else if(Ptr->Command == "Fns")
8676  {
8677  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetControllerTrainTime(6, Ptr->EventTime, RepNum, IncMins)) + ": Form new service " +
8678  TrainController->GetRepeatHeadCode(46, Ptr->OtherHeadCode, RepNum, IncDig) + " at " + Ptr->LocationName;
8679  PartStr = ControllerCheckNewServiceDepartureTime(0, Ptr, RepNum, TTDEPtr, Ptr->LinkedTrainEntryPtr, IncMins, PartStr); //if there is a next service this adds the new service departure time to PartStr
8680  }
8681  else if(Ptr->Command == "F-nshs")
8682  {
8683  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetControllerTrainTime(7, Ptr->EventTime, RepNum, IncMins)) + ": Form new service " +
8684  Ptr->NonRepeatingShuttleLinkHeadCode + " at " + Ptr->LocationName;
8685  PartStr = ControllerCheckNewServiceDepartureTime(1, Ptr, 0, TTDEPtr, Ptr->LinkedTrainEntryPtr, IncMins, PartStr); //if there is a next service this adds the new service departure time to RetStr
8686  //note that use LinkedTrainEntryPtr and not NonRepeatingShuttleLinkEntryPtr because the forward link from the feeder is LinkedTrainEntryPtr.
8687  //NonRepeatingShuttleLinkEntryPtr is in the shuttle's ActionVector to point back to the feeder.
8688  //NonRepeatingShuttleLinkEntryPtr is used below from the last shuttle as the forward link to the finishing service
8689  }
8690 //Since this is a new continuation entry service it can't be Fns-sh or Frh-sh but leave these in for consistency with TTrain::FloatingTimetableString
8691  else if((Ptr->Command == "Fns-sh") && (RepNum < (TTDEPtr->NumberOfTrains - 1))) // not the last repeat number
8692  {
8693  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetControllerTrainTime(8, Ptr->EventTime, RepNum, IncMins)) + ": Form new service " +
8694  TrainController->GetRepeatHeadCode(47, Ptr->OtherHeadCode, RepNum + 1, IncDig) + " at " + Ptr->LocationName;
8695  // use RepNum+1 because it's the repeat number of the NEXT shuttle service that is relevant
8696  PartStr = ControllerCheckNewServiceDepartureTime(2, Ptr, RepNum + 1, TTDEPtr, Ptr->LinkedTrainEntryPtr, IncMins, PartStr); //if there is a next service this adds the new service departure time to RetStr
8697  }
8698  else if((Ptr->Command == "Fns-sh") && (RepNum >= (TTDEPtr->NumberOfTrains - 1))) // last repeat number
8699  {
8700  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetControllerTrainTime(9, Ptr->EventTime, RepNum, IncMins)) + ": Form new service " +
8701  Ptr->NonRepeatingShuttleLinkHeadCode, + " at " + Ptr->LocationName;
8702  PartStr = ControllerCheckNewServiceDepartureTime(3, Ptr, 0, TTDEPtr, Ptr->NonRepeatingShuttleLinkEntryPtr, IncMins, PartStr); //if there is a next service this adds the new service departure time to RetStr
8703  }
8704  else if((Ptr->Command == "Frh-sh") && (RepNum < (TTDEPtr->NumberOfTrains - 1))) // not the last repeat number
8705  {
8706  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetControllerTrainTime(10, Ptr->EventTime, RepNum, IncMins)) + ": Form new service " +
8707  TrainController->GetRepeatHeadCode(48, Ptr->OtherHeadCode, RepNum + 1, IncDig) + " at " + Ptr->LocationName;
8708  // use RepNum+1 because it's the repeat number of the NEXT shuttle service that is relevant
8709  PartStr = ControllerCheckNewServiceDepartureTime(4, Ptr, RepNum + 1, TTDEPtr, Ptr->LinkedTrainEntryPtr, IncMins, PartStr); //if there is a next service this adds the new service departure time to RetStr
8710  }
8711  else if((Ptr->Command == "Frh-sh") && (RepNum >= (TTDEPtr->NumberOfTrains - 1))) // last repeat number
8712  {
8713  PartStr = "Terminate at " + Ptr->LocationName;
8714  }
8715  else if(Ptr->Command == "Frh")
8716  {
8717  PartStr = "Terminate at " + Ptr->LocationName;
8718  }
8719  else if(Ptr->Command == "Fer")
8720  {
8721  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetControllerTrainTime(11, Ptr->EventTime, RepNum, IncMins)) + ": Exit railway" +
8722  TrainController->GetExitLocationAndAt(3, Ptr->ExitList);
8723  }
8724  else if(Ptr->Command == "Fjo")
8725  {
8726  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetControllerTrainTime(12, Ptr->EventTime, RepNum, IncMins)) + ": Join " + TrainController->GetRepeatHeadCode(49,
8727  Ptr->OtherHeadCode, RepNum, IncDig) + " at " + Ptr->LocationName;
8728  }
8729  else if(Ptr->Command == "jbo")
8730  {
8731  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetControllerTrainTime(13, Ptr->EventTime, RepNum, IncMins)) + ": Joined by " + TrainController->GetRepeatHeadCode
8732  (50, Ptr->OtherHeadCode, RepNum, IncDig) + " at " + Ptr->LocationName;
8733  }
8734  else if(Ptr->Command == "fsp")
8735  {
8736  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetControllerTrainTime(14, Ptr->EventTime, RepNum, IncMins)) + ": Front split to " +
8737  TrainController->GetRepeatHeadCode(51, Ptr->OtherHeadCode, RepNum, IncDig) + " at " + Ptr->LocationName;
8738  }
8739  else if(Ptr->Command == "rsp")
8740  {
8741  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetControllerTrainTime(15, Ptr->EventTime, RepNum, IncMins)) + ": Rear split to " +
8742  TrainController->GetRepeatHeadCode(52, Ptr->OtherHeadCode, RepNum, IncDig) + " at " + Ptr->LocationName;
8743  }
8744  else if(Ptr->Command == "cdt")
8745  {
8746  PartStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetControllerTrainTime(16, Ptr->EventTime, RepNum, IncMins)) + ": Change direction at " + Ptr->LocationName;
8747  }
8748  if(RetStr != "")
8749  RetStr = RetStr + '\n' + PartStr;
8750  else
8751  RetStr = PartStr;
8752  Count++;
8753  }
8754  while(Ptr < TTDEPtr->ActionVector.end() && (Count < 33) && ((Ptr->Command == "") || ((Ptr->Command != "") && (Ptr->Command[1] != 'F'))));
8755  // limit of 33 allows a max of 34 entries (may have gone from 32 to 34 because of a TimeTimeLoc), which with track and train status gives
8756  // a max of 48 lines, at 13 pixels each, = 624 pixels & screen height has 641 so will fit comfortably. Also 34 timetable entries is as far
8757  // forward as anyone should wish to see without looking at the full timetable
8758  Utilities->CallLogPop(2072);
8759  return RetStr;
8760 }
8761 
8762 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
8763 
8764 AnsiString TTrainController::ControllerCheckNewServiceDepartureTime(int Caller, TActionVectorIterator Ptr, int RptNum, TTrainDataEntry *TDEPtr, TTrainDataEntry *LinkedTrainDataPtr, int IncrementalMinutes, AnsiString RetStr)
8765 {
8766  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + "," + AnsiString(Ptr - &TDEPtr->ActionVector.front()) + ","
8767  + AnsiString(RptNum) + ",ControllerCheckNewServiceDepartureTime," + TDEPtr->HeadCode);
8768  AnsiString DepTime = "", EventTime = "";
8769  bool CDTFlag = false; //reports if train changes direction before departs
8770  TActionVector NewServiceAV = LinkedTrainDataPtr->ActionVector;
8771  for(TActionVectorIterator AVI = NewServiceAV.begin(); AVI < NewServiceAV.end(); AVI++)
8772  {
8773  if(AVI->Command == "cdt")
8774  {
8775  CDTFlag = !CDTFlag; //toggles flag - allows for there being more than one cdt before departure
8776  continue;
8777  }
8778  if((AVI->Command == "fsp") || (AVI->Command == "rsp"))
8779  {
8780  EventTime = Utilities->Format96HHMM(TrainController->GetControllerTrainTime(21, AVI->EventTime, RptNum, IncrementalMinutes));
8781  RetStr += "\nNew service splits at " + EventTime;
8782  Utilities->CallLogPop(2237);
8783  return RetStr;
8784  }
8785  if(AVI->Command == "jbo")
8786  {
8787  EventTime = Utilities->Format96HHMM(TrainController->GetControllerTrainTime(22, AVI->EventTime, RptNum, IncrementalMinutes));
8788  RetStr += "\nNew service joined by " + AVI->OtherHeadCode + " at " + EventTime;
8789  Utilities->CallLogPop(2238);
8790  return RetStr;
8791  }
8792  if((AVI->FormatType == TimeLoc) && (AVI->DepartureTime > TDateTime(-1))) //departure time set
8793  {
8794  DepTime = Utilities->Format96HHMM(TrainController->GetControllerTrainTime(23, AVI->DepartureTime, RptNum, IncrementalMinutes));
8795  if(CDTFlag)
8796  {
8797  RetStr += "\nNew service changes direction then departs at " + DepTime;
8798  }
8799  else
8800  {
8801  RetStr += "\nNew service departs at " + DepTime;
8802  }
8803  Utilities->CallLogPop(2239);
8804  return RetStr;
8805  }
8806  }
8807  Utilities->CallLogPop(2223);
8808  return RetStr;
8809 }
8810 
8811 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
8812 // $$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$ Start of Timetable Functions $$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$
8813 /*
8814  Note: The terms 'action' and 'entry' have been used freely for individual code lines within services in comments & in variable names, but
8815  for messages and in the manual and help files the term Entry is reserved for a complete service or train (i.e. an entry in the timetable),
8816  and 'event' is reserved for and individual code line within a service. Repeats use the term 'item' if they use any at all.
8817 
8818  In references to 'HeadCode' can have an optional prefix - up to 4 additional characters that can be anything, so long as last 4 digits
8819  represent the headcode. This allows links to be uniquely identified regardless of the headcode - so can have same headcodes as often as
8820  user wishes
8821 
8822  Prior to start time, anything except a line beginning with a time [...leading spaces...] HH:MM is ignored - can be
8823  descriptive text or anything user wishes
8824  A time on its own line [HH:MM], with or without leading spaces, but with anything following it before the CR (which will
8825  be ignored) is taken as the timetable start time.
8826  Thereafter there must be text on every line in the timetable, as the first blank line (or end of file) will be taken as the end of the
8827  timetable. Text can follow the 'end of timetable' blank line if the user wishes.
8828  A line within the timetable beginning with '*', with or without leading spaces, is ignored. Such lines can add text
8829  within the timetable if required.
8830  Timetable entries consist of one line per headcode (i.e. per service, not necessarily per train, as one train can run several different
8831  services)
8832  Each line starts with HeadCode & full train information for a new train (Snt or Snt-sh), or, for a continuing service
8833  (Sfs, Sns, Sns-sh or Sns-fsh), can have (a) Headcode only or (b) HeadCode + Description, nothing else
8834 
8835  All leading & trailing spaces before & after a line or any entry in a line are stripped off - these can be included to make reading a
8836  text timetable file easier
8837 
8838  form:-
8839  HeadCode[;Description (plain text, no commas or semicolons)][;StartSpeed(kph); MaxRunningSpeed(kph); Mass(tonnes, prog converts to kg);
8840  MaxBrakeRate(tonnes force, prog converts to m/s/s); & gross power(kW, prog converts to power at rail in w)
8841  then multiple entries, separated by commas, of the form:-
8842 
8843  HH:MM;Snt;RearStartIdent FrontStartIdent }StartNew }
8844  HH:MM;Snt-sh;RearStartIdent FrontStartIdent;Fsh HeadCode }SNTShuttle }
8845  HH:MM;Sns-sh;Fxx-sh HeadCode;F-nshs HeadCode (non-repeating)}SNSShuttle }
8846 
8847  HH:MM;Command;HeadCode (Sfs Sns jbo fsp rsp Fns Fjo Frh-sh) }TimeCmdHeadCode } Train action entries
8848  HH:MM;F-nshs;NonRepeatingShuttleLinkHeadCode }FNSNonRepeatToShuttle }
8849  HH:MM;Sns-fsh;NonRepeatingShuttleLinkHeadCode }SNSNonRepeatFromShuttle }
8850 
8851  HH:MM;Command (cdt) }TimeCmd }
8852  HH:MM;Location (arr & dep) }TimeLoc }
8853  HH:MM;HH:MM;Location }TimeTimeLoc }
8854  HH:MM;pas;Location }PassTime }
8855  HH:MM;Fns-sh;Snx-sh HeadCode;Sns-fsh HeadCode (non-rep) }FSHNewService }
8856  HH:MM;Fer;set of allowable IDs }ExitRailway }
8857  Command (Frh only) }FinRemHere }
8858 
8859  R;mm;dd;nn. Repeat Repeat entry
8860 
8861  Formats:
8862 
8863  Command only: Frh
8864  Time;Command: cdt
8865  Time;Command;Headcode: Sfs Sns jbo fsp rsp Fns Fjo Frh-sh F-nshs Sns-fsh
8866  Time;Command;2 Element IDs: Snt
8867  Time;Comand;n Element IDs: Fer
8868  Time;Command;rep Headcode;nonrep Headcode: Sns-sh Fns-sh
8869  Time;Command;2 Element IDs;Headcode Snt-sh
8870  Time;Command;Location pas
8871  Time;Location Arr Dep
8872  Time;Time;Location Arr & dep together
8873 
8874  9 Single entries: Snt (located or unlocated); pas; cdt; TimeLoc arr & dep; TimeTimeLoc; Fer; Frh
8875 
8876  9 1x Linked entries: Non-shuttle: fsp or rsp -> Sfs; Fns -> Sns; Fjo -> jbo; times must match, headcodes must match
8877  Shuttle: F-nshs -> Sns-sh: times match, F-nshs HeadCode matches Sns-sh 2nd Headcode;
8878  Fns-sh -> Sns-fsh: Fns-sh time + all repeats = Sns-fsh time, Fns-sh 2nd headcode matches Sns-fsh Headcode
8879 
8880  4 2x Linked entries, all shuttles:
8881 
8882  Frh-sh -> Snt-sh: Frh-sh time = Snt-sh time + 1 repeat while repeating, Frh-sh Headcode = Snt-sh Headcode;
8883  -> Sns-sh: Frh-sh time = Sns-sh time + 1 repeat while repeating, Frh-sh Headcode = Sns-sh 1st Headcode;
8884  -> Remain Here (at finish location after all repeats)
8885  Fns-sh -> Snt-sh: Frh-sh time = Snt-sh time + 1 repeat while repeating, Fns-sh 1st Headcode = Snt-sh Headcode
8886  -> Sns-sh: Frh-sh time = Sns-sh time + 1 repeat while repeating, Fns-sh 1st Headcode = Sns-sh 1st Headcode
8887 
8888  Allowable successors:-
8889 
8890  Successor state Type
8891 
8892  Snt located AtLoc ) Snt AtLoc successors: TimeLoc dep/jbo/fsp/rsp/cdt/Frh/Fns/Fjo/Frh-sh/Fns-sh/F-nshs;
8893  Snt Unlocated Moving ) Snt Moving successors: TimeLoc arr/TimeTimeLoc/pas/Fer;
8894  Sfs AtLoc )
8895  Sns AtLoc ) Start
8896  Sns-fsh AtLoc )
8897  Snt-sh AtLoc )
8898  Sns-sh AtLoc )
8899 
8900  pas Moving )
8901  jbo AtLoc )
8902  fsp AtLoc )
8903  rsp AtLoc ) Intermediate
8904  cdt AtLoc )
8905  TimeLoc arr Moving (bef) )
8906  TimeLoc dep AtLoc (bef) )
8907  TimeTimeLoc Moving )
8908 
8909  Fns Repeat/Nothing)
8910  Fjo Repeat/Nothing)
8911  Frh Repeat/Nothing)
8912  Fer Repeat/Nothing) Finish
8913  Frh-sh Repeat )
8914  Fns-sh Repeat )
8915  F-nshs Nothing )
8916 
8917  Descriptions:
8918  Snt New train
8919  Sfs New service from split
8920  Sns New service from another service
8921  Sns-fsh New non-repeating service from a shuttle service
8922  Snt-sh New shuttle train at a timetabled stop
8923  Sns-sh New shuttle service from a feeder service
8924 
8925  pas Pass
8926  jbo Be joined by another train
8927  fsp Front split
8928  rsp Rear split
8929  cdt Change direction of train
8930  TimeLoc arr Arrival
8931  TimeLoc dep Departure
8932  TimeTimeLoc Arrival and departure
8933 
8934  Fns Finish & form a new service
8935  Fjo Finish & join another train
8936  Frh Finish & remain here
8937  Fer Finish & exit railway
8938  Frh-sh Finish & repeat shuttle, finally remain here
8939  Fns-sh Finish & repeat shuttle, finally form a non-repeating service
8940  F-nshs Finish & form a shuttle feeder service
8941 */
8942 
8943 bool TTrainController::TimetableIntegrityCheck(int Caller, char *FileName, bool GiveMessages, bool CheckLocationsExistInRailway) // true for success
8944 {
8945  // Error messages mainly given in called functions, five are given here - empty file; inability to find a start time; timetable containing
8946  // a line that is too long; timetable containing too few lines; and timetable failed to open.
8947  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",TimetableIntegrityCheck," + AnsiString(FileName));
8948  // new for v0.2b
8949  // compile ActiveTrackElementNameMap
8950  TTrack::TActiveTrackElementNameMapEntry ActiveTrackElementNameMapEntry;
8951 
8952  Track->ActiveTrackElementNameMap.clear();
8953  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < Track->TrackVector.size(); x++)
8954  {
8955  // if((Track->TrackVector.at(x).ActiveTrackElementName != "") && (Track->TrackVector.at(x).TrackType != Continuation))
8956  if((Track->TrackVector.at(x).ActiveTrackElementName != "") && (Track->ContinuationNameMap.find(Track->TrackVector.at(x).ActiveTrackElementName))
8957  == Track->ContinuationNameMap.end())
8958  { // exclude any name that appears in a continuation, error message given in tt validation if try to include such a name in a tt
8959  ActiveTrackElementNameMapEntry.first = Track->TrackVector.at(x).ActiveTrackElementName;
8960  ActiveTrackElementNameMapEntry.second = 0; // this is a dummy value
8961  Track->ActiveTrackElementNameMap.insert(ActiveTrackElementNameMapEntry);
8962  }
8963  }
8964  Track->ActiveTrackElementNameMapCompiledFlag = true;
8965  // end of new section
8966  std::ifstream TTBLFile(FileName, std::ios_base::binary);
8967 
8968  // binary mode so the "\r\n" pairs stay as they are rather than being entered as '\n'
8969  if(TTBLFile.is_open())
8970  {
8971  char *TrainTimetableString = new char[10000];
8972  // enough for over 200 stations, should be adequate!
8973  bool EndOfFile = false;
8974  int Count = 0;
8975  // counts 'relevant' lines, i.e ignores any before the start time on its own line
8976  TTBLFile.getline(TrainTimetableString, 10000, '\0');
8977  // delimiter is '\0' as it's an AnsiString
8978  if(TTBLFile.eof() && (TrainTimetableString[0] == '\0'))
8979  // file empty - stores a null in 1st position if doesn't load any characters
8980  { // may still have eof even if read a line (no CRLF at end), and
8981  // if so need to process it
8982  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Timetable invalid - file empty");
8983  TTBLFile.close();
8984  delete TrainTimetableString;
8985  Utilities->CallLogPop(1611);
8986  return false;
8987  }
8988  AnsiString OneLine(TrainTimetableString);
8989  bool FinalCallFalse = false;
8990  while((Count == 0) && !ProcessOneTimetableLine(5, Count, OneLine, EndOfFile, FinalCallFalse, GiveMessages, CheckLocationsExistInRailway))
8991  // get rid of lines before the start time
8992  {
8993  // ProcessOneTimetableLine returns true for a valid start time, an EndOfFile &/or a blank entry
8994  TTBLFile.getline(TrainTimetableString, 10000, '\0');
8995  if(TTBLFile.eof() && (TrainTimetableString[0] == '\0'))
8996  // stores a null in 1st position if doesn't load any characters
8997  { // may still have eof even if read a line (no CRLF at end), and
8998  // if so need to process it
8999  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Timetable invalid - unable to find a valid start time on its own line");
9000  TTBLFile.close();
9001  delete TrainTimetableString;
9002  Utilities->CallLogPop(772);
9003  return false;
9004  }
9005  OneLine = AnsiString(TrainTimetableString);
9006  }
9007  // here when have accepted the start time
9008  Count++; // increment past the start time
9009  while(!EndOfFile)
9010  {
9011  TTBLFile.getline(TrainTimetableString, 10000, '\0');
9012  // get next line after start time
9013  if(TTBLFile.eof() && (TrainTimetableString[0] == '\0'))
9014  // stores a null in 1st position if doesn't load any characters
9015  { // may still have eof even if read a line (no CRLF at end), and
9016  // if so need to process it
9017  EndOfFile = true;
9018  OneLine = "";
9019  }
9020  else
9021  OneLine = AnsiString(TrainTimetableString);
9022  if(OneLine.Length() > 9999)
9023  {
9024  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Timetable contains a line that is too long - 10,000 or more characters!");
9025  TTBLFile.close();
9026  delete TrainTimetableString;
9027  Utilities->CallLogPop(789);
9028  return false;
9029  }
9030  bool FinalCallFalse = false;
9031  if(!ProcessOneTimetableLine(6, Count, OneLine, EndOfFile, FinalCallFalse, GiveMessages, CheckLocationsExistInRailway))
9032  // false for FinalCall - just checking at this stage
9033  {
9034  TTBLFile.close();
9035  delete TrainTimetableString;
9036  Utilities->CallLogPop(770);
9037  return false;
9038  }
9039  if(EndOfFile && (Count < 2))
9040  // Timetable must contain at least two relevant lines, one for start time and at least one train
9041  {
9042  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Timetable has too few or no relevant entries - must have a start time on its own line and at least one train");
9043  TTBLFile.close();
9044  delete TrainTimetableString;
9045  Utilities->CallLogPop(771);
9046  return false;
9047  }
9048  Count++;
9049  }
9050  delete TrainTimetableString;
9051  TTBLFile.close();
9052  } // if(TTBLFile.is_open())
9053  else
9054  {
9055  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Failed to open timetable file, make sure it's not open in another application");
9056  Utilities->CallLogPop(2154);
9057  return false;
9058  }
9059  Utilities->CallLogPop(753);
9060  return true;
9061 }
9062 
9063 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
9064 
9065 bool TTrainController::ProcessOneTimetableLine(int Caller, int Count, AnsiString OneLine, bool &EndOfFile, bool FinalCall, bool GiveMessages,
9066  bool CheckLocationsExistInRailway) // return true for success
9067 
9068 /* Format:
9069  Prior to start time, anything except a line beginning with a time [...leading spaces...] HH:MM is ignored - can be
9070  descriptive text or anything user wishes
9071  A time on its own line [HH:MM], with or without leading spaces, but with anything following it before the CR (which will
9072  be ignored) is taken as the timetable start time.
9073  Thereafter there must be text on every line in the timetable, as the first blank line (or end of file) will be taken as the end of the
9074  timetable. Text can follow the 'end of timetable' blank line if the user wishes.
9075  A line within the timetable beginning with '*', with or without leading spaces, is ignored. Such lines can add text
9076  within the timetable if required.
9077  Timetable entries consist of one line per headcode (i.e. per service, not necessarily per train, as one train can run several different
9078  services)
9079  Each line starts with HeadCode & full train information for a new train (Snt or Snt-sh), or, for a continuing service
9080  (Sfs, Sns, Sns-sh or Sns-fsh), can have (a) Headcode only or (b) HeadCode + Description, nothing else
9081 
9082  All leading & trailing spaces before & after a line or any entry in a line are stripped off - these can be included to make reading a
9083  text timetable file easier
9084 
9085  form:-
9086  HeadCode[;Description (plain text, no commas or semicolons)][;StartSpeed(kph); MaxRunningSpeed(kph); Mass(tonnes, prog converts to kg);
9087  MaxBrakeRate(tonnes force, prog converts to m/s/s); & gross power(kW, prog converts to power at rail in w)
9088  then multiple entries, separated by commas, of the form:-
9089 
9090  Format FormatType
9091  [W]HH:MM;Command (cdt) }TimeCmd }
9092  [W]HH:MM;Fer;set of allowable IDs }ExitRailway }
9093  [W]HH:MM;pas;Location }PassTime }
9094  [W]HH:MM;Snt;RearStartIdent FrontStartIdent }StartNew }
9095  [W]HH:MM;Command;HeadCode (Sfs Sns jbo fsp rsp Fns Fjo Frh-sh) }TimeCmdHeadCode }
9096  [W]HH:MM;F-nshs;non-repeating headcode }FNSNonRepeatToShuttle }
9097  [W]HH:MM;Sns-fsh;NonRepeatingShuttleLinkHeadCode }SNSNonRepeatFromShuttle } Train action entries
9098  [W]HH:MM;Snt-sh;RearStartIdent FrontStartIdent;FSH HeadCode }SNTShuttle }
9099  [W]HH:MM;Sns-sh;FSH HeadCode;F-nshs HeadCode (non-repeating) }SNSShuttle }
9100  [W]HH:MM;Fns-sh;Details }FSHNewService }
9101  [W]HH:MM;Location (arr & dep) }TimeLoc }
9102  [W]HH:MM;HH:MM;Location }TimeTimeLoc }
9103  Command (Frh only) }FinRemHere }
9104 
9105  R;mm;dd;nn. Repeat Repeat entry
9106 
9107  Two times represent arrival & departure, without any other events between (if arrival and departure times are the same
9108  then departure is 30 sec after arrival), single time represents (a) event time; (b) arrival time if train not already
9109  at location; or (c) departure time if train already at location (including train started at location either as a new
9110  train or as a continuation service train at that location). All lines must contain a start entry and a finish entry,
9111  the finish being the last unless there is a repeat entry. The repeat entry begins with 'R', then the incremental
9112  minutes, incremental train headcode last 2 digits, and number of repeats.
9113 
9114  Shuttle entries are where can loop back to an earlier Snt-sh or Sns-sh entry from a Frh-sh or Fns-sh (Finish Shuttle)
9115  entry. Here the shuttle start can have two entries, one from a set position (Snt-sh, must be located) or from a F-nshs
9116  (Sns-sh) - with NO repeat from this source, and from a Fxx-sh, with repeats. After all shuttle repeats Frh-sh remains
9117  where it is, and Fns-sh links to a new service (via an Sns entry), but there must be no repeats in this new service
9118  (it's for a shuttle train to return to depot at end of services)
9119 
9120  Command/Location & details are as follows:-
9121 
9122  Although headcodes can be duplicated, all joins, splits, new services etc give other headcode from both trains' povs, and
9123  these have to match once only, i.e. if 2E44 splits to 2E45 then it can't split to 2E45 anywhere else, and 2E45 must give
9124  2E44 in its Sfs entry. All these are checked.
9125  ***add note re shuttles & their use of otherheadcodes + non-repeating headcodes***
9126 
9127  Start commands:-
9128  Snt (StartNew) = Start New Train, i.e. create new train, details = rearstartident, space, frontstartident (can't confuse
9129  with loc as a start entry can't have a location as details)
9130  Sfs (TimeCmdHeadCode) = Start From Split, create a new train that has split from another train (& listed in other train's
9131  timetable line), details = other headcode - (can't confuse with loc as start can't be a loc)
9132  Sns (TimeCmdHeadCode) = Start, headcode change from earlier service - no need to create train as already exists, it just
9133  changes its relevant information, details = old headcode (can't confuse with loc as start can't be a loc)
9134  Snt-sh (SNTShuttle) = Start New Train, i.e. create new train, details = rearstartident, space, frontstartident (can't
9135  confuse with loc as start can't be a loc) then the Fsh-XX service headcode (OtherHeadCode can't be same headcode)
9136  Sns-sh (SNSShuttle) = Start, headcode change from earlier service - no need to create train as already exists, it just
9137  changes its relevant information, details = the FSH-XX service headcode (OtherHeadCode, can't be same headcode)
9138  followed by the non-repeating F-nshs headcode (NonRepeatingShuttleLinkHeadCode)
9139  Sns-fsh (SNSNonRepeatFromShuttle) = Start as a non-repeating service from a shuttle service that has finished all its
9140  repeats, details = NonRepeatingShuttleLinkHeadCode for the corresponding shuttle Fns-sh service
9141 
9142  Intermediate commands:-
9143  Time - Location (TimeLoc), can be arrival or departure depending on context
9144  Time Time location (TimeTimeLoc), arrival and departure
9145  Location Name (exactly as used in the railway) in TimeLoc & TimeTimeLoc means that the train is required to stop at the location
9146  pas (PassTime), Time;pas;Location
9147  jbo (TimeCmdHeadCode) = Joined By Other = joined by other train, details = new headcode (await other train - may be delayed). Note that the
9148  joining train's finish details must correspond or the file check will fail
9149  fsp (TimeCmdHeadCode) = Front Split = a new train splits away from front of this train, both trains in same direction, details = new headcode (create
9150  new train - that train's starting information must correspond)
9151  rsp (TimeCmdHeadCode) = Rear Split = a new train splits away from rear of this train, both trains in same direction, details = new headcode (create
9152  new train - that train's starting information must correspond)
9153  cdt (TimeCmd) = Change Direction of Train = change direction, no details needed & no train creation
9154 
9155  Finish commands:-
9156  Fns (TimeCmdHeadCode) = Finish New Service = finish, form new service in same direction, details = new headcode (no train
9157  creation)
9158  F-nshs (FNSShuttle) = Finish New Service (Shuttle) = finish, form new shuttle service in same direction, details =
9159  shuttle headcode (no train creation)
9160  Fjo (TimeCmdHeadCode) = Finish Join Other = finish, join other train (which must be on an adjacent element, either end -
9161  may have to wait for it), details = new headcode (delete train)
9162  Frh (FinRemHere) = Finish Remain Here = stay here indefinitely, no details & no time needed
9163  Fer (ExitRailway) = Finish, exit railway (i.e at a continuation) - details = set of allowable exit IDs
9164  Frh-sh (TimeCmdHeadCode) = Finish then restart as a shuttle using Snt-sh or Sns-sh, when all shuttle repeats done remain
9165  here
9166  Fns-sh (FSHNewService) = Finish then restart as a shuttle using Snt-sh or Sns-sh, when all shuttle repeats done form new
9167  service via Sns-fsh using the NonRepeatingShuttleLinkHeadCode
9168 
9169  Repeat:-
9170  R;mm;dd;nn (Repeat) where mm = minute increment, dd = 2nd 2 headcode digit increment & nn = no. of repeats (no max as can duplicate
9171  headcodes - it is up to user to avoid duplicates if he/she wishes to.
9172 
9173  Checks carried out with error messages in this function:-
9174  At least one comma in a service line (it's based on a .csv file)
9175  No entries following train information;
9176  At least one comma in remainder after train information (i.e at least a start and a finish entry);
9177  SplitEntry returns false in an intermediate entry - message repeats the entry for information;
9178  First entry not a start entry;
9179  Train information incomplete before a start entry;
9180  Entry follows a finish entry but doesn't begin with 'R';
9181  SplitEntry returns false in a finish entry - message repeats the entry for information;
9182  Last action entry isn't a finish entry.
9183 
9184  Function returns false with no message if:-
9185  Timetable start time invalid (no message is given for an invalid time as the line is assumed to be an irrelevant line; if no start
9186  time is found at all then an error message is given in the calling function);
9187  SplitTrainInfo returns false (message given in called function);
9188  SplitRepeat returns false (message given in called function).
9189 */ {
9190  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",ProcessOneTimetableLine," + AnsiString(Count) + "," + OneLine + "," +
9191  AnsiString((short)FinalCall) + "," + AnsiString((short)CheckLocationsExistInRailway));
9192  TTrainDataEntry TempTrainDataEntry;
9193 
9194  EndOfFile = false;
9195  StripSpaces(0, OneLine);
9196  // strip both leading and trailing spaces at ends of line and spaces before and after all commas and
9197  // semicolons within the line
9198  ServiceReference = "";
9199  if(OneLine != "")
9200  {
9201  if(OneLine[1] != '*')
9202  {
9203  int SCPos = OneLine.Pos(';');
9204  if(SCPos == 0)
9205  ServiceReference = OneLine.SubString(1, 8);
9206  else
9207  ServiceReference = OneLine.SubString(1, (SCPos - 1));
9208  }
9209  }
9210  bool AllCommas = true;
9211 
9212  for(int x = 1; x < OneLine.Length() + 1; x++) // check for nothing but commas (may be all commas if created from Excel) or a blank line
9213  {
9214  if(OneLine[x] != ',')
9215  AllCommas = false;
9216  }
9217  if(AllCommas || (OneLine == ""))
9218  {
9219  if(Count > 0)
9220  {
9221  EndOfFile = true;
9222  // returns true for a blank line - treated as end of file
9223  Utilities->CallLogPop(1018);
9224  return true;
9225  }
9226  else // count == 0 so not yet found a start time, no message to be given
9227  {
9228  Utilities->CallLogPop(754);
9229  return false;
9230  }
9231  }
9232  AnsiString First = "", Second = "", Third = "", Fourth = "";
9233  int RearStartOrRepeatMins = 0, FrontStartOrRepeatDigits = 0, NumberOfRepeats = 0;
9234  TDateTime EventTime(0), ArrivalTime(0), DepartureTime(0);
9235  TDateTime StartTime(0);
9236  TExitList ExitList;
9237  bool Warning = false;
9238 
9239  if(Count == 0) // no start time found yet
9240  {
9241 /* dropped at v0.6b
9242  AnyHeadCodeValid = false;
9243  if(OneLine.SubString(6,5) == ";0000")
9244  {
9245  AnyHeadCodeValid = true;
9246  }
9247 */
9248  if(!CheckTimeValidity(0, OneLine, StartTime))
9249  {
9250  // no message is given for an invalid time as it's assumed to be an irrelevant line
9251  // if no start time is found at all then an error message is given in the calling function
9252  // AnyHeadCodeValid = false;
9253  Utilities->CallLogPop(755);
9254  return false;
9255  }
9256  if(FinalCall) // here if start time valid
9257  {
9258  TTClockTime = StartTime;
9259  TimetableStartTime = StartTime;
9260  }
9261  }
9262  else
9263  {
9264  AnsiString TrainInfoStr = "", HeadCode = "", Description = "";
9265  int StartSpeed = 0, MaxRunningSpeed = 0, Mass = 0;
9266  double MaxBrakeRate = 0;
9267  double PowerAtRail = 0;
9268  int SignallerSpeed = 0;
9269  if(OneLine[1] == '*')
9270  {
9271  Utilities->CallLogPop(1581);
9272  return true;
9273  // ignore any line beginning with '*' but return true as there is no error
9274  }
9275  int Pos = OneLine.Pos(',');
9276  if(Pos == 0)
9277  {
9278  int SubStringLength = 20;
9279  if(OneLine.Length() < 20)
9280  SubStringLength = OneLine.Length();
9281  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - entry incomplete: see '" + OneLine.SubString(1, SubStringLength) + "'....");
9282  Utilities->CallLogPop(766);
9283  return false;
9284  }
9285  TrainInfoStr = OneLine.SubString(1, Pos - 1);
9286  if(!SplitTrainInfo(0, TrainInfoStr, HeadCode, Description, StartSpeed, MaxRunningSpeed, Mass, MaxBrakeRate, PowerAtRail, SignallerSpeed,
9287  GiveMessages)) // error messages given in SplitTrainInfo
9288  {
9289  Utilities->CallLogPop(773);
9290  return false;
9291  }
9292  if(FinalCall)
9293  {
9294  // store Train info - conversions done in SplitTrainInfo
9295  // only headcode mandatory for continuing services
9296  TempTrainDataEntry.HeadCode = HeadCode;
9297  TempTrainDataEntry.ServiceReference = HeadCode;
9298  TempTrainDataEntry.Description = Description;
9299  TempTrainDataEntry.StartSpeed = StartSpeed;
9300  TempTrainDataEntry.Mass = Mass;
9301  TempTrainDataEntry.MaxRunningSpeed = MaxRunningSpeed;
9302  TempTrainDataEntry.MaxBrakeRate = MaxBrakeRate;
9303  TempTrainDataEntry.PowerAtRail = PowerAtRail;
9304  TempTrainDataEntry.SignallerSpeed = SignallerSpeed;
9305  TTrainOperatingData TempTrainOperatingData;
9306  TempTrainDataEntry.TrainOperatingDataVector.push_back(TempTrainOperatingData); // push empty vector for now
9307  }
9308  AnsiString NewRemainder = OneLine.SubString(Pos + 1, OneLine.Length() - Pos);
9309  // now left with series of entries for this train, but there may be a string of commas at the end of the line if created by Excel
9310  // so strip them off
9311  while(NewRemainder[NewRemainder.Length()] == ',')
9312  {
9313  if(NewRemainder.Length() > 1)
9314  {
9315  NewRemainder = NewRemainder.SubString(1, NewRemainder.Length() - 1);
9316  }
9317  else
9318  {
9319  NewRemainder = "";
9320  break;
9321  }
9322  }
9323  // check if zero length & fail if so
9324  if(NewRemainder == "")
9325  {
9326  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - no events following train: '" + OneLine + "'");
9327  Utilities->CallLogPop(769);
9328  return false;
9329  }
9330  // now have one more entry than there are commas
9331  int CommaCount = 0;
9332  for(int x = 1; x < NewRemainder.Length() + 1; x++)
9333  {
9334  if(NewRemainder[x] == ',')
9335  CommaCount++;
9336  } // must have at least 1 comma, for start & finish entries, unless train is entered under signaller control
9337  if(CommaCount == 0)
9338  {
9339  if((NewRemainder.SubString(7, 3) != "Snt") || (NewRemainder[NewRemainder.Length()] != 'S'))
9340  {
9341  int SubStringLength = 20;
9342  if(OneLine.Length() < 20)
9343  SubStringLength = OneLine.Length();
9344  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages,
9345  "Error in timetable - must have at least a start and a finish event for a train that is not started under signaller control - see line beginning: '" +
9346  OneLine.SubString(1, SubStringLength) + "'....");
9347  Utilities->CallLogPop(783);
9348  return false;
9349  }
9350  }
9351  AnsiString OneEntry = "";
9352  TTimetableFormatType FormatType;
9353  TTimetableSequenceType SequenceType;
9354  TTimetableLocationType LocationType;
9355  TTimetableShuttleLinkType ShuttleLinkType;
9356  bool FinishFlag = false;
9357  for(int x = 0; x < CommaCount + 1; x++)
9358  {
9359  if((CommaCount == 0) || (x < CommaCount))
9360  // i.e. train entered under signaller control with no repeats, or entry is not the last,
9361  // in which case there's a comma & finish element or repeat still to come this entry could
9362  // be a finish but can't be a repeat
9363  {
9364  if(CommaCount == 0)
9365  {
9366  OneEntry = NewRemainder;
9367  NewRemainder = "";
9368  }
9369  else
9370  {
9371  Pos = NewRemainder.Pos(',');
9372  OneEntry = NewRemainder.SubString(1, Pos - 1);
9373  NewRemainder = NewRemainder.SubString(Pos + 1, NewRemainder.Length() - Pos);
9374  }
9375  First = "";
9376  Second = "";
9377  Third = "";
9378  Fourth = "";
9379  RearStartOrRepeatMins = 0;
9380  FrontStartOrRepeatDigits = 0;
9381  NumberOfRepeats = 0;
9382  if(!SplitEntry(0, OneEntry, GiveMessages, CheckLocationsExistInRailway, First, Second, Third, Fourth, RearStartOrRepeatMins,
9383  FrontStartOrRepeatDigits, FormatType, LocationType, SequenceType, ShuttleLinkType, ExitList, Warning))
9384  {
9385  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - Event: '" + OneEntry + "'");
9386  Utilities->CallLogPop(756);
9387  return false;
9388  }
9389  // check if warning for Frh or Fjo & reject
9390  if(Warning && (Second == "Frh"))
9391  {
9392  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in line - '" + OneEntry + "': warnings cannot be given for 'Frh' events");
9393  Utilities->CallLogPop(1793);
9394  return false;
9395  }
9396  if(Warning && (Second == "Fjo"))
9397  {
9398  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in line - '" + OneEntry +
9399  "': warnings cannot be given for 'Fjo' events, for a train join warning add a 'W' prefix to the 'jbo' event");
9400  Utilities->CallLogPop(1794);
9401  return false;
9402  }
9403  if(x == 0) // should be start event
9404  {
9405  if(SequenceType != Start)
9406  {
9407  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - First event not a start event: '" + OneEntry + "'");
9408  Utilities->CallLogPop(784);
9409  return false;
9410  }
9411  if((Second == "Snt") && (Fourth == 'S') && (NewRemainder != ""))
9412  {
9413  if(NewRemainder[1] != 'R')
9414  {
9415  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages,
9416  "Error in timetable - the only event that can follow a train created under signaller control is a repeat, see '" +
9417  OneEntry + "'");
9418  Utilities->CallLogPop(787);
9419  return false;
9420  }
9421  }
9422  if((Second == "Snt") || (Second == "Snt-sh"))
9423  // need full train information including non-default values for at least HeadCode, Description,
9424  // MaxRunningSpeed, Mass, MaxBrakeRate, & PowerAtRail
9425  {
9426  if((HeadCode == "") || (Description == "") || (MaxRunningSpeed == 0) || (Mass == 0) || (MaxBrakeRate == 0)) // ||
9427  // (PowerAtRail == 0)) allowed 0 for power at v2.4.0
9428  {
9429  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - train information incomplete before 'Snt' or 'Snt-sh' start event: '" +
9430  OneEntry + "'");
9431  Utilities->CallLogPop(1783);
9432  return false;
9433  }
9434  }
9435  if((Second == "Sfs") || (Second == "Sns") || (Second == "Sns-sh") || (Second == "Sns-fsh"))
9436  // service continuation - need at least non-default value for HeadCode
9437  {
9438  if(HeadCode == "")
9439  {
9440  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - headcode missing before 'Sfs', 'Sns', 'Sns-sh' or 'Sns-fsh' start event: '" +
9441  OneEntry + "'");
9442  Utilities->CallLogPop(788);
9443  return false;
9444  }
9445  if((StartSpeed != 0) || (MaxRunningSpeed != 0) || (Mass != 0) || (MaxBrakeRate != 0) || (PowerAtRail != 0))
9446  {
9447  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages,
9448  "Error in timetable - information additional to a headcode & optional description given before 'Sfs', 'Sns', 'Sns-sh' or 'Sns-fsh' start event: '" +
9449  OneEntry + "'");
9450  Utilities->CallLogPop(843);
9451  return false;
9452  }
9453  }
9454  }
9455  if(SequenceType == Finish)
9456  {
9457  FinishFlag = true;
9458  // marker for only permitted additional entry being a repeat, only needed if the
9459  // finish entry is not the last entry
9460  }
9461  if(FinalCall)
9462  {
9463  // interpret & add to ActionVector
9464  TDateTime TempTime;
9465  TActionVectorEntry ActionVectorEntry;
9466  ActionVectorEntry.FormatType = FormatType;
9467  ActionVectorEntry.LocationType = LocationType;
9468  ActionVectorEntry.SequenceType = SequenceType;
9469  ActionVectorEntry.ShuttleLinkType = ShuttleLinkType;
9470  ActionVectorEntry.Warning = Warning;
9471  if(FormatType == TimeLoc)
9472  {
9473  if(CheckTimeValidity(1, First, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime))
9474  {;
9475  } // these will all be true as final call
9476  ActionVectorEntry.LocationName = Second;
9477  }
9478  else if(FormatType == PassTime) // new
9479  {
9480  if(CheckTimeValidity(17, First, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime))
9481  {;
9482  }
9483  ActionVectorEntry.Command = Second;
9484  ActionVectorEntry.LocationName = Third;
9485  }
9486  else if(FormatType == TimeTimeLoc)
9487  {
9488  if(CheckTimeValidity(2, First, ActionVectorEntry.ArrivalTime))
9489  {;
9490  }
9491  if(CheckTimeValidity(3, Second, ActionVectorEntry.DepartureTime))
9492  {;
9493  }
9494  ActionVectorEntry.LocationName = Third;
9495  }
9496  else if(FormatType == TimeCmd)
9497  {
9498  if(CheckTimeValidity(4, First, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime))
9499  {;
9500  }
9501  ActionVectorEntry.Command = Second;
9502  }
9503  else if(FormatType == ExitRailway)
9504  {
9505  if(CheckTimeValidity(18, First, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime))
9506  {;
9507  }
9508  ActionVectorEntry.Command = Second;
9509  ActionVectorEntry.ExitList = ExitList;
9510  }
9511  else if(FormatType == StartNew)
9512  {
9513  if(CheckTimeValidity(5, First, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime))
9514  {;
9515  }
9516  ActionVectorEntry.Command = Second;
9517  ActionVectorEntry.RearStartOrRepeatMins = RearStartOrRepeatMins;
9518  ActionVectorEntry.FrontStartOrRepeatDigits = FrontStartOrRepeatDigits;
9519  if(Fourth == 'S')
9520  ActionVectorEntry.SignallerControl = true;
9521  }
9522  else if(FormatType == SNTShuttle)
9523  {
9524  if(CheckTimeValidity(6, First, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime))
9525  {;
9526  }
9527  ActionVectorEntry.Command = Second;
9528  ActionVectorEntry.RearStartOrRepeatMins = RearStartOrRepeatMins;
9529  ActionVectorEntry.FrontStartOrRepeatDigits = FrontStartOrRepeatDigits;
9530  ActionVectorEntry.OtherHeadCode = Fourth;
9531  }
9532  else if(FormatType == SNSShuttle)
9533  {
9534  if(CheckTimeValidity(7, First, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime))
9535  {;
9536  }
9537  ActionVectorEntry.Command = Second;
9538  ActionVectorEntry.OtherHeadCode = Third;
9539  ActionVectorEntry.NonRepeatingShuttleLinkHeadCode = Fourth;
9540  }
9541  else if(FormatType == TimeCmdHeadCode)
9542  {
9543  if(CheckTimeValidity(8, First, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime))
9544  {;
9545  }
9546  ActionVectorEntry.Command = Second;
9547  ActionVectorEntry.OtherHeadCode = Third;
9548  }
9549  else if((FormatType == FNSNonRepeatToShuttle) || (FormatType == SNSNonRepeatFromShuttle))
9550  {
9551  if(CheckTimeValidity(9, First, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime))
9552  {;
9553  }
9554  ActionVectorEntry.Command = Second;
9555  ActionVectorEntry.NonRepeatingShuttleLinkHeadCode = Third;
9556  }
9557  else if(FormatType == FSHNewService)
9558  {
9559  if(CheckTimeValidity(10, First, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime))
9560  {;
9561  }
9562  ActionVectorEntry.Command = Second;
9563  ActionVectorEntry.OtherHeadCode = Third;
9564  ActionVectorEntry.NonRepeatingShuttleLinkHeadCode = Fourth;
9565  }
9566  else if(FormatType == FinRemHere)
9567  {
9568  ActionVectorEntry.Command = Second;
9569  }
9570  TempTrainDataEntry.ActionVector.push_back(ActionVectorEntry);
9571  }
9572  }
9573  else // last entry, & not entered under signaller control with no repeats, i.e. could be finish or repeat
9574  {
9575  OneEntry = NewRemainder;
9576  First = "";
9577  Second = "";
9578  Third = "";
9579  Fourth = "";
9580  RearStartOrRepeatMins = 0;
9581  FrontStartOrRepeatDigits = 0;
9582  NumberOfRepeats = 0;
9583  if((FinishFlag) && (OneEntry[1] != 'R'))
9584  // already had a finish entry
9585  {
9586  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - Last event = '" + OneEntry + "'. An earlier finish event has been found with something other than a repeat following it - only a repeat can follow a finish event.");
9587  Utilities->CallLogPop(79);
9588  return false;
9589  }
9590  if(OneEntry[1] != 'R') // must be finish
9591  {
9592  if(!SplitEntry(1, OneEntry, GiveMessages, CheckLocationsExistInRailway, First, Second, Third, Fourth, RearStartOrRepeatMins,
9593  FrontStartOrRepeatDigits, FormatType, LocationType, SequenceType, ShuttleLinkType, ExitList, Warning))
9594  {
9595  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - Event: '" + OneEntry + "'");
9596  Utilities->CallLogPop(757);
9597  return false;
9598  }
9599  if(SequenceType != Finish)
9600  {
9601  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - last event should be a finish: '" + OneEntry + "'");
9602  Utilities->CallLogPop(785);
9603  return false;
9604  }
9605  if(FinalCall)
9606  {
9607  // interpret & add to ActionVector
9608  TDateTime TempTime;
9609  TActionVectorEntry ActionVectorEntry;
9610  ActionVectorEntry.FormatType = FormatType;
9611  ActionVectorEntry.LocationType = LocationType;
9612  ActionVectorEntry.SequenceType = SequenceType;
9613  ActionVectorEntry.ShuttleLinkType = ShuttleLinkType;
9614  ActionVectorEntry.Warning = Warning;
9615  if(FormatType == TimeCmd)
9616  {
9617  if(CheckTimeValidity(11, First, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime))
9618  {;
9619  }
9620  ActionVectorEntry.Command = Second;
9621  }
9622  else if(FormatType == TimeCmdHeadCode)
9623  {
9624  if(CheckTimeValidity(12, First, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime))
9625  {;
9626  }
9627  ActionVectorEntry.Command = Second;
9628  ActionVectorEntry.OtherHeadCode = Third;
9629  }
9630  else if(FormatType == FNSNonRepeatToShuttle)
9631  {
9632  if(CheckTimeValidity(13, First, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime))
9633  {;
9634  }
9635  ActionVectorEntry.Command = Second;
9636  ActionVectorEntry.NonRepeatingShuttleLinkHeadCode = Third;
9637  }
9638  else if(FormatType == FSHNewService)
9639  {
9640  if(CheckTimeValidity(14, First, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime))
9641  {;
9642  }
9643  ActionVectorEntry.Command = Second;
9644  ActionVectorEntry.OtherHeadCode = Third;
9645  ActionVectorEntry.NonRepeatingShuttleLinkHeadCode = Fourth;
9646  }
9647  else if(FormatType == ExitRailway)
9648  {
9649  if(CheckTimeValidity(19, First, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime))
9650  {;
9651  }
9652  ActionVectorEntry.Command = Second;
9653  ActionVectorEntry.ExitList = ExitList;
9654  }
9655  else if(FormatType == FinRemHere)
9656  {
9657  ActionVectorEntry.Command = Second;
9658  }
9659  TempTrainDataEntry.ActionVector.push_back(ActionVectorEntry);
9660  }
9661  }
9662  else // repeat
9663  {
9664  if(!SplitRepeat(0, OneEntry, RearStartOrRepeatMins, FrontStartOrRepeatDigits, NumberOfRepeats, GiveMessages))
9665  {
9666  Utilities->CallLogPop(786);
9667  // error messages given in SplitRepeat
9668  return false;
9669  }
9670  if(FinalCall)
9671  {
9672  TActionVectorEntry ActionVectorEntry;
9673  ActionVectorEntry.FormatType = Repeat;
9674  ActionVectorEntry.LocationType = LocTypeForRepeatEntry;
9675  ActionVectorEntry.SequenceType = SequTypeForRepeatEntry;
9676  ActionVectorEntry.ShuttleLinkType = ShuttleLinkTypeForRepeatEntry;
9677  ActionVectorEntry.RearStartOrRepeatMins = RearStartOrRepeatMins;
9678  ActionVectorEntry.FrontStartOrRepeatDigits = FrontStartOrRepeatDigits;
9679  ActionVectorEntry.NumberOfRepeats = NumberOfRepeats;
9680  TempTrainDataEntry.ActionVector.push_back(ActionVectorEntry);
9681  }
9682  }
9683  }
9684  }
9685  if(FinalCall)
9686  {
9687  TrainDataVector.push_back(TempTrainDataEntry);
9688  }
9689  }
9690  Utilities->CallLogPop(80);
9691  return true;
9692 }

9694 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
9695 
9696 bool TTrainController::Last2CharactersBothDigits(int Caller, AnsiString HeadCode)
9697 {
9698  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",Last2CharactersBothDigits," + HeadCode);
9699  if((HeadCode[HeadCode.Length() - 1] < '0') || (HeadCode[HeadCode.Length() - 1] > '9'))
9700  {
9701  Utilities->CallLogPop(1890);
9702  return false;
9703  }
9704  if((HeadCode[HeadCode.Length()] < '0') || (HeadCode[HeadCode.Length()] > '9'))
9705  {
9706  Utilities->CallLogPop(1891);
9707  return false;
9708  }
9709  Utilities->CallLogPop(1892);
9710  return true;
9711 }
9712 
9713 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
9714 
9715 bool TTrainController::CheckTimeValidity(int Caller, AnsiString TimeStr, TDateTime &Time)
9716  // 1st 5 chars must be HH:MM, anything else will be ignored
9717 {
9718  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",CheckTimeValidity," + TimeStr);
9719  if(TimeStr.Length() < 5)
9720  {
9721  Utilities->CallLogPop(926);
9722  return false;
9723  }
9724  if((TimeStr[1] < '0') || (TimeStr[1] > '9'))
9725  {
9726  Utilities->CallLogPop(927);
9727  return false;
9728  }
9729  if((TimeStr[2] < '0') || (TimeStr[2] > '9'))
9730  {
9731  Utilities->CallLogPop(928);
9732  return false;
9733  }
9734  if(TimeStr[3] != ':')
9735  {
9736  Utilities->CallLogPop(929);
9737  return false;
9738  }
9739  if((TimeStr[4] < '0') || (TimeStr[4] > '5'))
9740  {
9741  Utilities->CallLogPop(930);
9742  return false;
9743  }
9744  if((TimeStr[5] < '0') || (TimeStr[5] > '9'))
9745  {
9746  Utilities->CallLogPop(931);
9747  return false;
9748  }
9749  while(TimeStr.Length() > 5)
9750  TimeStr = TimeStr.SubString(1, TimeStr.Length() - 1);
9751  double WholeHours = (AnsiString(TimeStr[1]) + AnsiString(TimeStr[2])).ToDouble();
9752  double FracHour = ((AnsiString(TimeStr[4]) + AnsiString(TimeStr[5])).ToDouble()) / 60.0;
9753 
9754  if((WholeHours + FracHour) >= 95.98334)
9755  {
9756  Utilities->CallLogPop(1817);
9757  return false; // > 95h 59m
9758  }
9759  Time = TDateTime((WholeHours + FracHour) / 24);
9760  Utilities->CallLogPop(932);
9761  return true;
9762 }
9763 
9764 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
9765 
9766 bool TTrainController::SplitEntry(int Caller, AnsiString OneEntry, bool GiveMessages, bool CheckLocationsExistInRailway, AnsiString &First, AnsiString &Second,
9767  AnsiString &Third, AnsiString &Fourth, int &RearStartOrRepeatMins, int &FrontStartOrRepeatDigits, TTimetableFormatType &FormatType,
9768  TTimetableLocationType &LocationType, TTimetableSequenceType &SequenceType, TTimetableShuttleLinkType &ShuttleLinkType, TExitList &ExitList, bool &Warning)
9769 /* This is a train action entry from a single line of the timetable, i.e. not train information and not a repeat entry.
9770  Return false for failure.
9771  See description above under ProcessOneTimetableLinefor details of train action entries
9772  NB all types set except LocationType for Sns as may be located or not
9773 */ {
9774  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",SplitEntry," + OneEntry);
9775  Warning = false;
9776  TDateTime TempTime;
9777 
9778  if(OneEntry.Length() > 0)
9779  {
9780  if(OneEntry[1] == 'W') // warning
9781  {
9782  Warning = true;
9783  OneEntry = OneEntry.SubString(2, OneEntry.Length() - 1);
9784  // strip it off
9785  }
9786  }
9787  if(OneEntry == "Frh")
9788  {
9789  FormatType = FinRemHere;
9790  SequenceType = Finish;
9791  LocationType = AtLocation;
9792  ShuttleLinkType = NotAShuttleLink;
9793  Second = "Frh";
9794  Utilities->CallLogPop(1016);
9795  return true;
9796  }
9797  if(OneEntry.Length() < 7)
9798  {
9799  Utilities->CallLogPop(907);
9800  return false; // 'HH:MM;' + at least a one-letter location name
9801  }
9802  int Pos = OneEntry.Pos(';'); // first segment delimiter
9803 
9804  if(Pos != 6)
9805  {
9806  Utilities->CallLogPop(908);
9807  return false;
9808  // no delimiter or delimiter not in position 6, has to be a time so fail
9809  }
9810  First = OneEntry.SubString(1, 5); // has to be a time
9811  if(!CheckTimeValidity(16, First, TempTime))
9812  {
9813  Utilities->CallLogPop(909);
9814  return false;
9815  }
9816  AnsiString Remainder = OneEntry.SubString(Pos + 1, OneEntry.Length() - Pos);
9817 
9818  if((Remainder[1] >= '0') && (Remainder[1] <= '9'))
9819  // next segment is a time so this is a TimeTimeLoc & 3rd seg has to be a location to be valid
9820  {
9821  if(Remainder.Length() < 7)
9822  {
9823  Utilities->CallLogPop(910);
9824  return false; // 'HH:MM;' + at least a one-letter location name
9825  }
9826  Pos = Remainder.Pos(';'); // second segment delimiter
9827  if(Pos == 0)
9828  {
9829  Utilities->CallLogPop(911);
9830  return false;
9831  // no delimiter, has to be one between departure time & location
9832  }
9833  Second = Remainder.SubString(1, 5); // has to be a time
9834  if(!CheckTimeValidity(15, Second, TempTime))
9835  {
9836  Utilities->CallLogPop(912);
9837  return false;
9838  }
9839  Third = Remainder.SubString(Pos + 1, Remainder.Length() - Pos);
9840  if(!CheckLocationValidity(0, Third, GiveMessages, CheckLocationsExistInRailway))
9841  {
9842  Utilities->CallLogPop(913);
9843  return false;
9844  }
9845  FormatType = TimeTimeLoc;
9846  SequenceType = Intermediate;
9847  LocationType = AtLocation;
9848  ShuttleLinkType = NotAShuttleLink;
9849  Utilities->CallLogPop(914);
9850  return true;
9851  }
9852  Pos = Remainder.Pos(';'); // second segment delimiter
9853  if(Pos == 0) // no third segment so second must be a location, or cdt
9854  {
9855  Second = Remainder;
9856  if(Second == "cdt")
9857  {
9858  FormatType = TimeCmd;
9859  ShuttleLinkType = NotAShuttleLink;
9860  LocationType = AtLocation;
9861  SequenceType = Intermediate;
9862  Utilities->CallLogPop(915);
9863  return true;
9864  }
9865  if(!CheckLocationValidity(1, Second, GiveMessages, CheckLocationsExistInRailway))
9866  {
9867  Utilities->CallLogPop(916);
9868  return false;
9869  }
9870  else
9871  {
9872  FormatType = TimeLoc;
9873  LocationType = AtLocation;
9874  SequenceType = Intermediate;
9875  ShuttleLinkType = NotAShuttleLink;
9876  Utilities->CallLogPop(917);
9877  return true;
9878  }
9879  }
9880  // here if second segment is a command, with a third & maybe fourth segments as details
9881  if((Pos != 4) && (Pos != 7) && (Pos != 8))
9882  {
9883  Utilities->CallLogPop(918);
9884  return false;
9885  // no third segement or not in position 4 or 7, & should be since all commands are 3, 6 or 7 letters
9886  }
9887  Second = Remainder.SubString(1, Pos - 1); // command
9888 
9889  Remainder = Remainder.SubString(Pos + 1, Remainder.Length() - Pos);
9890  // details
9891  Pos = Remainder.Pos(';'); // third segment delimiter
9892  if(Pos == 0)
9893  Third = Remainder;
9894  else
9895  {
9896  Third = Remainder.SubString(1, Pos - 1);
9897  Fourth = Remainder.SubString(Pos + 1, Remainder.Length() - Pos);
9898  }
9899  if((Second == "Snt") || (Second == "Snt-sh"))
9900  // third has to be 2 element idents with a space between
9901  {
9902  int SpacePos = Third.Pos(' ');
9903  if(SpacePos == 0)
9904  {
9905  Utilities->CallLogPop(919);
9906  return false; // no space
9907  }
9908  AnsiString RearStartStr = Third.SubString(1, SpacePos - 1);
9909  AnsiString FrontStartStr = Third.SubString(SpacePos + 1, Third.Length() - SpacePos);
9910  // int RearPosition=0, FrontPosition=0, RearExitPos=0;
9911  if(CheckLocationsExistInRailway)
9912  {
9913  if(!CheckStartPositionValidity(0, RearStartStr, FrontStartStr, GiveMessages))
9914  {
9915  Utilities->CallLogPop(920);
9916  return false;
9917  }
9918  RearStartOrRepeatMins = Track->GetTrackVectorPositionFromString(3, RearStartStr, GiveMessages);
9919  FrontStartOrRepeatDigits = Track->GetTrackVectorPositionFromString(4, FrontStartStr, GiveMessages);
9920  }
9921  if(Second == "Snt")
9922  {
9923  FormatType = StartNew;
9924  SequenceType = Start;
9925  LocationType = NoLocation;
9926  // can't be set until know whether located or not - done in SecondPassActions
9927  ShuttleLinkType = NotAShuttleLink;
9928  }
9929  else // Snt-sh
9930  {
9931  FormatType = SNTShuttle;
9932  LocationType = AtLocation;
9933  SequenceType = Start;
9934  ShuttleLinkType = ShuttleLink;
9935  if(!CheckHeadCodeValidity(0, GiveMessages, Fourth))
9936  {
9937  Utilities->CallLogPop(1038);
9938  return false;
9939  }
9940  }
9941  Utilities->CallLogPop(921);
9942  return true;
9943  }
9944 
9945  if(Second == "Sns-sh") // third & fourth have to be headcodes
9946  {
9947  FormatType = SNSShuttle;
9948  LocationType = AtLocation;
9949  SequenceType = Start;
9950  ShuttleLinkType = ShuttleLink;
9951  if(!CheckHeadCodeValidity(1, GiveMessages, Third))
9952  {
9953  Utilities->CallLogPop(1039);
9954  return false;
9955  }
9956  if(!CheckHeadCodeValidity(2, GiveMessages, Fourth))
9957  {
9958  Utilities->CallLogPop(1040);
9959  return false;
9960  }
9961  Utilities->CallLogPop(1041);
9962  return true;
9963  }
9964 
9965  if(Second == "F-nshs")
9966  {
9967  FormatType = FNSNonRepeatToShuttle;
9968  LocationType = AtLocation;
9969  SequenceType = Finish;
9970  ShuttleLinkType = ShuttleLink;
9971  if(!CheckHeadCodeValidity(3, GiveMessages, Third))
9972  {
9973  Utilities->CallLogPop(1047);
9974  return false;
9975  }
9976  Utilities->CallLogPop(1048);
9977  return true;
9978  }
9979 
9980  if(Second == "Sns-fsh")
9981  {
9982  FormatType = SNSNonRepeatFromShuttle;
9983  LocationType = AtLocation;
9984  SequenceType = Start;
9985  ShuttleLinkType = ShuttleLink;
9986  if(!CheckHeadCodeValidity(4, GiveMessages, Third))
9987  {
9988  Utilities->CallLogPop(1098);
9989  return false;
9990  }
9991  Utilities->CallLogPop(1099);
9992  return true;
9993  }
9994 
9995  if(Second == "Fns-sh") // third & fourth have to be headcodes
9996  {
9997  FormatType = FSHNewService;
9998  LocationType = AtLocation;
9999  SequenceType = Finish;
10000  ShuttleLinkType = ShuttleLink;
10001  if(!CheckHeadCodeValidity(5, GiveMessages, Third))
10002  {
10003  Utilities->CallLogPop(1050);
10004  return false;
10005  }
10006  if(!CheckHeadCodeValidity(6, GiveMessages, Fourth))
10007  {
10008  Utilities->CallLogPop(1051);
10009  return false;
10010  }
10011  Utilities->CallLogPop(1052);
10012  return true;
10013  }
10014 
10015  // new segment for 'pas'
10016  if(Second == "pas") // third has to be a location
10017  {
10018  FormatType = PassTime;
10019  LocationType = EnRoute;
10020  SequenceType = Intermediate;
10021  ShuttleLinkType = NotAShuttleLink;
10022  if(!CheckLocationValidity(2, Third, GiveMessages, CheckLocationsExistInRailway))
10023  {
10024  Utilities->CallLogPop(1515);
10025  return false;
10026  }
10027  Utilities->CallLogPop(1516);
10028  return true;
10029  }
10030 
10031  // new segment for revised 'Fer'
10032  if(Second == "Fer")
10033  // third has to be a set of IDs separated by spaces, and at least 1
10034  {
10035  FormatType = ExitRailway;
10036  LocationType = EnRoute;
10037  SequenceType = Finish;
10038  ShuttleLinkType = NotAShuttleLink;
10039  if(CheckLocationsExistInRailway)
10040  {
10041  if(!CheckAndPopulateListOfIDs(0, Third, ExitList, GiveMessages))
10042  {
10043  Utilities->CallLogPop(1519);
10044  return false;
10045  }
10046  }
10047  Utilities->CallLogPop(1520);
10048  return true;
10049  }
10050 
10051  // all remainder must be TimeCmdHeadCode types to be valid
10052  if((Second != "Fns") && (Second != "Fjo") && (Second != "jbo") && (Second != "fsp") && (Second != "rsp") && (Second != "Sfs") && (Second != "Sns") &&
10053  (Second != "Frh-sh"))
10054  {
10055  Utilities->CallLogPop(922);
10056  return false; // all TimeCmdHeadCode types
10057  }
10058 
10059  if(!CheckHeadCodeValidity(7, GiveMessages, Third))
10060  {
10061  Utilities->CallLogPop(923);
10062  return false;
10063  }
10064  FormatType = TimeCmdHeadCode;
10065  LocationType = AtLocation;
10066  if(Second == "Frh-sh")
10067  ShuttleLinkType = ShuttleLink;
10068  else
10069  ShuttleLinkType = NotAShuttleLink;
10070  if((Second == "Fns") || (Second == "Fjo") || (Second == "Frh-sh"))
10071  {
10072  SequenceType = Finish;
10073  }
10074  if((Second == "jbo") || (Second == "fsp") || (Second == "rsp"))
10075  {
10076  SequenceType = Intermediate;
10077  }
10078  if((Second == "Sfs") || (Second == "Sns"))
10079  {
10080  SequenceType = Start;
10081  }
10082  Utilities->CallLogPop(924);
10083  return true;
10084 }
10085 
10086 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
10087 
10088 bool TTrainController::CheckLocationValidity(int Caller, AnsiString LocStr, bool GiveMessages, bool CheckLocationsExistInRailway)
10089 {
10090  // check that the location name exists in the railway (only if CheckLocationsExistInRailway is true), doesn't begin with a number
10091  // and contains no special characters
10092  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",CheckLocationValidity," + LocStr);
10093  if(LocStr == "")
10094  {
10095  Utilities->CallLogPop(1353);
10096  return false; // has to have at least one character
10097  }
10098  if((LocStr[1] >= '0') && (LocStr[1] <= '9'))
10099  {
10100  Utilities->CallLogPop(1354);
10101  return false; // can't begin with a number
10102  }
10103  for(int x = 1; x < LocStr.Length() + 1; x++)
10104  {
10105  if(LocStr[x] < ' ')
10106  {
10107  Utilities->CallLogPop(1355);
10108  return false; // contains a special character
10109  }
10110  if(LocStr[x] > 'z')
10111  {
10112  Utilities->CallLogPop(1356);
10113  return false; // contains a character outside the standard ASCII set
10114  }
10115  }
10116  // check exists in railway location list if CheckLocationsExistInRailway is true
10117  if(CheckLocationsExistInRailway)
10118  {
10119  if(!Track->TimetabledLocationNameAllocated(3, LocStr))
10120  {
10121  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Location name '" + LocStr +
10122  "' appears in the timetable but is not a valid name. To be valid the name must apply to one or more platforms (not concourses on their own), or to track at a blue non-station named location other than a continuation.");
10123  Utilities->CallLogPop(1357);
10124  return false;
10125  }
10126  }
10127  Utilities->CallLogPop(1358);
10128  return true;
10129 }
10130 
10131 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
10132 
10133 bool TTrainController::CheckHeadCodeValidity(int Caller, bool GiveMessages, AnsiString HeadCode)
10134 {
10135  // if(!AnyHeadCodeValid) up to 8 characters total & last 4 characters must be NLNN where N = number and L = capital or small letter
10136  // if(AnyHeadCodeValid) up to 8 characters total, last 2 chars must be digits & last but 2 can be any alphanumeric, upper or lower case
10137  // NOTE: As of v0.6b AnyHeadCodeValid dropped, all headcodes are unrestricted
10138  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + "," + AnsiString((short)GiveMessages) + ",CheckHeadCodeValidity," +
10139  HeadCode);
10140  if((HeadCode.Length() < 4) || (HeadCode.Length() > 8))
10141  {
10142  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Headcode error in '" + HeadCode +
10143  "', length must be between 4 and 8 characters, and last 4 must be a legitimate headcode. This error can also be caused by omitting a service reference after Snt-sh, Sns-sh, Fns-sh or Frh-sh");
10144  Utilities->CallLogPop(1359);
10145  return false;
10146  }
10147  // firstly allow any printable character (ASCII >= CHAR(32) & <= CHAR(126)), as these allowed in 1st 4 characters
10148  for(int x = 1; x < (HeadCode.Length() + 1); x++)
10149  {
10150  if((HeadCode[x] < ' ') || (HeadCode[x] > '~'))
10151  {
10152  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Non-printable character in headcode '" + HeadCode + "'");
10153  Utilities->CallLogPop(1895);
10154  return false;
10155  }
10156  }
10157  // secondly ensure the true Headcode only has letters or digits
10158  for(int x = 3; x >= 0; x--)
10159  {
10160  if(((HeadCode[HeadCode.Length() - x] < 'A') || (HeadCode[HeadCode.Length() - x] > 'Z')) && ((HeadCode[HeadCode.Length() - x] < 'a') ||
10161  (HeadCode[HeadCode.Length() - x] > 'z')) && ((HeadCode[HeadCode.Length() - x] < '0') || (HeadCode[HeadCode.Length() - x] > '9')))
10162  {
10163  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Headcode error in '" + HeadCode + "', headcode must consist of letters and digits only");
10164  Utilities->CallLogPop(1790);
10165  return false;
10166  }
10167  }
10168  Utilities->CallLogPop(1364);
10169  return true;
10170 }
10171 
10172 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
10173 
10174 bool TTrainController::CheckAndPopulateListOfIDs(int Caller, AnsiString IDSet, TExitList &ExitList, bool GiveMessages)
10175  // set of legitimate track element IDs, separated by spaces, and at least 1 present
10176 {
10177  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",CheckSetOfIDs," + IDSet);
10178  ExitList.clear();
10179  AnsiString CurrentID = "";
10180 
10181  if(IDSet.Length() == 0)
10182  {
10183  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Must have at least one exit element ID following 'Fer'");
10184  Utilities->CallLogPop(1521);
10185  return false;
10186  }
10187  for(int x = 1; x <= IDSet.Length(); x++)
10188  {
10189  char C = IDSet[x];
10190  if(((C < '0') || (C > '9')) && (C != ' ') && (C != 'N') && (C != '-'))
10191  {
10192  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Illegal character in the set of element IDs following 'Fer' in '" + IDSet + "'");
10193  Utilities->CallLogPop(1522);
10194  return false;
10195  }
10196  }
10197  int Pos = IDSet.Pos(' '); // look for the first space
10198 
10199  while(true)
10200  {
10201  if(Pos == 0)
10202  {
10203  CurrentID = IDSet;
10204  IDSet = "";
10205  }
10206  else
10207  {
10208  CurrentID = IDSet.SubString(1, Pos - 1);
10209  IDSet = IDSet.SubString(Pos + 1, IDSet.Length() - Pos);
10210  }
10211  int VecPos = Track->GetTrackVectorPositionFromString(7, CurrentID, GiveMessages);
10212  if(VecPos == -1)
10213  {
10214  Utilities->CallLogPop(1523);
10215  return false; // messages given in GetTrackVectorPositionFromString
10216  }
10217  else
10218  {
10219  if(Track->TrackElementAt(722, VecPos).TrackType != Continuation)
10220  {
10221  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "The element ID '" + CurrentID + "' following 'Fer' is not an exit");
10222  Utilities->CallLogPop(1524);
10223  return false;
10224  }
10225  else
10226  {
10227  // first check for duplicates
10228  if(!ExitList.empty())
10229  {
10230  for(TExitListIterator ELIT = ExitList.begin(); ELIT != ExitList.end(); ELIT++)
10231  {
10232  if(*ELIT == VecPos)
10233  {
10234  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "The element ID '" + CurrentID + "' following 'Fer' duplicates an earlier element");
10235  Utilities->CallLogPop(1532);
10236  return false;
10237  }
10238  }
10239  }
10240  // of OK add it to the list
10241  ExitList.push_back(VecPos);
10242  }
10243  }
10244  if(IDSet == "")
10245  {
10246  Utilities->CallLogPop(1525);
10247  return true;
10248  }
10249  else
10250  {
10251  Pos = IDSet.Pos(' '); // look for the next space
10252  }
10253  } // while(true)
10254 }
10255 
10256 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
10257 bool TTrainController::SplitTrainInfo(int Caller, AnsiString TrainInfoStr, AnsiString &HeadCode, AnsiString &Description, int &StartSpeed, int &MaxRunningSpeed,
10258  int &Mass, double &MaxBrakeRate, double &PowerAtRail, int &SignallerSpeed, bool GiveMessages)
10259  // 7 or 8 items for a new train (6 or 7 semicolons), for a continuing service only need headcode, though can have a description, if other
10260  // data entered for continuing service then will be ignored - message given to warn user, checks appropriate number of items and validity
10261  // of each item
10262 {
10263  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",SplitTrainInfo," + TrainInfoStr);
10264  int Pos = 0;
10265  AnsiString Remainder = "";
10266  int SemiColonCount = 0;
10267 
10268  for(int x = 1; x < TrainInfoStr.Length() + 1; x++)
10269  {
10270  if(TrainInfoStr[x] == ';')
10271  SemiColonCount++;
10272  }
10273  if((SemiColonCount != 6) && (SemiColonCount != 7) && (SemiColonCount != 1) && (SemiColonCount != 0))
10274  {
10275  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in train information in '" + TrainInfoStr +
10276  "'. Should be headcode + optional description for a continuing service;" +
10277  " or headcode, description, start speed, max running speed, mass, brake force, power (and optional signaller max. speed) for a new service");
10278  Utilities->CallLogPop(880);
10279  return false;
10280  }
10281  if(SemiColonCount == 0)
10282  {
10283  HeadCode = TrainInfoStr;
10284  if(!CheckHeadCodeValidity(8, GiveMessages, HeadCode))
10285  {
10286  Utilities->CallLogPop(881);
10287  return false;
10288  }
10289  Utilities->CallLogPop(882);
10290  return true;
10291  }
10292  if(SemiColonCount == 1) // headcode & description only
10293  {
10294  Pos = TrainInfoStr.Pos(';'); // 1st delimiter
10295  HeadCode = TrainInfoStr.SubString(1, Pos - 1);
10296  Description = TrainInfoStr.SubString(Pos + 1, TrainInfoStr.Length() - Pos);
10297  if(!CheckHeadCodeValidity(9, GiveMessages, HeadCode))
10298  {
10299  Utilities->CallLogPop(883);
10300  return false;
10301  }
10302  if(Description == "")
10303  {
10304  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Train description missing in '" + TrainInfoStr + "'");
10305  Utilities->CallLogPop(884);
10306  return false;
10307  }
10308  if(Description.Length() > 60)
10309  {
10310  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Train description too long, limit of 60 characters '" + TrainInfoStr + "'");
10311  Utilities->CallLogPop(1157);
10312  return false;
10313  }
10314  for(int x = 1; x < Description.Length() + 1; x++)
10315  {
10316  if((Description[x] < ' ') || (Description[x] > '~'))
10317  {
10318  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Train description contains invalid characters in '" + TrainInfoStr + "'");
10319  Utilities->CallLogPop(885);
10320  return false;
10321  }
10322  }
10323  Utilities->CallLogPop(886);
10324  return true;
10325  }
10326  // if here must have 6 or 7 semicolons
10327  Pos = TrainInfoStr.Pos(';'); // 1st delimiter
10328  HeadCode = TrainInfoStr.SubString(1, Pos - 1);
10329  Remainder = TrainInfoStr.SubString(Pos + 1, TrainInfoStr.Length() - Pos);
10330  if(!CheckHeadCodeValidity(10, GiveMessages, HeadCode))
10331  {
10332  Utilities->CallLogPop(887);
10333  return false;
10334  }
10335  Pos = Remainder.Pos(';'); // 2nd delimiter
10336  Description = Remainder.SubString(1, Pos - 1);
10337  Remainder = Remainder.SubString(Pos + 1, Remainder.Length() - Pos);
10338  if(Description == "")
10339  {
10340  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Train description missing in '" + TrainInfoStr + "'");
10341  Utilities->CallLogPop(888);
10342  return false;
10343  }
10344  if(Description.Length() > 60)
10345  {
10346  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Train description too long, limit of 60 characters '" + TrainInfoStr + "'");
10347  Utilities->CallLogPop(1158);
10348  return false;
10349  }
10350  for(int x = 1; x < Description.Length() + 1; x++)
10351  {
10352  if((Description[x] < ' ') || (Description[x] > 126))
10353  {
10354  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Train description contains invalid characters in '" + TrainInfoStr + "'");
10355  Utilities->CallLogPop(889);
10356  return false;
10357  }
10358  }
10359  Pos = Remainder.Pos(';'); // 3rd delimiter
10360  AnsiString StartSpeedStr = Remainder.SubString(1, Pos - 1);
10361 
10362  Remainder = Remainder.SubString(Pos + 1, Remainder.Length() - Pos);
10363  if(StartSpeedStr == "")
10364  {
10365  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Train starting speed missing in '" + TrainInfoStr + "'");
10366  Utilities->CallLogPop(890);
10367  return false;
10368  }
10369  for(int x = 1; x < StartSpeedStr.Length() + 1; x++)
10370  {
10371  if((StartSpeedStr[x] < '0') || (StartSpeedStr[x] > '9'))
10372  {
10373  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Train start speed contains invalid characters in '" + TrainInfoStr + "'");
10374  Utilities->CallLogPop(891);
10375  return false;
10376  }
10377  }
10378  StartSpeed = StartSpeedStr.ToInt();
10379  if(StartSpeed > TTrain::MaximumSpeedLimit) // 400kph = 250mph
10380  {
10381  StartSpeed = TTrain::MaximumSpeedLimit;
10382  if(!SSHigh) // added at v2.4.0
10383  {
10384  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Train starting speed > 400km/h in '" + TrainInfoStr + "'. Setting it to 400km/h");
10385  SSHigh = true;
10386  }
10387  }
10388  Pos = Remainder.Pos(';'); // 4th delimiter
10389  AnsiString MaxRunningSpeedStr = Remainder.SubString(1, Pos - 1);
10390 
10391  Remainder = Remainder.SubString(Pos + 1, Remainder.Length() - Pos);
10392  if(MaxRunningSpeedStr == "")
10393  {
10394  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Train maximum running speed missing in '" + TrainInfoStr + "'");
10395  Utilities->CallLogPop(892);
10396  return false;
10397  }
10398  for(int x = 1; x < MaxRunningSpeedStr.Length() + 1; x++)
10399  {
10400  if((MaxRunningSpeedStr[x] < '0') || (MaxRunningSpeedStr[x] > '9'))
10401  {
10402  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Train maximum running speed contains invalid characters in '" + TrainInfoStr + "'");
10403  Utilities->CallLogPop(893);
10404  return false;
10405  }
10406  }
10407  MaxRunningSpeed = MaxRunningSpeedStr.ToInt();
10408  if(MaxRunningSpeed > TTrain::MaximumSpeedLimit) // 400kph = 250mph
10409  {
10410  MaxRunningSpeed = TTrain::MaximumSpeedLimit;
10411  if(!MRSHigh) // added at v2.4.0
10412  {
10413  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Train maximum running speed > 400km/h in '" + TrainInfoStr + "'. Setting it to 400km/h");
10414  MRSHigh = true;
10415  }
10416  }
10417  if(MaxRunningSpeed < 10)
10418  // changed at v0.6 to prevent low max speeds - can cause problems in SetTrainMovementValues
10419  {
10420  MaxRunningSpeed = 10;
10421  if(!MRSLow) // added at v2.4.0
10422  {
10423  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Train maximum running speed can't be less than 10km/h in '" + TrainInfoStr + "', it will be set to 10km/h");
10424  MRSLow = true;
10425  }
10426  }
10427  Pos = Remainder.Pos(';'); // 5th delimiter
10428  AnsiString MassStr = Remainder.SubString(1, Pos - 1);
10429 
10430  Remainder = Remainder.SubString(Pos + 1, Remainder.Length() - Pos);
10431  if(MassStr == "")
10432  {
10433  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Train mass missing in '" + TrainInfoStr + "'");
10434  Utilities->CallLogPop(895);
10435  return false;
10436  }
10437  for(int x = 1; x < MassStr.Length() + 1; x++)
10438  {
10439  if((MassStr[x] < '0') || (MassStr[x] > '9'))
10440  {
10441  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Train mass contains invalid characters in '" + TrainInfoStr + "'");
10442  Utilities->CallLogPop(896);
10443  return false;
10444  }
10445  }
10446  Mass = MassStr.ToInt() * 1000; // convert tonnes to kg
10447  if(Mass > TTrain::MaximumMassLimit) // 10,000tonnes
10448  {
10449  Mass = TTrain::MaximumMassLimit;
10450  if(!MassHigh) // added at v2.4.0
10451  {
10452  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Train mass > 10,000 tonnes in '" + TrainInfoStr + "'. Setting it to 10,000 tonnes");
10453  MassHigh = true;
10454  }
10455  }
10456  if(Mass == 0)
10457  {
10458  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Train mass zero in '" + TrainInfoStr + "'");
10459  Utilities->CallLogPop(897);
10460  return false;
10461  }
10462  Pos = Remainder.Pos(';'); // 6th delimiter
10463  AnsiString MaxBrakeForceStr = Remainder.SubString(1, Pos - 1);
10464 
10465  Remainder = Remainder.SubString(Pos + 1, Remainder.Length() - Pos);
10466  if(MaxBrakeForceStr == "")
10467  {
10468  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Train braking force missing in '" + TrainInfoStr + "'");
10469  Utilities->CallLogPop(898);
10470  return false;
10471  }
10472  for(int x = 1; x < (MaxBrakeForceStr.Length() + 1); x++)
10473  {
10474  if((MaxBrakeForceStr[x] != '.') && ((MaxBrakeForceStr[x] < '0') || (MaxBrakeForceStr[x] > '9')))
10475  {
10476  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Train braking force contains invalid characters in '" + TrainInfoStr + "'");
10477  Utilities->CallLogPop(899);
10478  return false;
10479  }
10480  }
10481  double MaxBrakeForce = MaxBrakeForceStr.ToDouble() * 1000;
10482 
10483  // convert to kg force
10484  if((MaxBrakeForce / Mass) > 1) // gives 'g' braking - 9.81m/s/s
10485  {
10486  MaxBrakeForce = Mass;
10487  if(!BFHigh) // added at v2.4.0
10488  {
10489  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Train braking force too high in '" + TrainInfoStr + "'. Setting it to the same as the train mass");
10490  BFHigh = true;
10491  }
10492  }
10493  if((MaxBrakeForce / Mass) < 0.01)
10494  {
10495  MaxBrakeForce = Mass * 0.01;
10496  if(!BFLow) // added at v2.4.0
10497  {
10498  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Train braking force too low in '" + TrainInfoStr + "'. Setting it to 1% of the train mass");
10499  BFLow = true;
10500  }
10501  }
10502  // convert to m/s/s
10503  MaxBrakeRate = MaxBrakeForce / Mass * 9.81;
10504  // now may have just a power entry or power and signaller max. speed
10505  AnsiString GrossPowerStr = "", SignallerSpeedStr = "";
10506 
10507  if(SemiColonCount == 6)
10508  {
10509  GrossPowerStr = Remainder;
10510  SignallerSpeedStr = "30"; // default value
10511  }
10512  else // must be 7
10513  {
10514  Pos = Remainder.Pos(';'); // 7th delimiter
10515  GrossPowerStr = Remainder.SubString(1, Pos - 1);
