10516  SignallerSpeedStr = Remainder.SubString(Pos + 1, Remainder.Length() - Pos);
10517  }
10518  // deal with GrossPower
10519  if(GrossPowerStr == "")
10520  {
10521  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Train power missing in '" + TrainInfoStr + "'");
10522  Utilities->CallLogPop(901);
10523  return false;
10524  }
10525  for(int x = 1; x < GrossPowerStr.Length() + 1; x++)
10526  {
10527  if((GrossPowerStr[x] < '0') || (GrossPowerStr[x] > '9'))
10528  {
10529  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Train power contains invalid characters in '" + TrainInfoStr + "'");
10530  Utilities->CallLogPop(902);
10531  return false;
10532  }
10533  }
10534 
10535  double GrossPower = GrossPowerStr.ToInt() * 1000; // convert to W
10536 
10537  if(GrossPower > TTrain::MaximumPowerLimit) // 100MW
10538  {
10539  GrossPower = TTrain::MaximumPowerLimit;
10540  if(!PwrHigh)
10541  {
10542  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Train power > 100,000kW in '" + TrainInfoStr + "'. Setting it to 100,000kW");
10543  PwrHigh = true;
10544  }
10545  }
10546  else if(GrossPower == 0) // changed at v2.4.0
10547  {
10548  GrossPower = 0.1;
10549  // can't be zero or AValue is zero and then have divide by zero error, so set to 0.1W so acceleration tiny (though should be intercepted before accel calculated)
10550  }
10551  else if((GrossPower > 0) && (GrossPower < 10000))
10552  // added at v2.4.0 to ensure min power of 8kW at rail unless zero (otherwise could have too low AValues
10553  {
10554  GrossPower = 10000;
10555  }
10556  PowerAtRail = GrossPower * 0.8;
10557  // apply ratio of 80% for rail to gross power (seems about average from an internet search)
10558 
10559  // deal with SignallerSpeed
10560  if(SignallerSpeedStr == "")
10561  {
10562  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Signaller speed not set in '" + TrainInfoStr + "', either set a value or remove the extra semicolon");
10563  Utilities->CallLogPop(1771);
10564  return false;
10565  }
10566  for(int x = 1; x < SignallerSpeedStr.Length() + 1; x++)
10567  {
10568  if((SignallerSpeedStr[x] < '0') || (SignallerSpeedStr[x] > '9'))
10569  {
10570  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Signaller speed contains invalid characters in '" + TrainInfoStr + "'");
10571  Utilities->CallLogPop(1769);
10572  return false;
10573  }
10574  }
10575  SignallerSpeed = SignallerSpeedStr.ToInt();
10576  if(SignallerSpeed > TTrain::MaximumSpeedLimit)
10577  {
10578  SignallerSpeed = TTrain::MaximumSpeedLimit;
10579  if(!SigSHigh)
10580  {
10581  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Signaller speed > 400km/h in '" + TrainInfoStr + "'. Setting it to 400km/h");
10582  SigSHigh = true;
10583  }
10584  }
10585  if(SignallerSpeed < 10)
10586  // changed at v0.6 to prevent low max speeds - can cause problems in SetTrainMovementValues
10587  {
10588  SignallerSpeed = 10;
10589  if(!SigSLow)
10590  {
10591  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Signaller speed can't be less than 10km/h in '" + TrainInfoStr + "', it will be set to 10km/h");
10592  SigSLow = true;
10593  }
10594  // Utilities->CallLogPop(1770);
10595  // return false;
10596  }
10597  Utilities->CallLogPop(904);
10598  return true;
10599 }
10600 
10601 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
10602 
10603 bool TTrainController::SplitRepeat(int Caller, AnsiString OneEntry, int &RearStartOrRepeatMins, int &FrontStartOrRepeatDigits, int &NumberOfRepeats,
10604  bool GiveMessages)
10605 {
10606  // Format must be: R;mm;dd;nn mm may be 1, 2 or more digits, dd may be 1 or 2 digits, nn may be 1, 2 or more digits
10607  // function checks validity of each item and returns false for error
10608  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",SplitRepeat," + OneEntry);
10609  if(OneEntry.Length() < 7)
10610  {
10611  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in repeat: '" + OneEntry + "' - should be 'R;m;d;n'");
10612  Utilities->CallLogPop(865);
10613  return false;
10614  }
10615  int SemiColonCount = 0;
10616 
10617  for(int x = 1; x < OneEntry.Length() + 1; x++)
10618  {
10619  if(OneEntry[x] == ';')
10620  SemiColonCount++;
10621  }
10622  if(SemiColonCount != 3)
10623  {
10624  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in repeat: '" + OneEntry + "' - should be 'R;m;d;n'");
10625  Utilities->CallLogPop(866);
10626  return false;
10627  }
10628  if((OneEntry[1] != 'R') || (OneEntry[2] != ';'))
10629  {
10630  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in repeat: '" + OneEntry + "' - should be 'R;m;d;n'");
10631  Utilities->CallLogPop(867);
10632  return false;
10633  }
10634  AnsiString Remainder = OneEntry.SubString(3, OneEntry.Length() - 2);
10635  // strip off R;
10636 
10637  int Pos = 0;
10638 
10639  Pos = Remainder.Pos(';');
10640  AnsiString MinutesStr = Remainder.SubString(1, Pos - 1);
10641 
10642  Remainder = Remainder.SubString(Pos + 1, Remainder.Length() - Pos);
10643  if(MinutesStr == "")
10644  {
10645  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in repeat: '" + OneEntry + "' - minute increment segment missing");
10646  Utilities->CallLogPop(868);
10647  return false;
10648  }
10649  if(MinutesStr.Length() > 3)
10650  // added for v2.3.1 following Albie Vowles' reported error in repeat value 03/02/20
10651  {
10652  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in repeat: '" + OneEntry + "' - minute value too high, maximum value is 999");
10653  Utilities->CallLogPop(2119);
10654  return false;
10655  }
10656  for(int x = 1; x < MinutesStr.Length() + 1; x++)
10657  {
10658  if((MinutesStr[x] < '0') || (MinutesStr[x] > '9'))
10659  {
10660  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in repeat: '" + OneEntry + "' - non-digit character in minute increment segment");
10661  Utilities->CallLogPop(869);
10662  return false;
10663  }
10664  }
10665  RearStartOrRepeatMins = MinutesStr.ToInt();
10666  if(RearStartOrRepeatMins == 0)
10667  {
10668  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Repeat minute increment is zero in: '" + OneEntry + "' - can't have a zero value");
10669  Utilities->CallLogPop(870);
10670  return false;
10671  }
10672  Pos = Remainder.Pos(';');
10673  AnsiString DigitsStr = Remainder.SubString(1, Pos - 1);
10674 
10675  Remainder = Remainder.SubString(Pos + 1, Remainder.Length() - Pos);
10676  if(DigitsStr == "")
10677  {
10678  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in repeat: '" + OneEntry + "' - headcode increment segment missing");
10679  Utilities->CallLogPop(871);
10680  return false;
10681  }
10682  for(int x = 1; x < DigitsStr.Length() + 1; x++)
10683  {
10684  if((DigitsStr[x] < '0') || (DigitsStr[x] > '9'))
10685  {
10686  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in repeat: '" + OneEntry + "' - non-digit character in headcode increment segment");
10687  Utilities->CallLogPop(872);
10688  return false;
10689  }
10690  }
10691  if(DigitsStr.Length() > 2)
10692  {
10693  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in repeat: '" + OneEntry + "' - maximum number of digits for headcode increment is 2");
10694  Utilities->CallLogPop(873);
10695  return false;
10696  }
10697  FrontStartOrRepeatDigits = DigitsStr.ToInt();
10698 /* allow zero digit increments so HC can stay same for repeated services - for many suburban services the headcode digits relate to the
10699  route rather than the service
10700  if(FrontStartOrRepeatDigits == 0)
10701  {
10702  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Repeat headcode increment is zero in: '" + OneEntry + "' - can't have a zero value");
10703  Utilities->CallLogPop(874);
10704  return false;
10705  }
10706 */
10707  if(!Last2CharactersBothDigits(0, ServiceReference) && (FrontStartOrRepeatDigits > 0))
10708  // new for v0.6b for unrestricted headcodes
10709  {
10710  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in repeat: '" + OneEntry +
10711  "' - a repeating service with incrementing digits must have digits as its last two headcode characters");
10712  Utilities->CallLogPop(1889);
10713  return false;
10714  }
10715  AnsiString NumberStr = Remainder;
10716 
10717  if(NumberStr == "")
10718  {
10719  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in repeat: '" + OneEntry + "' - number of repeats missing");
10720  Utilities->CallLogPop(875);
10721  return false;
10722  }
10723  if(NumberStr.Length() > 4)
10724  // added for v2.3.1 following Albie Vowles' reported error 03/02/20
10725  {
10726  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in repeat: '" + OneEntry + "' - repeat value too high, no timetabled event can exceed 95 hours & 59 minutes");
10727  Utilities->CallLogPop(2118);
10728  return false;
10729  }
10730  for(int x = 1; x < NumberStr.Length() + 1; x++)
10731  {
10732  if((NumberStr[x] < '0') || (NumberStr[x] > '9'))
10733  // catches negative numbers
10734  {
10735  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in repeat: '" + OneEntry + "' - non-digit character in number of repeats");
10736  Utilities->CallLogPop(876);
10737  return false;
10738  }
10739  }
10740  NumberOfRepeats = NumberStr.ToInt();
10741  if(NumberOfRepeats == 0)
10742  {
10743  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Number of repeats is zero in: '" + OneEntry + "' - if no repeats are needed the repeat should be omitted");
10744  Utilities->CallLogPop(877);
10745  return false;
10746  }
10747  Utilities->CallLogPop(878);
10748  return true;
10749 }
10750 
10751 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
10752 
10753 bool TTrainController::SecondPassActions(int Caller, bool GiveMessages)
10754 /* Note that here the TrainDataVector has been compiled with FinalCall true in ProcessOneTimetableLine so work on the
10755  vector rather than the timetable
10756  Note also that for unlocated Snt entries the LocationType hasn't yet been set
10757 
10758  Many of the errors caught here duplicate those in the preliminary checks, but leave in for completeness
10759 
10760  For info:-
10761  class TActionVectorEntry //contains a single train action - repeat entry is also of this class though no train action is taken for it
10762  {
10763  public:
10764  AnsiString LocationName, Command, OtherHeadCode, NonRepeatingShuttleLinkHeadCode; ///< string values for timetabled action entries, null
10766  bool SignallerControl; ///< indicates a train that is defined by the timetable as under signaller control
10767  bool Warning; ///< if set triggers an alert in the warning panel when the action is reached
10768  int NumberOfRepeats; ///< the number of repeating services
10769  int RearStartOrRepeatMins, FrontStartOrRepeatDigits; ///< dual-purpose variables used for the TrackVectorPositions of the rear and front
10771  TDateTime EventTime, ArrivalTime, DepartureTime; ///< relevant times at which the action is timetabled, zeroed on creation so change
10773  TExitList ExitList; ///< the list of valid train exit TrackVector positions for 'Fer' entries (empty to begin with)
10774  TTimetableFormatType FormatType; ///< defines the timetable action type
10775  TTimetableLocationType LocationType; ///< indicates where the train is when the relevant action occurs
10776  TTimetableSequenceType SequenceType; ///< indicates where in the sequence of codes the action lies
10777  TTimetableShuttleLinkType ShuttleLinkType; ///< indicates whether or not the action relates to a shuttle service link
10778  TTrainDataEntry *LinkedTrainEntryPtr; ///< link pointer for use between fsp/rsp & Sfs; Fjo & jbo; Fns & Sns; & all shuttle to shuttle
10780  TTrainDataEntry *NonRepeatingShuttleLinkEntryPtr; ///< pointer used by shuttles for the non-shuttle train links, in & out, the
10782 
10783  // inline function
10784 
10786  TActionVectorEntry() {
10787  RearStartOrRepeatMins=0; FrontStartOrRepeatDigits=0; NumberOfRepeats=0; FormatType=NoFormat;
10788  SequenceType=NoSequence; LocationType=NoLocation; ShuttleLinkType=NoShuttleLink, EventTime=TDateTime(-1);
10789  ArrivalTime=TDateTime(-1); DepartureTime=TDateTime(-1); LinkedTrainEntryPtr=0; NonRepeatingShuttleLinkEntryPtr=0;
10790  Warning = false; SignallerControl = false;
10791  }
10792  };
10793 
10794  typedef std::vector<TActionVectorEntry> TActionVector;//contains all actions for a single train
10795 
10796  class TTrainDataEntry //contains all data for a single train - copied into train object when becomes active
10797  {
10798  public:
10799  AnsiString HeadCode, ServiceReference, Description; ///< headcode is the first train's headcode, rest are calculated from repeat
10802  double MaxBrakeRate; ///< in metres/sec/sec
10803  double MaxRunningSpeed; ///< in km/h
10804  double PowerAtRail; ///< in Watts (taken as 80% of the train's Gross Power, i.e. that entered by the user)
10805  int Mass; ///< in kg
10806  int NumberOfTrains; ///< number of repeats + 1
10807  int SignallerSpeed; ///< in km/h for use when under signaller control
10808  int StartSpeed; ///< in km/h
10809  TActionVector ActionVector; ///< all the actions for the train
10810  TTrainOperatingDataVector TrainOperatingDataVector; ///< operating information for the train including all its repeats
10811 
10812  //inline function
10813 
10815  TTrainDataEntry()
10816  {
10817  StartSpeed=0; MaxRunningSpeed=0; NumberOfTrains=0;
10818  }
10819  };
10820 
10821  Allowable successors:-
10822  Snt unlocated -> Fer, TimeLoc (arr), TimeTimeLoc, (new) pas; No others
10823  Snt located -> No starts, no finishes except Frh & Fjo (as of v2.0.0), no repeat, pas or TimeTimeLoc; any other cmd or TimeLoc (dep) OK
10824  Snt-sh -> No starts, finishes, repeats, pas or TimeTimeLoc; any other cmd or TimeLoc (dep) OK
10825  Sfs -> No starts, finishes, repeats, pas or TimeTimeLoc; any other cmd or TimeLoc (dep) OK (must have a TimeLoc departure somewhere in sequence to
10826  set location, else fails)
10827  Sns -> No starts, finishes, repeats, pas or TimeTimeLoc; any other cmd or TimeLoc (dep) OK (must have a TimeLoc departure somewhere in sequence to
10828  set location, else fails)
10829  Sns-sh -> No starts, finishes, repeats, pas or TimeTimeLoc; any other cmd or TimeLoc (dep) OK (must have a TimeLoc departure somewhere in sequence to
10830  set location, else fails)
10831  Sns-fsh -> No starts, finishes, repeats, pas or TimeTimeLoc; any other cmd or TimeLoc (dep) OK (must have a TimeLoc departure somewhere in sequence to
10832  set location, else fails)
10833  Fns -> R only
10834  F-nshs -> Nothing (no repeats permitted)
10835  Fjo -> R only
10836  Frh -> R only
10837  Fer -> R only
10838  Frh-sh -> R only
10839  Fns-sh -> R only
10840  jbo -> No starts, finishes, repeats, splits, pas or TimeTimeLoc; TimeLoc (dep), jbo or cdt OK
10841  fsp -> No starts, repeats, Fer, pas or TimeTimeLoc; TimeLoc (dep) or any other OK
10842  rsp -> No starts, repeats, Fer, pas or TimeTimeLoc; TimeLoc (dep) or any other OK
10843  cdt -> No starts, repeats, Fer, pas or TimeTimeLoc; TimeLoc (dep) or any other OK
10844  TimeLoc (arr) -> No starts, repeats, Fer, pas or TimeTimeLoc; TimeLoc (dep) or any other OK
10845  TimeLoc (dep) -> Fer, TimeLoc (arr), or TimeTimeLoc, (new) pas OK, no others
10846  TimeTimeLoc -> Fer, TimeLoc (arr), or TimeTimeLoc, (new) pas OK, no others
10847  (new) pas -> Fer, TimeLoc (arr), or TimeTimeLoc, (new) pas OK, no others
10848  Repeat -> Nothing
10849 
10850  There must be a TimeLoc arrival (or a Sns start at location) in a sequence so successive cmd locations can be set
10851  Check all Snt's & set Locations if located (located = zero start speed, either element at a location (but if rear element
10852  is a continuation then treated as unlocated), and location listed in the next TimeLoc entry, though needn't be immediately after)
10853  If Snt entry at a location specified in a following TimeLoc entry but start speed > 0 give error message
10854  Check all times increase or stay same through ActionVector
10855  Cycle through all entries in vector setting arr & dep times based on above list
10856  Add locations to all relevant cmd entries based on earlier arrival location (or earlier reference for Sfs & Sns)
10857  Check locations match the arr & dep TimeLoc entries
10858  Check same location doesn't appear twice before a cdt except for separate arr & dep TimeLocs
10859  Make above valid succession checks
10860  Check all splits have matching Sfs headcodes (both ways), add locations to SFSs & check times same
10861  Check all new service headcodes (Sns) have matching headcodes (both ways), add locations to SNHs & check times same
10862  Check a split to 'x' doesn't again split to 'x' (anywhere, not just for one train, since headcodes can be duplicated)
10863  Check each Fns has matching Sns headcodes (both ways), add locations to SNHs & check times same
10864  Check all joins have matching headcodes (both ways), locations & times & don't occur in same sequence
10865  Check each joined by train not joined by same train again (anywhere, not just for one train, since headcodes can be duplicated)
10866  Set train info for Sfs & Sns entries
10867  Check each repeat entry exactly matches any included joins or splits (user has to enter it to show that really wants it)
10868  Check at least one platform long enough for a split (only need 2 lengths) & disallow if not, need length of 2 & 1 extra
10869  element at each end, or length of 3 & 1 extra element at either end
10870  Check all TimeLocs have either Arr or Dep times set and EventTime == -1
10871  Check all Cmds have EventTime set & Arr & Dep times = -1
10872  Check all Sfs & Sns entries followed somewhere in sequence by a TimeLoc departure
10873  Check all locations except unlocated Snts, Fers and Repeats have a LocationName
10874 
10875  Give messages in function if errors detected and clear the vector. Return false for failure.
10876 */
10877 
10878 /* Earlier checks:-
10879  Checks carried out with error messages in this function:-
10880  At least one comma in the line (it's based on a csv file);
10881  No entries following train information;
10882  At least one comma in remainder after train information (i.e at least a start and a finish entry);
10883  SplitEntry returns false in an intermediate entry - message repeats the entry for information;
10884  First entry not a start entry;
10885  Train information incomplete before a start entry;
10886  Entry follows a finish entry but doesn't begin with 'R';
10887  SplitEntry returns false in a finish entry - message repeats the entry for information;
10888  Last action entry isn't a finish entry.
10889 
10890  Function returns false with no message if:-
10891  Timetable start time invalid (no message is given for an invalid time as the line is assumed to be an irrelevant line; if no start
10892  time is found at all then an error message is given in the calling function);
10893  SplitTrainInfo returns false (message given in called function);
10894  SplitRepeat returns false (message given in called function).
10895 */ {
10896  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",SecondPassActions,");
10897  if(TrainDataVector.empty())
10898  {
10899  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - there appear to be no train services in the timetable, it must contain at least one");
10900  TrainDataVector.clear();
10901  Utilities->CallLogPop(1832);
10902  return false;
10903  }
10904 
10905 /* new preliminary checks for v0.2b without changing anything, carry each out separately:-
10906  1) must have at least one actionvector entry
10907  2) if first actionvector entry not SignallerControl then must have at least one more actionvector entry
10908  3) if first actionvector entry is SignallerControl then must have no more actionvector entries except a repeat
10909  4) first entry must be a start;
10910  4a) if first entry is Snt and not signallercontrol and second is a finish then it can only be Frh, Fjo or Fer//added for v2.0.0
10911  5) a start must be the first entry;
10912  6) a repeat entry must be the last;
10913  7) for other than SignallerControl the last entry must be repeat or finish; if last entry is a repeat the last but one must be a finish;
10914  8) a finish entry must be the last or last but one, and if last but one the last must be a repeat
10915  Other successor errors will be caught later as all 'throws' changed to messages prior to the bulk of the sucessor checks
10916 */
10917 
10918  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++) // (1)
10919  {
10920  const TTrainDataEntry &TDEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x);
10921  if(TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.empty())
10922  {
10923  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - the following service has no listed events, there must be at least one: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
10924  TrainDataVector.clear();
10925  Utilities->CallLogPop(1833);
10926  return false;
10927  }
10928  }
10929  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++) // (2)
10930  {
10931  const TTrainDataEntry &TDEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x);
10932  TActionVectorEntry AVEntry0 = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(0);
10933  if(!(AVEntry0.SignallerControl))
10934  {
10935  if(TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size() == 1)
10936  {
10937  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - service must have a start event and at least one other for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
10938  TrainDataVector.clear();
10939  Utilities->CallLogPop(1822);
10940  return false;
10941  }
10942  }
10943  }
10944  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++) // (3)
10945  {
10946  const TTrainDataEntry &TDEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x);
10947  TActionVectorEntry AVEntry0 = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(0);
10948  if(AVEntry0.SignallerControl)
10949  {
10950  if(TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size() > 2)
10951  {
10952  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages,
10953  "Error in timetable - a signaller control service can have no more than one item (a repeat) after the start event, see: " +
10954  TDEntry.HeadCode);
10955  TrainDataVector.clear();
10956  Utilities->CallLogPop(1837);
10957  return false;
10958  }
10959  if(TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size() > 1)
10960  {
10961  TActionVectorEntry AVEntry1 = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(1);
10962  if(AVEntry1.FormatType != Repeat)
10963  {
10964  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages,
10965  "Error in timetable - a signaller control service cannot have any other than a repeat after the start event, see: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
10966  TrainDataVector.clear();
10967  Utilities->CallLogPop(1838);
10968  return false;
10969  }
10970  }
10971  }
10972  }
10973  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++) // (4)
10974  {
10975  const TTrainDataEntry &TDEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x);
10976  TActionVectorEntry AVEntry0 = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(0);
10977  if(AVEntry0.SequenceType != Start)
10978  {
10979  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - the first event must be a start for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
10980  TrainDataVector.clear();
10981  Utilities->CallLogPop(1824);
10982  return false;
10983  }
10984  if((AVEntry0.Command == "Snt") && !(AVEntry0.SignallerControl))
10985  // 4a added at v2.0.0. This is only a rough check, Fer only valid for an unlocated Snt
10986  // and others for a located Snt, but those checks done later
10987  {
10988  TActionVectorEntry AVEntry1 = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(1);
10989  // must be a second entry if first not signallercontrol
10990  if((AVEntry1.SequenceType == Finish) && ((AVEntry1.Command == "Fns-sh") || (AVEntry1.Command == "Frh-sh")))
10991  {
10992  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - finish events Fns-sh and Frh-sh not permitted immediately after an Snt entry for: " +
10993  TDEntry.HeadCode);
10994  TrainDataVector.clear();
10995  Utilities->CallLogPop(2046);
10996  return false;
10997  }
10998  }
10999  }
11000  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++) // (5)
11001  {
11002  const TTrainDataEntry &TDEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x);
11003  for(unsigned int y = 0; y < TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size(); y++)
11004  {
11005  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y);
11006  if((AVEntry.SequenceType == Start) && (y != 0))
11007  {
11008  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - a start event is present that is not the first event for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11009  TrainDataVector.clear();
11010  Utilities->CallLogPop(1825);
11011  return false;
11012  }
11013  }
11014  }
11015  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++) // (6)
11016  {
11017  const TTrainDataEntry &TDEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x);
11018  for(unsigned int y = 0; y < TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size(); y++)
11019  {
11020  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y);
11021  if((AVEntry.FormatType == Repeat) && (y != (TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size() - 1)))
11022  {
11023  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - a repeat is present that is not the last item for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11024  TrainDataVector.clear();
11025  Utilities->CallLogPop(1826);
11026  return false;
11027  }
11028  }
11029  }
11030  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++) // (7)
11031  {
11032  const TTrainDataEntry &TDEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x);
11033  for(unsigned int y = 0; y < TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size(); y++)
11034  {
11035  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y);
11036  if((y == 0) && AVEntry.SignallerControl)
11037  {
11038  break;
11039  }
11040  if(y == (TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size() - 1))
11041  {
11042  if((AVEntry.FormatType != Repeat) && (AVEntry.SequenceType != Finish))
11043  {
11044  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - the last item must be either a finish event or a repeat for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11045  TrainDataVector.clear();
11046  Utilities->CallLogPop(1827);
11047  return false;
11048  }
11049  if(AVEntry.FormatType == Repeat)
11050  {
11051  const TActionVectorEntry &LastAVEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y - 1);
11052  if(LastAVEntry.SequenceType != Finish)
11053  {
11054  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - the last event before the repeat must be a finish for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11055  TrainDataVector.clear();
11056  Utilities->CallLogPop(1828);
11057  return false;
11058  }
11059  }
11060  }
11061  }
11062  }
11063  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++) // (8)
11064  {
11065  const TTrainDataEntry &TDEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x);
11066  for(unsigned int y = 0; y < TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size(); y++)
11067  {
11068  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y);
11069  if(AVEntry.SequenceType == Finish)
11070  {
11071  if((y != (TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size() - 1)) && (y != (TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size() - 2)))
11072  {
11073  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - a finish event must be either the last or last but one for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11074  TrainDataVector.clear();
11075  Utilities->CallLogPop(1829);
11076  return false;
11077  }
11078  if(y == (TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size() - 2))
11079  {
11080  if(TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y + 1).FormatType != Repeat)
11081  {
11082  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - the only event that can follow a finish event is a repeat for: " +
11083  TDEntry.HeadCode);
11084  TrainDataVector.clear();
11085  Utilities->CallLogPop(1830);
11086  return false;
11087  }
11088  }
11089  }
11090  }
11091  }
11092 
11093  // end of new preliminary checks
11094 
11095  // check ActionVector present and check start event successor validity
11096  // For Snt & Snt-sh set location if stopped, don't set any times yet
11097  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++)
11098  {
11099  const TTrainDataEntry &TDEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x);
11100  TActionVectorEntry & AVEntry0 = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(0);
11101  // use reference so can change internals where necessary
11102  if((AVEntry0.Command == "Snt") || (AVEntry0.Command == "Snt-sh"))
11103  {
11104  AnsiString LocationName = "";
11105  if(IsSNTEntryLocated(0, TDEntry, LocationName))
11106  // it is at a location
11107  {
11108  if(TDEntry.StartSpeed == 0) // stopped
11109  {
11110  AVEntry0.LocationName = LocationName;
11111  AVEntry0.LocationType = AtLocation;
11112  // check successor validity for located Snt that isn't a SignallerControl entry
11113  if(!AVEntry0.SignallerControl)
11114  {
11115  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry1 = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(1);
11116  // at least 2 entries present checked in integrity check so (1) valid
11117  if(!AtLocSuccessor(AVEntry1))
11118  {
11119  // Frh following Snt-sh will return false in location check, so no need to check here
11120  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - stopped 'Snt' or 'Snt-sh' followed by an illegal event for: " +
11121  TDEntry.HeadCode + ". The event isn't valid for a stationary train.");
11122  TrainDataVector.clear();
11123  Utilities->CallLogPop(523);
11124  return false;
11125  }
11126  }
11127  }
11128  else
11129  {
11130  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - 'Snt' or 'Snt-sh' event at stop location but start speed not zero for: " +
11131  TDEntry.HeadCode);
11132  TrainDataVector.clear();
11133  Utilities->CallLogPop(791);
11134  return false;
11135  }
11136  }
11137  else // check not Snt-sh & carry out successor validity checks for unlocated Snt that isn't a SignallerControl entry
11138  {
11139  if(AVEntry0.Command == "Snt-sh")
11140  {
11141  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - 'Snt-sh' event not at stop location for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11142  TrainDataVector.clear();
11143  Utilities->CallLogPop(1042);
11144  return false;
11145  }
11146  AVEntry0.LocationType = EnRoute;
11147  if(!AVEntry0.SignallerControl)
11148  {
11149  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry1 = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(1);
11150  // at least 2 entries checked in integrity check so (1) valid
11151  if(!MovingSuccessor(AVEntry1))
11152  {
11153  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - unlocated 'Snt' not followed by 'Fer', 'pas' or an arrival for: " +
11154  TDEntry.HeadCode);
11155  TrainDataVector.clear();
11156  Utilities->CallLogPop(790);
11157  return false;
11158  }
11159  }
11160  }
11161  }
11162  // check other start successors
11163  else if(AVEntry0.SequenceType == Start)
11164  {
11165  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry1 = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(1);
11166  // at least 2 entries present checked in integrity check so (1) valid
11167  if(!AtLocSuccessor(AVEntry1))
11168  {
11169  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - 'Sfs', 'Sns', 'Sns-sh' or 'Sns-fsh' followed by an illegal event for: " +
11170  TDEntry.HeadCode + ". The event isn't valid for a stationary train.");
11171  TrainDataVector.clear();
11172  Utilities->CallLogPop(793);
11173  return false;
11174  }
11175  }
11176  }
11177 
11178  // set Sfs, Sns, Sns-sh & 'Sns-fsh' locations same as following TimeLoc departure entry location, if no departure before end of sequence give error message
11179  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++)
11180  {
11181  bool FoundFlag = false;
11182  const TTrainDataEntry &TDEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x);
11183  TActionVectorEntry & AVEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(0);
11184  // use reference so can change internals
11185  if((AVEntry.Command == "Sfs") || (AVEntry.Command == "Sns") || (AVEntry.Command == "Sns-sh") || (AVEntry.Command == "Sns-fsh"))
11186  {
11187  for(unsigned int y = 1; y < TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size(); y++)
11188  {
11189  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry2 = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y);
11190  if(AVEntry2.FormatType == TimeLoc)
11191  {
11192  FoundFlag = true;
11193  AVEntry.LocationName = AVEntry2.LocationName;
11194  break;
11195  }
11196  }
11197  if(!FoundFlag)
11198  {
11199  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - no location departure following an 'Sfs', 'Sns', 'Sns-sh'or 'Sns-fsh' event for: " +
11200  TDEntry.HeadCode);
11201  TrainDataVector.clear();
11202  Utilities->CallLogPop(851);
11203  return false;
11204  }
11205  }
11206  }
11207 
11208  // set all cmd locations based on earlier location name in TimeLoc arrival or Sfs/Sns/Sns-sh/Sns-fsh/located Snt/Snt-sh locations
11209  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++)
11210  {
11211  const TTrainDataEntry &TDEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x);
11212  for(unsigned int y = 0; y < TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size(); y++)
11213  {
11214  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y);
11215  if((AVEntry.FormatType == TimeLoc) || ((AVEntry.SequenceType == Start) && (AVEntry.LocationType == AtLocation)))
11216  {
11217  if(AVEntry.LocationName == "")
11218  // if TimeLoc turns out to be a TimeLoc departure then will emerge & be rejected in successor checks for TimeLocs
11219  {
11220  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable for " + TDEntry.HeadCode +
11221  ": an event should have had a location name associated with it but it could not be found");
11222  TrainDataVector.clear();
11223  Utilities->CallLogPop(1831);
11224  return false;
11225  // throw Exception("Error, entry location null in TimeLoc/Sfs/Sns/Sns-sh/Sns-fsh/Snt-sh/located Snt for Train: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11226  }
11227  for(unsigned int z = y + 1; z < TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size(); z++)
11228  {
11229  TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry2 = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(z);
11230  // use reference so can change internals where necessary
11231  if((AVEntry2.Command != "") && (AVEntry2.LocationType == AtLocation))
11232  {
11233  AVEntry2.LocationName = AVEntry.LocationName;
11234  }
11235  else
11236  break;
11237  }
11238  }
11239  }
11240  }
11241  // all location names now set
11242 
11243  // check remaining successor validity except for TimeLoc arr & dep since those times not set yet
11244  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++)
11245  {
11246  const TTrainDataEntry &TDEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x);
11247  for(unsigned int y = 0; y < TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size(); y++)
11248  {
11249  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y);
11250  if((AVEntry.SequenceType == Finish) && (AVEntry.Command != "F-nshs"))
11251  {
11252  if(y < (TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size() - 1))
11253  // i.e at least one more, must be a repeat
11254  {
11255  if(TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y + 1).FormatType != Repeat)
11256  {
11257  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - only a repeat can follow a finish entry for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11258  TrainDataVector.clear();
11259  Utilities->CallLogPop(798);
11260  return false;
11261  }
11262  }
11263  }
11264  if(AVEntry.Command == "F-nshs")
11265  {
11266  if(y != (TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size() - 1))
11267  // i.e has to be the last
11268  {
11269  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - F-nshs (shuttle link) must be the last event for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11270  TrainDataVector.clear();
11271  Utilities->CallLogPop(1049);
11272  return false;
11273  }
11274  }
11275  if(AVEntry.Command == "pas")
11276  {
11277  if(y >= (TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size() - 1))
11278  {
11279  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - a 'pas' can't be the last event for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11280  TrainDataVector.clear();
11281  Utilities->CallLogPop(1518);
11282  return false;
11283  }
11284  }
11285  if(AVEntry.Command == "jbo")
11286  {
11287  if(y >= (TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size() - 1))
11288  {
11289  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - a 'jbo' can't be the last event for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11290  TrainDataVector.clear();
11291  Utilities->CallLogPop(800);
11292  return false;
11293  }
11294  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry2 = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y + 1);
11295  if(!AtLocSuccessor(AVEntry2))
11296  {
11297  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - a jbo event is followed by an illegal event for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode +
11298  ". The event isn't valid for a stationary train.");
11299  TrainDataVector.clear();
11300  Utilities->CallLogPop(801);
11301  return false;
11302  }
11303  }
11304  if((AVEntry.Command == "fsp") || (AVEntry.Command == "rsp"))
11305  {
11306  if(y >= (TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size() - 1))
11307  {
11308  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - a train split can't be the last event for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11309  TrainDataVector.clear();
11310  Utilities->CallLogPop(802);
11311  return false;
11312  }
11313  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry2 = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y + 1);
11314  if(!AtLocSuccessor(AVEntry2))
11315  {
11316  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - a train split is followed by an illegal event for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode +
11317  ". The event isn't valid for a stationary train.");
11318  TrainDataVector.clear();
11319  Utilities->CallLogPop(803);
11320  return false;
11321  }
11322  }
11323  if(AVEntry.Command == "cdt")
11324  {
11325  if(y >= (TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size() - 1))
11326  {
11327  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - a 'cdt' can't be the last event for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11328  TrainDataVector.clear();
11329  Utilities->CallLogPop(804);
11330  return false;
11331  }
11332  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry2 = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y + 1);
11333  if(!AtLocSuccessor(AVEntry2))
11334  {
11335  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - a 'cdt' is followed by an illegal event for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode +
11336  ". The event isn't valid for a stationary train.");
11337  TrainDataVector.clear();
11338  Utilities->CallLogPop(805);
11339  return false;
11340  }
11341  }
11342  if(AVEntry.FormatType == TimeTimeLoc)
11343  {
11344  if(y >= (TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size() - 1))
11345  {
11346  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - a timed arrival and departure can't be the last event for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11347  TrainDataVector.clear();
11348  Utilities->CallLogPop(806);
11349  return false;
11350  }
11351  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry2 = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y + 1);
11352  if(!MovingSuccessor(AVEntry2))
11353  {
11354  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - a timed arrival and departure is followed by an illegal event for: " +
11355  TDEntry.HeadCode + ". The event isn't valid for a moving train.");
11356  TrainDataVector.clear();
11357  Utilities->CallLogPop(807);
11358  return false;
11359  }
11360  }
11361  if(AVEntry.FormatType == PassTime)
11362  {
11363  if(y >= (TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size() - 1))
11364  {
11365  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - a pass time can't be the last event for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11366  TrainDataVector.clear();
11367  Utilities->CallLogPop(1530);
11368  return false;
11369  }
11370  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry2 = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y + 1);
11371  if(!MovingSuccessor(AVEntry2))
11372  {
11373  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - a pass time is followed by an illegal event for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode +
11374  ". The event isn't valid for a moving train.");
11375  TrainDataVector.clear();
11376  Utilities->CallLogPop(1531);
11377  return false;
11378  }
11379  }
11380  if(AVEntry.FormatType == Repeat)
11381  {
11382  if(y != (TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size() - 1))
11383  {
11384  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - a repeat is not the last item for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11385  TrainDataVector.clear();
11386  Utilities->CallLogPop(808);
11387  return false;
11388  }
11389  }
11390  }
11391  }
11392 
11393  // set arrival & departure times for TimeLocs & set their EventTimes to -1
11394  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++)
11395  {
11396  bool LastEntryIsAnArrival = false;
11397  const TTrainDataEntry & TDEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x);
11398  // first deal with unlocated Snt entries - so next entry (TimeLoc or TimeTimeLoc) is an arrival, all else stopped so the next TimeLoc is a departure
11399  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry0 = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(0);
11400  if((AVEntry0.Command == "Snt") && (AVEntry0.LocationType == EnRoute))
11401  // StartSpeed may or may not be 0, but train will move forwards (if capable of doing so), & next TimeLoc will be an arrival, whether or not after one or more TimeTimeLocs
11402  {
11403  LastEntryIsAnArrival = false;
11404  for(unsigned int y = 0; y < TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size(); y++)
11405  {
11406  TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y);
11407  if(AVEntry.FormatType == TimeLoc)
11408  {
11409  if((AVEntry.ArrivalTime > TDateTime(-1)) || (AVEntry.DepartureTime > TDateTime(-1)) || (AVEntry.EventTime == TDateTime(-1)))
11410  {
11411  throw Exception("Timetable error, TimeLoc times not as initially set for " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11412  }
11413  if(LastEntryIsAnArrival)
11414  {
11415  AVEntry.DepartureTime = AVEntry.EventTime;
11416  AVEntry.EventTime = TDateTime(-1);
11417  LastEntryIsAnArrival = false;
11418  }
11419  else // last entry a departure
11420  {
11421  AVEntry.ArrivalTime = AVEntry.EventTime;
11422  AVEntry.EventTime = TDateTime(-1);
11423  LastEntryIsAnArrival = true;
11424  }
11425  }
11426  }
11427  }
11428  else // all others stopped at beginning
11429  {
11430  LastEntryIsAnArrival = true;
11431  for(unsigned int y = 0; y < TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size(); y++)
11432  {
11433  TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y);
11434  if(AVEntry.FormatType == TimeLoc)
11435  {
11436  if((AVEntry.ArrivalTime > TDateTime(-1)) || (AVEntry.DepartureTime > TDateTime(-1)) || (AVEntry.EventTime == TDateTime(-1)))
11437  {
11438  throw Exception("Timetable error, TimeLoc times not as initially set for " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11439  }
11440  if(LastEntryIsAnArrival)
11441  {
11442  AVEntry.DepartureTime = AVEntry.EventTime;
11443  AVEntry.EventTime = TDateTime(-1);
11444  LastEntryIsAnArrival = false;
11445  }
11446  else // last entry a departure
11447  {
11448  AVEntry.ArrivalTime = AVEntry.EventTime;
11449  AVEntry.EventTime = TDateTime(-1);
11450  LastEntryIsAnArrival = true;
11451  }
11452  }
11453  }
11454  }
11455  }
11456  // perform remaining successor checks for TimeLocs
11457  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++)
11458  {
11459  const TTrainDataEntry &TDEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x);
11460  for(unsigned int y = 0; y < TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size(); y++)
11461  {
11462  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y);
11463  if((AVEntry.FormatType == TimeLoc) && (AVEntry.ArrivalTime >= TDateTime(0))) // arrival
11464  // TimeLoc (arr) -> No starts, repeats, Fer or TimeTimeLoc; TimeLoc (dep) or any other OK
11465  {
11466  if(y >= (TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size() - 1))
11467  {
11468  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - a timed arrival can't be the last event for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11469  TrainDataVector.clear();
11470  Utilities->CallLogPop(809);
11471  return false;
11472  }
11473  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry2 = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y + 1);
11474  if(!AtLocSuccessor(AVEntry2))
11475  {
11476  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - a timed arrival is followed by an illegal event for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode +
11477  ". The event isn't valid for a stationary train.");
11478  TrainDataVector.clear();
11479  Utilities->CallLogPop(810);
11480  return false;
11481  }
11482  }
11483  if((AVEntry.FormatType == TimeLoc) && (AVEntry.DepartureTime >= TDateTime(0))) // departure
11484  // TimeLoc (dep) -> Fer, TimeLoc (arr), TimeTimeLoc, (new) pas OK, no others
11485  {
11486  if(y >= (TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size() - 1))
11487  {
11488  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - a timed departure can't be the last event for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11489  TrainDataVector.clear();
11490  Utilities->CallLogPop(811);
11491  return false;
11492  }
11493  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry2 = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y + 1);
11494  if(!MovingSuccessor(AVEntry2))
11495  {
11496  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - a timed departure is followed by an illegal event for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode +
11497  ". The event isn't valid for a moving train.");
11498  TrainDataVector.clear();
11499  Utilities->CallLogPop(812);
11500  return false;
11501  }
11502  }
11503  }
11504  }
11505 
11506  // check all TimeLocs have either Arr or Dep time set and EventTime == -1, all Cmds have EventTime set & Arr & Dep times == -1,
11507  // & repeats have no times set
11508  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++)
11509  {
11510  const TTrainDataEntry &TDEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x);
11511  for(unsigned int y = 0; y < TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size(); y++)
11512  {
11513  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y);
11514  if(AVEntry.FormatType == TimeLoc)
11515  {
11516  if(AVEntry.EventTime != TDateTime(-1))
11517  {
11518  throw Exception("Timetable error, TimeLoc entry has EventTime not -1 for " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11519  }
11520  if((AVEntry.ArrivalTime == TDateTime(-1)) && (AVEntry.DepartureTime == TDateTime(-1)))
11521  {
11522  throw Exception("Timetable error, TimeLoc entry has neither arrival nor departure time set for " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11523  }
11524  }
11525  if(AVEntry.FormatType == TimeTimeLoc)
11526  {
11527  if(AVEntry.EventTime != TDateTime(-1))
11528  {
11529  throw Exception("Timetable error, TimeTimeLoc entry has EventTime not -1 for " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11530  }
11531  if((AVEntry.ArrivalTime == TDateTime(-1)) || (AVEntry.DepartureTime == TDateTime(-1)))
11532  {
11533  throw Exception("Timetable error, TimeTimeLoc entry has either arrival or departure time not set for " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11534  }
11535  }
11536  if((AVEntry.FormatType == TimeCmd) || (AVEntry.FormatType == TimeCmdHeadCode) || (AVEntry.FormatType == StartNew) ||
11537  (AVEntry.FormatType == SNTShuttle) || (AVEntry.FormatType == SNSShuttle) || (AVEntry.FormatType == FNSNonRepeatToShuttle) ||
11538  (AVEntry.FormatType == FSHNewService) || (AVEntry.FormatType == PassTime))
11539  {
11540  if(AVEntry.EventTime == TDateTime(-1))
11541  {
11542  throw Exception("Timetable error, Cmd or PassTime entry has EventTime not set for " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11543  }
11544  if((AVEntry.ArrivalTime != TDateTime(-1)) || (AVEntry.DepartureTime != TDateTime(-1)))
11545  {
11546  throw Exception("Timetable error, Cmd or PassTime entry has either arrival or departure time set for " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11547  }
11548  }
11549  if(AVEntry.FormatType == Repeat)
11550  {
11551  if((AVEntry.EventTime != TDateTime(-1)) || (AVEntry.ArrivalTime != TDateTime(-1)) || (AVEntry.DepartureTime != TDateTime(-1)))
11552  {
11553  throw Exception("Timetable error, Repeat entry has a time set for " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11554  }
11555  }
11556  }
11557  }
11558 
11559  // check times stay same or increase, note that can have time of 0 if include midnight
11560  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++)
11561  {
11562  TDateTime CurrentTime = TTClockTime; // the timetable start time
11563  const TTrainDataEntry &TDEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x);
11564  for(unsigned int y = 0; y < TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size(); y++)
11565  {
11566  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y);
11567  if(AVEntry.FormatType == Repeat)
11568  break;
11569  if(AVEntry.FormatType == FinRemHere)
11570  break;
11571  if(AVEntry.FormatType == TimeTimeLoc)
11572  {
11573  if(AVEntry.DepartureTime < AVEntry.ArrivalTime)
11574  {
11575  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - a timed arrival and departure has a later arrival than departure time for: " +
11576  TDEntry.HeadCode);
11577  TrainDataVector.clear();
11578  Utilities->CallLogPop(813);
11579  return false;
11580  }
11581  if(AVEntry.ArrivalTime < CurrentTime)
11582  {
11583  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - a timed arrival and departure has too early an arrival time for: " +
11584  TDEntry.HeadCode);
11585  TrainDataVector.clear();
11586  Utilities->CallLogPop(814);
11587  return false;
11588  }
11589  CurrentTime = AVEntry.DepartureTime;
11590  continue;
11591  }
11592  if(AVEntry.FormatType == TimeLoc)
11593  {
11594  if(AVEntry.ArrivalTime >= TDateTime(0))
11595  {
11596  if(AVEntry.ArrivalTime < CurrentTime)
11597  {
11598  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - a timed location event has a time that is too early for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11599  TrainDataVector.clear();
11600  Utilities->CallLogPop(815);
11601  return false;
11602  }
11603  CurrentTime = AVEntry.ArrivalTime;
11604  }
11605  else
11606  {
11607  if(AVEntry.DepartureTime < CurrentTime)
11608  // both may be 0 legitimately so must allow for this
11609  {
11610  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - a timed location event has a time that is too early for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11611  TrainDataVector.clear();
11612  Utilities->CallLogPop(816);
11613  return false;
11614  }
11615  CurrentTime = AVEntry.DepartureTime;
11616  }
11617  continue;
11618  }
11619  if(AVEntry.EventTime < CurrentTime)
11620  // all others have EventTime set
11621  {
11622  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - a train event has a time that is set too early for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode +
11623  ", may be before timetable start time");
11624  TrainDataVector.clear();
11625  Utilities->CallLogPop(835);
11626  return false;
11627  }
11628  CurrentTime = AVEntry.EventTime;
11629  continue;
11630  }
11631  }
11632 
11633  // check locations consistent
11634  AnsiString LastLocationName = "";
11635 
11636  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++)
11637  {
11638  bool LastEntryIsAnArrival = false;
11639  const TTrainDataEntry &TDEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x);
11640  // first deal with moving Snt entries (all else stopped)
11641  if((TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(0).Command == "Snt") && (TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(0).LocationType == EnRoute))
11642  {
11643  LastEntryIsAnArrival = false;
11644  LastLocationName = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(0).LocationName; // should be ""
11645  if(LastLocationName != "")
11646  {
11647  throw Exception("Timetable error, moving Snt entry has LocationName set for " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11648  }
11649  for(unsigned int y = 1; y < TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size();
11650  y++) // note that immediate successor to a moving Snt can only be a Moving type
11651  // if it's a SignallerControl entry then the condition isn't met
11652  {
11653  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y);
11654  if(AVEntry.FormatType == Repeat)
11655  break; // repeat = reached end (+allows repeat after signaller controlled entry)
11656  else if((AVEntry.FormatType == TimeCmdHeadCode) || (AVEntry.FormatType == FNSNonRepeatToShuttle))
11657  {
11658  if(AVEntry.LocationName != LastLocationName)
11659  {
11660  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - a location event is inconsistent for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode + " && " +
11661  AVEntry.Command);
11662  TrainDataVector.clear();
11663  Utilities->CallLogPop(823);
11664  return false;
11665  }
11666  }
11667  else if(AVEntry.FormatType == TimeCmd)
11668  // cdt is the only TimeCmd
11669  {
11670  if(AVEntry.LocationName != LastLocationName)
11671  {
11672  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - a location event is inconsistent for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode + " && " +
11673  AVEntry.Command);
11674  TrainDataVector.clear();
11675  Utilities->CallLogPop(824);
11676  return false;
11677  }
11678  }
11679  else if(AVEntry.FormatType == TimeTimeLoc)
11680  {
11681  if(AVEntry.LocationName == LastLocationName)
11682  // last entry must be a departure or would have failed earlier
11683  {
11684  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages,
11685  "Error in timetable - a location event in a timed arrival and departure is the same as the last location for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11686  TrainDataVector.clear();
11687  Utilities->CallLogPop(825);
11688  return false;
11689  }
11690  LastLocationName = AVEntry.LocationName;
11691  LastEntryIsAnArrival = false;
11692  }
11693  else if(AVEntry.FormatType == TimeLoc)
11694  {
11695  if(LastEntryIsAnArrival && (AVEntry.LocationName != LastLocationName))
11696  {
11697  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages,
11698  "Error in timetable - a location event for a timed departure is different from the arrival location for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11699  TrainDataVector.clear();
11700  Utilities->CallLogPop(826);
11701  return false;
11702  }
11703  else if(!LastEntryIsAnArrival && (AVEntry.LocationName == LastLocationName))
11704  {
11705  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages,
11706  "Error in timetable - a location event for a timed arrival is the same as the earlier departure location for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11707  TrainDataVector.clear();
11708  Utilities->CallLogPop(827);
11709  return false;
11710  }
11711  LastLocationName = AVEntry.LocationName;
11712  LastEntryIsAnArrival = !LastEntryIsAnArrival;
11713  }
11714  }
11715  }
11716  else // all stationary starting entries
11717  {
11718  LastEntryIsAnArrival = true;
11719  LastLocationName = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(0).LocationName;
11720  for(unsigned int y = 0; y < TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size(); y++)
11721  {
11722  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y);
11723  if(AVEntry.FormatType == Repeat)
11724  break;
11725  else if((AVEntry.FormatType == TimeCmdHeadCode) || (AVEntry.FormatType == FNSNonRepeatToShuttle))
11726  // no need to add anything for shuttle starts since they are at loc (0) anyway
11727  {
11728  if(AVEntry.LocationName != LastLocationName)
11729  {
11730  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - a location event is inconsistent for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode + " && " +
11731  AVEntry.Command);
11732  TrainDataVector.clear();
11733  Utilities->CallLogPop(828);
11734  return false;
11735  }
11736  }
11737  else if(AVEntry.FormatType == TimeCmd)
11738  // cdt is the only TimeCmd
11739  {
11740  if(AVEntry.LocationName != LastLocationName)
11741  {
11742  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - a location event is inconsistent for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode + " && " +
11743  AVEntry.Command);
11744  TrainDataVector.clear();
11745  Utilities->CallLogPop(829);
11746  return false;
11747  }
11748  }
11749  else if(AVEntry.FormatType == TimeTimeLoc)
11750  {
11751  if(AVEntry.LocationName == LastLocationName)
11752  // last entry must be a departure or would have failed earier
11753  {
11754  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages,
11755  "Error in timetable - a location event in a timed arrival and departure is the same as the last location for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11756  TrainDataVector.clear();
11757  Utilities->CallLogPop(830);
11758  return false;
11759  }
11760  LastLocationName = AVEntry.LocationName;
11761  LastEntryIsAnArrival = false;
11762  }
11763  else if(AVEntry.FormatType == TimeLoc)
11764  {
11765  if(LastEntryIsAnArrival && (AVEntry.LocationName != LastLocationName))
11766  {
11767  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages,
11768  "Error in timetable - a location event for a timed departure is different from the arrival location for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11769  TrainDataVector.clear();
11770  Utilities->CallLogPop(831);
11771  return false;
11772  }
11773  if(!LastEntryIsAnArrival && (AVEntry.LocationName == LastLocationName))
11774  {
11775  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages,
11776  "Error in timetable - a location event for a timed arrival is the same as the earlier departure location for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11777  TrainDataVector.clear();
11778  Utilities->CallLogPop(832);
11779  return false;
11780  }
11781  LastLocationName = AVEntry.LocationName;
11782  LastEntryIsAnArrival = !LastEntryIsAnArrival;
11783  }
11784  }
11785  }
11786  }
11787 
11788  // Check same location doesn't appear twice before a cdt except for separate arr & dep TimeLocs
11789  // i.e. same location can appear in any number of consecutive entries but once changed can't repeat
11790  // before a direction change
11791  AnsiString LocationNameToBeChecked = "";
11792 
11793  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++)
11794  {
11795  const TTrainDataEntry & TDEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x);
11796  unsigned int y = 0;
11797  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry0 = TDEntry.ActionVector.at(0);
11798  // first discard unlocated Snt entries as they don't have location name set
11799  if((AVEntry0.Command == "Snt") && (AVEntry0.LocationType == EnRoute))
11800  {
11801  y = 1;
11802  }
11803  while(y < TDEntry.ActionVector.size())
11804  // need to check each location name separately in turn, skipped for SignallerControl entries
11805  // if y == 1
11806  {
11807  if((TDEntry.ActionVector.at(y).Command == "Fer") || (TDEntry.ActionVector.at(y).FormatType == Repeat))
11808  {
11809  break; // out of the 'while' loop since have reached the end & 'Fer' & 'Repeat' have no location name set
11810  }
11811  LocationNameToBeChecked = TDEntry.ActionVector.at(y).LocationName;
11812  for(unsigned int z = y; z < TDEntry.ActionVector.size(); z++)
11813  {
11814  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry = TDEntry.ActionVector.at(z);
11815  if((AVEntry.Command == "Fer") || (AVEntry.FormatType == Repeat))
11816  {
11817  break; // out of the 'z' loop since have reached the end & 'Fer' & 'Repeat' have no location name set
11818  }
11819  if(AVEntry.Command == "cdt")
11820  {
11821  break; // out of the 'z' loop since the check is only valid up to a change of direction
11822  }
11823  if(AVEntry.LocationName == LocationNameToBeChecked)
11824  continue; // keep going while name same
11825  if(AVEntry.LocationName != LocationNameToBeChecked)
11826  // if name different check forwards to see if repeats
11827  {
11828  for(unsigned int a = z; a < TDEntry.ActionVector.size(); a++)
11829  {
11830  if(TDEntry.ActionVector.at(a).Command == "cdt")
11831  {
11832  break; // out of the 'a' & 'z' loops since the check is only valid up to a change of direction
11833  }
11834  if(TDEntry.ActionVector.at(a).LocationName == LocationNameToBeChecked)
11835  {
11836  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - a location entry appears twice inappropriately for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11837  TrainDataVector.clear();
11838  Utilities->CallLogPop(833);
11839  return false;
11840  }
11841  }
11842  break; // out of the 'z' loop since have checked 'a' as far as need to
11843  }
11844  }
11845  y++;
11846  }
11847  }
11848 
11849  // check all locations except unlocated 'Snt' & 'Fer' have LocationName set
11850  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++)
11851  {
11852  const TTrainDataEntry &TDEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x);
11853  for(unsigned int y = 0; y < TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size(); y++)
11854  {
11855  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y);
11856  if((AVEntry.LocationName == "") && (AVEntry.Command != "Snt") && (AVEntry.Command != "Fer") && (AVEntry.FormatType != Repeat))
11857  {
11858  throw Exception("Error, non- 'Snt', 'Fer' or Repeat entry doesn't have a location name set for " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11859  }
11860  AnsiString LocName = "";
11861  // dummy, only used so can call IsSNTEntryLocated
11862  if((AVEntry.Command == "Snt") && (IsSNTEntryLocated(1, TrainDataVector.at(x), LocName)))
11863  {
11864  if(AVEntry.LocationName == "")
11865  {
11866  throw Exception("Error, 'Snt' entry at a stop location doesn't have a location name set for " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11867  }
11868  }
11869  if((AVEntry.Command == "Snt") && !(IsSNTEntryLocated(2, TrainDataVector.at(x), LocName)))
11870  {
11871  if(AVEntry.LocationName != "")
11872  {
11873  throw Exception("Error, 'Snt' unlocated entry has a location name set for " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
11874  }
11875  }
11876  }
11877  }
11878 
11879 /* Check a split to 'x' doesn't again split to 'x' (anywhere, not just for one train, since headcodes can be duplicated)
11880  Check each joined by train not joined by same train again (anywhere, not just for one train, since headcodes can be duplicated)
11881  Check each change of headcode not repeated anywhere else (anywhere, not just for one train, since headcodes can be duplicated)
11882 
11883  i.e. check everywhere where there is an 'OtherHeadCode' that it matches once only with its reference (both ways) + set
11884  the OtherHeadCodeStartingEntryPtr pointers where appropriate + train information for splits & new services
11885 
11886  BUT need to separate the shuttles from non-shuttles, because can have two trains reference each other in both forms,
11887  eg 2F44 Sns-sh ends in Fns to 2F45, & Sns 2F45 ends in Fns-sh to 2F44. Here 2F45 is the 'OtherHeadCode' for both
11888  Sns-sh & Fns in train 2F44, & 2F44 is the 'OtherHeadCode' for both Sns & Fns-sh in train 2F45.
11889 */
11890  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++) // new test to ensure no duplicate links at all, other checks ensure none for shuttles,
11891  // non-shuttles & non-repeating links separately, but don't check that there isn't a
11892  // duplicate between a non-repeating shuttle and another - leave original tests in as
11893  // these also set the pointers
11894  {
11895  const TTrainDataEntry &TDEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x);
11896  for(unsigned int y = 0; y < TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size(); y++)
11897  {
11898  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y);
11899  if(AVEntry.OtherHeadCode != "")
11900  {
11901  if(!CheckForDuplicateCrossReferences(0, TDEntry.HeadCode, AVEntry.OtherHeadCode, GiveMessages))
11902  {
11903  Utilities->CallLogPop(1584);
11904  return false; // error message given in called function
11905  }
11906  }
11907  if(AVEntry.NonRepeatingShuttleLinkHeadCode != "")
11908  {
11909  if(!CheckForDuplicateCrossReferences(1, TDEntry.HeadCode, AVEntry.NonRepeatingShuttleLinkHeadCode, GiveMessages))
11910  {
11911  Utilities->CallLogPop(1585);
11912  return false; // error message given in called function
11913  }
11914  }
11915  }
11916  }
11917 
11918  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++)
11919  {
11920  const TTrainDataEntry &TDEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x);
11921  for(unsigned int y = 0; y < TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size(); y++)
11922  {
11923  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y);
11924  if((AVEntry.Command != "Sns-sh") && (AVEntry.Command != "Snt-sh") && (AVEntry.Command != "Fns-sh") && (AVEntry.Command != "Frh-sh"))
11925  {
11926  if(AVEntry.OtherHeadCode != "")
11927  {
11928  if(!CheckCrossReferencesAndSetData(0, TDEntry.HeadCode, AVEntry.OtherHeadCode, false, GiveMessages))
11929  // false = non-shuttle
11930  {
11931  Utilities->CallLogPop(864);
11932  return false; // error message given in called function
11933  }
11934  }
11935  }
11936  }
11937  }
11938 
11939  // now repeat the check just for the shuttles
11940  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++)
11941  {
11942  const TTrainDataEntry &TDEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x);
11943  for(unsigned int y = 0; y < TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size(); y++)
11944  {
11945  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y);
11946  if((AVEntry.Command == "Sns-sh") || (AVEntry.Command == "Snt-sh") || (AVEntry.Command == "Fns-sh") || (AVEntry.Command == "Frh-sh"))
11947  {
11948  if(AVEntry.OtherHeadCode != "")
11949  {
11950  if(!CheckCrossReferencesAndSetData(1, TDEntry.HeadCode, AVEntry.OtherHeadCode, true, GiveMessages))
11951  // true = shuttle
11952  {
11953  Utilities->CallLogPop(1100);
11954  return false; // error message given in called function
11955  }
11956  }
11957  }
11958  }
11959  }
11960 
11961  // check for proper non-repeating link cross references and that they have no repeats & that times are consistent
11962  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++)
11963  {
11964  const TTrainDataEntry &TDEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x);
11965  for(unsigned int y = 0; y < TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size(); y++)
11966  {
11967  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y);
11968  if(AVEntry.NonRepeatingShuttleLinkHeadCode != "")
11969  {
11970  if(!CheckNonRepeatingShuttleLinksAndSetData(0, TDEntry.HeadCode, AVEntry.NonRepeatingShuttleLinkHeadCode, GiveMessages))
11971  {
11972  Utilities->CallLogPop(1060);
11973  return false; // error message given in called function
11974  }
11975  }
11976  }
11977  }
11978 
11979  // check that each shuttle start ends either in Fns or Fxx-sh (though a single service can't end in Fxx-sh), and that
11980  // when the Fxx-sh is reached it references the original start and not another shuttle - not allowed to link two shuttles,
11981  // don't ever need to and as designed would skip repeats
11982  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++)
11983  {
11984  for(unsigned int y = 0; y < TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size(); y++)
11985  {
11986  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y);
11987  if((AVEntry.Command == "Sns-sh") || (AVEntry.Command == "Snt-sh"))
11988  {
11989  if(!CheckShuttleServiceIntegrity(0, &(TrainDataVector.at(x)), GiveMessages))
11990  {
11991  Utilities->CallLogPop(1090);
11992  return false; // error message given in called function
11993  }
11994  }
11995  }
11996  }
11997 
11998  // check all entries have all types set to something
11999  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++)
12000  {
12001  const TTrainDataEntry &TDEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x);
12002  for(unsigned int y = 0; y < TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size(); y++)
12003  {
12004  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y);
12005  if(AVEntry.FormatType == NoFormat)
12006  {
12007  throw Exception("Error - timetable ActionVector entry no. " + AnsiString(y) + " has FormatType unset for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
12008  }
12009  else if(AVEntry.SequenceType == NoSequence)
12010  {
12011  throw Exception("Error - timetable ActionVector entry no. " + AnsiString(y) + " has SequenceType unset for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
12012  }
12013  else if(AVEntry.LocationType == NoLocation)
12014  {
12015  throw Exception("Error - timetable ActionVector entry no. " + AnsiString(y) + " has LocationType unset for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
12016  }
12017  else if(AVEntry.ShuttleLinkType == NoShuttleLink)
12018  {
12019  throw Exception("Error - timetable ActionVector entry no. " + AnsiString(y) + " has ShuttleLinkType unset for: " + TDEntry.HeadCode);
12020  }
12021  }
12022  }
12023 
12024  // all OK if reach here, so set up the TrainOperatingDataVector (already has one entry) & NumberOfTrains
12025  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++)
12026  {
12027  TTrainDataEntry & TDEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x);
12028  // non-const reference so can alter content
12029  TTrainOperatingData TData;
12030  const TActionVectorEntry &LastAVEntry = TDEntry.ActionVector.at(TDEntry.ActionVector.size() - 1);
12031  if(LastAVEntry.FormatType == Repeat) // check if a repeat
12032  {
12033 /*
12034  class TTrainOperatingData
12035  {
12036  public:
12037  int TrainID; - default, set at construction
12038  TActionEventType EventReported; used during operation
12039  TRunningEntry RunningEntry; - default, set at construction
12040  TTrainOperatingData() {TrainID = -1; EventReported= NoEvent; RunningEntry=NotStarted;} //constructor, values set to defaults
12041  };
12042 */
12043  TDEntry.NumberOfTrains = LastAVEntry.NumberOfRepeats + 1;
12044  for(int y = 1; y < TDEntry.NumberOfTrains; y++)
12045  {
12046  TDEntry.TrainOperatingDataVector.push_back(TData);
12047  }
12048  }
12049  else
12050  TDEntry.NumberOfTrains = 1;
12051  }
12052 
12053  // check that don't include any Continuation names
12054  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++)
12055  {
12056  for(unsigned int y = 0; y < TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size(); y++)
12057  {
12058  AnsiString LocName = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y).LocationName;
12059  AnsiString HC = TrainDataVector.at(x).HeadCode;
12060  if(LocName != "")
12061  {
12062  if(Track->ContinuationNameMap.find(LocName) != Track->ContinuationNameMap.end())
12063  {
12064  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - continuation names (" + LocName + ") must not be included, see service " + HC);
12065  TrainDataVector.clear();
12066  Utilities->CallLogPop(1578);
12067  return false;
12068  }
12069  }
12070  }
12071  }
12072 
12073  // check that all repeat times below 96h
12074  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++)
12075  {
12076  int NumRepeats = (TrainDataVector.at(x).NumberOfTrains) - 1;
12077  int IncMinutes = 0;
12078  if(TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size() - 1).FormatType == Repeat)
12079  {
12080  IncMinutes = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size() - 1).RearStartOrRepeatMins;
12081  }
12082  else
12083  continue; // basic times already checked in CheckTimeValidity
12084  AnsiString HC = TrainDataVector.at(x).HeadCode;
12085  for(unsigned int y = 0; y < TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size(); y++)
12086  {
12087  if((double)TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y).EventTime > -1)
12088  {
12089  if(((double)GetRepeatTime(32, TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y).EventTime, NumRepeats, IncMinutes) >= 3.9994))
12090  {
12091  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - a repeat time exceeds 95h 59m, see service " + HC); // 3d 23h 59m = 3.9993055556
12092  TrainDataVector.clear();
12093  Utilities->CallLogPop(1818);
12094  return false;
12095  }
12096  }
12097  if((double)TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y).ArrivalTime > -1)
12098  {
12099  if(((double)GetRepeatTime(33, TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y).EventTime, NumRepeats, IncMinutes) >= 3.9994))
12100  // 3d 23h 59m = 3.9993055556
12101  {
12102  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - a repeat entry time exceeds 95h 59m, see service " + HC);
12103  TrainDataVector.clear();
12104  Utilities->CallLogPop(1819);
12105  return false;
12106  }
12107  }
12108  if((double)TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y).DepartureTime > -1)
12109  {
12110  if(((double)GetRepeatTime(34, TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y).EventTime, NumRepeats, IncMinutes) >= 3.9994))
12111  // 3d 23h 59m = 3.9993055556
12112  {
12113  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - a repeat entry time exceeds 95h 59m, see service " + HC);
12114  TrainDataVector.clear();
12115  Utilities->CallLogPop(1820);
12116  return false;
12117  }
12118  }
12119  }
12120  }
12121 
12122  // Now that all set up change any extended headcodes back to ordinary headcodes
12123  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++)
12124  {
12125  StripExcessFromHeadCode(0, TrainDataVector.at(x).HeadCode);
12126  for(unsigned int y = 0; y < TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size(); y++)
12127  {
12128  StripExcessFromHeadCode(1, TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y).OtherHeadCode);
12129  StripExcessFromHeadCode(2, TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y).NonRepeatingShuttleLinkHeadCode);
12130  }
12131  }
12132 
12133  // SaveTrainDataVectorToFile(0);//test
12134  BuildContinuationTrainExpectationMultiMap(0);
12135  Utilities->CallLogPop(782);
12136  return true;
12137 }
12138 
12139 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
12140 // Moving successors: TimeLoc arr/TimeTimeLoc/pas/Fer;
12141 bool TTrainController::MovingSuccessor(const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry)
12142 {
12143  return ((AVEntry.FormatType == TimeLoc) || (AVEntry.FormatType == TimeTimeLoc) || (AVEntry.Command == "pas") || (AVEntry.Command == "Fer"));
12144 }
12145 
12146 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
12147 // AtLoc successors: TimeLoc dep/jbo/fsp/rsp/cdt/Frh/Fns/Fjo/Frh-sh/Fns-sh/F-nshs;
12148 bool TTrainController::AtLocSuccessor(const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry)
12149 {
12150  return ((AVEntry.FormatType == TimeLoc) || (AVEntry.Command == "jbo") || (AVEntry.Command == "fsp") || (AVEntry.Command == "rsp") ||
12151  (AVEntry.Command == "cdt") || (AVEntry.Command == "Frh") || (AVEntry.Command == "Fns") || (AVEntry.Command == "Fjo") || (AVEntry.Command == "Frh-sh") ||
12152  (AVEntry.Command == "Fns-sh") || (AVEntry.Command == "F-nshs"));
12153 }
