12157 void TTrainController::StripExcessFromHeadCode(int Caller, AnsiString &HeadCode)
12158 {
12159  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",StripExcessFromHeadCode," + HeadCode);
12160  if(HeadCode.Length() > 4) // ignore otherwise
12161  {
12162  HeadCode = HeadCode.SubString(HeadCode.Length() - 3, 4);
12163  }
12164  Utilities->CallLogPop(1593);
12165 }
12166 
12167 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
12168 
12169 bool TTrainController::CheckForDuplicateCrossReferences(int Caller, AnsiString MainHeadCode, AnsiString SecondHeadCode, bool GiveMessages)
12170 {
12171  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",CheckForDuplicateCrossReferences," + MainHeadCode + "," +
12172  SecondHeadCode);
12173  int ForwardCount = 0;
12174  int ReverseCount = 0;
12175 
12176  if(MainHeadCode == SecondHeadCode)
12177  {
12178  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - Service " + MainHeadCode + " has an event that references itself");
12179  TrainDataVector.clear();
12180  Utilities->CallLogPop(1594);
12181  return false;
12182  }
12183 
12184  // forward check
12185  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++)
12186  {
12187  const TTrainDataEntry &TDEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x);
12188  if(TDEntry.HeadCode == MainHeadCode)
12189  {
12190  for(unsigned int y = 0; y < TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size(); y++)
12191  {
12192  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y);
12193  if(AVEntry.OtherHeadCode == SecondHeadCode)
12194  {
12195  ForwardCount++;
12196  }
12197  if(AVEntry.NonRepeatingShuttleLinkHeadCode == SecondHeadCode)
12198  // need own check in case both 'Other' & 'NonRepeating' have same headcode
12199  {
12200  ForwardCount++;
12201  }
12202  }
12203  }
12204  }
12205  if(ForwardCount == 0)
12206  // this is an exception because the headcodes are selected in the same order as the forward check
12207  {
12208  throw Exception("Error, ForwardCount == 0 in CheckForDuplicateCrossReferences after called with found values");
12209  }
12210 
12211  if(ForwardCount > 2)
12212  // can have 2 if one is Sns-sh linking from another leg of the shuttle, and Fns links out to that same leg
12213  {
12214  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - found more than two references to " + SecondHeadCode + " from a train whose headcode is " +
12215  MainHeadCode + ". Check the service cross references from each service, and check whether one or other service is listed twice or more.");
12216  TrainDataVector.clear();
12217  Utilities->CallLogPop(1587);
12218  return false;
12219  }
12220 
12221  // reverse check
12222  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++)
12223  {
12224  const TTrainDataEntry &TDEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x);
12225  if(TDEntry.HeadCode == SecondHeadCode)
12226  {
12227  for(unsigned int y = 0; y < TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size(); y++)
12228  {
12229  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y);
12230  if(AVEntry.OtherHeadCode == MainHeadCode)
12231  {
12232  ReverseCount++;
12233  }
12234  if(AVEntry.NonRepeatingShuttleLinkHeadCode == MainHeadCode)
12235  {
12236  ReverseCount++;
12237  }
12238  }
12239  }
12240  }
12241 
12242  if(ReverseCount == 0)
12243  {
12244  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - cross reference missing in either " + MainHeadCode + " or " + SecondHeadCode);
12245  TrainDataVector.clear();
12246  Utilities->CallLogPop(1588);
12247  return false;
12248  }
12249  if(ReverseCount > 2)
12250  // can have 2 if one is a second shuttle leg with a link in from Fns, and it links out to the same service with Fxx-sh
12251  {
12252  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - found more than two references to " + MainHeadCode + " from a train whose headcode is " +
12253  SecondHeadCode + ". Check the service cross references from each service, and check whether one or other service is listed twice or more.");
12254  TrainDataVector.clear();
12255  Utilities->CallLogPop(1589);
12256  return false;
12257  }
12258 
12259  if(ForwardCount != ReverseCount)
12260  {
12261  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - " + MainHeadCode + " has a different number of references to " + SecondHeadCode +
12262  " than the other way round");
12263  TrainDataVector.clear();
12264  Utilities->CallLogPop(1610);
12265  return false;
12266  }
12267 
12268  Utilities->CallLogPop(1590);
12269  return true;
12270 }
12271 
12272 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
12273 
12274 bool TTrainController::CheckCrossReferencesAndSetData(int Caller, AnsiString MainHeadCode, AnsiString OtherHeadCode, bool Shuttle, bool GiveMessages)
12275 /* Return false for no find or more than one find, check correct types of link
12276  First run through all trains whose headcode is the MainHeadCode (may be > 1) & for each entry whose
12277  'other' is OtherHeadCode increment a forward counter. Keep a pointer to the 'OtherHeadCode' entry for use later
12278  Must be exactly 1 forward count. NB Forward relates to MainHeadCode
12279  Then do the same in reverse.
12280  Using the pointers check the event times, then check that the locations & commands match - if main is a split then other must be Sfs;
12281  if main is Fns other must be Sns; if main is jbo other must be Fjo.
12282  Also check platform lengths OK for a split location (call to Track function for this - at least one platform at location has to be long
12283  enough). If all succeeds so far set the relevant OtherHeadCodeStartingEntryPtr to the new service starting point + train information
12284  for Sfs & Sns services. Finally check the repeat entries if present are consistent
12285 
12286  Check all except the NonRepeatingShuttleLinkHeadCodes, which only occur from F-nshs to Sns-sh, and from Fns-sh to
12287  Sns-fsh. All others should check out OK, but check shuttles & non-shuttles separately.
12288 
12289  /NB prohibit main & other headcodes being same, causes probs in failing to recognise locations
12290 */
12291 
12292 {
12293  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",CheckCrossReferencesAndSetData," + MainHeadCode + "," + OtherHeadCode);
12294  int ForwardCount = 0;
12295  int ReverseCount = 0;
12296  unsigned int ForwardTDVectorNumber, ReverseTDVectorNumber;
12297  TActionVectorEntry *ReverseEntryPtr = 0, *ForwardEntryPtr = 0;
12298  TTrainDataEntry *MainTrainDataPtr = 0;
12299  TTrainDataEntry *OtherTrainDataPtr = 0;
12300 
12301  // forward check
12302  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++)
12303  {
12304  const TTrainDataEntry &TDEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x);
12305  if(TDEntry.HeadCode == MainHeadCode)
12306  {
12307  for(unsigned int y = 0; y < TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size(); y++)
12308  {
12309  TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y);
12310  if(!Shuttle && (AVEntry.Command != "Sns-sh") && (AVEntry.Command != "Snt-sh") && (AVEntry.Command != "Fns-sh") && (AVEntry.Command != "Frh-sh"))
12311  {
12312  if(AVEntry.OtherHeadCode == OtherHeadCode)
12313  {
12314  MainTrainDataPtr = &TrainDataVector.at(x);
12315  ForwardEntryPtr = &AVEntry;
12316  ForwardCount++;
12317  ForwardTDVectorNumber = x;
12318  }
12319  }
12320  else if(Shuttle && ((AVEntry.Command == "Sns-sh") || (AVEntry.Command == "Snt-sh") || (AVEntry.Command == "Fns-sh") ||
12321  (AVEntry.Command == "Frh-sh")))
12322  {
12323  if(AVEntry.OtherHeadCode == OtherHeadCode)
12324  {
12325  MainTrainDataPtr = &TrainDataVector.at(x);
12326  ForwardEntryPtr = &AVEntry;
12327  ForwardCount++;
12328  ForwardTDVectorNumber = x;
12329  }
12330  }
12331  }
12332  }
12333  }
12334  if(ForwardCount == 0)
12335  // this is an exception because the headcodes are selected in the same order as the forward check
12336  {
12337  throw Exception("Error, ForwardCount == 0 in CheckCrossReferencesAndSetData after called with found values");
12338  }
12339  if(ForwardCount > 1)
12340  {
12341  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - found more than one reference to " + OtherHeadCode + " from a train whose headcode is " +
12342  MainHeadCode);
12343  TrainDataVector.clear();
12344  Utilities->CallLogPop(836);
12345  return false;
12346  }
12347 
12348  // reverse check
12349  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++)
12350  {
12351  const TTrainDataEntry &TDEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x);
12352  if(TDEntry.HeadCode == OtherHeadCode)
12353  {
12354  for(unsigned int y = 0; y < TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size(); y++)
12355  {
12356  TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y);
12357  if(!Shuttle && (AVEntry.Command != "Sns-sh") && (AVEntry.Command != "Snt-sh") && (AVEntry.Command != "Fns-sh") && (AVEntry.Command != "Frh-sh"))
12358  {
12359  if(AVEntry.OtherHeadCode == MainHeadCode)
12360  {
12361  OtherTrainDataPtr = &TrainDataVector.at(x);
12362  ReverseCount++;
12363  ReverseEntryPtr = &AVEntry;
12364  ReverseTDVectorNumber = x;
12365  }
12366  }
12367  else if(Shuttle && ((AVEntry.Command == "Sns-sh") || (AVEntry.Command == "Snt-sh") || (AVEntry.Command == "Fns-sh") || (AVEntry.Command == "Frh-sh")))
12368  {
12369  if(AVEntry.OtherHeadCode == MainHeadCode)
12370  {
12371  OtherTrainDataPtr = &TrainDataVector.at(x);
12372  ReverseCount++;
12373  ReverseEntryPtr = &AVEntry;
12374  ReverseTDVectorNumber = x;
12375  }
12376  }
12377  }
12378  }
12379  }
12380 
12381  if(ReverseCount == 0)
12382  {
12383  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - cross reference missing in either " + MainHeadCode + " or " + OtherHeadCode);
12384  TrainDataVector.clear();
12385  Utilities->CallLogPop(837);
12386  return false;
12387  }
12388  if(ReverseCount > 1)
12389  {
12390  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - found more than one reference to " + MainHeadCode + " from a train whose headcode is " +
12391  OtherHeadCode);
12392  TrainDataVector.clear();
12393  Utilities->CallLogPop(838);
12394  return false;
12395  }
12396 
12397  // these will all be false for !Shuttle
12398  bool ForwardShuttleStart = ((ForwardEntryPtr->Command == "Sns-sh") || (ForwardEntryPtr->Command == "Snt-sh"));
12399  bool ForwardShuttleFinish = ((ForwardEntryPtr->Command == "Fns-sh") || (ForwardEntryPtr->Command == "Frh-sh"));
12400  bool ReverseShuttleStart = ((ReverseEntryPtr->Command == "Sns-sh") || (ReverseEntryPtr->Command == "Snt-sh"));
12401  bool ReverseShuttleFinish = ((ReverseEntryPtr->Command == "Fns-sh") || (ReverseEntryPtr->Command == "Frh-sh"));
12402 
12403  if(Shuttle && MainTrainDataPtr->ActionVector.back().FormatType != Repeat)
12404  {
12405  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - shuttle train " + MainHeadCode + " does not have a repeat");
12406  TrainDataVector.clear();
12407  Utilities->CallLogPop(1058);
12408  return false;
12409  }
12410 
12411  if(Shuttle && OtherTrainDataPtr->ActionVector.back().FormatType != Repeat)
12412  {
12413  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - shuttle train " + OtherHeadCode + " does not have a repeat");
12414  TrainDataVector.clear();
12415  Utilities->CallLogPop(1059);
12416  return false;
12417  }
12418 
12419  if(ForwardEntryPtr->LocationName == "")
12420  {
12421  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - location error in cross referenced trains " + MainHeadCode + " and " + OtherHeadCode +
12422  ". One or other service does not have a location set");
12423  TrainDataVector.clear();
12424  Utilities->CallLogPop(526);
12425  return false;
12426  }
12427 
12428  if(ReverseEntryPtr->LocationName == "")
12429  {
12430  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - location error in cross referenced trains " + MainHeadCode + " and " + OtherHeadCode +
12431  ". One or other service does not have a location set");
12432  TrainDataVector.clear();
12433  Utilities->CallLogPop(527);
12434  return false;
12435  }
12436 
12437  if(ForwardEntryPtr->LocationName != ReverseEntryPtr->LocationName)
12438  {
12439  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - cross referenced train " + OtherHeadCode +
12440  " is at a different location to the referencing train " + MainHeadCode);
12441  TrainDataVector.clear();
12442  Utilities->CallLogPop(842);
12443  return false;
12444  }
12445 
12446  // ignore shuttle repeat links for first time check
12447  if(!Shuttle)
12448  {
12449  if(ForwardEntryPtr->EventTime != ReverseEntryPtr->EventTime)
12450  {
12451  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - cross referenced train " + OtherHeadCode +
12452  " has a different event time to the referencing train " + MainHeadCode);
12453  TrainDataVector.clear();
12454  Utilities->CallLogPop(525);
12455  return false;
12456  }
12457  }
12458 
12459  // need to allow for repeat times multiplying up by repeating time for shuttle repeat links
12460  // no need to check from reverse to forward as already checked links consistent, and if include will send message twice
12461  if(ForwardShuttleStart && ReverseShuttleFinish)
12462  // Shuttle must be true if these are true
12463  {
12464  if(!CheckShuttleRepeatTime(0, ForwardEntryPtr->EventTime, ReverseEntryPtr->EventTime, OtherTrainDataPtr->ActionVector.back().RearStartOrRepeatMins))
12465  {
12466  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - shuttle service " + MainHeadCode +
12467  " first repeat restart time not consistent with finish service " + OtherHeadCode);
12468  TrainDataVector.clear();
12469  Utilities->CallLogPop(1055);
12470  return false;
12471  }
12472  }
12473 
12474  if((ReverseEntryPtr->Command == "Sfs") || (ReverseEntryPtr->Command == "Sns"))
12475  // doesn't matter about ForwardEntryPtr being Sfs/Sns as called for every occurrence of an 'OtherHeadCode' so won't escape
12476  {
12477  if(ReverseTDVectorNumber == ForwardTDVectorNumber)
12478  {
12479  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - an 'Sfs' or 'Sns' event (" + OtherHeadCode +
12480  ") appears in the same sequence as the corresponding linked event " + MainHeadCode);
12481  TrainDataVector.clear();
12482  Utilities->CallLogPop(528);
12483  return false;
12484  }
12485  }
12486 
12487  if(ReverseEntryPtr->Command == "Fjo")
12488  // doesn't matter about ForwardEntryPtr being Fjo as called for every occurrence of an 'OtherHeadCode' so won't escape
12489  {
12490  if(ReverseTDVectorNumber == ForwardTDVectorNumber)
12491  {
12492  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - an 'Fjo' event (" + OtherHeadCode +
12493  ") appears in the same sequence as the corresponding linked event " + MainHeadCode);
12494  TrainDataVector.clear();
12495  Utilities->CallLogPop(862);
12496  return false;
12497  }
12498  }
12499 
12500  if(ReverseEntryPtr->Command == "Fns")
12501  // doesn't matter about ForwardEntryPtr being Fns as called for every occurrence of an 'OtherHeadCode' so won't escape
12502  {
12503  if(ReverseTDVectorNumber == ForwardTDVectorNumber)
12504  {
12505  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - an 'Fns' event (" + OtherHeadCode +
12506  ") appears in the same sequence as the corresponding linked event " + MainHeadCode);
12507  TrainDataVector.clear();
12508  Utilities->CallLogPop(529);
12509  return false;
12510  }
12511  }
12512 
12513  if(ForwardEntryPtr->Command == "Sfs")
12514  {
12515  if((ReverseEntryPtr->Command != "fsp") && (ReverseEntryPtr->Command != "rsp"))
12516  {
12517  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages,
12518  "Error in timetable - unable to find a corresponding split train event for the train that starts from a split whose headcode is " +
12519  MainHeadCode);
12520  TrainDataVector.clear();
12521  Utilities->CallLogPop(530);
12522  return false;
12523  }
12524  }
12525 
12526  if((ForwardEntryPtr->Command == "fsp") || (ForwardEntryPtr->Command == "rsp"))
12527  {
12528  if(ReverseEntryPtr->Command != "Sfs")
12529  {
12530  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - unable to find a corresponding 'Sfs' event for the train split whose headcode is " +
12531  MainHeadCode);
12532  TrainDataVector.clear();
12533  Utilities->CallLogPop(839);
12534  return false;
12535  }
12536  else
12537  {
12538  if(!(Track->TimetabledLocationNameAllocated(4, ForwardEntryPtr->LocationName)))
12539  {
12540  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - can't find timetabled location '" + ForwardEntryPtr->LocationName + "' in railway");
12541  TrainDataVector.clear();
12542  Utilities->CallLogPop(849);
12543  return false;
12544  }
12545  if(!(Track->OneNamedLocationElementAtLocation(0, ForwardEntryPtr->LocationName)))
12546  {
12547  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - can't find any named location elements at '" + ForwardEntryPtr->LocationName + "'");
12548  TrainDataVector.clear();
12549  Utilities->CallLogPop(850);
12550  return false;
12551  }
12552  if(!(Track->OneNamedLocationLongEnoughForSplit(0, ForwardEntryPtr->LocationName)))
12553  {
12554  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - location too short to split a train at " + ForwardEntryPtr->LocationName);
12555  TrainDataVector.clear();
12556  Utilities->CallLogPop(846);
12557  return false;
12558  }
12559  ForwardEntryPtr->LinkedTrainEntryPtr = OtherTrainDataPtr;
12560  ReverseEntryPtr->LinkedTrainEntryPtr = MainTrainDataPtr;
12561  if(OtherTrainDataPtr->Description == "")
12562  OtherTrainDataPtr->Description = MainTrainDataPtr->Description;
12563  // NB: May not be set if main train is a service continuation without a description, if so can't do much about it but doesn't affect operation, just the train information display
12564  OtherTrainDataPtr->MaxRunningSpeed = MainTrainDataPtr->MaxRunningSpeed;
12565  // Probably redundant as this is continued from the earlier service when the changeover happens (also may not be set here yet if a service continuation)
12566  }
12567  }
12568 
12569  if(ForwardEntryPtr->Command == "Sns")
12570  {
12571  if(ReverseEntryPtr->Command != "Fns")
12572  {
12573  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - unable to find a corresponding 'Fns' event for the 'Sns' train whose headcode is " +
12574  MainHeadCode + " and is formed from a service with headcode " + OtherHeadCode);
12575  TrainDataVector.clear();
12576  Utilities->CallLogPop(531);
12577  return false;
12578  }
12579  }
12580 
12581  if(ForwardEntryPtr->Command == "Fns")
12582  {
12583  if(ReverseEntryPtr->Command != "Sns")
12584  {
12585  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - unable to find a corresponding 'Sns' event for the train whose headcode is " + MainHeadCode +
12586  " and forms a new service with headcode " + OtherHeadCode);
12587  TrainDataVector.clear();
12588  Utilities->CallLogPop(840);
12589  return false;
12590  }
12591  else
12592  {
12593  ForwardEntryPtr->LinkedTrainEntryPtr = OtherTrainDataPtr;
12594  ReverseEntryPtr->LinkedTrainEntryPtr = MainTrainDataPtr;
12595  if(OtherTrainDataPtr->Description == "")
12596  OtherTrainDataPtr->Description = MainTrainDataPtr->Description;
12597  // Probably redundant as this is continued from the earlier service when the changeover happens (also may not be set here yet if a service continuation)
12598  OtherTrainDataPtr->MaxRunningSpeed = MainTrainDataPtr->MaxRunningSpeed;
12599  // Probably redundant as this is continued from the earlier service when the changeover happens (also may not be set here yet if a service continuation)
12600  }
12601  }
12602  if(ForwardEntryPtr->Command == "jbo")
12603  {
12604  if(ReverseEntryPtr->Command != "Fjo")
12605  {
12606  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - unable to find a corresponding 'Fjo' event for the train whose headcode is " + MainHeadCode +
12607  " and is joined by a train with headcode " + OtherHeadCode);
12608  TrainDataVector.clear();
12609  Utilities->CallLogPop(841);
12610  return false;
12611  }
12612  }
12613 
12614  if(ForwardEntryPtr->Command == "Fjo")
12615  {
12616  if(ReverseEntryPtr->Command != "jbo")
12617  {
12618  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - unable to find a corresponding 'jbo' event for the train whose headcode is " + MainHeadCode +
12619  " and joins a train with headcode " + OtherHeadCode);
12620  TrainDataVector.clear();
12621  Utilities->CallLogPop(532);
12622  return false;
12623  }
12624  else
12625  {
12626  ForwardEntryPtr->LinkedTrainEntryPtr = OtherTrainDataPtr;
12627  ReverseEntryPtr->LinkedTrainEntryPtr = MainTrainDataPtr;
12628  if((MainTrainDataPtr->MaxRunningSpeed > 5) && (MainTrainDataPtr->MaxRunningSpeed < OtherTrainDataPtr->MaxRunningSpeed))
12629  OtherTrainDataPtr->MaxRunningSpeed = MainTrainDataPtr->MaxRunningSpeed;
12630  // added test for > 5 [5 used instead of 0 because of possible floating point errors - though unlikely] above at v1.3.1 because the train will have a zero MaxRunningSpeed if it continues from another service - its max speed is set when it takes over from the other service
12631  // notified of this problem by Ian Walker in his email of 25/03/13. Probably redundant anyway because the max speed is reduced at the changeover if the 'joined by' train's max speed is less.
12632  }
12633  }
12634 
12635  if(ForwardShuttleStart)
12636  // (ForwardEntryPtr->Command == "Sns-sh") || (ForwardEntryPtr->Command == "Snt-sh"))
12637  {
12638  if(!ReverseShuttleFinish)
12639  // (ReverseEntryPtr->Command != "Fns-sh") && (ReverseEntryPtr->Command != "Frh-sh"))
12640  {
12641  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - incorrect shuttle link to train whose headcode is " + MainHeadCode +
12642  " from train whose headcode is " + OtherHeadCode + ", has to be Fns-sh, Frh-sh");
12643  TrainDataVector.clear();
12644  Utilities->CallLogPop(1056);
12645  return false;
12646  }
12647  }
12648 
12649  if(ReverseShuttleStart)
12650  // (ReverseEntryPtr->Command == "Sns-sh") || (ReverseEntryPtr->Command == "Snt-sh"))
12651  {
12652  if(!ForwardShuttleFinish)
12653  // (ForwardEntryPtr->Command != "Fns-sh") && (ForwardEntryPtr->Command != "Frh-sh"))
12654  {
12655  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - incorrect shuttle link to train whose headcode is " + OtherHeadCode +
12656  " from train whose headcode is " + MainHeadCode + ", has to be Fns-sh, Frh-sh");
12657  TrainDataVector.clear();
12658  Utilities->CallLogPop(1057);
12659  return false;
12660  }
12661  else
12662  {
12663  ForwardEntryPtr->LinkedTrainEntryPtr = OtherTrainDataPtr;
12664  ReverseEntryPtr->LinkedTrainEntryPtr = MainTrainDataPtr;
12665 /* don't need LinkedTrainEntryPtr for 'OtherTrain' & don't need data transfer as this is done in the
12666  non-repeating link for Sns-sh & is provided at the outset for Snt-sh
12667 */
12668  }
12669  }
12670 
12671  // check repeat information consistent if present
12672  // note that won't be affected by the non-repeating shuttle links as these are in NonRepeatingShuttleLinkHeadCode
12673  // and those not accessed here
12674 
12675  // still need to check the non-repeating links and that they have no repeats - do that outside this function
12676  bool MainRepeat = false, OtherRepeat = false;
12677  TActionVectorEntry MainRepeatEntry, OtherRepeatEntry;
12678 
12679  if(MainTrainDataPtr->ActionVector.at(MainTrainDataPtr->ActionVector.size() - 1).FormatType == Repeat)
12680  {
12681  MainRepeat = true;
12682  MainRepeatEntry = MainTrainDataPtr->ActionVector.at(MainTrainDataPtr->ActionVector.size() - 1);
12683  }
12684  if(OtherTrainDataPtr->ActionVector.at(OtherTrainDataPtr->ActionVector.size() - 1).FormatType == Repeat)
12685  {
12686  OtherRepeat = true;
12687  OtherRepeatEntry = OtherTrainDataPtr->ActionVector.at(OtherTrainDataPtr->ActionVector.size() - 1);
12688  }
12689  if((MainRepeat && !OtherRepeat) || (!MainRepeat && OtherRepeat))
12690  {
12691  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - only one repeat is provided for the train whose headcode is " + MainHeadCode +
12692  " and the associated train with headcode " + OtherHeadCode);
12693  TrainDataVector.clear();
12694  Utilities->CallLogPop(844);
12695  return false;
12696  }
12697  if(MainRepeat && OtherRepeat)
12698  {
12699  if((MainRepeatEntry.EventTime != OtherRepeatEntry.EventTime) || (MainRepeatEntry.RearStartOrRepeatMins != OtherRepeatEntry.RearStartOrRepeatMins) ||
12700  (MainRepeatEntry.FrontStartOrRepeatDigits != OtherRepeatEntry.FrontStartOrRepeatDigits) ||
12701  (MainRepeatEntry.NumberOfRepeats != OtherRepeatEntry.NumberOfRepeats))
12702  {
12703  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - repeat items don't correspond for the train whose headcode is " + MainHeadCode +
12704  " and the associated train with headcode " + OtherHeadCode);
12705  TrainDataVector.clear();
12706  Utilities->CallLogPop(845);
12707  return false;
12708  }
12709  }
12710  Utilities->CallLogPop(863);
12711  return true;
12712 }

12714 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
12715 
12716 void TTrainController::StripSpaces(int Caller, AnsiString &Input)
12717  // strip both leading and trailing spaces at ends of text and spaces before and after all commas and semicolons within the text
12718 {
12719  // strip spaces from extreme ends of input
12720  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",StripSpaces," + AnsiString(Input));
12721  if(Input == "")
12722  {
12723  Utilities->CallLogPop(856);
12724  return;
12725  }
12726  while(Input[1] == ' ')
12727  {
12728  if(Input.Length() > 1)
12729  {
12730  Input = Input.SubString(2, Input.Length() - 1);
12731  }
12732  else
12733  {
12734  Input = "";
12735  Utilities->CallLogPop(857);
12736  return;
12737  }
12738  }
12739  if(Input == "")
12740  {
12741  Utilities->CallLogPop(858);
12742  return;
12743  }
12744  while(Input[Input.Length()] == ' ')
12745  {
12746  if(Input.Length() > 1)
12747  {
12748  Input = Input.SubString(1, Input.Length() - 1);
12749  }
12750  else
12751  {
12752  Input = "";
12753  Utilities->CallLogPop(859);
12754  return;
12755  }
12756  }
12757  // now strip spaces immediately after all commas and semicolons within the text
12758  AnsiString Output = "";
12759  bool DelimiterFound = false;
12760 
12761  for(int x = 1; x < Input.Length() + 1; x++)
12762  {
12763  if(DelimiterFound)
12764  {
12765  if(Input[x] == ' ')
12766  continue;
12767  }
12768  if((Input[x] != ',') && (Input[x] != ';'))
12769  {
12770  DelimiterFound = false;
12771  Output = Output + Input[x];
12772  }
12773  else
12774  {
12775  DelimiterFound = true;
12776  Output = Output + Input[x];
12777  }
12778  }
12779  if(Output == "")
12780  {
12781  Input = "";
12782  Utilities->CallLogPop(860);
12783  return;
12784  }
12785  // now strip spaces immediately before all commas and semicolons within the text
12786  Input = Output;
12787  Output = "";
12788  DelimiterFound = false;
12789  for(int x = Input.Length(); x > 0; x--)
12790  {
12791  if(DelimiterFound)
12792  {
12793  if(Input[x] == ' ')
12794  continue;
12795  }
12796  if((Input[x] != ',') && (Input[x] != ';'))
12797  {
12798  DelimiterFound = false;
12799  Output = AnsiString(Input[x]) + Output;
12800  }
12801  else
12802  {
12803  DelimiterFound = true;
12804  Output = AnsiString(Input[x]) + Output;
12805  }
12806  }
12807  Input = Output;
12808  Utilities->CallLogPop(861);
12809 }
12810 
12811 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
12812 
12813 bool TTrainController::IsSNTEntryLocated(int Caller, const TTrainDataEntry &TDEntry, AnsiString &LocationName)
12814  // checks if an Snt or Snt-sh entry followed (somewhere, not necessarily immediately) by a TimeLoc has the same LocationName
12815  // and if so returns true. Also returns true for Snt, not Snt-sh, if at least 1 start element is a location & the entry is either
12816  // a signaller control entry & speed is zero or it is followed immediately by Frh or Fjo (mod at v2.0.0 for empty stock pickup).
12817  // Always return false for entry at a continuation (may be named but not a stop location). Note that no successor validity checks
12818  // are done in this function, they must be done elsewhere.
12819 {
12820  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",IsSNTEntryLocated," + AnsiString(TDEntry.HeadCode));
12821  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry0 = TDEntry.ActionVector.at(0);
12822 
12823  LocationName = "";
12824  if((AVEntry0.Command != "Snt") && (AVEntry0.Command != "Snt-sh"))
12825  {
12826  throw Exception("Error, first entry not 'Snt' or 'Snt-sh' in IsSNTEntryLocated");
12827  }
12828  if(Track->TrackElementAt(506, AVEntry0.RearStartOrRepeatMins).TrackType == Continuation)
12829  {
12830  Utilities->CallLogPop(852);
12831  return false;
12832  }
12833  AnsiString LocRear = Track->TrackElementAt(507, AVEntry0.RearStartOrRepeatMins).ActiveTrackElementName;
12834  AnsiString LocFront = Track->TrackElementAt(508, AVEntry0.FrontStartOrRepeatDigits).ActiveTrackElementName;
12835 
12836  if(LocRear != "")
12837  LocationName = LocRear;
12838  else
12839  LocationName = LocFront;
12840  if(LocationName == "")
12841  {
12842  Utilities->CallLogPop(1036);
12843  return false;
12844  }
12845  if((AVEntry0.SignallerControl) && (TDEntry.StartSpeed == 0))
12846  {
12847  Utilities->CallLogPop(1773);
12848  return true;
12849  }
12850  else if((AVEntry0.SignallerControl) && (TDEntry.StartSpeed > 0))
12851  {
12852  LocationName = "";
12853  Utilities->CallLogPop(1784);
12854  return false;
12855  }
12856 
12857  // here if not a signaller start entry so must be at least one more entry
12858  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry1 = TDEntry.ActionVector.at(1);
12859 
12860  // has to be at least 2 AV entries to pass the > 1 comma test in the preliminary check
12861  if(((AVEntry1.Command == "Frh") || (AVEntry1.Command == "Fjo") || (AVEntry1.Command == "F-nshs") || (AVEntry1.Command == "Fns")) && (AVEntry0.Command == "Snt")) // added Fjo at v2.0.0 for empty stock
12862  { //added F-nshs at v2.5.1 so can stay at a
12863  Utilities->CallLogPop(1037); //location until become a new shuttle service
12864  return true; //added Fns at same time as saw no reason to exclude
12865  }
12866  AnsiString TimeLocLocationName;
12867  bool FoundFlag = false;
12868 
12869  for(unsigned int y = 0; y < TDEntry.ActionVector.size(); y++)
12870  {
12871  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry = TDEntry.ActionVector.at(y);
12872  if(AVEntry.FormatType == TimeLoc)
12873  {
12874  FoundFlag = true;
12875  TimeLocLocationName = AVEntry.LocationName;
12876  break;
12877  }
12878  }
12879  if(!FoundFlag)
12880  {
12881  Utilities->CallLogPop(853);
12882  return false;
12883  }
12884  if(TimeLocLocationName == LocationName)
12885  {
12886  Utilities->CallLogPop(854);
12887  return true;
12888  }
12889  Utilities->CallLogPop(855);
12890  return false;
12891 }

12894 
12895 bool TTrainController::CheckStartPositionValidity(int Caller, AnsiString RearElementStr, AnsiString FrontElementStr, bool GiveMessages)
12896 {
12897  // checks that the new train start elements are valid - both exist & are connected, and that not
12898  // attempting to start on a diverging leg (i.e. one segment on points & other on element connected to diverging leg)
12899  // & not starting with front on a continuation
12900  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",CheckStartPositionValidity," + RearElementStr + "," + FrontElementStr);
12901  int RearPosition = 0, FrontPosition = 0, RearExitPos = 0;
12902 
12903  RearPosition = Track->GetTrackVectorPositionFromString(5, RearElementStr, GiveMessages);
12904  if(RearPosition < 0)
12905  // error message given in GetTrackVectorPositionFromString
12906  {
12907  Utilities->CallLogPop(759);
12908  return false;
12909  }
12910  FrontPosition = Track->GetTrackVectorPositionFromString(6, FrontElementStr, GiveMessages);
12911  if(FrontPosition < 0)
12912  // error message given in GetTrackVectorPositionFromString
12913  {
12914  Utilities->CallLogPop(760);
12915  return false;
12916  }
12917  TTrackElement RearTrackElement = Track->TrackElementAt(490, RearPosition);
12918  TTrackElement FrontTrackElement = Track->TrackElementAt(491, FrontPosition);
12919  TTrackType RearType = RearTrackElement.TrackType, FrontType = FrontTrackElement.TrackType;
12920 
12921  // check front & rear connected
12922  for(int x = 0; x < 4; x++)
12923  {
12924  if(RearTrackElement.Conn[x] == FrontPosition)
12925  {
12926  RearExitPos = x;
12927  break;
12928  }
12929  if(x == 3)
12930  {
12931  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Front element: " + FrontTrackElement.ElementID + " not linked to rear element: " + RearTrackElement.ElementID);
12932  Utilities->CallLogPop(762);
12933  return false;
12934  }
12935  }
12936  // check not starting with front on a continuation
12937  if(FrontType == Continuation)
12938  {
12939  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Front of train attempting to start on a continuation at: " + FrontElementStr);
12940  Utilities->CallLogPop(937);
12941  return false;
12942  }
12943 
12944  // check not starting on a level crossing
12945  if(Track->IsLCAtHV(43, FrontTrackElement.HLoc, FrontTrackElement.VLoc))
12946  {
12947  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Train attempting to start on a level crossing at: " + FrontElementStr);
12948  Utilities->CallLogPop(1951);
12949  return false;
12950  }
12951  if(Track->IsLCAtHV(44, RearTrackElement.HLoc, RearTrackElement.VLoc))
12952  {
12953  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Train attempting to start on a level crossing at: " + RearElementStr);
12954  Utilities->CallLogPop(1952);
12955  return false;
12956  }
12957 
12958  // check if trying to start on diverging leg of points
12959  if((RearType == Points) && (RearExitPos == 3))
12960  {
12961  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Front of train attempting to start on element connected to diverging points at: " + RearElementStr);
12962  Utilities->CallLogPop(936);
12963  return false;
12964  }
12965 
12966  if((FrontType == Points) && (RearTrackElement.ConnLinkPos[RearExitPos] == 3))
12967  {
12968  TimetableMessage(GiveMessages, "Rear of train attempting to start on element connected to diverging points at: " + FrontElementStr);
12969  Utilities->CallLogPop(1808);
12970  return false;
12971  }
12972  Utilities->CallLogPop(905);
12973  return true;
12974 }
12975 
12976 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
12977 
12978 bool TTrainController::CheckStartAllowable(int Caller, int RearPosition, int RearExitPos, AnsiString HeadCode, bool ReportFlag, TActionEventType &EventType)
12979  // Rear & front element validity already checked in CheckStartPositionValidity
12980  // This checks for points in correct orientation, no train at start position and not starting on a locked route
12981 {
12982  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",CheckStartAllowable," + AnsiString(RearPosition) + "," +
12983  AnsiString(RearExitPos));
12984  TTrackElement RearTrackElement = Track->TrackElementAt(517, RearPosition);
12985 
12986  if(RearTrackElement.TrackType == Continuation)
12987  EventType = FailTrainEntry;
12988  else
12989  EventType = FailCreateTrain;
12990  int FrontPosition = RearTrackElement.Conn[RearExitPos];
12991  TTrackElement FrontTrackElement = Track->TrackElementAt(798, FrontPosition);
12992  int FrontEntryPos = RearTrackElement.ConnLinkPos[RearExitPos];
12993  TTrackType RearType = RearTrackElement.TrackType;
12994  TTrackType FrontType = FrontTrackElement.TrackType;
12995  AnsiString RearName, FrontName;
12996 
12997  if(RearTrackElement.ActiveTrackElementName != "")
12998  RearName = RearTrackElement.ActiveTrackElementName;
12999  else
13000  RearName = RearTrackElement.ElementID;
13001  if(FrontTrackElement.ActiveTrackElementName != "")
13002  FrontName = FrontTrackElement.ActiveTrackElementName;
13003  else
13004  FrontName = FrontTrackElement.ElementID;
13005 
13006  TPrefDirElement PrefDirElement; // needed for next function but not used
13007  int LockedVectorNumber; // needed for next function but not used
13008 
13009  if(AllRoutes->IsElementInLockedRouteGetPrefDirElementGetLockedVectorNumber(12, FrontPosition, FrontEntryPos, PrefDirElement, LockedVectorNumber))
13010  {
13011  if(ReportFlag)
13012  {
13013  if(EventType == FailCreateTrain)
13014  EventType = FailCreateLockedRoute;
13015  else
13016  EventType = FailEnterLockedRoute;
13017  LogActionError(47, HeadCode, "", EventType, FrontName);
13018  }
13019  Utilities->CallLogPop(940);
13020  return false;
13021  }
13022 
13023  if(AllRoutes->IsElementInLockedRouteGetPrefDirElementGetLockedVectorNumber(13, RearPosition, RearExitPos, PrefDirElement, LockedVectorNumber))
13024  {
13025  if(ReportFlag)
13026  {
13027  if(EventType == FailCreateTrain)
13028  EventType = FailCreateLockedRoute;
13029  else
13030  EventType = FailEnterLockedRoute;
13031  LogActionError(48, HeadCode, "", EventType, RearName);
13032  }
13033  Utilities->CallLogPop(1809);
13034  return false;
13035  }
13036 
13037  if((RearType != Bridge) && (RearTrackElement.TrainIDOnElement > -1))
13038  {
13039  if(ReportFlag)
13040  {
13041  LogActionError(27, HeadCode, "", EventType, RearName);
13042  }
13043  Utilities->CallLogPop(1810);
13044  return false;
13045  }
13046 
13047  if((FrontType != Bridge) && (FrontTrackElement.TrainIDOnElement > -1))
13048  {
13049  if(ReportFlag)
13050  {
13051  if(EventType == FailCreateTrain)
13052  LogActionError(28, HeadCode, "", EventType, FrontName);
13053  else
13054  LogActionError(43, HeadCode, "", EventType, RearName);
13055  }
13056  Utilities->CallLogPop(941);
13057  return false;
13058  }
13059  if(RearType == Bridge)
13060  {
13061  if((RearExitPos > 1) && (RearTrackElement.TrainIDOnBridgeTrackPos23 > -1))
13062  {
13063  if(ReportFlag)
13064  {
13065  LogActionError(29, HeadCode, "", EventType, RearName);
13066  }
13067  Utilities->CallLogPop(942);
13068  return false;
13069  }
13070  if((RearExitPos < 2) && (RearTrackElement.TrainIDOnBridgeTrackPos01 > -1))
13071  {
13072  if(ReportFlag)
13073  {
13074  LogActionError(30, HeadCode, "", EventType, RearName);
13075  }
13076  Utilities->CallLogPop(943);
13077  return false;
13078  }
13079  }
13080  if(FrontType == Bridge)
13081  {
13082  if((FrontEntryPos > 1) && (FrontTrackElement.TrainIDOnBridgeTrackPos23 > -1))
13083  {
13084  if(ReportFlag)
13085  {
13086  if(EventType == FailCreateTrain)
13087  LogActionError(31, HeadCode, "", EventType, FrontName);
13088  else
13089  LogActionError(44, HeadCode, "", EventType, RearName);
13090  }
13091  Utilities->CallLogPop(944);
13092  return false;
13093  }
13094  if((FrontEntryPos < 2) && (FrontTrackElement.TrainIDOnBridgeTrackPos01 > -1))
13095  {
13096  if(ReportFlag)
13097  {
13098  if(EventType == FailCreateTrain)
13099  LogActionError(45, HeadCode, "", EventType, FrontName);
13100  else
13101  LogActionError(46, HeadCode, "", EventType, RearName);
13102  }
13103  Utilities->CallLogPop(945);
13104  return false;
13105  }
13106  }
13107 
13108  EventType = FailCreatePoints;
13109  if(RearType == Points)
13110  {
13111  if(RearTrackElement.Attribute == 1)
13112  {
13113  if(ReportFlag)
13114  {
13115  LogActionError(33, HeadCode, "", FailCreatePoints, RearName);
13116  }
13117  Utilities->CallLogPop(933);
13118  return false;
13119  }
13120  }
13121  if(FrontType == Points)
13122  {
13123  if(FrontTrackElement.Attribute == 1)
13124  {
13125  if(ReportFlag)
13126  {
13127  LogActionError(34, HeadCode, "", FailCreatePoints, FrontName);
13128  }
13129  Utilities->CallLogPop(934);
13130  return false;
13131  }
13132  }
13133  Utilities->CallLogPop(939);
13134  return true;
13135 }
13136 
13137 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
13138 
13139 AnsiString TTrainController::GetRepeatHeadCode(int Caller, AnsiString BaseHeadCode, int RepeatNumber, int IncDigits)
13140 {
13141  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",GetRepeatHeadCode," + BaseHeadCode + "," + AnsiString(RepeatNumber) +
13142  "," + AnsiString(IncDigits));
13143  if(!Last2CharactersBothDigits(1, BaseHeadCode) && (IncDigits > 0))
13144  {
13145  throw Exception("Error, last 2 characters not both digits and IncDigits > 0 in GetRepeatHeadCode");
13146  }
13147  if(!Last2CharactersBothDigits(2, BaseHeadCode))
13148  {
13149  Utilities->CallLogPop(1893);
13150  return BaseHeadCode;
13151  }
13152  int BaseDigits = BaseHeadCode.SubString(3, 2).ToInt();
13153  int NextRepeatDigits = BaseDigits + (IncDigits * RepeatNumber);
13154 
13155  while(NextRepeatDigits >= 100)
13156  {
13157  NextRepeatDigits -= 100; // rolls over after 99
13158  }
13159  AnsiString NextRepeatDigitsStr = AnsiString(NextRepeatDigits);
13160 
13161  if(NextRepeatDigitsStr.Length() < 2)
13162  NextRepeatDigitsStr = AnsiString('0') + NextRepeatDigitsStr;
13163  AnsiString NextRepeatHeadCode = BaseHeadCode.SubString(1, 2) + NextRepeatDigitsStr;
13164 
13165  Utilities->CallLogPop(1365);
13166  return NextRepeatHeadCode;
13167 }
13168 
13169 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
13170 
13171 TDateTime TTrainController::GetRepeatTime(int Caller, TDateTime BasicTime, int RepeatNumber, int IncMinutes)
13172 {
13173  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",GetRepeatTime," + AnsiString(double(BasicTime)) + "," +
13174  AnsiString(RepeatNumber) + "," + AnsiString(IncMinutes));
13175  TDateTime NextRepeatTime = BasicTime + TDateTime(((double)(RepeatNumber * IncMinutes)) / 1440.0); // 1440 = no. of minutes in 24h
13176 
13177  Utilities->CallLogPop(1366);
13178  return NextRepeatTime;
13179 }

13181 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
13182 
13183 bool TTrainController::CheckShuttleRepeatTime(int Caller, TDateTime ForwardEventTime, TDateTime ReverseEventTime, int RepeatMinutes)
13184  // For success the ForwardEventTime + repeat time should == ReverseEventTime (allow 10secs either way since converting to doubles)
13185 {
13186  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",CheckShuttleRepeatTime," + AnsiString(double(ForwardEventTime)) + "," +
13187  AnsiString(double(ReverseEventTime)) + "," + AnsiString(RepeatMinutes));
13188  int ForwardSecs = int(double(ForwardEventTime) * 86400);
13189  int ReverseSecs = int(double(ReverseEventTime) * 86400);
13190  int RepeatSecs = RepeatMinutes * 60;
13191 
13192  if((ForwardSecs > (ReverseSecs - RepeatSecs + 10)) || (ForwardSecs < (ReverseSecs - RepeatSecs - 10)))
13193  {
13194  Utilities->CallLogPop(1367);
13195  return false;
13196  }
13197  else
13198  {
13199  Utilities->CallLogPop(1368);
13200  return true;
13201  }
13202 }

13204 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
13205 
13206 bool TTrainController::CheckNonRepeatingShuttleLinksAndSetData(int Caller, AnsiString MainHeadCode, AnsiString NonRepeatingHeadCode, bool GiveMessages)
13207  // check for proper non-repeating link cross references and that they have no repeats & that times are consistent
13208 {
13209  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",CheckNonRepeatingShuttleLinksAndSetData," + MainHeadCode + "," +
13210  NonRepeatingHeadCode);
13211  int ForwardCount = 0;
13212  int ReverseCount = 0;
13213  unsigned int ForwardTDVectorNumber, ReverseTDVectorNumber;
13214  TActionVectorEntry *ReverseEntryPtr = 0, *ForwardEntryPtr = 0;
13215  // Forward corresponds to Main, Reverse to Other
13216  TTrainDataEntry *MainTrainDataPtr = 0;
13217  TTrainDataEntry *OtherTrainDataPtr = 0;
13218 
13219  // forward check
13220  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++)
13221  {
13222  const TTrainDataEntry &TDEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x);
13223  if(TDEntry.HeadCode == MainHeadCode)
13224  {
13225  for(unsigned int y = 0; y < TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size(); y++)
13226  {
13227  TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y);
13228  if(AVEntry.NonRepeatingShuttleLinkHeadCode == NonRepeatingHeadCode)
13229  {
13230  MainTrainDataPtr = &TrainDataVector.at(x);
13231  ForwardEntryPtr = &AVEntry;
13232  ForwardCount++;
13233  ForwardTDVectorNumber = x;
13234  }
13235  }
13236  }
13237  }
13238  if(ForwardCount == 0)
13239  // this is an exception because the headcodes are selected in the same order as the forward check
13240  {
13241  throw Exception("Error, ForwardCount == 0 in CheckNonRepeatingShuttleLinksAndSetData after called with found values");
13242  }
13243  if(ForwardCount > 1)
13244  {
13245  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - found more than one reference to " + NonRepeatingHeadCode + " from a train whose headcode is " +
13246  MainHeadCode);
13247  TrainDataVector.clear();
13248  Utilities->CallLogPop(1061);
13249  return false;
13250  }
13251 
13252  // reverse check
13253  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++)
13254  {
13255  const TTrainDataEntry &TDEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x);
13256  if(TDEntry.HeadCode == NonRepeatingHeadCode)
13257  {
13258  for(unsigned int y = 0; y < TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.size(); y++)
13259  {
13260  TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x).ActionVector.at(y);
13261  if(AVEntry.NonRepeatingShuttleLinkHeadCode == MainHeadCode)
13262  {
13263  OtherTrainDataPtr = &TrainDataVector.at(x);
13264  ReverseCount++;
13265  ReverseEntryPtr = &AVEntry;
13266  ReverseTDVectorNumber = x;
13267  }
13268  }
13269  }
13270  }
13271 
13272  if(ReverseCount == 0)
13273  {
13274  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - cross reference missing in either " + MainHeadCode + " or " + NonRepeatingHeadCode);
13275  TrainDataVector.clear();
13276  Utilities->CallLogPop(1062);
13277  return false;
13278  }
13279  if(ReverseCount > 1)
13280  {
13281  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - found more than one reference to " + MainHeadCode + " from a train whose headcode is " +
13282  NonRepeatingHeadCode);
13283  TrainDataVector.clear();
13284  Utilities->CallLogPop(1063);
13285  return false;
13286  }
13287 
13288  if(((ForwardEntryPtr->Command == "F-nshs") || (ForwardEntryPtr->Command == "Sns-fsh")) && (MainTrainDataPtr->ActionVector.back().FormatType == Repeat))
13289  {
13290  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - shuttle connecting train " + MainHeadCode + " shouldn't have a repeat");
13291  TrainDataVector.clear();
13292  Utilities->CallLogPop(1064);
13293  return false;
13294  }
13295 
13296  if((ForwardEntryPtr->Command != "F-nshs") && (ForwardEntryPtr->Command != "Sns-fsh") && (MainTrainDataPtr->ActionVector.back().FormatType != Repeat))
13297  {
13298  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - shuttle train " + MainHeadCode + " does not have a repeat item");
13299  TrainDataVector.clear();
13300  Utilities->CallLogPop(1065);
13301  return false;
13302  }
13303 
13304  if(ForwardEntryPtr->LocationName == "")
13305  {
13306  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - location error in cross referenced trains " + MainHeadCode + " and " + NonRepeatingHeadCode +
13307  ". One or other service does not have a location set");
13308  TrainDataVector.clear();
13309  Utilities->CallLogPop(1066);
13310  return false;
13311  }
13312 
13313  if(ReverseEntryPtr->LocationName == "")
13314  {
13315  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - location error in cross referenced trains " + MainHeadCode + " and " + NonRepeatingHeadCode +
13316  ". One or other service does not have a location set");
13317  TrainDataVector.clear();
13318  Utilities->CallLogPop(1067);
13319  return false;
13320  }
13321 
13322  if(ForwardEntryPtr->LocationName != ReverseEntryPtr->LocationName)
13323  {
13324  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - cross referenced train " + NonRepeatingHeadCode +
13325  " is at a different location to the referencing train " + MainHeadCode);
13326  TrainDataVector.clear();
13327  Utilities->CallLogPop(1068);
13328  return false;
13329  }
13330 
13331  if(ForwardEntryPtr->Command == "F-nshs")
13332  // i.e. the non repeating link into the shuttle service
13333  {
13334  if(ForwardEntryPtr->EventTime != ReverseEntryPtr->EventTime)
13335  {
13336  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - shuttle in-link service " + MainHeadCode +
13337  " finish time not consistent with start time of shuttle service " + NonRepeatingHeadCode);
13338  TrainDataVector.clear();
13339  Utilities->CallLogPop(1069);
13340  return false;
13341  }
13342  }
13343 
13344  if(ForwardEntryPtr->Command == "Fns-sh")
13345  // i.e. the non repeating link out from the shuttle service
13346  {
13347  if(!CheckNonRepeatingShuttleLinkTime(0, ForwardEntryPtr->EventTime, ReverseEntryPtr->EventTime,
13348  MainTrainDataPtr->ActionVector.back().RearStartOrRepeatMins, MainTrainDataPtr->ActionVector.back().NumberOfRepeats))
13349  {
13350  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - service " + NonRepeatingHeadCode + ", which links out from shuttle service " + MainHeadCode +
13351  ", has the wrong start time. It should correspond to the finish time of the last shuttle.");
13352  TrainDataVector.clear();
13353  Utilities->CallLogPop(1070);
13354  return false;
13355  }
13356  }
13357 
13358  if((ForwardEntryPtr->Command == "F-nshs") || (ForwardEntryPtr->Command == "Sns-fsh"))
13359  // i.e. a non repeating link to or from the shuttle service
13360  {
13361  if(ReverseTDVectorNumber == ForwardTDVectorNumber)
13362  {
13363  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - the non repeating link service " + NonRepeatingHeadCode +
13364  " appears in the same sequence as the corresponding shuttle service " + MainHeadCode);
13365  TrainDataVector.clear();
13366  Utilities->CallLogPop(1071);
13367  return false;
13368  }
13369  }
13370 /* it's allowed to have a different description
13371  if((ForwardEntryPtr->Command == "F-nshs") || (ForwardEntryPtr->Command == "Sns-fsh"))//i.e. a non repeating link to or from the shuttle service
13372  {
13373  if((MainTrainDataPtr->Description != "") && (OtherTrainDataPtr->Description != "") && (MainTrainDataPtr->Description != OtherTrainDataPtr->Description))
13374  {
13375  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - the non repeating link service " + NonRepeatingHeadCode + " has a different description to the corresponding shuttle service " + MainHeadCode);
13376  TrainDataVector.clear();
13377  Utilities->CallLogPop(1072);
13378  return false;
13379  }
13380  }
13381 */
13382  if(ForwardEntryPtr->Command == "Sns-sh")
13383  {
13384  if(ReverseEntryPtr->Command != "F-nshs")
13385  {
13386  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - unable to find a corresponding 'F-nshs' event for the 'Sns-sh' train whose headcode is " +
13387  MainHeadCode + " and is a new shuttle service formed from the service with headcode " + NonRepeatingHeadCode);
13388  TrainDataVector.clear();
13389  Utilities->CallLogPop(1073);
13390  return false;
13391  }
13392  }
13393 
13394  if(ForwardEntryPtr->Command == "F-nshs")
13395  {
13396  if(ReverseEntryPtr->Command != "Sns-sh")
13397  {
13398  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - unable to find a corresponding 'Sns-sh' event for the 'F-nshs' train whose headcode is " +
13399  MainHeadCode + " and forms a new shuttle service with headcode " + NonRepeatingHeadCode);
13400  TrainDataVector.clear();
13401  Utilities->CallLogPop(1074);
13402  return false;
13403  }
13404  else
13405  {
13406  ForwardEntryPtr->LinkedTrainEntryPtr = OtherTrainDataPtr;
13407  ReverseEntryPtr->NonRepeatingShuttleLinkEntryPtr = MainTrainDataPtr;
13408  if(OtherTrainDataPtr->Description == "")
13409  OtherTrainDataPtr->Description = MainTrainDataPtr->Description;
13410  // Probably redundant as this is continued from the earlier service when the changeover happens (also may not be set here yet if a service continuation)
13411  OtherTrainDataPtr->MaxRunningSpeed = MainTrainDataPtr->MaxRunningSpeed;
13412  // Probably redundant as this is continued from the earlier service when the changeover happens (also may not be set here yet if a service continuation)
13413  }
13414  }
13415 
13416  if(ForwardEntryPtr->Command == "Sns-fsh")
13417  {
13418  if(ReverseEntryPtr->Command != "Fns-sh")
13419  {
13420  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages,
13421  "Error in timetable - unable to find a corresponding 'Fns-sh' event for the 'Sns-fsh' non-shuttle service whose headcode is " + MainHeadCode +
13422  " formed from a shuttle service with headcode " + NonRepeatingHeadCode);
13423  TrainDataVector.clear();
13424  Utilities->CallLogPop(1075);
13425  return false;
13426  }
13427  }
13428 
13429  if(ForwardEntryPtr->Command == "Fns-sh")
13430  {
13431  if(ReverseEntryPtr->Command != "Sns-fsh")
13432  {
13433  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages,
13434  "Error in timetable - unable to find a corresponding 'Sns-fsh' event for the 'Fns-sh' shuttle service whose headcode is " + MainHeadCode +
13435  " and forms a new non-shuttle service with headcode " + NonRepeatingHeadCode);
13436  TrainDataVector.clear();
13437  Utilities->CallLogPop(1076);
13438  return false;
13439  }
13440  else
13441  {
13442  ForwardEntryPtr->NonRepeatingShuttleLinkEntryPtr = OtherTrainDataPtr;
13443  // links to the non-repeating non-shuttle linked service
13444  ReverseEntryPtr->LinkedTrainEntryPtr = MainTrainDataPtr;
13445  // needed for creating formatted timetable
13446  if(OtherTrainDataPtr->Description == "")
13447  OtherTrainDataPtr->Description = MainTrainDataPtr->Description;
13448  // Probably redundant as this is continued from the earlier service when the changeover happens (also may not be set here yet if a service continuation)
13449  OtherTrainDataPtr->MaxRunningSpeed = MainTrainDataPtr->MaxRunningSpeed;
13450  // Probably redundant as this is continued from the earlier service when the changeover happens (also may not be set here yet if a service continuation)
13451  }
13452  }
13453 
13454  Utilities->CallLogPop(1077);
13455  return true;
13456 }

13459 
13460 bool TTrainController::CheckNonRepeatingShuttleLinkTime(int Caller, TDateTime ForwardEventTime, TDateTime ReverseEventTime, int RepeatMinutes, int RepeatNumber)
13461  // Forward train is the finish shuttle entry 'Fns-sh'.
13462  // The Reverse (new non-repeating service) time must == Forward time + (RepeatMins * RepeatNumber) but allow 10 secs either side
13463 {
13464  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",CheckNonRepeatingShuttleLinkTime," + AnsiString(double(ForwardEventTime))
13465  + "," + AnsiString(double(ReverseEventTime)) + "," + AnsiString(RepeatMinutes) + "," + AnsiString(RepeatNumber));
13466  int ForwardSecs = int(double(ForwardEventTime) * 86400);
13467  int ReverseSecs = int(double(ReverseEventTime) * 86400);
13468  int RepeatSecs = RepeatMinutes * RepeatNumber * 60;
13469 
13470  if((ReverseSecs > (ForwardSecs + RepeatSecs + 10)) || (ReverseSecs < (ForwardSecs + RepeatSecs - 10)))
13471  {
13472  Utilities->CallLogPop(1369);
13473  return false;
13474  }
13475  else
13476  {
13477  Utilities->CallLogPop(1370);
13478  return true;
13479  }
13480 }

13482 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
13483 
13484 bool TTrainController::CheckShuttleServiceIntegrity(int Caller, TTrainDataEntry *TDEntryPtr, bool GiveMessages)
13485  // check that each shuttle start ends either in Fns or Fxx-sh (though a single service can't end in Fxx-sh), and that
13486  // when the Fxx-sh is reached it references the original start and not another shuttle - not allowed to link two shuttles,
13487  // don't ever need to and as designed would skip repeats.
13488 
13489  // enter with TDEntry a shuttle start - Snt-sh or Sns-sh
13490 {
13491  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",CheckShuttleServiceIntegrity," + AnsiString(TDEntryPtr->HeadCode));
13492  if(TDEntryPtr->ActionVector.back().FormatType != Repeat)
13493  {
13494  throw Exception("Error - last entry in " + TDEntryPtr->HeadCode + " service is not a repeat - should have already found this error");
13495  }
13496  TTrainDataEntry *ShuttleStartAddress = TDEntryPtr;
13497  AnsiString OriginalHeadCode = TDEntryPtr->HeadCode;
13498  AnsiString LastActionCommand = (TDEntryPtr->ActionVector.end() - 2)->Command;
13499 
13500  if((LastActionCommand != "Fns") && (LastActionCommand != "Fns-sh") && (LastActionCommand != "Frh-sh"))
13501  {
13502  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - last event in shuttle service " + TDEntryPtr->HeadCode + " is not 'Fns', 'Fns-sh' or 'Frh-sh'");
13503  TrainDataVector.clear();
13504  Utilities->CallLogPop(1091);
13505  return false;
13506  }
13507  while(LastActionCommand == "Fns")
13508  {
13509  TDEntryPtr = (TDEntryPtr->ActionVector.end() - 2)->LinkedTrainEntryPtr;
13510  LastActionCommand = (TDEntryPtr->ActionVector.end() - 2)->Command;
13511  if((LastActionCommand != "Fns") && (LastActionCommand != "Fns-sh") && (LastActionCommand != "Frh-sh"))
13512  {
13513  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages,
13514  "Error in timetable - last event in a continuation shuttle service (i.e links back to a shuttle) whose headcode is " + TDEntryPtr->HeadCode +
13515  " is not 'Fns', 'Fns-sh' or 'Frh-sh'");
13516  TrainDataVector.clear();
13517  Utilities->CallLogPop(1092);
13518  return false;
13519  }
13520  }
13521  // exit the 'while' with LastActionCommand FSH-XX
13522  if((TDEntryPtr->ActionVector.end() - 2)->LinkedTrainEntryPtr != ShuttleStartAddress)
13523  {
13524  SecondPassMessage(GiveMessages, "Error in timetable - the event that ends service " + TDEntryPtr->HeadCode +
13525  " is a shuttle finish, but it doesn't link back to the start of the original shuttle starting service " + OriginalHeadCode +
13526  ". The linking of two or more shuttles is not permitted.");
13527  TrainDataVector.clear();
13528  Utilities->CallLogPop(1093);
13529  return false;
13530  }
13531  Utilities->CallLogPop(1094);
13532  return true;
13533 }

13537 void TTrainController::TimetableMessage(bool GiveMessages, AnsiString Message)
13538 {
13539  if(!GiveMessages)
13540  return;
13541 
13542  // if(ServiceReference == "") ShowMessage(Message);
13543  if(!CheckHeadCodeValidity(12, false, ServiceReference))
13544  ShowMessage(Message);
13545  // changed from above at v2.3.0 as a meaningless value for 'Timetable invalid - unable to find a valid start time on its own line' (uses last entry text)
13546  // false means don't give messages within the function
13547  else
13548  ShowMessage("Service " + ServiceReference + ": " + Message);
13549 }

13564 void TTrainController::LogActionError(int Caller, AnsiString HeadCode, AnsiString OtherHeadCode, TActionEventType ActionEventType, AnsiString LocationID)
13565  // FailTrainEntry: 06:00:10 HELD: 2F43 can't enter railway, train obstructing entry position 57-N5

13575  // FailSplitDueToOtherTrain: 06:00:10 HELD: 2F43 unable to split - another train is obstructing at Essex Road

13577  // FailDerailed: 06:00:10: ERROR: 2F43 DERAILED at position 46-N7

13580  // FailMissedSplit: 06:00:10: ERROR: 2F43 failed to split at Essex Road

13584  // FailMissedNewService: 06:00:10: ERROR: 2F43 failed to form new service at Essex Road

13589  // FailBufferCrash: 06:00:10: ERROR: 2F43 CRASHED INTO BUFFERS at 46-N7

13594 {

13596  AnsiString(ActionEventType) + "," + LocationID);
13597  AnsiString BaseLog = "", Prefix = "", ErrorLog = "", WarningStr = "";

13899  break;

13908  (AVEntry.ArrivalTime).c_str() << ',' << Utilities->Format96HHMM(AVEntry.DepartureTime).c_str() << ',' << AVEntry.LocationName.c_str()

13910  << ',' << AVEntry.LinkedTrainEntryPtr << ',' << AVEntry.RearStartOrRepeatMins << ',' << AVEntry.FrontStartOrRepeatDigits << ',' <<
13911  AVEntry.NumberOfRepeats << '\n';
13912  }

13915  for(unsigned int y = 0; y < TrainDataVector.at(x).TrainOperatingDataVector.size(); y++)
13916  {

13919  // NotStarted, Running, Exited
13920  switch(TOD.RunningEntry)
13921  {

13924  RunningEntryStr = "NotStarted";
13925  break;
13926  }
13927 
13928  case 1:
13929  {
13930  RunningEntryStr = "Running";
13931  break;
13932  }
13933 
13934  case 2:
13935  {
13936  RunningEntryStr = "Exited";
13937  break;
13938  }}
13939  OutFile << ',' << ',' << TOD.TrainID << ',' << RunningEntryStr.c_str() << ',' << '\n';
13940  }
13941  OutFile << '\n';

13949 void TTrainController::StopTTClockMessage(int Caller, AnsiString Message)
13950  // ShowMessage stops everything so this function used where a message is needed when may be in Operating mode.
13951  // The timetable Restart and BaseTimes are reset so the timetable clock stops & restarts when 'OK' button pressed
13952 {
13953  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",StopTTClockMessage," + Message);
13954  StopTTClockFlag = true; // so TTClock stopped during MasterClockTimer function
13955  RestartTime = TTClockTime;
13956  ShowMessage(Message);
13957  BaseTime = TDateTime::CurrentDateTime();
13958  StopTTClockFlag = false;
13959  Utilities->CallLogPop(1374);
13960 }

13980 void TTrainController::LoadSessionTrains(int Caller, std::ifstream &SessionFile)
13981 {
13982  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",LoadSessionTrains");
13983  int NumberOfTrains = Utilities->LoadFileInt(SessionFile);
13984  TTrain *NewTrain = new TTrain(1, 0, 0, "", 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, (TTrainMode)0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0); // have to have >0 for mass, else have divide
13985 
13986  // by zero error in calculating AValue, use 1
13987  for(int x = 0; x < NumberOfTrains; x++)
13988  {
13989  *NewTrain = TTrain(2, 0, 0, "", 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, (TTrainMode)0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0); // have to have >0 for mass, else have divide
13990  // by zero error in calculating AValue, use 1
13991  NewTrain->LoadOneSessionTrain(0, SessionFile);
13992  if((NewTrain->EntrySpeed < 1) && (NewTrain->PowerAtRail < 1))
13993  // added at v2.4.0. have to include as that value not stored in session file
13994  {
13995  NewTrain->StoppedWithoutPower = true;
13996  }
13997  TrainVector.push_back(*NewTrain);
13998  LastTrainLoaded = x;
13999  }
14000  delete NewTrain;
14001  Utilities->CallLogPop(1376);
14002 }

14167  return false;
14168  }
14169  if(!Utilities->CheckFileInt(SessionFile, 0, 3))
14170  {
14171  Utilities->CallLogPop(1393);
14172  return false;
14173  }
14174  if(!Utilities->CheckFileDouble(SessionFile))
14175  {
14176  Utilities->CallLogPop(1405);
14177  return false;
14178  }
14179  if(!Utilities->CheckFileDouble(SessionFile))
14180  {
14181  Utilities->CallLogPop(1406);
14182  return false;
14183  }
14184  if(!Utilities->CheckFileDouble(SessionFile))
14185  {
14186  Utilities->CallLogPop(1407);
14187  return false;
14188  }
14189  if(!Utilities->CheckFileDouble(SessionFile))
14190  {
14191  Utilities->CallLogPop(1394);
14192  return false;
14193  }
14194  }
14195  Utilities->CallLogPop(1395);
14196  return true;
14197 }

14200 
14201 /*
14202  class TContinuationTrainExpectationEntry //for expected trains at continuation entries
14203  {
14204  public:
14205  AnsiString Description; ///< service description
14206  AnsiString HeadCode; ///< service headcode
14207  int RepeatNumber; ///< service RepeatNumber
14208  int IncrementalMinutes; ///< Repeat separation in minutes
14209  int IncrementalDigits; ///< Repeat headcode separation
14210  int VectorPosition; ///< TrackVectorPosition for the continuation element
14211  TTrainDataEntry *TrainDataEntryPtr; ///< points to the service entry in the timetable's TrainDataVector
14212  };
14213 
14214 
14215  typedef std::multimap<TDateTime,TContinuationTrainExpectationEntry> TContinuationTrainExpectationMultiMap;
14216  typedef pair<TDateTime, TContinuationTrainExpectationEntry> TContinuationTrainExpectationMultiMapPair;
14217 */
14218 
14219 void TTrainController::BuildContinuationTrainExpectationMultiMap(int Caller)
14220  // build this into timetable load so session loading can use it too
14221  // being a multimap it automatically sorts in ascending EventTime order
14222 {
14223  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",BuildContinuationTrainExpectationMultiMap");
14224  ContinuationTrainExpectationMultiMap.clear();
14225  // need to clear as this called twice when load a session
14226  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++)
14227  {
14228  TTrainDataEntry & TDEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x);
14229  const TActionVectorEntry &AVFirstEntry = TDEntry.ActionVector.at(0);
14230  const TActionVectorEntry &AVLastEntry = TDEntry.ActionVector.at(TDEntry.ActionVector.size() - 1);
14231 
14232  if(AVFirstEntry.Command == "Snt")
14233  // new train (no need to include Snt-sh since they can't start at a continuation)
14234  {
14235  TContinuationTrainExpectationMultiMapPair CTEMMP;
14236  if(Track->TrackElementAt(665, AVFirstEntry.RearStartOrRepeatMins).TrackType == Continuation)
14237  {
14238  TContinuationTrainExpectationEntry CTEEntry;
14239  CTEEntry.VectorPosition = AVFirstEntry.RearStartOrRepeatMins;
14240  // retains this value for all repeats
14241  CTEEntry.RepeatNumber = 0; // for first entry
14242  CTEEntry.TrainDataEntryPtr = &TDEntry;
14243  // retains this value for all repeats
14244  CTEEntry.HeadCode = TDEntry.HeadCode;
14245  CTEEntry.Description = TDEntry.Description;
14246  CTEEntry.IncrementalMinutes = 0;
14247  CTEEntry.IncrementalDigits = 0;
14248  if(AVLastEntry.FormatType == Repeat)
14249  {
14250  CTEEntry.IncrementalMinutes = AVLastEntry.RearStartOrRepeatMins;
14251  // retains this value or 0 for all repeats
14252  CTEEntry.IncrementalDigits = AVLastEntry.FrontStartOrRepeatDigits;
14253  // retains this value or 0 for all repeats
14254  }
14255  CTEMMP.first = AVFirstEntry.EventTime;
14256  CTEMMP.second = CTEEntry;
14257  ContinuationTrainExpectationMultiMap.insert(CTEMMP);
14258  // base entry
14259  if(TDEntry.NumberOfTrains > 1)
14260  {
14261  if(AVLastEntry.FormatType != Repeat)
14262  {
14263  throw Exception("Error, Last ActionVectorEntry not a repeat in BuildContinuationTrainExpectationMultiMap");
14264  }
14265  for(int y = 1; y < TDEntry.NumberOfTrains; y++)
14266  {
14267  CTEEntry.RepeatNumber = y;
14268  CTEEntry.HeadCode = GetRepeatHeadCode(23, TDEntry.HeadCode, y, AVLastEntry.FrontStartOrRepeatDigits);
14269  // CTEEntry.VectorPosition stays same
14270  CTEMMP.first = GetRepeatTime(3, AVFirstEntry.EventTime, y, AVLastEntry.RearStartOrRepeatMins);
14271  CTEMMP.second = CTEEntry;
14272  ContinuationTrainExpectationMultiMap.insert(CTEMMP);
14273  }
14274  }
14275  }
14276  }
14277  }
14278  Utilities->CallLogPop(1396);
14279 }
14280

14283 void TTrainController::PlotAllTrainsInZoomOutMode(int Caller, bool Flash)
14284 {
14285  // called when WarningFlashCount == 0 or when press zoomout button
14286  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",PlotTrainsInZoomOutMode");
14287  if(!Display->ZoomOutFlag)
14288  {
14289  Utilities->CallLogPop(1156);
14290  return;
14291  }
14292  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainVector.size(); x++)
14293  {
14294  // plot blanks & track for all train, even if to be overplotted, since when flashing need to overplot all anyway
14295  // if OldPlotElement[x] == -1 then ignore (not plotted)
14296  TrainVectorAt(56, x).UnplotTrainInZoomOutMode(1);
14297  TrainVectorAt(57, x).PlotTrainInZoomOutMode(0, Flash);
14298  }
14299  Display->Update();
14300  // need to keep this since Update() not called for PlotSmallOutput as too slow
14301  Utilities->CallLogPop(742);
14302 }

14306 TTrain &TTrainController::TrainVectorAt(int Caller, int VecPos)
14307 {

14310  {

14321  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",CreateFormattedTimetable");
14322  AnsiString RetStr = "", PartStr = "";
14323 
14324 
14325 /*

14405  //formatted timetable types
