14436 
14437  AnsiString TTFileName = TDateTime::CurrentDateTime().FormatString("dd-mm-yyyy hh.nn.ss");
14438 
14439  // format "16/06/2009 20:55:17"
14440  // avoid characters in filename:= / \ : * ? " < > |
14441  TTFileName = CurDir + "\\Formatted timetables\\Timetable " + TTFileName + "; " + RailwayTitle + "; " + TimetableTitle + ".csv";
14442 
14443  AnsiString ShortTTName = "";
14444 
14445  for(int x = TTFileName.Length(); x > 0; x--)
14446  {
14447  if(TTFileName[x] == '\\')
14448  {
14449  ShortTTName = TTFileName.SubString(x + 1, TTFileName.Length() - x - 4);
14450  break;
14451  }
14452  }
14453 
14454  ShowMessage("Creates two timetables named " + ShortTTName +
14455  " in the 'Formatted timetables' folder, one in service order in '.csv' format, and one in chronological order in '.txt' format");
14456 
14457  Screen->Cursor = TCursor(-11); // Hourglass
14458 
14459  AnsiString FormatNoDPStr = "#######0";
14460  AnsiString TableTitle = "", TimetableTimeStr = "", MassStr = "", PowerStr = "", BrakeStr = "", MaxSpeedStr = "", FirstHeadCode = "", Header = "";
14461 
14462  TimetableTimeStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(TrainController->TimetableStartTime);
14463  TableTitle = "Railway: " + RailwayTitle + "; Timetable: " + TimetableTitle + "; Start time: " + TimetableTimeStr;
14464  TAllFormattedTrains *AllTTTrains = new TAllFormattedTrains;
14465 
14466  // all timetable in formatted form
14467  //create the AllTTTrains vector
14468  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++)
14469  {
14470  MassStr = "", PowerStr = "", BrakeStr = "", MaxSpeedStr = "";
14471  const TTrainDataEntry &TrainDataEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x);
14472  if(TrainDataEntry.Mass > 0)
14473  MassStr = "; Mass " + AnsiString::FormatFloat(FormatNoDPStr, ((double)TrainDataEntry.Mass) / 1000) + "Te; ";
14474  if(TrainDataEntry.PowerAtRail > 0)
14475  PowerStr = "Power " + AnsiString::FormatFloat(FormatNoDPStr, TrainDataEntry.PowerAtRail / 1000 / 0.8) + "kW; ";
14476  if(TrainDataEntry.MaxBrakeRate > 0)
14477  BrakeStr = "Brake force " + AnsiString::FormatFloat(FormatNoDPStr, (TrainDataEntry.MaxBrakeRate * TrainDataEntry.Mass / 9810)) + "Te; ";
14478  if(TrainDataEntry.MaxRunningSpeed > 0)
14479  MaxSpeedStr = "Maximum speed " + AnsiString::FormatFloat(FormatNoDPStr, TrainDataEntry.MaxRunningSpeed) + " km/h";
14480  FirstHeadCode = TrainDataEntry.HeadCode;
14481  int IncDigits = 0, IncMinutes = 0;
14482  const TActionVector &ActionVector = TrainDataEntry.ActionVector;
14483  if(!ActionVector.empty())
14484  {
14485  if(ActionVector.at(ActionVector.size() - 1).FormatType == Repeat)
14486  {
14487  IncDigits = ActionVector.at(ActionVector.size() - 1).FrontStartOrRepeatDigits;
14488  IncMinutes = ActionVector.at(ActionVector.size() - 1).RearStartOrRepeatMins;
14489  }
14490  }
14491 
14492  TTrainFormattedInformation OneTTLine;
14493  // contains all information for a single TT entry (including repeats)
14494  for(int y = 0; y < TrainDataEntry.NumberOfTrains; y++)
14495  {
14496  OneTTLine.Header = "";
14497  if((TrainDataEntry.Description != "") && (MassStr != ""))
14498  OneTTLine.Header = TrainDataEntry.Description + MassStr + PowerStr + BrakeStr + MaxSpeedStr;
14499  else if(TrainDataEntry.Description != "")
14500  OneTTLine.Header = TrainDataEntry.Description;
14501  OneTTLine.NumberOfTrains = TrainDataEntry.NumberOfTrains;
14502  TOneCompleteFormattedTrain OneTTTrain; // headcode + list of actions
14503  for(unsigned int z = 0; z < ActionVector.size(); z++)
14504  {
14505  TOneTrainFormattedEntry OneTTEntry;
14506  OneTTTrain.HeadCode = GetRepeatHeadCode(24, FirstHeadCode, y, IncDigits);
14507  TActionVectorEntry ActionVectorEntry = ActionVector.at(z);
14508  AnsiString PartStr = "", TimeStr = "";
14509 /*
14510  enum TTimetableFormatType {NoFormat, TimeLoc, TimeTimeLoc, TimeCmd, StartNew, TimeCmdHeadCode, FinRemHere,
14511  FNSNonRepeatToShuttle, SNTShuttle, SNSShuttle, SNSNonRepeatFromShuttle, FSHNewService, Repeat, PassTime,
14512  ExitRailway};
14513  enum TTimetableSequenceType {NoSequence, Start, Finish, Intermediate, SequTypeForRepeatEntry};
14514  enum TTimetableLocationType {NoLocation, AtLocation, EnRoute, LocTypeForRepeatEntry};
14515  enum TTimetableShuttleLinkType {NoShuttleLink, NotAShuttleLink, ShuttleLink, ShuttleLinkTypeForRepeatEntry};
14516 */
14517  if(ActionVectorEntry.SequenceType == Start)
14518  {
14519  if(ActionVectorEntry.FormatType == StartNew)
14520  {
14521  if(ActionVectorEntry.LocationName != "")
14522  {
14523  if(Track->TrackElementAt(742, ActionVectorEntry.RearStartOrRepeatMins).TrackType == Continuation)
14524  {
14525  PartStr = "Enters at " + ActionVectorEntry.LocationName;
14526  }
14527  else
14528  {
14529  PartStr = "Created at " + ActionVectorEntry.LocationName;
14530  }
14531  }
14532  else // may be a named continuation or other element, and if so report that
14533  {
14534  AnsiString LocName = Track->TrackElementAt(739, ActionVectorEntry.RearStartOrRepeatMins).ActiveTrackElementName;
14535  if(Track->TrackElementAt(740, ActionVectorEntry.RearStartOrRepeatMins).TrackType == Continuation)
14536  {
14537  if(LocName != "")
14538  {
14539  PartStr = "Enters at " + LocName;
14540  }
14541  else // use rear position if it's a continuation
14542  {
14543  PartStr = "Enters at " + Track->TrackElementAt(737, ActionVectorEntry.RearStartOrRepeatMins).ElementID;
14544  }
14545  }
14546  else // not a continuation
14547  {
14548  if(LocName != "")
14549  // if not a continuation then LocName should be same as ActionVectorEntry.LocationName
14550  // but include anyway
14551  {
14552  PartStr = "Created at " + LocName;
14553  }
14554  else // use rear position again
14555  {
14556  PartStr = "Created at " + Track->TrackElementAt(741, ActionVectorEntry.RearStartOrRepeatMins).ElementID;
14557  }
14558  }
14559  }
14560  TimeStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetRepeatTime(20, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime, y, IncMinutes));
14561  }
14562  else if(ActionVectorEntry.FormatType == SNTShuttle)
14563  {
14564  if(y == 0) // first train
14565  {
14566  PartStr = "Enters at " + ActionVectorEntry.LocationName;
14567  TimeStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetRepeatTime(21, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime, y, IncMinutes));
14568  }
14569  else
14570  {
14571  PartStr = "Repeat shuttle service at " + ActionVectorEntry.LocationName + " from ";
14572  TimeStr = GetRepeatHeadCode(45, ActionVectorEntry.OtherHeadCode, y - 1, IncDigits) + " at " +
14573  Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetRepeatTime(26, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime, y, IncMinutes));
14574  } // y-1 for headcode above since it is the last repeat value that the train is from
14575  }
14576  else if(ActionVectorEntry.Command == "Sfs")
14577  {
14578  PartStr = "New service at " + ActionVectorEntry.LocationName + " split from";
14579  TimeStr = GetRepeatHeadCode(33, ActionVectorEntry.OtherHeadCode, y, IncDigits) + " at " +
14580  Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetRepeatTime(24, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime, y, IncMinutes));
14581  }
14582  else if(ActionVectorEntry.Command == "Sns")
14583  {
14584  PartStr = "New service at " + ActionVectorEntry.LocationName + " from";
14585  TimeStr = GetRepeatHeadCode(34, ActionVectorEntry.OtherHeadCode, y, IncDigits) + " at " +
14586  Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetRepeatTime(25, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime, y, IncMinutes));
14587  }
14588  else if(ActionVectorEntry.FormatType == SNSShuttle)
14589  {
14590  if(y == 0) // first entry from shuttle
14591  {
14592  PartStr = "New service at " + ActionVectorEntry.LocationName + " from";
14593  TimeStr = ActionVectorEntry.NonRepeatingShuttleLinkHeadCode + " at " +
14594  Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetRepeatTime(27, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime, y, IncMinutes));
14595  }
14596  else
14597  {
14598  PartStr = "Repeat shuttle service at " + ActionVectorEntry.LocationName + " from ";
14599  TimeStr = GetRepeatHeadCode(35, ActionVectorEntry.OtherHeadCode, y - 1, IncDigits) + " at " +
14600  Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetRepeatTime(22, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime, y, IncMinutes));
14601  } // y-1 for headcode above since it is the last repeat value that the train is from
14602  }
14603  else if(ActionVectorEntry.FormatType == SNSNonRepeatFromShuttle)
14604  {
14605  PartStr = "New service at " + ActionVectorEntry.LocationName + " from";
14606  // need repeat for the non-repeating headcode as it's the last train of the repeating shuttle
14607  TTrainDataEntry *TDE = ActionVectorEntry.LinkedTrainEntryPtr;
14608  AnsiString FirstHeadCode = TDE->HeadCode;
14609  int LastRepeatNumber = TDE->NumberOfTrains - 1;
14610  // a shuttle has to have at least 1 repeat
14611  int IncrementalDigits = TDE->ActionVector.at(TDE->ActionVector.size() - 1).FrontStartOrRepeatDigits;
14612  TimeStr = GetRepeatHeadCode(36, FirstHeadCode, LastRepeatNumber, IncrementalDigits) + " at " +
14613  Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetRepeatTime(23, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime, y, IncMinutes));
14614  }
14615  }
14616  else if(ActionVectorEntry.SequenceType == Intermediate)
14617  {
14618  if(ActionVectorEntry.FormatType == TimeTimeLoc)
14619  {
14620  // here need 2 entries if times different so push the first right away & the second later
14621  // if times same just give the arrival entry
14622  if(ActionVectorEntry.DepartureTime != ActionVectorEntry.ArrivalTime)
14623  {
14624  PartStr = "Arrives at " + ActionVectorEntry.LocationName;
14625  TimeStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetRepeatTime(4, ActionVectorEntry.ArrivalTime, y, IncMinutes));
14626  OneTTEntry.Action = PartStr;
14627  OneTTEntry.Time = TimeStr;
14628  OneTTTrain.OneFormattedTrainVector.push_back(OneTTEntry);
14629  PartStr = "Departs from " + ActionVectorEntry.LocationName;
14630  TimeStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetRepeatTime(5, ActionVectorEntry.DepartureTime, y, IncMinutes));
14631  }
14632  else
14633  {
14634  PartStr = "Arrives & departs " + ActionVectorEntry.LocationName;
14635  TimeStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetRepeatTime(29, ActionVectorEntry.ArrivalTime, y, IncMinutes));
14636  }
14637  }
14638  else if((ActionVectorEntry.FormatType == TimeLoc) && (ActionVectorEntry.ArrivalTime != TDateTime(-1)))
14639  {
14640  PartStr = "Arrives at " + ActionVectorEntry.LocationName;
14641  TimeStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetRepeatTime(6, ActionVectorEntry.ArrivalTime, y, IncMinutes));
14642  }
14643  else if((ActionVectorEntry.FormatType == TimeLoc) && (ActionVectorEntry.ArrivalTime == TDateTime(-1)))
14644  {
14645  PartStr = "Departs from " + ActionVectorEntry.LocationName;
14646  TimeStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetRepeatTime(7, ActionVectorEntry.DepartureTime, y, IncMinutes));
14647  }
14648  else if(ActionVectorEntry.FormatType == PassTime)
14649  {
14650  PartStr = "Passes " + ActionVectorEntry.LocationName;
14651  TimeStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetRepeatTime(8, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime, y, IncMinutes));
14652  }
14653  else if(ActionVectorEntry.Command == "jbo")
14654  {
14655  PartStr = "Joined at " + ActionVectorEntry.LocationName + " by";
14656  TimeStr = GetRepeatHeadCode(37, ActionVectorEntry.OtherHeadCode, y, IncDigits) + " at " +
14657  Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetRepeatTime(9, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime, y, IncMinutes));
14658  }
14659  else if(ActionVectorEntry.Command == "fsp")
14660  {
14661  PartStr = "Splits from front at " + ActionVectorEntry.LocationName + " to form";
14662  TimeStr = GetRepeatHeadCode(38, ActionVectorEntry.OtherHeadCode, y, IncDigits) + " at " +
14663  Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetRepeatTime(10, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime, y, IncMinutes));
14664  }
14665  else if(ActionVectorEntry.Command == "rsp")
14666  {
14667  PartStr = "Splits from rear at " + ActionVectorEntry.LocationName + " to form";
14668  TimeStr = GetRepeatHeadCode(39, ActionVectorEntry.OtherHeadCode, y, IncDigits) + " at " +
14669  Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetRepeatTime(11, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime, y, IncMinutes));
14670  }
14671  else if(ActionVectorEntry.Command == "cdt")
14672  {
14673  PartStr = "Changes direction at " + ActionVectorEntry.LocationName;
14674  TimeStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetRepeatTime(12, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime, y, IncMinutes));
14675  }
14676  }
14677  else if(ActionVectorEntry.SequenceType == Finish)
14678  {
14679  if(ActionVectorEntry.Command == "Fns")
14680  {
14681  PartStr = "At " + ActionVectorEntry.LocationName + " forms new service";
14682  TimeStr = GetRepeatHeadCode(40, ActionVectorEntry.OtherHeadCode, y, IncDigits) + " at " +
14683  Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetRepeatTime(13, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime, y, IncMinutes));
14684  }
14685  else if(ActionVectorEntry.Command == "F-nshs")
14686  {
14687  PartStr = "At " + ActionVectorEntry.LocationName + " forms new service";
14688  TimeStr = ActionVectorEntry.NonRepeatingShuttleLinkHeadCode + " at " + Utilities->Format96HHMM
14689  (GetRepeatTime(17, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime, y, IncMinutes));
14690  }
14691  else if((ActionVectorEntry.Command == "Fns-sh") && (y < (TrainDataEntry.NumberOfTrains - 1)))
14692  {
14693  PartStr = "At " + ActionVectorEntry.LocationName + " forms new service ";
14694  TimeStr = GetRepeatHeadCode(41, ActionVectorEntry.OtherHeadCode, y + 1, IncDigits) + " at " +
14695  Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetRepeatTime(14, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime, y, IncMinutes));
14696  // y+1 because it's the NEXT service repeat number that is relevant
14697  }
14698  else if((ActionVectorEntry.Command == "Fns-sh") && (y >= (TrainDataEntry.NumberOfTrains - 1)))
14699  {
14700  PartStr = "At " + ActionVectorEntry.LocationName + " forms new service";
14701  TimeStr = ActionVectorEntry.NonRepeatingShuttleLinkHeadCode + " at " + Utilities->Format96HHMM
14702  (GetRepeatTime(15, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime, y, IncMinutes));
14703  }
14704  else if((ActionVectorEntry.Command == "Frh-sh") && (y < (TrainDataEntry.NumberOfTrains - 1)))
14705  {
14706  PartStr = "At " + ActionVectorEntry.LocationName + " forms new service";
14707  TimeStr = GetRepeatHeadCode(43, ActionVectorEntry.OtherHeadCode, y + 1, IncDigits) + " at " +
14708  Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetRepeatTime(16, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime, y, IncMinutes));
14709  // y+1 because it's the NEXT service repeat number that is relevant
14710  }
14711  else if((ActionVectorEntry.Command == "Frh-sh") && (y >= (TrainDataEntry.NumberOfTrains - 1)))
14712  {
14713  PartStr = "Terminates shuttle service at " + ActionVectorEntry.LocationName;
14714  // only used in chronological tt
14715  TimeStr = "End at " + Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetRepeatTime(28, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime, y, IncMinutes));
14716  // the "End at " is stripped out of the chronological tt but displayed in the traditional tt
14717  }
14718  else if(ActionVectorEntry.Command == "Frh")
14719  {
14720  PartStr = "Terminates at " + ActionVectorEntry.LocationName;
14721  // need here to examine the time of the preceding entry, may be ArrivalTime if TimeLoc, or EventTime otherwise
14722  if(z > 0)
14723  // should be for finish entry but include check for safety
14724  {
14725  if(ActionVector.at(z - 1).EventTime != TDateTime(-1))
14726  {
14727  TimeStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetRepeatTime(30, ActionVector.at(z - 1).EventTime, y, IncMinutes));
14728  }
14729  else if(ActionVector.at(z - 1).ArrivalTime != TDateTime(-1))
14730  {
14731  TimeStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetRepeatTime(31, ActionVector.at(z - 1).ArrivalTime, y, IncMinutes));
14732  }
14733  else
14734  TimeStr = " "; // shouldn't ever get here
14735  }
14736  }
14737  else if(ActionVectorEntry.Command == "Fer")
14738  {
14739  PartStr = "Exits railway" + GetExitLocationAndAt(0, ActionVectorEntry.ExitList);
14740  TimeStr = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetRepeatTime(18, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime, y, IncMinutes));
14741  }
14742  else if(ActionVectorEntry.Command == "Fjo")
14743  {
14744  PartStr = "At " + ActionVectorEntry.LocationName + " joins";
14745  TimeStr = GetRepeatHeadCode(44, ActionVectorEntry.OtherHeadCode, y, IncDigits) + " at " +
14746  Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetRepeatTime(19, ActionVectorEntry.EventTime, y, IncMinutes));
14747  }
14748  }
14749  else if(ActionVectorEntry.SequenceType == SequTypeForRepeatEntry)
14750  continue; // no entry needed for a repeat
14751  OneTTEntry.Action = PartStr;
14752  OneTTEntry.Time = TimeStr;
14753  OneTTTrain.OneFormattedTrainVector.push_back(OneTTEntry);
14754  // one per action
14755  }
14756  OneTTLine.OneCompleteFormattedTrainVector.push_back(OneTTTrain);
14757  // one per repeat
14758  }
14759  AllTTTrains->push_back(OneTTLine); // one per repeating train
14760  }
14761  // AllTTTrains vector now complete
14762 
14763  std::ofstream TTFile(TTFileName.c_str()); //formatted timetable
14764 
14765  if(TTFile == 0)
14766  {
14767  StopTTClockMessage(64, "Formatted timetable file failed to open - can't be created");
14768  delete AllTTTrains;
14769  Utilities->CallLogPop(1567);
14770  return;
14771  }

14879  // 'NXNN at HH:MM' (will return true if H/C as integ check passed)
14880  { // fails for HH:MM because of ':' or 'End at HH:MM' because of ' '
14881  AnsiString OtherHeadCode = TimeString.SubString(1, 4);
14882  TimeString = TimeString.SubString(9, 5);
14883  ActionString += " " + OtherHeadCode;
14884  }

14886  // for Frh-sh final entry

14889  }

14892  AnsiMultiMapEntry.second = OneLine;

14894  }
14895  }
14896  }

14910 bool TTrainController::CreateTTAnalysisFile(int Caller, AnsiString RailwayTitle, AnsiString TimetableTitle, AnsiString CurDir, bool ArrChecked, bool DepChecked,

14934 
14935  //first have to check through all the services and give each one a unique name, or the analysis won't recognise differences between services that have the same reference
14936  //to do that need a new TrainDataVector as don't want to change anything in the original. TrainDataVectorCopy is used for building AllServiceCallingLocsMap & LocServiceTimesVector
14937 
14938  TTrainDataVector TrainDataVectorCopy = TrainDataVector; //don't need it on heap as TrainController is on the heap. Didn't need others in CreatFormattedTimetables but leave as is.

14941  int IteratorNumber = 0;

14944  {

14948  {

14950  {
14951  Suffix++; //first value is 1
14952  AnsiSuffix = AnsiString(Suffix);
14953  TDVCopyIt->ServiceReference = TDVIt->ServiceReference + "/" + AnsiSuffix;
14954  }
14955  }
14956  }
14957 
14958  //build AllServiceCallingLocsMap, it only uses the base service reference (with /1, /2 etc suffixes) as later times are calculated from the repeat number
14959  TServiceCallingLocsList ServiceCallingLocsList;
14960  std::pair<AnsiString, TServiceCallingLocsList> AllServiceCallingLocsEntry;
14961  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVectorCopy.size(); x++)
14962  {

14964  const TActionVector &ActionVector = TrainDataEntry.ActionVector;
14965  AllServiceCallingLocsEntry.first = TrainDataEntry.ServiceReference;

14967  if(ActionVector.empty())
14968  {
14969  continue;
14970  }
14971  if(ActionVector.at(0).SignallerControl)
14972  {
14973  continue;
14974  }
14975  for(unsigned int z = 0; z < ActionVector.size(); z++)
14976  {
14977  TActionVectorEntry AVE = ActionVector.at(z);
14978  if(AVE.FormatType == StartNew)
14979  {
14980  if(AVE.LocationType == AtLocation) //located Snt
14981  {
14982  ServiceCallingLocsList.push_back(AVE.LocationName);
14983  }
14984  else //unlocated Snt (could be entering at continuation)
14985  {
14986  TTrackElement TE = Track->TrackElementAt(994, AVE.RearStartOrRepeatMins);
14987  if(TE.ActiveTrackElementName != "")
14988  {
14989  ServiceCallingLocsList.push_back(TE.ActiveTrackElementName);
14990  }
14991  else
14992  {
14993  int HLoc = TE.HLoc;
14994  int VLoc = TE.VLoc;
14995  AnsiString HString;
14996  AnsiString VString;
14997  if(HLoc < 0)
14998  {
14999  HString = 'N' + AnsiString(HLoc).SubString(2, AnsiString(HLoc).Length() - 1); //strip off '-'
15000  }
15001  else
15002  {
15003  HString = AnsiString(HLoc);
15004  }
15005  if(VLoc < 0)
15006  {
15007  VString = 'N' + AnsiString(VLoc).SubString(2, AnsiString(VLoc).Length() - 1); //strip off '-'
15008  }
15009  else
15010  {
15011  VString = AnsiString(VLoc);
15012  }
15013  ServiceCallingLocsList.push_back(HString + '-' + VString);
15014  }
15015  }
15016  }
15017  else if(AVE.SequenceType == Start) //other start entries, all located
15018  {
15019  ServiceCallingLocsList.push_back(AVE.LocationName);
15020  }
15021  else if(AVE.FormatType == TimeLoc) //z must be > 0
15022  {

15026  }
15027  }
15028  else if(AVE.FormatType == PassTime)
15029  {
15030  ServiceCallingLocsList.push_back(AVE.LocationName);
15031  }
15032  else if(AVE.FormatType == TimeTimeLoc)
15033  {
15034  ServiceCallingLocsList.push_back(AVE.LocationName);
15035  }

15037  {

15039  {
15040  continue;
15041  }
15042  else if(ActionVector.at(z+1).SequenceType == Finish) //although deal with Fer entries cdt (train stopped) can't precede FER (train moving)
15043  {
15044  continue;
15045  }
15046  else

15048  AnsiString TimeString = Utilities->Format96HHMM(AVE.EventTime);
15049  ServiceCallingLocsList.push_back("%%%" + TimeString); //%%% is a marker - unlikely that any locations will begin with this & easy to check to identify a time
15050  }
15051  }
15052  else if(AVE.FormatType == ExitRailway) //Fer
15053  {
15054  TTrackElement TE = Track->TrackElementAt(995, AVE.ExitList.front());
15055  AnsiString LName = TE.ActiveTrackElementName;
15056  if(LName != "")
15057  {
15058  ServiceCallingLocsList.push_back(LName);
15059  }

15062  int HLoc = TE.HLoc;
15063  int VLoc = TE.VLoc;
15064  AnsiString HString;
15065  AnsiString VString;
15066  if(HLoc < 0)
15067  {
15068  HString = 'N' + AnsiString(HLoc).SubString(2, AnsiString(HLoc).Length() - 1); //strip off '-'
15069  }
15070  else
15071  {
15072  HString = AnsiString(HLoc);
15073  }
15074  if(VLoc < 0)
15075  {
15076  VString = 'N' + AnsiString(VLoc).SubString(2, AnsiString(VLoc).Length() - 1); //strip off '-'
15077  }
15078  else
15079  {
15080  VString = AnsiString(VLoc);
15081  }
15082  ServiceCallingLocsList.push_back(HString + '-' + VString);
15083  }
15084  }
15085  }
15086  AllServiceCallingLocsEntry.second = ServiceCallingLocsList;
15087  AllServiceCallingLocsMap.insert(AllServiceCallingLocsEntry);
15088  }
15089  //AllServiceCallingLocsMap built

15091  //test validity of AllServiceCallingLocsMap

15116 
15117  //initialise variables before calc LastTTTime & build LocServiceTimesVector

15121  Utilities->CallLogPop(2209);
15122  return false;
15123  }
15124  TLocServiceTimes TLSTEntry;
15125  TLocServiceTimesVector LocServiceTimesVector; //will be on heap as TrainController is on the heap
15126  bool NumPlatsAtThisLocCalculated = false, ArrivalsPrinted = false, DeparturesPrinted = false, AtLocsPrinted = false;
15127  AnsiString PreviousService = "", PreviousServiceAndRepeatNumTotalOutput = "", BasicTime = "", MinuteString = "", LastAnsiTime = "";

15129  LastTTTime = "";
15130 
15131  //calculate LastTTTime
15132  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVectorCopy.size(); x++)
15133  {
15134  TTrainDataEntry &TrainDataEntry = TrainDataVectorCopy.at(x);
15135  TActionVector &ActionVector = TrainDataEntry.ActionVector;
15136  TActionVectorIterator AVLast = ActionVector.end() - 1;//points to last entry
15137  TDateTime LastTDTime;

15140  if(ActionVector.empty())
15141  {
15142  continue;
15143  }
15144  if(ActionVector.at(0).SignallerControl)
15145  {
15146  continue;
15147  }
15148  if(AVLast->FormatType == Repeat)
15149  {
15150  IncMinutes = ActionVector.at(ActionVector.size() - 1).RearStartOrRepeatMins;
15151  AVLast--; //now points to the command before the repeat
15152  }
15153  if(AVLast->FormatType == FinRemHere) //not 'else if' as may have both a repeat and an Frh
15154  {
15155  AVLast--; //points to last timed entry
15156  }
15157  //here AVLast points to last entry with a time
15158  if(AVLast->ArrivalTime != TDateTime(-1))

15161  }
15162  else if(AVLast->EventTime != TDateTime(-1)) //can't be a departure time
15163  {
15164  LastTDTime = AVLast->EventTime;
15165  }
15166  else
15167  {
15168  continue; //shouldn't ever reach here but if do then skip this service
15169  }
15170  if(NumTrains == 1)
15171  {
15172  LastAnsiTime = Utilities->Format96HHMM(LastTDTime);
15173  }
15174  else
15175  {
15176  LastAnsiTime = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetRepeatTime(59, LastTDTime, NumTrains - 1, IncMinutes));
15177  }
15178  if(LastAnsiTime > LastTTTime)
15179  {
15180  LastTTTime = LastAnsiTime;
15181  }
15182  }
15183 
15184 //build LocServiceTimesVector
15185 
15186 /* struct TLocServiceTimes
15187  {
15188  AnsiString Location;
15189  AnsiString ServiceAndRepeatNum;
15190  AnsiString AtLocTime;
15191  AnsiString ArrTime;
15192  AnsiString DepTime;
15193  };
15194  typedef std::vector<TLocServiceTimes> TLocServiceTimesVector;
15195 
15196 This works as follows:
15197 ServiceAndRepeatNum is taken from the TrainDataVector as it is the same for all actionvector entries
15198 Location is taken from ActionVectorEntry.LocationName if there is one, or from the H & V locations if not (e.g. at an unnamed Fer)
15199 AtLocTime is always entered either on its own or with ArrTime or DepTime as appropriate
15200 
15201 Every action for every train is examined and times entered as follows:-
15202 a) a located Snt: entry time becomes the AtLocTime, and all subsequent minutes entered too up to but not including a departure or a finish
15203 b) an unlocated Snt: entry time becomes DepTime
15204 c) all other start entries: entry time becomes AtLoc, and all subsequent minutes entered too up to but not including a departure or a finish
15205 d) TimeLoc Arr: entry time becomes ArrTime, and all subsequent minutes entered too up to but not including a departure or a finish
15206 e) TimeLoc Dep: entry time becomes DepTime, checks if DepTime same as earlier ArrTime and if so all times go in as one entry
15207 f) TimeTimeLoc: Arrival time entered as ErrTime, a check if Arr & Dep same and if s go in as one entry, else all minutes between entered as AtLocs then DepTime
15208 g) ExitRailway (Fer): check if located and use Locationname if so. else use H & V positions, time becomes AtLocTime
15209 h) Frh: use the earlier vector time as the AtLocTime and set FrhMarker, and enter all minutes to end of timetable as AtLocs
15210 i) Frh-sh: for the last train use time as AtLocTime, set FrhMarker, and enter all minutes to end of timetable as AtLocs
15211 j) all other finish entries (all link to another service) are ignored as will be listed for the linked service
15212 */
15213  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVectorCopy.size(); x++)
15214  {
15215  const TTrainDataEntry &TrainDataEntry = TrainDataVectorCopy.at(x);
15216  const TActionVector &ActionVector = TrainDataEntry.ActionVector;
15217  AnsiString ServiceRef = TrainDataEntry.ServiceReference;
15218  int IncMinutes = 0;
15219  NumTrains = TrainDataEntry.NumberOfTrains;
15220  if(ActionVector.empty())
15221  {
15222  continue;
15223  }
15224  if(ActionVector.at(0).SignallerControl)
15225  {
15226  continue;
15227  }
15228  if(ActionVector.at(ActionVector.size() - 1).FormatType == Repeat)
15229  {
15230  IncMinutes = ActionVector.at(ActionVector.size() - 1).RearStartOrRepeatMins;
15231  }
15232 
15233  for(int y = 0; y < NumTrains; y++)
15234  {
15235  if(NumTrains == 1)
15236  {
15237  TLSTEntry.ServiceAndRepeatNum = ServiceRef;
15238  }
15239  else if(y == 0)
15240  {
15241  TLSTEntry.ServiceAndRepeatNum = ServiceRef + " (First service)";
15242  }
15243  else
15244  {
15245  TLSTEntry.ServiceAndRepeatNum = ServiceRef + " (Repeat " + AnsiString(y) + ")";
15246  }
15247  for(unsigned int z = 0; z < ActionVector.size(); z++)
15248  {
15249  TActionVectorEntry AVE = ActionVector.at(z);
15250  TLSTEntry.AtLocTime = "";
15251  TLSTEntry.ArrTime = "";
15252  TLSTEntry.DepTime = "";
15253  TLSTEntry.Location = "";

15255 
15256  if(AVE.FormatType == StartNew) //Snt only
15257  {

15259  {

15262  LocServiceTimesVector.push_back(TLSTEntry);
15263 
15264  //now look forwards until find a departure or a Fns, Fns-sh etc & add in all the minutes up to but not including the dep or finish times
15265  AnsiString IncTime = "", FoundStopTime = ""; //these handled in later checks
15266  for(unsigned int a = z + 1; a < ActionVector.size(); a++)
15267  {
15268  if(ActionVector.at(a).FormatType == TimeLoc) //must be a departure
15269  {
15270  FoundStopTime = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetRepeatTime(62, ActionVector.at(a).DepartureTime, y, IncMinutes));
15271  break;
15272  }
15273  if(ActionVector.at(a).SequenceType == Finish) //finish catered in a later test
15274  {
15275  FoundStopTime = Utilities->Format96HHMM(GetRepeatTime(63, ActionVector.at(a).EventTime, y, IncMinutes));
15276  break;
15277  }
15278  }
15279  if(FoundStopTime == "")
15280  {
15281  throw Exception("Failure to determine FoundStopTime for located Snt");
15282  }

15284  while(true)
15285  {
15286  //add minutes until reach StopAddingMinutesTime but don't add that time
15287  WhileCount++;
15288  IncTime = Utilities->IncrementAnsiTimeOneMinute(TLSTEntry.AtLocTime);
15289  TLSTEntry.AtLocTime = IncTime;//all entered times will be AtLocs
15290  TLSTEntry.DepTime = "";
15291  TLSTEntry.ArrTime = "";
15292  if(IncTime >= FoundStopTime) //don't add that time
15293  {
15294  break;
15295  }
15296  LocServiceTimesVector.push_back(TLSTEntry);
15297  if(WhileCount > 2000)
15298  {
15299  throw Exception("While loop failed to break in 2000 loops for located Snt");
15300  }
15301  }
15302  }
15303  else //unlocated Snt, use the EventTime as DepTime for this vector

15309  }

15317  {

15319  }
15320  else
15321  {
15322  HString = AnsiString(HLoc);
15323  }
15324  if(VLoc < 0)
15325  {
15326  VString = 'N' + AnsiString(VLoc).SubString(2, AnsiString(VLoc).Length() - 1); //strip off '-'
15327  }
15328  else
15329  {
15330  VString = AnsiString(VLoc);
15331  }
15332  TLSTEntry.Location = HString + '-' + VString;
15333  }

15335  TLSTEntry.AtLocTime = TLSTEntry.DepTime;
15336  LocServiceTimesVector.push_back(TLSTEntry);
15337  }
15338  }

15641  //routine for arrivals - number of trains arriving within the specified range with services listed at the end

15653  Ptr1 = LocServiceTimesVector.begin();

15659  ServiceAndRepeatNumTotal = "";

15664  {

15666  NumTrainsAtLoc = 0;

15668  NumPlats = 0;

15672  Ptr2++;

15674  {
15675  break;
15676  }
15677  }

15679  {
15680  break;
15681  }

15683  {
15684  PreviousService = "";

15688  if((Ptr1->Location == "") && (Ptr2->Location == ""))
15689  {
15690  break;
15691  }
15692  while(!WithinTimeRange(0, BasicTime, Ptr2->ArrTime, ArrRange) || ((Ptr1->ArrTime == "") && (Ptr2->ArrTime == "")))
15693  {
15694  BasicTime = Ptr2->ArrTime; //used to compare later times or last can exceed first
15695  Ptr1++;
15696  Ptr2++;
15697  if(Ptr2 == LocServiceTimesVector.end())
15698  {
15699  break;
15700  }
15701  if(Ptr2->Location != Ptr1->Location)
15702  {
15703  break;
15704  }
15705  }

15707  {
15708  break;

15711  {
15712  break;
15713  }
15714  while(WithinTimeRange(1, BasicTime, Ptr2->ArrTime, ArrRange))
15715  {
15716  if((Ptr1->ArrTime == "") && (Ptr2->ArrTime == ""))
15717  {
15718  break;
15719  }

15723  NumPlatsAtThisLocCalculated = true;

15730  NumTrainsAtLoc = 1;
15731  }
15732  else
15733  {
15734  ServiceAndRepeatNumTotal = ServiceAndRepeatNumTotal + "," + Ptr1->ServiceAndRepeatNum + "," + Ptr1->ArrTime;
15735  }

15738  if(ServiceAndRepeatNumTotal == "")
15739  {
15740  ServiceAndRepeatNumTotal = Ptr2->ServiceAndRepeatNum + "," + Ptr2->ArrTime;

15742  }

15746  }

15752  ServiceAndRepeatNumTotalOutput = ConsolidateSARNTArrDep(1, ServiceAndRepeatNumTotal, NumTrainsAtLoc, Ptr1->Location, true, AnalysisError, MaxNumberOfSameDirections); //sort into alphabetical order and remove duplicates
15753  if(AnalysisError) //has to be Ptr1->Location as Ptr2 loc may have changed
15754  {
15755 // ShowMessage("Error in arrival analysis - file will be incomplete and/or corrupt. Please send railway and timetable files to railwayfeedback@gmail.com for investigation - thanks. Details: " + ServiceAndRepeatNumTotalOutput);
15756  TTFile3.close();
15757  throw Exception(ServiceAndRepeatNumTotalOutput.c_str());
15758 // Utilities->CallLogPop(2224);
15759 // return false;
15760  }
15761  AnsiString Asterisk = "";
15762  if(MaxNumberOfSameDirections >= NumPlats)
15763  {
15764  Asterisk = "* ";
15765  }

15768  ArrivalsPrinted = true;
15769  ServiceAndRepeatNumTotal = "";
15770  }
15771  if(Ptr2 == LocServiceTimesVector.end())
15772  {
15773  break;
15774  }
15775  if(Ptr2->Location != Ptr1->Location)
15776  {
15777  break;
15778  }
15779  }
15780  if(Ptr2 == LocServiceTimesVector.end())
15781  {
15782  break;
15783  }
15784  }
15785  }
15786  if(!ArrivalsPrinted)
15787  {
15788  TTFile3 << "Nothing to report for arrivals";
15789  }
15790  TTFile3 << "\n\n\n";
15791  }

15793 
15794  //departures
15795  if(DepChecked)
15796  {
15797  //sort in DepTime order for each location

15799  Ptr2 = Ptr1 + 1;
15800  while(Ptr2 != LocServiceTimesVector.end())
15801  {

15808  }

15818  //routine for departures - number of trains departing within the specified range with services listed at the end
15819  TTFile3 << "Departure analysis - an asterisk means that the number of same exit code departures is equal to or greater than the number of platforms\n\n";

15821  AnsiString ServiceAndRepeatNumTotal = "", ServiceAndRepeatNumTotalOutput = "";

16204 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
16205 
16206 bool TTrainController::WithinTimeRange(int Caller, AnsiString Time1, AnsiString Time2, int MinuteRange) //times are "HH:MM"
16207 {
16208 //convert times to integer minutes
16209  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",WithinTimeRange," + Time1 + "," + Time2 + "," + AnsiString(MinuteRange));
16210  if((Time1 == "") || (Time2 == ""))
16211  {
16212  Utilities->CallLogPop(2213);
16213  return false;
16214  }
16215  int Mins = Time1.SubString(4,2).ToInt();
16216  int Hours = Time1.SubString(1,2).ToInt();
16217  int Time1Mins = (Hours * 60) + Mins;
16218  Mins = Time2.SubString(4,2).ToInt();
16219  Hours = Time2.SubString(1,2).ToInt();
16220  int Time2Mins = (Hours * 60) + Mins;
16221  if(abs(Time1Mins - Time2Mins) <= MinuteRange)
16222  {
16223  Utilities->CallLogPop(2214);
16224  return true;
16225  }
16226  Utilities->CallLogPop(2215);
16227  return false;
16228 }

16231 
16232 AnsiString TTrainController::ConsolidateSARNTArrDep(int Caller, const AnsiString Input, int &NumTrainsAtLoc, AnsiString Location, bool Arrival,
16233  bool &AnalysisError, int &MaxNumberOfSameDirections)
16234 {//input consists of services and service Arr or Dep times as a comma separated list, Location needed to determine direction information
16235 
16236  try
16237  {
16238  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",ConsolidateSARNTArrDep," + Input);
16239  AnsiString Output = "", OneService = "", TempStr1 = "", TempStr2 = "";
16240  int SCPos = 0;
16241  std::list<AnsiString> ServiceList; //this is the list of services with times extracted from Input - not to be confused with ServiceCallingPointsList
16242  //first change every second comma in Input to a semicolon so can separate services but keep times with services
16243  bool EvenComma = false;
16244  for(int x = 1; x <= Input.Length(); x++)
16245  {
16246  TempStr1 = Input[x];
16247  if(TempStr1 == AnsiString(',') && EvenComma)
16248  {
16249  TempStr2 += ';';
16250  }
16251  else
16252  {
16253  TempStr2 += Input[x];
16254  }
16255  if(TempStr1 == AnsiString(','))
16256  {
16257  EvenComma = !EvenComma;
16258  }
16259  }
16260  //load up the list of services with associated times
16261  while(TempStr2.Length() > 0)
16262  {
16263  SCPos = TempStr2.Pos(';');
16264  if(SCPos > 0) //0 if not found, as won't be when only one service left
16265  {
16266  OneService = TempStr2.SubString(1, SCPos - 1);
16267  ServiceList.push_back(OneService);
16268  TempStr2 = TempStr2.SubString(SCPos + 1, TempStr2.Length() - SCPos);
16269  }
16270  else //no semicolon so looking at last (or only) element
16271  {
16272  ServiceList.push_back(TempStr2);
16273  TempStr2 = "";
16274  }
16275  }
16276  ServiceList.sort(); // alphabetical order
16277  ServiceList.unique(); //remove duplicates
16278  NumTrainsAtLoc = ServiceList.size(); //calc this after removing duplicates as may not have changed
16279 
16280  //now add direction information from AllServiceCallingLocsMap - key is service ref and value a list of calling points in order
16281  int DirectionMarker = 0; //this is added in & runs from 1 upwards, same marker for diff services = same direction
16282  //first add the direction marker "&0" for not yet allocated - '&' is an identifier
16283  std::list<AnsiString>::iterator SLIt, SLIt1, SLIt2, SLIt3;
16284 
16285  for(SLIt = ServiceList.begin(); SLIt != ServiceList.end(); SLIt++)
16286  {
16287  *SLIt = *SLIt + "&0"; //add in a basic direction marker to each service
16288  }
16289  SLIt3 = ServiceList.end();
16290  SLIt3--; //so points to last element
16291  AnsiString ServiceRef1, ServiceRef2, AnsiTime1, AnsiTime2, RepeatInfo1, RepeatInfo2; //1 refers to first for..next loop & 2 to second
16292  int AmpersandPos, SpacePos, CommaPos1, CommaPos2, RepeatNum1, RepeatNum2;
16293  TAllServiceCallingLocsMap::iterator ASCLIt1, ASCLIt2;
16294  TServiceCallingLocsList ServiceCallingLocsList1, ServiceCallingLocsList2;
16295  MaxNumberOfSameDirections = 0; //at end of each SLIt loop if SameDirectionCount > MaxNumberOfSameDirections then MaxNumberOfSameDirections = SameDirectionCount
16296  int SameDirectionCount = 0; //starts at 1 at each SLIt loop (because SLIt1 entry already has a DirectionMarker) and increments for every same direction
16297 
16298  for(std::list<AnsiString>::iterator SLIt1 = ServiceList.begin(); SLIt1 != SLIt3; SLIt1++) //should be end() - 1 but can't use -1 with lists so have to improvise
16299  {
16300  SLIt = SLIt1;
16301  SLIt++; //so points to one after SLIt1
16302  if(SLIt1->SubString(SLIt1->Length() - 1, 2) != AnsiString("&0"))
16303  {
16304  continue; //already allocated so skip to the next
16305  }
16306  else
16307  {
16308  CommaPos1 = SLIt1->Pos(','); //can't be 0
16309  ServiceRef1 = SLIt1->SubString(1, CommaPos1 - 1);
16310  //but this contains "(First service..." etc so need to strip these, but use to extract RepeatNum
16311  SpacePos = ServiceRef1.Pos(' ');
16312  RepeatNum1 = 0;
16313  if(SpacePos > 0) //otherwise it's already correct
16314  {
16315  RepeatInfo1 = ServiceRef1.SubString(SpacePos + 2, ServiceRef1.Length() - SpacePos - 2); //drops the brackets and leaves "First service", "Repeat 2" etc
16316  ServiceRef1 = ServiceRef1.SubString(1, SpacePos - 1);
16317  if(RepeatInfo1[1] == 'F')
16318  {
16319  RepeatNum1 = 0;
16320  }
16321  else
16322  {
16323  SpacePos = RepeatInfo1.Pos(' ');
16324  RepeatNum1 = RepeatInfo1.SubString(SpacePos + 1, RepeatInfo1.Length() - SpacePos).ToInt();
16325  }
16326  }
16327  AnsiTime1 = SLIt1->SubString(CommaPos1 + 1, SLIt1->Length() - CommaPos1);
16328  //but this includes the "&0" etc so need to strip these
16329  AmpersandPos = AnsiTime1.Pos('&');
16330  AnsiTime1 = AnsiTime1.SubString(1, AmpersandPos - 1);
16331 
16332  ASCLIt1 = AllServiceCallingLocsMap.find(ServiceRef1);
16333  if(ASCLIt1 == AllServiceCallingLocsMap.end()) //can't find it
16334  {
16335  throw Exception("ASCLIt1 Error in " + Input);
16336  }
16337  ServiceCallingLocsList1 = ASCLIt1->second;
16338  AmpersandPos = SLIt1->Pos('&');
16339  *SLIt1 = SLIt1->SubString(1, AmpersandPos); //truncate up to & leave in the '&'
16340  *SLIt1 = *SLIt1 + AnsiString(++DirectionMarker); //now add the next marker (pre-increment), allow for it being more than one digit
16341 
16342  SameDirectionCount = 1;
16343  for(SLIt2 = SLIt; SLIt2 != ServiceList.end(); SLIt2++)
16344  {
16345  CommaPos2 = SLIt2->Pos(','); //can't be 0
16346  ServiceRef2 = SLIt2->SubString(1, CommaPos2 - 1);
16347  //but this contains "(First service..." etc so need to strip these
16348  SpacePos = ServiceRef2.Pos(' ');
16349  RepeatNum2 = 0;
16350  if(SpacePos > 0) //otherwise it's already correct
16351  {
16352  RepeatInfo2 = ServiceRef2.SubString(SpacePos + 2, ServiceRef2.Length() - SpacePos - 2); //drops the brackets and leaves "First service", "Repeat 2" etc
16353  ServiceRef2 = ServiceRef2.SubString(1, SpacePos - 1);
16354  if(RepeatInfo2[1] == 'F')
16355  {
16356  RepeatNum2 = 0;
16357  }
16358  else
16359  {
16360  SpacePos = RepeatInfo2.Pos(' ');
16361  RepeatNum2 = RepeatInfo2.SubString(SpacePos + 1, RepeatInfo2.Length() - SpacePos).ToInt();
16362  }
16363 
16364  }
16365  AnsiTime2 = SLIt2->SubString(CommaPos2 + 1, SLIt2->Length() - CommaPos2);
16366  //but this includes the "&0" etc so need to strip these
16367  AmpersandPos = AnsiTime2.Pos('&');
16368  AnsiTime2 = AnsiTime2.SubString(1, AmpersandPos - 1);
16369 
16370  ASCLIt2 = AllServiceCallingLocsMap.find(ServiceRef2);
16371  if(ASCLIt2 == AllServiceCallingLocsMap.end()) //can't find it
16372  {
16373  throw Exception("ASCLIt2 Error in " + Input);
16374  }
16375  ServiceCallingLocsList2 = ASCLIt2->second;
16376  //now compare the two
16377  if(SameDirection(0, ServiceRef1, ServiceRef2, AnsiTime1, AnsiTime2, RepeatNum1, RepeatNum2, ServiceCallingLocsList1, ServiceCallingLocsList2, Location, Arrival))
16378  {
16379  int AmpersandPos = SLIt2->Pos('&');
16380  *SLIt2 = SLIt2->SubString(1, AmpersandPos); //truncate up to & leave in the '&'
16381  *SLIt2 = *SLIt2 + AnsiString(DirectionMarker); //now add the same marker as *SLIt1
16382  SameDirectionCount++;
16383  }
16384  }
16385  if(SameDirectionCount > MaxNumberOfSameDirections)
16386  {
16387  MaxNumberOfSameDirections = SameDirectionCount;
16388  }
16389  }
16390  }
16391 
16392  if(SLIt3->SubString(SLIt3->Length() - 1, 2) == AnsiString("&0"))//*SLTIt3 is the last in the list and may not have been allocated, if not it doesn't match
16393  { //any existing direction so allocate it now
16394  AmpersandPos = SLIt3->Pos('&');
16395  *SLIt3 = SLIt3->SubString(1, AmpersandPos); //truncate up to & leave in the '&'
16396  *SLIt3 = *SLIt3 + AnsiString(++DirectionMarker);
16397  }
16398 
16399  //now change direction markers to upper case letters beginning with 'A' (and continuing with 'AA' if exceed 26) & add a comma before so have ServiceRef, DirectionMarker, Time
16400  for(SLIt = ServiceList.begin(); SLIt != ServiceList.end(); SLIt++)
16401  {
16402  //extract the DirectionMarker as an integer
16403  AmpersandPos = SLIt->Pos('&');
16404  AnsiString DirectionMarkerString = SLIt->SubString(AmpersandPos + 1, SLIt->Length() - AmpersandPos); //extract the number as an ansistring
16405  AnsiString ServiceWithoutMarker = SLIt->SubString(1, AmpersandPos - 1); //truncate the &number
16406  DirectionMarker = DirectionMarkerString.ToInt();
16407  AnsiString DirectionSuffix = "";
16408  char c;
16409  if(DirectionMarker < 27)
16410  {
16411  c = 64 + DirectionMarker; //so 1 -> 'A'
16412  DirectionSuffix = "," + AnsiString(c);
16413  }
16414  else if(DirectionMarker < 53)
16415  {
16416  c = 65 + DirectionMarker - 27; //so 27 -> 'AA'
16417  DirectionSuffix = ",A" + AnsiString(c);
16418  }
16419  else
16420  {
16421  DirectionSuffix = ",?"; //shouldn'tn ever get this far!
16422  }
16423  *SLIt = ServiceWithoutMarker + DirectionSuffix;
16424  }
16425  //now prepare the final consolidated output
16426  for(SLIt = ServiceList.begin(); SLIt != ServiceList.end(); SLIt++)
16427  {
16428  Output = Output + *SLIt + ","; //will end up with an unwanted comma at the end
16429  }
16430  if(Output.Length() > 0)
16431  {
16432  Output = Output.SubString(1, Output.Length() - 1); //remove the last comma
16433  }
16434  Utilities->CallLogPop(2216);
16435  return Output;
16436  }
16437 
16438  catch(const Exception &e)
16439  {
16440  AnalysisError = true;
16441  Utilities->CallLogPop(2227);
16442  return e.Message;
16443  }
16444 }

16447 
16448 AnsiString TTrainController::ConsolidateSARNTAtLoc(int Caller, const AnsiString Input, int &NumTrainsAtLoc)
16449 {//similar to above but doesn't include times in the input
16450  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",ConsolidateSARNTAtLoc," + Input);
16451  AnsiString InternalInput = Input, Output = "", OneService = "";
16452  int CommaPos = 0;
16453  std::list<AnsiString> ServiceList;
16454  //load up the list
16455  while(InternalInput.Length() > 0)
16456  {
16457  CommaPos = InternalInput.Pos(',');
16458  if(CommaPos > 0) //0 if not found, as won't be when only one service left
16459  {
16460  OneService = InternalInput.SubString(1, CommaPos - 1);
16461  ServiceList.push_back(OneService);
16462  InternalInput = InternalInput.SubString(CommaPos + 1, InternalInput.Length() - CommaPos);
16463  }
16464  else //no comma so looking at last (or only) element
16465  {
16466  ServiceList.push_back(InternalInput);
16467  InternalInput = "";
16468  }
16469  }
16470 
16471  ServiceList.sort(); // alphabetical order
16472  ServiceList.unique(); //remove duplicates
16473  NumTrainsAtLoc = ServiceList.size(); //calc this after removing duplicates as may not have changed
16474  for(std::list<AnsiString>::iterator SLIt = ServiceList.begin(); SLIt != ServiceList.end(); SLIt++)
16475  {
16476  Output = Output + *SLIt + ","; //will end up with an unwanted comma at the end
16477  }
16478  if(Output.Length() > 0)
16479  {
16480  Output = Output.SubString(1, Output.Length() - 1); //remove the last comma
16481  }
16482  Utilities->CallLogPop(2217);
16483  return Output;
16484 }

16488 
16489 bool TTrainController::SameDirection(int Caller, AnsiString Ref1In, AnsiString Ref2In, AnsiString Time1, AnsiString Time2, int RepeatNum1, int RepeatNum2, TServiceCallingLocsList List1,
16490  TServiceCallingLocsList List2, AnsiString Location, bool Arrival)
16491  {
16492  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",SameDirection," + Ref1In + "," + Ref2In + "," + Time1 + "," + Time2 + "," +
16493  AnsiString(RepeatNum1) + "," + AnsiString(RepeatNum2) + "," + Location);
16494 
16495  std::list<AnsiString>::iterator LP1 = 0, LP2 = 0, ListPtr1 = 0, ListPtr2 = 0, LocPtr1 = 0, LocPtr2 = 0; //LP1 & 2 are temporary pointers, ListPtrs are
16496  //general list pointers, LocPtrs point to Location in the two lists
16497 
16498  //first find the relevant values for LocPtr1 & LocPtr2 taking account of cdts and times
16499  //for List1
16500  bool LocFound = false;
16501  AnsiString Ref1 = Ref1In, Ref2 = Ref2In;
16502  int IncMinutes;
16503  TDateTime FirstServiceTime;
16504 
16505  //first need to strip off /1, /2 etc if present from Ref1 & Ref2 (leave Ref1In & Ref2In for error message & retain value as target in finding the correct reference for cdts)
16506  int Ref1Target = 0, Ref1Count = 0;
16507  int SlashPos = Ref1.Pos('/');
16508  if(SlashPos > 0) //if 0 Ref1 == Ref1In & target stays at 0
16509  {
16510  Ref1Target = Ref1.SubString(SlashPos + 1, Ref1.Length() - SlashPos).ToInt();
16511  Ref1 = Ref1.SubString(1, SlashPos - 1); //truncate up to but omit '/'
16512  }
16513  int Ref2Target = 0, Ref2Count = 0;
16514  SlashPos = Ref2.Pos('/');
16515  if(SlashPos > 0) //if 0 leave as is
16516  {
16517  Ref2Target = Ref2.SubString(SlashPos + 1, Ref2.Length() - SlashPos).ToInt();
16518  Ref2 = Ref2.SubString(1, SlashPos - 1); //truncate up to but omit '/'
16519  }
16520 
16521  for(ListPtr1 = List1.begin(); ListPtr1 != List1.end(); ListPtr1++) //note that when this routine entered Ref1In & Ref2In are already set to the correct services,
16522  { //even if others have same names. But if there are cdt's then need to refind the correct service
16523  if((*ListPtr1) == Location) //
16524  {
16525  LocPtr1 = ListPtr1; //may be modified later
16526  LocFound = true;
16527  }
16528  if(ListPtr1->SubString(1, 3) == "%%%")
16529  {
16530  AnsiString CDTTime = ListPtr1->SubString(4, 5);
16531  //now adjust the time to correspond to the repeat if there is one
16532  if(RepeatNum1 > 0) //if it is 0 then AnsiTime1 is already valid
16533  {
16534  IncMinutes = -1;
16535  FirstServiceTime = TDateTime(-1);
16536  bool BreakFlag = false;
16537  for(TTrainDataVector::iterator TDVIt = TrainDataVector.begin(); TDVIt != TrainDataVector.end(); TDVIt++)
16538  {
16539  if(TDVIt->ServiceReference == Ref1)
16540  {
16541  if(Ref1Target > Ref1Count)
16542  {
16543  Ref1Count++;
16544  continue;
16545  }
16546  IncMinutes = TDVIt->ActionVector.back().RearStartOrRepeatMins;
16547  for(TActionVector::iterator AVIt = TDVIt->ActionVector.begin(); AVIt != TDVIt->ActionVector.end(); AVIt++)
16548  {
16549  if(Utilities->Format96HHMM(AVIt->EventTime) == CDTTime)
16550  {
16551  FirstServiceTime = AVIt->EventTime; //i.e. the FirstService value of CDTTime
16552  BreakFlag = true;
16553  break;
16554  }
16555  if(Utilities->Format96HHMM(AVIt->ArrivalTime) == CDTTime) //add arr & dep in case find sooner (though dep shouldn't be sooner)
16556  {
16557  FirstServiceTime = AVIt->ArrivalTime;
16558  BreakFlag = true;
16559  break;
16560  }
16561  if(Utilities->Format96HHMM(AVIt->DepartureTime) == CDTTime)
16562  {
16563  FirstServiceTime = AVIt->DepartureTime;
16564  BreakFlag = true;
16565  break;
16566  }
16567  }
16568  if(BreakFlag)
16569  {
16570  break;
16571  }
16572  }
16573  }
16574  if(IncMinutes == -1)
16575  {
16576  throw Exception("Failed to find service for ServiceRef1 in SameDirection " + Ref1In + " " + Ref2In + " " + Time1 + " " + Time2 + " " + AnsiString(RepeatNum1) + " " + AnsiString(RepeatNum2) + " " + Location);
16577  }
16578  if(FirstServiceTime == TDateTime(-1))
16579  {
16580  throw Exception("Failed to find first service time for ServiceRef1 in SameDirection " + Ref1In + " " + Ref2In + " " + Time1 + " " + Time2 + " " + AnsiString(RepeatNum1) + " " + AnsiString(RepeatNum2) + " " + Location);
16581  }
16582  CDTTime = Utilities->Format96HHMM(TrainController->GetRepeatTime(60, FirstServiceTime, RepeatNum1, IncMinutes));
16583  }
16584  if(!Arrival && (Time1 == CDTTime)) //continue if equal in case next is a departure for the Location
16585  {
16586  LocFound = false;
16587  continue;
16588  }
16589  if(Arrival && (Time1 == CDTTime)) //gone far enough so can stop
16590  {
16591  break;
16592  }
16593  if(Time1 > CDTTime) //not there yet so go on
16594  {
16595  LocFound = false;
16596  continue;
16597  }
16598  if(Time1 < CDTTime) //gone too far so can stop now
16599  {
16600  break;
16601  }
16602  }
16603  }
16604  if(!LocFound) //have to find it in both lists
16605  {
16606  Utilities->CallLogPop(2228);
16607  return false;
16608  }
16609 
16610  //for List2
16611  LocFound = false;
16612  for(ListPtr2 = List2.begin(); ListPtr2 != List2.end(); ListPtr2++)
16613  {
16614  if((*ListPtr2) == Location)
16615  {
16616  LocPtr2 = ListPtr2; //may be modified later
16617  LocFound = true;
16618  }
16619  if(ListPtr2->SubString(1, 3) == "%%%")
16620  {
16621  AnsiString CDTTime = ListPtr2->SubString(4, 5);
16622  //now adjust the time to correspond to the repeat if there is one
16623  if(RepeatNum2 > 0) //if it is 0 then AnsiTime1 is already valid
16624  {
16625  IncMinutes = -1;
16626  FirstServiceTime = TDateTime(-1);
16627  bool BreakFlag = false;
16628  for(TTrainDataVector::iterator TDVIt = TrainDataVector.begin(); TDVIt != TrainDataVector.end(); TDVIt++)
16629  {
16630  if(TDVIt->ServiceReference == Ref2)
16631  {
16632  if(Ref2Target > Ref2Count)
16633  {
16634  Ref2Count++;
16635  continue;
16636  }
16637  IncMinutes = TDVIt->ActionVector.back().RearStartOrRepeatMins;
16638  for(TActionVector::iterator AVIt = TDVIt->ActionVector.begin(); AVIt != TDVIt->ActionVector.end(); AVIt++)
16639  {
16640  if(Utilities->Format96HHMM(AVIt->EventTime) == CDTTime)
16641  {
16642  FirstServiceTime = AVIt->EventTime;
16643  BreakFlag = true;
16644  break;
16645  }
16646  if(Utilities->Format96HHMM(AVIt->ArrivalTime) == CDTTime)
16647  {
16648  FirstServiceTime = AVIt->ArrivalTime;
16649  BreakFlag = true;
16650  break;
16651  }
16652  if(Utilities->Format96HHMM(AVIt->DepartureTime) == CDTTime)
16653  {
16654  FirstServiceTime = AVIt->DepartureTime;
16655  BreakFlag = true;
16656  break;
16657  }
16658  }
16659  if(BreakFlag)
16660  {
16661  break;
16662  }
16663  }
16664  }
16665  if(IncMinutes == -1)
16666  {
16667  throw Exception("IncMinutes -1 for ServiceRef2 in SameDirection " + Ref1In + " " + Ref2In + " " + Time1 + " " + Time2 + " " + AnsiString(RepeatNum1) + " " + AnsiString(RepeatNum2) + " " + Location);
16668  }
16669  if(FirstServiceTime == TDateTime(-1))
16670  {
16671  throw Exception("First service time -1 for ServiceRef2 in SameDirection " + Ref1In + " " + Ref2In + " " + Time1 + " " + Time2 + " " + AnsiString(RepeatNum1) + " " + AnsiString(RepeatNum2) + " " + Location);
16672  }
16673  CDTTime = Utilities->Format96HHMM(TrainController->GetRepeatTime(61, FirstServiceTime, RepeatNum2, IncMinutes));
16674  }
16675  if(!Arrival && (Time2 == CDTTime)) //continue if equal in case next is a departure for the Location
16676  {
16677  LocFound = false;
16678  continue;
16679  }
16680  if(Arrival && (Time2 == CDTTime)) //gone far enough so can stop
16681  {
16682  break;
16683  }
16684  if(Time2 > CDTTime) //not there yet so go on
16685  {
16686  LocFound = false;
16687  continue;
16688  }
16689  if(Time2 < CDTTime) //gone too far so can stop now
16690  {
16691  break;
16692  }
16693  }
16694  }
16695  if(!LocFound) //have to find it in both lists, and should be found but allow for it not being
16696  {
16697  Utilities->CallLogPop(2229);
16698  return false;
16699  }
16700 
16701  //now, for the arrival analysis, see if there is a common location before the LocPtrs & within any cdts, and if so return true, else return false
16702  //set ListPtr1 to the search start position
16703  if(Arrival)
16704  {
16705  LP1 = List1.begin();
16706  LP1--; //now points to before the first entry
16707  for(ListPtr1 = LocPtr1; ListPtr1 != LP1; ListPtr1--) //search backwards from Location
16708  {
16709  if(ListPtr1 == List1.begin())
16710  {
16711  break;
16712  }
16713  if(ListPtr1->SubString(1, 3) == "%%%") //a cdt event
16714  {
16715  ListPtr1++; //point to one past the cdt
16716  break;
16717  }
16718  }
16719  //set ListPtr2 to the search start position
16720  LP2 = List2.begin();
16721  LP2--; //now points to before the first entry
16722  for(ListPtr2 = LocPtr2; ListPtr2 != LP2; ListPtr2--)
16723  {
16724  if(ListPtr2 == List2.begin())
16725  {
16726  break;
16727  }
16728  if(ListPtr2->SubString(1, 3) == "%%%") //a cdt event
16729  {
16730  ListPtr2++; //point to one past the cdt
16731  break;
16732  }
16733  }
16734  //ListPtr1 & 2 now at search start position
16735  LP1 = ListPtr1;
16736  LP2 = ListPtr2;
16737  //now search forwards, i.e. for common locations before Location
16738  for(ListPtr1 = LP1; ListPtr1 != List1.end(); ListPtr1++)
16739  {
16740  if(ListPtr1 == LocPtr1) //reached Location without finding a common earlier location so skip to the backwards check
16741  {
16742  break;
16743  }
16744  if(ListPtr1->SubString(1, 3) == "%%%") //reached a cdt event without finding a common earlier location
16745  {
16746  break;
16747  }
16748  for(ListPtr2 = LP2; ListPtr2 != List2.end(); ListPtr2++)
16749  {
16750  if(ListPtr2 == LocPtr2) //not found common earlier location so go to the next ListPtr1
16751  {
16752  break;
16753  }
16754  if(ListPtr2->SubString(1, 3) == "%%%") //reached a cdt event without finding a common earlier location so go to the next ListPtr1
16755  {
16756  break;
16757  }
16758  if((*ListPtr1) == (*ListPtr2)) //found a common earlier location
16759  {
16760  Utilities->CallLogPop(2230);
16761  return true;
16762  }
16763  }
16764  }
16765  }
16766 
16767  //now, for the departure analysis, reset the start positions and search locations after Location
16768 
16769  else
16770  {
16771  LP1 = LocPtr1; LP1++; //start at one past the location itself
16772  LP2 = LocPtr2; LP2++;
16773  for(ListPtr1 = LP1; ListPtr1 != List1.end(); ListPtr1++)
16774  {
16775  if(ListPtr1 == List1.end()) //reached end point so stop
16776  {
16777  break;
16778  }
16779  if(ListPtr1->SubString(1, 3) == "%%%") //reached a cdt event without finding a common location
16780  {
16781  break;
16782  }
16783  for(ListPtr2 = LP2; ListPtr2 != List2.end(); ListPtr2++)
16784  {
16785  if(ListPtr2 == List2.end()) //reached end point so go to next ListPtr1
16786  {
16787  break;
16788  }
16789  if(ListPtr2->SubString(1, 3) == "%%%") //reached a cdt event without finding a common location so go to the next ListPtr1
16790  {
16791  break;
16792  }
16793  if((*ListPtr1) == (*ListPtr2)) //found a common later location
16794  {
16795  Utilities->CallLogPop(2231);
16796  return true;
16797  }
16798  }
16799  }
16800  }
16801  Utilities->CallLogPop(2232);
16802  return false;
16803  }

16874 
16875 void TTrainController::SendPerformanceSummary(int Caller, std::ofstream &PerfFile)
16876 {
16877  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",SendPerformanceSummary");
16878  AnsiString FormatStr = "####0.0";
16879  AnsiString AvLateArrMins = "";
16880  AnsiString AvEarlyArrMins = "";
16881  AnsiString AvLatePassMins = "";
16882  AnsiString AvEarlyPassMins = "";
16883  AnsiString AvLateDepMins = "";
16884 
16885  if(LateArrivals > 0)
16886  AvLateArrMins = FormatFloat(FormatStr, (TotLateArrMins / LateArrivals));
16887  if(EarlyArrivals > 0)
16888  AvEarlyArrMins = FormatFloat(FormatStr, (TotEarlyArrMins / EarlyArrivals));
16889  if(LatePasses > 0)
16890  AvLatePassMins = FormatFloat(FormatStr, (TotLatePassMins / LatePasses));
16891  if(EarlyPasses > 0)
16892  AvEarlyPassMins = FormatFloat(FormatStr, (TotEarlyPassMins / EarlyPasses));
16893  if(LateDeps > 0)
16894  AvLateDepMins = FormatFloat(FormatStr, (TotLateDepMins / LateDeps));
16895 
16896  PerfFile << '\n' << '\n' << "***************************************";
16897  PerfFile << '\n' << '\n' << "Performance summary:" << '\n';
16898 
16899  if(OnTimeArrivals != 1)
16900  PerfFile << OnTimeArrivals << " on-time arrivals" << '\n';
16901  else
16902  PerfFile << OnTimeArrivals << " on-time arrival" << '\n';
16903 
16904  if(LateArrivals > 1)
16905  PerfFile << LateArrivals << " late arrivals (average " << AvLateArrMins.c_str() << " min)" << '\n';
16906  else if(LateArrivals == 1)
16907  PerfFile << LateArrivals << " late arrival (" << AvLateArrMins.c_str() << " min)" << '\n';
16908  else
16909  PerfFile << LateArrivals << " late arrivals" << '\n';
16910 
16911  if(EarlyArrivals > 1)
16912  PerfFile << EarlyArrivals << " early arrivals (average " << AvEarlyArrMins.c_str() << " min)" << '\n';
16913  else if(EarlyArrivals == 1)
16914  PerfFile << EarlyArrivals << " early arrival (" << AvEarlyArrMins.c_str() << " min)" << '\n';
16915  else
16916  PerfFile << EarlyArrivals << " early arrivals" << '\n';
16917 
16918  if(OnTimePasses != 1)
16919  PerfFile << OnTimePasses << " on-time passes" << '\n';
16920  else
16921  PerfFile << OnTimePasses << " on-time pass" << '\n';
16922 
16923  if(LatePasses > 1)
16924  PerfFile << LatePasses << " late passes (average " << AvLatePassMins.c_str() << " min)" << '\n';
16925  else if(LatePasses == 1)
16926  PerfFile << LatePasses << " late pass (" << AvLatePassMins.c_str() << " min)" << '\n';
16927  else
16928  PerfFile << LatePasses << " late passes" << '\n';
16929 
16930  if(EarlyPasses > 1)
16931  PerfFile << EarlyPasses << " early passes (average " << AvEarlyPassMins.c_str() << " min)" << '\n';
16932  else if(EarlyPasses == 1)
16933  PerfFile << EarlyPasses << " early pass (" << AvEarlyPassMins.c_str() << " min)" << '\n';
16934  else
16935  PerfFile << EarlyPasses << " early passes" << '\n';
16936 
16937  if(OnTimeDeps != 1)
16938  PerfFile << OnTimeDeps << " on-time departures" << '\n';
16939  else
16940  PerfFile << OnTimeDeps << " on-time departure" << '\n';
16941 
16942  if(LateDeps > 1)
16943  PerfFile << LateDeps << " late departures (average " << AvLateDepMins.c_str() << " min)" << '\n';
16944  else if(LateDeps == 1)
16945  PerfFile << LateDeps << " late departure (" << AvLateDepMins.c_str() << " min)" << '\n';
16946  else
16947  PerfFile << LateDeps << " late departures" << '\n';
16948 
16949  AnsiString FormattedExcessLCDownMins = FormatFloat(FormatStr, ExcessLCDownMins);
16950 
16951  if(ExcessLCDownMins > 0.1)
16952  PerfFile << FormattedExcessLCDownMins.c_str() << " excess minutes of level crossing barrier down time" << '\n';
16953 
16954  if(MissedStops != 1)
16955  PerfFile << MissedStops << " missed stops" << '\n';
16956  else
16957  PerfFile << MissedStops << " missed stop" << '\n';
16958 
16959  if(OtherMissedEvents != 1)
16960  PerfFile << OtherMissedEvents << " other missed events" << '\n';
16961  else
16962  PerfFile << OtherMissedEvents << " other missed event" << '\n';
16963 
16964  if(UnexpectedExits != 1)
16965  PerfFile << UnexpectedExits << " unexpected train exits" << '\n';
16966  else
16967  PerfFile << UnexpectedExits << " unexpected train exit" << '\n';
16968 
16969  if(IncorrectExits != 1)
16970  PerfFile << IncorrectExits << " incorrect train exits" << '\n';
16971  else
16972  PerfFile << IncorrectExits << " incorrect train exit" << '\n';
16973 
16974  if(NumFailures != 1)
16975  PerfFile << NumFailures << " train failures" << '\n';
16976  else
16977  PerfFile << NumFailures << " train failure" << '\n';
16978 
16979  if(AvHoursIntValue > 0)
16980  {
16981  if(AvHoursIntValue == 1)
16982  {
16983  PerfFile << AvHoursIntValue << " hour mean time betweeen train failures" << '\n';
16984  }
16985  else
16986  {
16987  PerfFile << AvHoursIntValue << " hours mean time betweeen train failures" << '\n';
16988  }
16989  }
16990 
16991  AnsiString AvLateMinsLocsNotReached = "";
16992 
16993  CalcOperatingAndNotStartedTrainLateness(0);
16994  int LocsNotReached = (NotStartedTrainArrDep + OperatingTrainArrDep) / 2;
16995 
16996  // each location has an arrival and departure (generally) so divide by 2
16997  if(LocsNotReached > 0)
16998  {
16999  AvLateMinsLocsNotReached = FormatFloat(FormatStr, (OperatingTrainLateMins + NotStartedTrainLateMins) / (NotStartedTrainArrDep + OperatingTrainArrDep));
17000  PerfFile << LocsNotReached << " locations that trains failed to reach (average lateness " << AvLateMinsLocsNotReached.c_str() << " min)" << '\n';
17001  }
17002 
17003  if(SPADRisks != 1)
17004  PerfFile << SPADRisks << " SPAD risks" << '\n';
17005  else
17006  PerfFile << SPADRisks << " SPAD risk" << '\n';
17007 
17008  if(SPADEvents != 1)
17009  PerfFile << SPADEvents << " SPADs" << '\n';
17010  else
17011  PerfFile << SPADEvents << " SPAD" << '\n';
17012 
17013  if(Derailments != 1)
17014  PerfFile << Derailments << " derailments" << '\n';
17015  else
17016  PerfFile << Derailments << " derailment" << '\n';
17017 
17018  if(CrashedTrains != 1)
17019  PerfFile << CrashedTrains << " crashed trains" << '\n';
17020  else
17021  PerfFile << CrashedTrains << " crashed train" << '\n';
17022 
17023  PerfFile << '\n' << "***************************************" << '\n';
17024 
17025  bool DerailSPADFlag = false, CrashFlag = false;
17026 
17027  int OverallScorePercent = 100;
17028  int TotArrDep = 0;
17029  double TotLateMinsFactor = 1;
17030  double MissedStopAndSPADRiskFactor = 1;
17031  double NetNegFactor = 1;
17032 
17033  TotArrDep = OnTimeArrivals + LateArrivals + EarlyArrivals + OnTimeDeps + LateDeps + NotStartedTrainArrDep + OperatingTrainArrDep;
17034  // TotArrDep: total number of arrivals & departures including those for trains that haven't reached their destinations yet and are late
17035  // changed at v1.1.4 - calc was inside "if(OverallScorePercent == 100).." block so could remain 0 for SPADs & crashes, & then received the
17036  // 'no timetabled departures... message, which was inappropriate
17037 
17038  if((SPADEvents > 0) || (Derailments > 0))
17039  {
17040  OverallScorePercent = 5; // overrides other calculations
17041  DerailSPADFlag = true;
17042  }
17043  if(CrashedTrains > 0)
17044  {
17045  OverallScorePercent = 0; // overrides other calculations
17046  CrashFlag = true;
17047  }
17048  if(OverallScorePercent == 100)
17049  {
17050  if(TotArrDep > 0)
17051  {
17052  TotLateMinsFactor =
17053  exp((-0.1732) * (TotLateArrMins + TotLateDepMins + OperatingTrainLateMins + NotStartedTrainLateMins +
17054  ((OtherMissedEvents + UnexpectedExits + ExcessLCDownMins) * 15)) / TotArrDep);
17055  // TotLateMinsFactor: negative exponential factor based on overall average arr & dep minutes late (with OtherMissedEvents & UnexpectedExits
17056  // counting as 15 mins late each), where 4 mins late average = half, 8 mins late = a quarter etc
17057  MissedStopAndSPADRiskFactor = exp((-17.33) * (MissedStops + SPADRisks + IncorrectExits) / TotArrDep);
17058  // MissedEventAndSPADRiskFactor: negative exponential factor based on number of missed stops, SPAD risks & IncorrectExits as a proportion
17059  // of arrivals & departures, where 4% = half, 8% = a quarter etc
17060  NetNegFactor = TotLateMinsFactor * MissedStopAndSPADRiskFactor;
17061  // NetNegfactor: product of the above two
17062  OverallScorePercent = 100 * NetNegFactor;
17063  }
17064  }
17065  if((TotArrDep > 0) || DerailSPADFlag || CrashFlag)
17066  // flag condits added at v1.1.4 - see above for what the error was
17067  {
17068  AnsiString OneFailureString = ", though the failure would account for some poor performance";
17069  AnsiString TwoOrMoreFailureString = ", though the failures would account for some poor performance";
17070  AnsiString AddedString = "";
17071  if(NumFailures == 1)
17072  AddedString = OneFailureString;
17073  if(NumFailures > 1)
17074  AddedString = TwoOrMoreFailureString;
17075  PerfFile << "\nOverall score: " << OverallScorePercent << "%\n";
17076  AnsiString Rating = "";
17077  if(OverallScorePercent == 100)
17078  Rating = "Perfect!";
17079  else if(OverallScorePercent >= 95)
17080  Rating = "Excellent";
17081  else if(OverallScorePercent >= 90)
17082  Rating = "Very good";
17083  else if(OverallScorePercent >= 80)
17084  Rating = "Good";
17085  else if(OverallScorePercent >= 70)
17086  Rating = "Fair";
17087  else if(OverallScorePercent >= 60)
17088  Rating = "Unacceptable" + AddedString;
17089  else if(OverallScorePercent >= 50)
17090  Rating = "Poor" + AddedString;
17091  else if(OverallScorePercent >= 40)
17092  Rating = "Bad" + AddedString;
17093  else if(OverallScorePercent >= 30)
17094  Rating = "Very bad" + AddedString;
17095  else if(OverallScorePercent >= 20)
17096  Rating = "Terrible" + AddedString;
17097  else if(OverallScorePercent >= 10)
17098  Rating = "Appalling" + AddedString;
17099  else if(OverallScorePercent >= 5)
17100  {
17101  if(DerailSPADFlag)
17102  Rating = "Disastrous - potential loss of life";
17103  // SPADs/Derailments
17104  else
17105  Rating = "Dire" + AddedString;
17106  }
17107  else if(OverallScorePercent < 5)
17108  {
17109  if(CrashFlag)
17110  Rating = "Catastrophic - loss of life"; // Crashes
17111  else
17112  Rating = "Abysmal";
17113  }
17114  PerfFile << "Overall rating: " << Rating.c_str() << '\n';
17115  }
17116  else
17117  {
17118  PerfFile << "\nThere were no timetabled departures or arrivals so there is insufficient information to provide a performance score or rating" << '\n';
17119  }
17120  PerfFile << '\n' << "***************************************";
17121  Utilities->CallLogPop(1736);
17122 }

17126 void TTrainController::SetWarningFlags(int Caller)
17127 {
17128  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",SetWarningFlags");
17129  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainVector.size(); x++)
17130  {
17131  TTrain &Train = TrainVectorAt(58, x);
17132  if(Train.Crashed)
17133  // can't use background colours for crashed & derailed because same colour
17134  {
17135  CrashWarning = true;
17136  }
17137  else if(Train.Derailed)
17138  // can't use background colours for crashed & derailed because same colour
17139  {
17140  DerailWarning = true;
17141  }
17142  else if(Train.BackgroundColour == clSPADBackground)
17143  // use colour as that changes as soon as passes signal
17144  {
17145  SPADWarning = true;
17146  }
17147  else if(Train.BackgroundColour == clTrainFailedBackground)
17148  {
17149  TrainFailedWarning = true;
17150  }
17151  else if(Train.BackgroundColour == clCallOnBackground)
17152  // use colour as also stopped at signal
17153  {
17154  CallOnWarning = true;
17155  }
17156  else if(Train.BackgroundColour == clSignalStopBackground)
17157  // use colour to distinguish from call-on
17158  {
17159  SignalStopWarning = true;
17160  }
17161  else if(Train.BackgroundColour == clBufferAttentionNeeded)
17162  // use colour to distinguish from ordinary buffer stop
17163  {
17164  BufferAttentionWarning = true;
17165  }
17166  }
17167  Utilities->CallLogPop(1796);
17168 }
