17170 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
17171 
17172 void TTrainController::CalcOperatingAndNotStartedTrainLateness(int Caller)
17173 {
17174  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",CalcSignalStopLateness");
17175 
17176  // calculate lateness for running trains
17177  OperatingTrainLateMins = 0;
17178  OperatingTrainArrDep = 0;
17179  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainVector.size(); x++)
17180  {
17181  TTrain &Train = TrainVectorAt(64, x);
17182  for(TActionVectorEntry * AVEntryPtr = &Train.TrainDataEntryPtr->ActionVector.front(); AVEntryPtr < &Train.TrainDataEntryPtr->ActionVector.back();
17183  AVEntryPtr++)
17184  {
17185  if(AVEntryPtr < Train.ActionVectorEntryPtr)
17186  continue;
17187  if((AVEntryPtr->ArrivalTime > TDateTime(-1)) && (GetRepeatTime(42, AVEntryPtr->ArrivalTime, Train.RepeatNumber, Train.IncrementalMinutes) <
17188  TTClockTime))
17189  {
17190  OperatingTrainLateMins += 1440 * double(TTClockTime - GetRepeatTime(43, AVEntryPtr->ArrivalTime, Train.RepeatNumber, Train.IncrementalMinutes));
17191  OperatingTrainArrDep++;
17192  }
17193  if((AVEntryPtr->DepartureTime > TDateTime(-1)) && (GetRepeatTime(44, AVEntryPtr->DepartureTime, Train.RepeatNumber, Train.IncrementalMinutes) <
17194  TTClockTime))
17195  {
17196  OperatingTrainLateMins += 1440 * double(TTClockTime - GetRepeatTime(45, AVEntryPtr->DepartureTime, Train.RepeatNumber,
17197  Train.IncrementalMinutes));
17198  OperatingTrainArrDep++;
17199  }
17200  }
17201  }
17202 
17203  // calculate lateness for trains that haven't started yet (could be held awaiting entry)
17204  NotStartedTrainLateMins = 0;
17205  NotStartedTrainArrDep = 0;
17206 
17207  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainDataVector.size(); x++)
17208  {
17209  TTrainDataEntry & TDEntry = TrainDataVector.at(x);
17210  const TActionVectorEntry &AVEntryLast = TDEntry.ActionVector.at(TDEntry.ActionVector.size() - 1);
17211  int IncrementalMinutes = 0;
17212  if(AVEntryLast.FormatType == Repeat)
17213  {
17214  IncrementalMinutes = AVEntryLast.RearStartOrRepeatMins;
17215  }
17216  for(int y = 0; y < TDEntry.NumberOfTrains; y++)
17217  {
17218  TTrainOperatingData &TTOD = TDEntry.TrainOperatingDataVector.at(y);
17219  if(TTOD.RunningEntry != NotStarted)
17220  continue;
17221  // note that can't rely on the above for sessionfiles saved before v0.6b as wasn't set to Running for Sns/Fsp/rsp & shuttles
17222  // but if trains had exited then would be set to Exited, so need to check against trains still operating - use the test below
17223  bool TrainOperatingFlag = false;
17224  for(unsigned int a = 0; a < TrainController->TrainVector.size(); a++)
17225  {
17226  if((TrainController->TrainVector.at(a).TrainDataEntryPtr == &TDEntry) && (TrainController->TrainVector.at(a).RepeatNumber == y))
17227  {
17228  TrainOperatingFlag = true;
17229  break;
17230  }
17231  }
17232  if(TrainOperatingFlag)
17233  continue;
17234 
17235  if(GetRepeatTime(46, TDEntry.ActionVector.at(0).EventTime, y, IncrementalMinutes) > TTClockTime)
17236  {
17237  break; // if the first time is greater than TTClockTime then all the rest will also be greater (& default of -1 will be less so will be ignored)
17238  }
17239  for(unsigned int z = 0; z < TDEntry.ActionVector.size(); z++)
17240  {
17241  TActionVectorEntry &AVEntry = TDEntry.ActionVector.at(z);
17242  if(GetRepeatTime(35, AVEntry.EventTime, y, IncrementalMinutes) > TTClockTime)
17243  {
17244  break; // all the rest will also be greater (& default of -1 will be less)
17245  }
17246  if(GetRepeatTime(36, AVEntry.ArrivalTime, y, IncrementalMinutes) > TTClockTime)
17247  {
17248  break; // all the rest will also be greater (& default of -1 will be less)
17249  }
17250  if(GetRepeatTime(37, AVEntry.DepartureTime, y, IncrementalMinutes) > TTClockTime)
17251  {
17252  break; // all the rest will also be greater (& default of -1 will be less)
17253  }
17254  if((AVEntry.ArrivalTime > TDateTime(-1)) && (GetRepeatTime(38, AVEntry.ArrivalTime, y, IncrementalMinutes) < TTClockTime))
17255  {
17256  NotStartedTrainLateMins += 1440 * double(TTClockTime - GetRepeatTime(39, AVEntry.ArrivalTime, y, IncrementalMinutes));
17257  NotStartedTrainArrDep++;
17258  }
17259  if((AVEntry.DepartureTime > TDateTime(-1)) && (GetRepeatTime(40, AVEntry.DepartureTime, y, IncrementalMinutes) < TTClockTime))
17260  {
17261  NotStartedTrainLateMins += 1440 * double(TTClockTime - GetRepeatTime(41, AVEntry.DepartureTime, y, IncrementalMinutes));
17262  NotStartedTrainArrDep++;
17263  }
17264  }
17265  }
17266  }
17267  Utilities->CallLogPop(1894);
17268 }
17269 
17270 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
17271 
17272 void TTrainController::RebuildOpTimeToActMultimap(int Caller)
17273  // new v2.2.0 for OperatorActionPanel
17274  // clears entries then adds values for running trains then for continuation entries
17275  // dont limit size here as need to check all trains (OAListBox is limites to 20 trains in Interface.cpp)
17276 {
17277  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",RebuildOpTimeToActMultimap");
17278  OpTimeToActMultiMap.clear();
17279  TOpTimeToActMultiMapEntry OpTimeToActMultiMapEntry;
17280 
17281  if(!TrainVector.empty())
17282  // build OpTimeToActMultiMap entries for running trains
17283  {
17284  AnsiString HeadCode;
17285  // dropped in favour of TrainID for running trains int VecPos; //TrackVectorPosition of LeadElement or continuation where train is to enter
17286  int TrainID;
17287  THCandTrainPosParam HCandTrainPosParam;
17288  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < TrainVector.size(); x++)
17289  {
17290  HeadCode = TrainVectorAt(62, x).HeadCode;
17291  TrainID = TrainVectorAt(63, x).TrainID;
17292  HCandTrainPosParam.first = HeadCode;
17293  HCandTrainPosParam.second = TrainID;
17294  float TimeToAct = TrainVectorAt(65, x).OpTimeToAct;
17295  if((TimeToAct >= 0) && (TimeToAct < 59.9))
17296  // -1 indicates don't display
17297  {
17298  OpTimeToActMultiMapEntry.first = TimeToAct;
17299  OpTimeToActMultiMapEntry.second = HCandTrainPosParam;
17300  OpTimeToActMultiMap.insert(OpTimeToActMultiMapEntry);
17301  }
17302  }
17303  }
17304 
17305 /*
17306  * class TContinuationTrainExpectationEntry
17307  {
17308  public:
17309  AnsiString Description; ///< service description
17310  AnsiString HeadCode; ///< service headcode
17311  int RepeatNumber; ///< service RepeatNumber
17312  int IncrementalMinutes; ///< Repeat separation in minutes
17313  int IncrementalDigits; ///< Repeat headcode separation
17314  int VectorPosition; ///< TrackVectorPosition for the continuation element
17315  TTrainDataEntry *TrainDataEntryPtr; ///< points to the service entry in the timetable's TrainDataVector
17316  };
17317 
17318  Multimap class for TContinuationTrainExpectationEntry objects, where the access key is the expectation time
17319  typedef std::multimap<TDateTime, TContinuationTrainExpectationEntry> TContinuationTrainExpectationMultiMap;
17320  typedef TContinuationTrainExpectationMultiMap::iterator TContinuationTrainExpectationMultiMapIterator; ///< iterator for the multimap
17321  typedef std::pair<TDateTime, TContinuationTrainExpectationEntry> TContinuationTrainExpectationMultiMapPair; ///< a single multimap entry
17322 */
17323 
17324  if(!ContinuationTrainExpectationMultiMap.empty())
17325  // build OpTimeToActMultiMap entries for expected trains
17326  {
17327  // note that using the ContinuationTrainExpectationMultiMap automatically ensures that entries are in ascending time order
17328  // first have to calculate times to red signal for each train due to enter (ignore later trains as will likely change before they are due)
17329  float TimeToAct = 0; // minutes
17330  int DistanceToRedSignal = 0; // metres
17331  TContinuationEntryVecPosVector ContinuationEntryVecPosVector;
17332  // used to ensure only one train displayed for a given continuation
17333  ContinuationEntryVecPosVector.clear();
17334  bool LaterTrain = false;
17335  TContinuationTrainExpectationMultiMapIterator CTEIt = ContinuationTrainExpectationMultiMap.begin();
17336  while(CTEIt != TrainController->ContinuationTrainExpectationMultiMap.end())
17337  {
17338  LaterTrain = false;
17339  if(CTEIt->second.TrainDataEntryPtr->TrainOperatingDataVector.at(CTEIt->second.RepeatNumber).RunningEntry != NotStarted)
17340  {
17341  CTEIt++;
17342  continue; // not interested in running or exited trains
17343  }
17344  if(Track->TrackElementAt(934, CTEIt->second.VectorPosition).TrainIDOnElement > 0)
17345  {
17346  CTEIt++;
17347  continue;
17348  // don't include trains not entered yet when a train is already on the continuation
17349  }
17350  if(!ContinuationEntryVecPosVector.empty())
17351  {
17352  for(unsigned int x = 0; x < ContinuationEntryVecPosVector.size(); x++)
17353  {
17354  if(CTEIt->second.VectorPosition == ContinuationEntryVecPosVector.at(x))
17355  {
17356  LaterTrain = true; ;
17357  // skip past remaining trains waiting to enter at same point
17358  break;
17359  }
17360  }
17361  }
17362  if(LaterTrain)
17363  {
17364  CTEIt++;
17365  continue;
17366  }
17367  ContinuationEntryVecPosVector.push_back(CTEIt->second.VectorPosition);
17368  AnsiString HeadCode = CTEIt->second.HeadCode;
17369  float CurrentStopTime; // set to 0 at start of function
17370  float LaterStopTime; // set to 0 at start of function
17371  float RecoverableTime; // set to 0 at start of function
17372  int AvTrackSpeed; // set to 0 at start of function
17373  int TrainID = -1; // not yet allocated for train still to enter
17374  bool SigControlAndCanPassRedSignal = false;
17375  // doesn't apply for a continuation
17376  DistanceToRedSignal = CalcDistanceToRedSignalandStopTime(1, CTEIt->second.VectorPosition, 0,
17377  // EntryPos always 0 for entering at a continuation
17378  SigControlAndCanPassRedSignal, &CTEIt->second.TrainDataEntryPtr->ActionVector.at(1),
17379  // at(1) to skip past the Start train value
17380  HeadCode, TrainID, CurrentStopTime, LaterStopTime, RecoverableTime, AvTrackSpeed);
17381  // for above VectorPosition is the first element to have its length included in the sum, so for a continuation it's the continuation itself
17382  // for a train it's the one in front of LeadElement
17383  if(AvTrackSpeed < 30)
17384  AvTrackSpeed = 30;
17385  if(DistanceToRedSignal == -1)
17386  {
17387  TimeToAct = 60.0;
17388  }
17389  else
17390  {
17391  int Speed = AvTrackSpeed;
17392  int MaxSpeed = int(CTEIt->second.TrainDataEntryPtr->MaxRunningSpeed);
17393  if(AvTrackSpeed > MaxSpeed)
17394  Speed = MaxSpeed;
17395  if(CTEIt->second.TrainDataEntryPtr->ActionVector.at(1).SignallerControl)
17396  // defined in timetable as under signaller control
17397  {
17398  Speed = CTEIt->second.TrainDataEntryPtr->SignallerSpeed;
17399  LaterStopTime = 0;
17400  }
17401  TimeToAct = LaterStopTime + DistanceToRedSignal * 3.6 / 60 / Speed;
17402  // accel & decel taken into account in
17403  // CalcDistanceToRedSignalandStopTime
17404  // 3.6 convertsKm/h to m/s & 60 converts seconds to minutes
17405  // don't need CurrentStopTime or RecoverableTime for continuation entries
17406  float MinsBefEnter = double(CTEIt->first - TTClockTime) * 86400.0 / 60.0;
17407  TimeToAct += MinsBefEnter;
17408  }
17409  THCandTrainPosParam HCandTrainPosParam;
17410  HCandTrainPosParam.first = HeadCode;
17411  HCandTrainPosParam.second = -1 - CTEIt->second.VectorPosition;
17412  // -1-CTE... because 2nd value covers TrainID if +ve &
17413  // continuation track vector position if -ve, -1 allows for vecpos being 0
17414  if(TimeToAct < 59.9) // if 60 don't enter a value in multimap
17415  {
17416  OpTimeToActMultiMapEntry.first = TimeToAct;
17417  OpTimeToActMultiMapEntry.second = HCandTrainPosParam;
17418  OpTimeToActMultiMap.insert(OpTimeToActMultiMapEntry);
17419  }
17420  CTEIt++;
17421  }
17422  }
17423  Utilities->CallLogPop(2081);
17424 }
17425 
17426 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
17427 
17428 int TTrainController::CalcDistanceToRedSignalandStopTime(int Caller, int TrackVectorPosition, int TrackVectorPositionEntryPos,
17429  bool SigControlAndCanPassRedSignal, TActionVectorEntry *AVPtr, AnsiString HeadCode, int TrainID, float &CurrentStopTime, float &LaterStopTime,
17430  float &RecoverableTime, int &AvTrackSpeed)
17431  // new v2.2.0
17432  // vectorPosition is the value for the first element to be measured - for a continuation it's the continuation itself, for a train
17433  // it's the one after LeadElement, returns -1 for infinity - i.e. not approaching red signal (e.g. maybe cdt before reach it).
17434  // CurrentStopTime is the time to depart from the current station (if stopped at a station) and LaterStopTime is the total station
17435  // stop times for stations after the current one. DistanceToRedSignal is what the name implies, if -1 is returned the other values
17436  // aren't used - this means there is no display for the train in question
17437 {
17438  Utilities->CallLog.push_back(Utilities->TimeStamp() + "," + AnsiString(Caller) + ",DistanceToRedSignal, " + AnsiString(TrackVectorPosition) + ", " +
17439  AnsiString(TrackVectorPositionEntryPos) + ", " + AVPtr->Command);
17440  int DistanceToRedSignal = 0;
17441  int CumTrackSpeed = 0;
17442  // average track speed, in case need to use in time calc
17443  int TrackSpeedCount = 0;
17444 
17445  AvTrackSpeed = 0;
17446  int CurrentElement = TrackVectorPosition;
17447  int CurrentEntryPos = TrackVectorPositionEntryPos;
17448  int NextElement;
17449  int NextEntryPos;
17450  int NextExitPos;
17451 
17452  CurrentStopTime = 0;
17453  LaterStopTime = 0;
17454  RecoverableTime = 0;
17455  if(CurrentElement == -1) // end element, no action needed
17456  {
17457  Utilities->CallLogPop(2094);
17458  return -1;
17459  }
17460  int CurrentExitPos;
17461 
17462  // get ExitPos for first element to be measured
17463  if(Track->TrackElementAt(935, CurrentElement).TrackType == Points)
17464  {
17465  if((CurrentEntryPos == 0) || (CurrentEntryPos == 2)) // leading point
17466  {
17467  if(Track->TrackElementAt(936, CurrentElement).Attribute == 0)
17468  CurrentExitPos = 1;
17469  else
17470  CurrentExitPos = 3;
17471  }
17472  else
17473  CurrentExitPos = 0; // trailing point
17474  }
17475  else
17476  CurrentExitPos = Track->GetNonPointsOppositeLinkPos(CurrentEntryPos);
17477  // get CumTrackSpeed for first measured element
17478 
17479  TConfiguration CurrentExitConfig = Track->TrackElementAt(937, CurrentElement).Config[CurrentExitPos];
17480  int CurrentAttribute = Track->TrackElementAt(938, CurrentElement).Attribute;
17481 
17482  // check if currently stopped at a location, and if so add the remaining dwell time
17483  // can't use CurrentElement as that is in front of LeadElement and might not be at the location
17484  if(TrainID > -1)
17485  // -1 for a continuation and can't be at a location as not yet entered
17486  {
17487  TTrain Train = TrainVectorAtIdent(39, TrainID);
17488  Train.FirstLaterStopRecoverableTime = 0;
17489  // this used to deduct from RecoverableTime when arrive at a location
17490  if(Train.StoppedAtLocation)
17491  {
17492  if(Train.StoppedForTrainInFront)
17493  {
17494  Utilities->CallLogPop(2082);
17495  return -1; // no action needed
17496  }
17497  else if(!((Train.ActionVectorEntryPtr->FormatType == TimeTimeLoc) || (Train.ActionVectorEntryPtr->FormatType == TimeLoc)))
17498  {
17499  Utilities->CallLogPop(2083);
17500  return -1; // not due a departure so no action needed
17501  }
17502  else // due a departure
17503  {
17504  double TimeToDepart = double(Train.ReleaseTime - TrainController->TTClockTime) * 86400 / 60; // mins to depart
17505  // can't convert a TDateTime to a float directly
17506  CurrentStopTime = float(TimeToDepart);
17507  AVPtr++;
17508  }
17509  }
17510  }
17511 
17512  // check if CurrentElement is a red signal, but ok if autosig route after
17513  if((CurrentExitConfig == Signal) && (CurrentAttribute == 0))
17514  // ok if autosig route after red signal
17515  {
17516  int NextElement = Track->TrackElementAt(939, CurrentElement).Conn[CurrentExitPos];
17517  int NextEntryPos = Track->TrackElementAt(940, CurrentElement).ConnLinkPos[CurrentExitPos];
17518  int RouteNumber; // holder for referenced value, not used
17519  if(AllRoutes->GetRouteTypeAndNumber(33, NextElement, NextEntryPos, RouteNumber) == TAllRoutes::AutoSigsRoute)
17520  {
17521  Utilities->CallLogPop(2078);
17522  return -1;
17523  }
17524  else if(SigControlAndCanPassRedSignal)
17525  // ignore signal and increment CurrentElement to NextElement
17526  {
17527  if(Track->TrackElementAt(941, NextElement).TrackType == Points)
17528  {
17529  if((NextEntryPos == 0) || (NextEntryPos == 2))
17530  // leading entry point
17531  {
17532  if(Track->TrackElementAt(942, NextElement).Attribute == 0)
17533  NextExitPos = 1;
17534  else
17535  NextExitPos = 3;
17536  }
17537  else
17538  NextExitPos = 0; // trailing entry point
17539  }
17540  else
17541  NextExitPos = Track->GetNonPointsOppositeLinkPos(NextEntryPos);
17542 
17543  CurrentElement = NextElement;
17544  CurrentEntryPos = NextEntryPos;
17545  CurrentExitPos = NextExitPos;
17546  CurrentExitConfig = Track->TrackElementAt(943, CurrentElement).Config[CurrentExitPos];
17547  CurrentAttribute = Track->TrackElementAt(944, CurrentElement).Attribute;
17548  }
17549  else if((TrainID > -1) && (TrainVectorAtIdent(40, TrainID).TrainMode == Timetable)) // ignore signallercontrol or will
17550  // give 'NOW' indication after allowed to pass red signal when LeadMidLag (AllowedToPassRedSignal reset by this point)
17551  {
17552  Utilities->CallLogPop(2084);
17553  return 0;
17554  // stopped with red signal in front, don't need AvSpeedLimit in this case, & if at location awaiting departure dwell time already calculated
17555  }
17556  }
17557  int LaterStopNumber = 0;
17558  int x = 0;
17559 
17560  // added in v2.4.0 to prevent endless circling round track loops - spotted by Xeon 09/03/20 & reported by emsil
17561  while(!((CurrentExitConfig == Signal) && (CurrentAttribute == 0)))
17562  // not red signal next (in fwd direction) so enter loop to calc CumLength
17563  {
17564  x++; // added in v2.4.0 as above
17565  if(x > 5000)
17566  {
17567  Utilities->CallLogPop(2120);
17568  return -1;
17569  }
17570  if(CurrentEntryPos > 1)
17571  {
17572  DistanceToRedSignal += Track->TrackElementAt(916, CurrentElement).Length23;
17573  CumTrackSpeed += Track->TrackElementAt(945, CurrentElement).SpeedLimit23;
17574  }
17575  else
17576  {
17577  DistanceToRedSignal += Track->TrackElementAt(917, CurrentElement).Length01;
17578  CumTrackSpeed += Track->TrackElementAt(946, CurrentElement).SpeedLimit01;
17579  }
17580  TrackSpeedCount++;
17581 
17582  // check for train in front, but if on a bridge on other track then ok
17583  TTrackElement TE = Track->TrackElementAt(947, CurrentElement);
17584  int TrainOnElement;
17585  if(TE.TrackType != Bridge)
17586  {
17587  TrainOnElement = TE.TrainIDOnElement;
17588  }
17589  else
17590  {
17591  if(CurrentEntryPos > 1)
17592  TrainOnElement = TE.TrainIDOnBridgeTrackPos23;
17593  else
17594  TrainOnElement = TE.TrainIDOnBridgeTrackPos01;
17595  }
17596  if((TrainOnElement > -1) && (TrainOnElement != TrainID))
17597  // train in front before red signal
17598  {
17599  Utilities->CallLogPop(2085);
17600  return -1;
17601  }
17602 
17603  // add to stoptime if required
17604  if(Track->TrackElementAt(948, CurrentElement).ActiveTrackElementName != "")
17605  {
17606  double StopTimeDouble;
17607  while(AVPtr->FormatType == PassTime)
17608  AVPtr++; // skip past any passes
17609  if((Track->TrackElementAt(949, CurrentElement).ActiveTrackElementName == AVPtr->LocationName) && ((AVPtr->FormatType == TimeLoc) ||
17610  (AVPtr->FormatType == TimeTimeLoc)))
17611  // stop due here so calc dwell time & advance Ptr
17612  {
17613  if(AVPtr->FormatType == TimeTimeLoc)
17614  {
17615  LaterStopNumber++;
17616  StopTimeDouble = double(AVPtr->DepartureTime - AVPtr->ArrivalTime) * 86400.0 / 60.0;
17617  if(StopTimeDouble < 0.5)
17618  StopTimeDouble = 0.5;
17619  // at least 30 secs delay at station
17620  // can't convert a TDateTime to a float directly
17621  LaterStopTime += float(StopTimeDouble);
17622  RecoverableTime += StopTimeDouble - 0.5;
17623  if((LaterStopNumber == 1) && (TrainID > -1))
17624  TrainVectorAtIdent(41, TrainID).FirstLaterStopRecoverableTime = RecoverableTime;
17625  AVPtr++;
17626  }
17627  else if((AVPtr->FormatType == TimeLoc) && (AVPtr->ArrivalTime != TDateTime(-1))) // must be an arrival
17628  {
17629  if((AVPtr + 1)->FormatType == TimeLoc)
17630  // must be a departure
17631  {
17632  LaterStopNumber++;
17633  StopTimeDouble = double((AVPtr + 1)->DepartureTime - AVPtr->ArrivalTime) * 86400.0 / 60.0;
17634  // can't convert a TDateTime to a float directly
17635  if(StopTimeDouble < 0.5)
17636  StopTimeDouble = 0.5;
17637  // at least 30 secs delay at station
17638  LaterStopTime += float(StopTimeDouble);
17639  RecoverableTime += StopTimeDouble - 0.5;
17640  if((LaterStopNumber == 1) && (TrainID > -1))
17641  TrainVectorAtIdent(42, TrainID).FirstLaterStopRecoverableTime = RecoverableTime;
17642  AVPtr++;
17643  AVPtr++;
17644  }
17645  else // not a departure, does something else at the location so no calculation needed
17646  {
17647  Utilities->CallLogPop(2086);
17648  return -1;
17649  }
17650  }
17651  }
17652  }
17653 
17654  NextElement = Track->TrackElementAt(950, CurrentElement).Conn[CurrentExitPos];
17655  if(NextElement == -1) // reached end element, no action needed
17656  {
17657  Utilities->CallLogPop(2077);
17658  return -1;
17659  }
17660  NextEntryPos = Track->TrackElementAt(919, CurrentElement).ConnLinkPos[CurrentExitPos];
17661  // get NextExitPos
17662  if(Track->TrackElementAt(920, NextElement).TrackType == Points)
17663  {
17664  if((NextEntryPos == 0) || (NextEntryPos == 2))
17665  // leading entry point
17666  {
17667  if(Track->TrackElementAt(921, NextElement).Attribute == 0)
17668  NextExitPos = 1;
17669  else
17670  NextExitPos = 3;
17671  }
17672  else
17673  NextExitPos = 0; // trailing entry point
17674  }
17675  else
17676  NextExitPos = Track->GetNonPointsOppositeLinkPos(NextEntryPos);
17677 
17678  CurrentElement = NextElement;
17679  CurrentEntryPos = NextEntryPos;
17680  CurrentExitPos = NextExitPos;
17681  CurrentExitConfig = Track->TrackElementAt(922, CurrentElement).Config[CurrentExitPos];
17682  CurrentAttribute = Track->TrackElementAt(923, CurrentElement).Attribute;
17683  }
17684  if((CurrentExitConfig == Signal) && (CurrentAttribute == 0))
17685  // ok if autosig route after red signal, no action needed
17686  {
17687  int NextElement = Track->TrackElementAt(924, CurrentElement).Conn[CurrentExitPos];
17688  int NextEntryPos = Track->TrackElementAt(925, CurrentElement).ConnLinkPos[CurrentExitPos];
17689  int RouteNumber; // holder for referenced value, not used
17690  if(AllRoutes->GetRouteTypeAndNumber(31, NextElement, NextEntryPos, RouteNumber) == TAllRoutes::AutoSigsRoute)
17691  {
17692  Utilities->CallLogPop(2095);
17693  return -1;
17694  }
17695  }
17696  // Av speed calculation based on formula: Speed = 8.75*(kms/location stop) + 44 km/sec (from experiments), subject to a maximum of
17697  // average line speed/2 (for half distance accelerating and half decelerating.
17698 
17699  float MaxAllowableSpeed;
17700 
17701  if(TrackSpeedCount > 0)
17702  MaxAllowableSpeed = CumTrackSpeed / TrackSpeedCount;
17703  else // shouldn't reach here but include to prevent divide by zero error
17704  {
17705  if(CurrentEntryPos > 1)
17706  {
17707  MaxAllowableSpeed = Track->TrackElementAt(951, CurrentElement).SpeedLimit23;
17708  }
17709  else
17710  {
17711  MaxAllowableSpeed = Track->TrackElementAt(952, CurrentElement).SpeedLimit01;
17712  }
17713  // Train MaxRunningSpeed taken into account in RebuildOpTimeToActMultimap
17714  }
17715  float KmPerLocationStop;
17716 
17717  if(LaterStopNumber > 0)
17718  {
17719  KmPerLocationStop = float(DistanceToRedSignal) / LaterStopNumber / 1000; // m to km
17720  AvTrackSpeed = (8.75 * KmPerLocationStop) + 44;
17721  }
17722  else
17723  {
17724  AvTrackSpeed = (sqrt(float(DistanceToRedSignal) / 1000) * 44) + 60;
17725  // using linear trendline for accel & decel distance at various speeds
17726  // at half braking, speed never < 60 using this
17727  }
17728  if(AvTrackSpeed > MaxAllowableSpeed)
17729  AvTrackSpeed = MaxAllowableSpeed;
17730  Utilities->CallLogPop(2096);
17731  return DistanceToRedSignal;
17732 }
